('700f5038-5b59-4c7e-9204-70ab7365c5e6','What does the ''*'' operator do when used before a pointer variable?','Declares a pointer','Dereferences the pointer','Calculates the address','Multiplies the pointer','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The dereference operator ''*'' accesses the value stored at the address held by the pointer.','pregenerated'),
('700f5038-5b59-4c7e-9204-70ab7365c5e6','If ''ptr'' is of type ''int*'', what is the increment size of ''ptr++''?','1 byte','2 bytes','sizeof(int) bytes','4 bytes always','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Pointer arithmetic is scaled by the size of the underlying data type.','pregenerated'),
('700f5038-5b59-4c7e-9204-70ab7365c5e6','How do you access the first element of an array ''arr'' using pointers?','*arr','&arr','arr[1]','ptr(arr)','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The array name decays to a pointer to its first element; dereferencing it yields arr[0].','pregenerated'),
('700f5038-5b59-4c7e-9204-70ab7365c5e6','Which symbol is used for the address-of operator?','*','#','&','@','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The ''&'' operator retrieves the memory address of a variable.','pregenerated'),
('700f5038-5b59-4c7e-9204-70ab7365c5e6','A ''NULL'' pointer usually points to which address?','1','random','0','stack start','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'NULL is a macro representing a pointer that does not point to any valid memory location (often 0).','pregenerated'),
('700f5038-5b59-4c7e-9204-70ab7365c5e6','What is the correct syntax to declare a pointer to a function returning void?','void ptr();','void (*ptr)();','void *ptr();','void &ptr();','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The parenthesis around *ptr are necessary to distinguish it from a function returning a void pointer.','pregenerated'),
('700f5038-5b59-4c7e-9204-70ab7365c5e6','If `int arr[5];`, is `arr` an lvalue?','Yes','No, it''s a constant pointer','Only in C++','Depends on scope','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Array names are non-modifiable lvalues (essentially constant pointers to their first element).','pregenerated'),
('700f5038-5b59-4c7e-9204-70ab7365c5e6','What is the equivalent of `ptr[i]` in pointer notation?','ptr + i','*(ptr + i)','&ptr + i','(*ptr) + i','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Array subscripting is defined as dereferencing the sum of the pointer and the offset.','pregenerated'),
('700f5038-5b59-4c7e-9204-70ab7365c5e6','Which pointer type can point to any data type?','int*','generic*','void*','char*','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'A void pointer (void*) is a generic pointer type that can hold any object address.','pregenerated'),
('700f5038-5b59-4c7e-9204-70ab7365c5e6','What is output of `int a=10; int *p=&a; printf("%d", ++*p);`?','10','11','Address of a','Pointer error','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'++*p increments the value pointed to by p (i.e., a becomes 11) and then prints it.','pregenerated'),
('700f5038-5b59-4c7e-9204-70ab7365c5e6','Given `int arr[3] = {10, 20, 30}; int *p = arr;`, what is `*p + 1`?','20','11','30','Garbage','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'*p is 10. 10 + 1 = 11. (Note: *(p+1) would be 20).','pregenerated'),
('700f5038-5b59-4c7e-9204-70ab7365c5e6','What does `void (*f)(int)` declare?','A function returning a pointer','A pointer to a function taking an int and returning void','An array of void pointers','A function taking a pointer','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'This is standard syntax for declaring a function pointer with one argument.','pregenerated'),
('700f5038-5b59-4c7e-9204-70ab7365c5e6','Can a pointer be assigned to another pointer of a different type without a cast?','Yes, always','Only in older C versions','No, it requires an explicit cast (except void*)','Yes, if they are the same size','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'C is strictly typed for pointers; void* is the only type that allows implicit conversion usually.','pregenerated'),
('700f5038-5b59-4c7e-9204-70ab7365c5e6','What is a ''dangling pointer''?','A pointer that is not initialized','A pointer pointing to a deallocated memory block','A pointer to a NULL address','A pointer that points to itself','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'Dangling pointers point to memory that has been freed or is no longer valid.','pregenerated'),
('700f5038-5b59-4c7e-9204-70ab7365c5e6','If `int arr[] = {1, 2, 3};`, what is `&arr[0]` equivalent to?','arr','*arr','&&arr','arr+1','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'The address of the first element is the same as the base address of the array.','pregenerated'),
('700f5038-5b59-4c7e-9204-70ab7365c5e6','What is the size of a pointer on a 64-bit system?','4 bytes','2 bytes','8 bytes','Depends on data type','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'On a 64-bit architecture, pointers are 8 bytes to address the full memory space.','pregenerated'),
('700f5038-5b59-4c7e-9204-70ab7365c5e6','How do you pass a pointer to a function to change the original variable''s value?','By value','By reference (using pointers)','By constant','By copying','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'Passing a pointer (address) allows the function to access and modify the original memory.','pregenerated'),
