('700f5038-5b59-4c7e-9204-70ab7365c5e6','Which of these is legal pointer arithmetic in C?','p1 + p2 (adding two pointers)','p1 * p2 (multiplying two pointers)','p1 - p2 (subtracting two pointers of same type)','p1 / 5','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'Subtracting pointers of the same type gives the number of elements between them; other operations are illegal.','pregenerated'),
('700f5038-5b59-4c7e-9204-70ab7365c5e6','What is the result of `*(arr + i)` where `arr` is an array and `i` is an index?','Base address of arr','arr[i]','Address of arr[i]','Invalid expression','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'This is the pointer equivalent of the array subscript notation arr[i].','pregenerated'),
('700f5038-5b59-4c7e-9204-70ab7365c5e6','What is a ''wild pointer''?','A pointer that points to complex data','An uninitialized pointer','A pointer to the heap','A pointer used in recursions','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'Wild pointers are uninitialized pointers that point to arbitrary memory locations.','pregenerated'),
('700f5038-5b59-4c7e-9204-70ab7365c5e6','If `int arr[2][3];`, what is the type of `arr[0]`?','int','int*','int (*)[3]','int**','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'In a 2D array, arr[0] is interpreted as a 1D array of 3 integers, which decays to int*.','pregenerated'),
('700f5038-5b59-4c7e-9204-70ab7365c5e6','How do you declare a pointer to an array of 5 integers?','int *ptr[5];','int (*ptr)[5];','int ptr[5]*;','int *[5]ptr;','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'Parenthesis are required to make it a pointer to an array, otherwise it''s an array of pointers.','pregenerated'),
