('700f5038-5b59-4c7e-9204-70ab7365c5e6','What is output of `char *s = "Hello"; printf("%c", *s+1);`?','e','I','H','f','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'*s is ''H'' (72). 72 + 1 = 73, which is ''I'' in ASCII.','pregenerated'),
('700f5038-5b59-4c7e-9204-70ab7365c5e6','Pointer to a function can be passed as an argument to another function?','True','False','Only for recursive functions','Only if using typedef','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'Function pointers are used as arguments to implement ''callback'' functions.','pregenerated'),
