('8996ac1b-e61b-4b0b-9b9e-05aac10d8522','What is ''Shift Left'' security?','Moving computer monitors to the left','Integrating security practices earlier in the software development lifecycle (further to the ''left'' on the timeline)','Only hiring security experts from the left','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Shift-left reduces the cost and risk of security issues by catching them during development.','pregenerated'),
('8996ac1b-e61b-4b0b-9b9e-05aac10d8522','Which command is used to add specific files to the staging area?','git add [file]','git stage [file]','git commit [file]','git include [file]','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'''git add'' marks changes in a file to be included in the next commit.','pregenerated'),
('8996ac1b-e61b-4b0b-9b9e-05aac10d8522','What is a ''Pipeline''?','A physical water pipe','A series of automated steps code must pass through to be built, tested, and deployed','A list of programmer names','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'Pipelines define the ''factory line'' for software creation.','pregenerated'),
('8996ac1b-e61b-4b0b-9b9e-05aac10d8522','What is ''Downtime''?','Time to sleep','A period when a service is unavailable to users','The time spent writing code','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'CI/CD aims to minimize downtime through automated and safe deployment techniques.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is ''Trunk-Based Development''?','Developing code on a separate branch for months','A strategy where developers frequently merge small updates to a single shared branch (trunk)','Deleting the main branch','Only working on weekends','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Trunk-based development avoids long-lived feature branches and reduces ''merge hell''.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','Which stage typically comes AFTER ''Build'' but BEFORE ''Deplay'' in a standard CI/CD pipeline?','Requirement Gathering','Test (Unit/Integration)','Market Research','Coding','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Artifacts produced in the build stage must be verified by tests before they are considered safe for deployment.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is the purpose of a ''Pull Request'' (PR) or ''Merge Request'' (MR)?','To download code','To propose changes and request a code review before merging into the target branch','To delete a repository','To reset the server','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'PRs are essential for collaboration and maintaining code quality through peer review.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is an ''Artifact Repository'' (e.g. Nexus, Artifactory)?','A place to store old computers','A centralized server for storing and managing dependency libraries and build outputs (artifacts)','A ways to name pods','A source code hosting service','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Artifact repositories ensure that builds are reproducible and dependencies are secure.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is the difference between ''Declarative'' and ''Imperative'' IaC?','Declarative defines the ''how''; Imperative defines the ''what''','Declarative defines the desired final ''state''; Imperative defines the series of ''commands'' to reach it','There is no difference','Declarative is for users, Imperative is for machines','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Declarative IaC (like Terraform) is generally preferred because it is easier to maintain and reason about.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is ''GitOps''?','A new version of Git','An operational framework that uses Git repositories as the ''single source of truth'' for infrastructure and application configurations','Only used for frontend apps','A ways to delete Git history','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'With GitOps, every change to the environment is executed by updating the configuration in Git.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What does ''SAST'' stand for in a pipeline context?','Secure Automated Software Tool','Static Application Security Testing','Source Analysis and System Tracking','Secret Access Security Token','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'SAST tools analyze source code for vulnerabilities without executing the program.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is ''Idempotency'' in the context of automation scripts?','A script that runs very fast','The property where a script produces the same result no matter how many times it is run from the same starting state','A script that deletes data','A ways to rename a server','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Idempotency is crucial for reliable infrastructure automation to prevent duplicate resources.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','Which strategy involves running two identical versions of an app and switching traffic between them?','Rolling Update','Blue-Green Deployment','Recreate','Direct Push','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Blue-Green allows zero-downtime deployments and instant rollbacks.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is a ''Jenkinsfile''?','A file that lists Jenkins developers','A text file that contains the definition of a Jenkins Pipeline as code','A log file','A backup file','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Jenkinsfiles allow you to version control your pipeline configuration alongside your app code.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What does `git cherry-pick [commit-hash]` do?','Deletes the commit','Applies the changes from a specific commit from another branch onto the current branch','Reverts the branch','Renames a branch','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Cherry-picking is useful for bringing specific bug fixes into a release branch without merging everything.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is the 12-factor app''s recommendation for storing configuration (like API keys)?','Hardcoded in the source code','In Environment Variables','In a database','In the user''s brain','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Storing config in environment variables keeps it separate from code and allows it to vary across environments.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is the difference between `git merge` and `git rebase`?','Merge is for code, Rebase is for files','Merge creates a new commit combining histories; Rebase moves your changes on top of the target branch''s base, rewriting history','There is no difference','Merge is faster','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Rebasing creates a cleaner linear history but should be used carefully on shared branches.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is ''Docker Hub'' an example of?','A code editor','A Container Registry','A cloud provider','An operating system','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Docker Hub is a public registry for sharing and storing container images.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is a ''Webook'' used for in Git providers (GitHub/GitLab)?','To download code','To notify external services (like CI servers) automatically when an event happens (like a push or pull request)','To name a branch','To delete a user','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Webhooks ''trigger'' the pipeline as soon as code is pushed to the repository.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','In ''Gitflow'', which branch is typically used for preparing a new production release?','develop','release','master','feature','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Release branches allow for last-minute bug fixes and documentation updates before a major merge into master.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is a ''Canary Deployment''?','A deployment that uses birds','Releasing a new version to a small subset of users first to monitor for issues before a full rollout','Updating the whole cluster at once','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Canary releases reduce risk by testing live traffic on a small percentage of the infrastructure.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is ''DAST'' in a security pipeline?','Data Automated Security Tool','Dynamic Application Security Testing','Direct Access Security Test','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'DAST tests the application while it is running, usually by simulating attacks on the exposed endpoints.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is an ''Automated Rollback''?','A ways to delete code','The process where a deployment system automatically reverts to the previous stable version if health checks fail','Rolling a dice','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Automated rollbacks minimize the impact of faulty deployments on end users.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What characterizes ''Immutable Infrastructure''?','Servers that never change','Infrastructure that is replaced rather than modified when updates are needed','Infrastructure that cannot be deleted','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Immutability prevents ''configuration drift'' where servers slowly become different from their original setup.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is a ''Feature Flag'' (or Feature Toggle)?','A way to name a feature','A mechanism to enable or disable features in an application at runtime without redeploying code','A bug in the code','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Feature flags enable ''dark launches'' and rapid A/B testing.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What does a ''Static Analysis'' tool (like SonarQube) do?','Tests the app while it''s running','Scans the source code for bugs, vulnerabilities, and code smells without executing it','Increases the server speed','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Static analysis helps maintain high standards for maintainability and security.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is ''Parallelism'' in a CI/CD pipeline?','Running one job after another','Running multiple jobs or tests simultaneously to reduce the total pipeline duration','Deleting the pipeline','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Parallelism is the primary way to speed up slow test suites in large projects.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is ''SCA'' (Software Composition Analysis)?','Scritping code analysis','Identifying and managing vulnerabilities in open-source dependencies (libraries) used by your application','Analyzing the user interface','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'SCA tools (like Snyk or Dependabot) ensure you aren''t shiping code with known security holes in its libraries.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is a ''Multi-stage Build'' in Docker?','Building many images at once','A feature that allows using multiple intermediate images in one Dockerfile to keep the final production image small and clean','A ways to name the layers','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Multi-stage builds allow you to include build tools in the build phase but exclude them from the final image.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What does ''SLI'' stand for in Site Reliability Engineering?','Service Level Interface','Service Level Indicator','System Level Integration','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'SLIs are specific quantitative measures of some aspect of the level of service that is provided (e.g., latency).','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is an ''SLO'' (Service Level Objective)?','A target value or range of values for a service level that is measured by an SLI','A way to call the manager','A list of server names','none of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'SLOs represent the ''reliability targets'' that a dev team tries to meet.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is a ''Post-Mortem'' in operational culture?','A funeral for a computer','A document written after an incident to analyze what happened, why it happened, and how to prevent it in the future','Deleting the logs after an error','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Blameless post-mortems are vital for learning and improving system reliability.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is ''Terraform State Locking''?','Locking the computer','A mechanism that prevents multiple users from modifying the infrastructure at the same time, avoiding state corruption','A ways to delete the state','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'State locking is usually handled by a backend like S3/DynamoDB or Terraform Cloud.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What defines a ''Breaking Change'' in Semantic Versioning?','A fix for a bug','A change that is not backwards compatible (e.g., removing a public function)','A change that breaks the computer','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Breaking changes require an increment to the ''Major'' version number (e.g., 1.x.x to 2.x.x).','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is a ''Pre-commit'' hook typically used for?','Sending an email before committing','Running linters or checks automatically before Git allows a commit to be created','Deleting the files','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'Pre-commit hooks help developers catch simple mistakes (like formatting or secrets) locally.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is ''Forking'' in a Git provider (like GitHub)?','Deleting a repository','Creating a personal copy of someone else''s repository into your own account to make changes independently','Merging two repositories','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Forking is the foundation of open-source collaboration on platforms like GitHub.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is a ''Jenkins Slave'' (now called Agent)?','A developer who works on Jenkins','A distributed machine that offloads build and test processing from the main Jenkins controller','A ways to delete Jenkins','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Distributing builds across many agents allows Jenkins to scale and handle hundreds of concurrent pipelines.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is an ''Immutable Artifact''?','An artifact that cannot be deleted','An artifact that is never changed once it is built and versioned (e.g., v1.1.0 never points to new code)','An artifact with no name','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Immutability ensures that ''what you test is what you deploy'' and prevents mysterious failures from changing packages.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is a ''Trigger'' in a CI/CD context?','A person who is angry','An event (like code push, schedule, or manual click) that starts the execution of a pipeline','A ways to delete the code','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'Triggers automate the ''Integration'' part of CI.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is ''Log Aggregation''?','Printing logs on paper','Collecting logs from many different sources (servers, containers) into a central location for searching and analysis','Deleting the logs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Tools like ELK stack or Grafana Loki are essential for troubleshooting distributed systems.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What characterizes ''Least Privilege'' for a CI/CD service account?','Giving the account full admin access','Giving the account only the minimum permissions necessary to perform its specific task (e.g., ''only push to one bucket'')','Having no account at all','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Least privilege reduces the ''blast radius'' if a CI/CD credentials are stolen.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is ''Hotfixing''?','Fixing a computer that is hot','A process to quickly fix a critical bug directly in the production environment or staging, bypassing the normal development cycle','Deleting the production server','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Hotfixes are urgent and usually merged back into the development branches immediately.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is the purpose of `git stash`?','To delete current work','To temporarily save (shelve) uncommitted changes so you can work on something else with a clean directory, and bring them back later','To rename a file','To speed up Git','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Stashing is helpful when you need to switch branches urgently but aren''t ready to commit.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is a ''Smoke Test'' in a deployment pipeline?','Testing if the server has smoke','A quick set of tests to verify that the most critical functions of the application work after a deployment (e.g., ''does the site load?'')','Deleting the app','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Smoke tests are the first line of defense after a deploy to catch major failures instantly.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','In `1.4.2`, which number represents the ''Minor'' version in SemVer?','1','4','2','none','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'In MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH, the second number is the minor version (usually for new features).','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is ''Upstream'' in the context of forks?','The original repository from which you forked','A server located in the attic','Deleting the code','none of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Developers keep their local forks in sync by pulling from the ''upstream'' repository.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is a ''Docker Image Tag'' usually used for in a pipeline?','Naming the container','Versioning the image (e.g., ''latest'', ''v1.2'', or the commit SHA) to identify which version to deploy','Deleting the image','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Avoid using ''latest'' in production because it can point to different versions at different times, leading to inconsistent environments.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is ''Zero Downtime Deployment''?','A deployment that takes no time','A strategy where the new version is brought online without any interruption of service to the users','Deleting the app during the day','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'This is achieved through techniques like Blue-Green or Rolling Updates.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is a ''Provisioner'' in IaC (e.g., in Terraform)?','A person who provides food','A component used to execute scripts or shell commands on a local or remote machine as part of resource creation/deletion','A ways to delete a server','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Provisioners are often used for bootstrapping initial software setup on a newly created server.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What does `git bisect` do?','Cuts the code in half','Uses binary search to find the specific commit that introduced a bug (regression)','Deletes the Git folders','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Bisect is a powerful debugging tool for finding when a long-standing bug was merged.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is ''Jenkins Pipeline'' syntax ''Scripted'' vs ''Declarative''?','One is old, one is new','Scripted uses full Groovy flexibility; Declarative uses a stricter, pre-defined structure that is easier for most users','There is no difference','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Declarative is now the recommended standard for modern Jenkins pipelines.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is a ''Build Promotion''?','Giving the build a raise','The process of marking an artifact as ''validated'' for the next environment (e.g., moving from Staging to Production)','Deleting the build','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Promotion ensures that only thoroughly tested binaries reach the production stage.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What characterizes ''Secrets Scanning''?','Scanning for secret files','Automatically checking every commit to ensure no passwords, API keys, or certificates are committed in plain text','Deleting the commits','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Tools like ''git-secrets'' or GitHub''s native secret scanning prevent major security leaks.','pregenerated'),
('add5fc9b-8950-4777-a8b5-1f731cc54b76','What is ''Event-Driven'' CI/CD?','Starting pipelines only on holidays','A system where pipelines are triggered by specific events (like a GitHub issue comment, a new image in a registry, or a cloud alert)','Deleting the events','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Event-driven workflows enable advanced automation scenarios beyond just code pushes.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is the role of an ''Operator'' (e.g. ArgoCD, Flux) in GitOps?','To download code','To continuously monitor the Git repository and ensure the cluster state matches the desired state defined in Git','To delete pods','To write code','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'GitOps operators like ArgoCD automate the synchronization between Git (the source) and Kubernetes (the target).','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is ''Software Supply Chain Security''?','Building computers','The practice of securing all code, dependencies, and tools used in the software development life cycle','Only for hardware','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Supply chain security involves things like code signing, vulnerability scanning, and SBOM (Software Bill of Materials).','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is ''Contract Testing''?','Testing the legal department','Testing the interactions between services to ensure following a shared agreement without needing to spin up the whole system','Deleting the code','Only for frontend','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Contract testing (like Pact) is essential for microservices to ensure that changes in one service don''t break others.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is the ''Three Pillars of Observability''?','CPU, RAM, Disk','Logs, Metrics, Traces','Users, Apps, Servers','Code, Test, Deplay','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Logs (detailed events), Metrics (aggregated numbers), and Traces (request flow) provide a complete view of system health.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','How does a Service Mesh (like Istio) help with Canary deployments?','It deletes old pods','It provides fine-grained traffic routing to send a specific percentage of requests to the new version','It writes the tests','It manages the database','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Service meshes allow you to shift traffic based on headers, weights, or user IDs without changing app code.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is ''Mutable'' vs ''Immutable'' Infrastructure?','Mutable is for users, Immutable is for robots','Mutable infrastructure is updated in-place; Immutable infrastructure is replaced entirely with a new version for every change','There is no difference','Immutable is slow','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Immutable infrastructure (e.g., cattle, not pets) reduces configuration drift and improves reliability.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is ''Feature Toggling'' (Feature Flags)?','A ways to name a branch','A technique to decouple code deployment from feature release, allowing features to be turned on/off dynamically','Deleting old features','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Feature flags allow teams to merge code into the main branch even if it''s not finished, hiding it behind a toggle.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is a ''Quality Gate'' in a pipeline?','A literal gate at the office','A threshold (e.g. at least 80% test coverage) that code must meet to proceed through the pipeline','A ways to name a test','A backup server','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Quality gates ensure that only code meeting the organization''s standards can reach production.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is a ''Pre-commit'' hook used for?','To delete code','To run checks (like linting or formatting) locally before a commit is even created','To push code to remote','To rename a file','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Pre-commit hooks catch simple errors early, before they reach the central repository.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is the purpose of ''Git Submodules''?','To name the files','To keep a Git repository as a subdirectory of another Git repository, maintaining its own history','To delete history','To speed up Git','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Submodules allow you to include external libraries while tracking specific versions.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is ''DAST''?','Detailed Automated System Tracking','Dynamic Application Security Testing: Testing the application while it is running from the outside (like a hacker)','Data Analysis and Source Testing','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'DAST probes running applications to find vulnerabilities like SQL injection or Z-day exploits.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What does ''Shield Left'' mean in DevSecOps?','Moving security tasks earlier in the software development lifecycle','Buying more shields','Deleting the database','Deploying only on the left side of the data center','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Shifting left means integrating security checks during the design and coding stages, not just at the end.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is ''Self-Healing'' in a CI/CD context?','The computer fixing itself','The ability of the system to automatically detect and correct failures (e.g. restarting a crashed pod) without human intervention','Deleting the server','Naming the pods','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Platforms like Kubernetes provide native self-healing capabilities through control loops.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is ''Semantic Versioning'' (SemVer)?','Naming files by their meaning','A versioning scheme (MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH) that conveys meaning about the underlying changes','Deleting old versions','A ways to count lines of code','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'SemVer helps users understand the impact of upgrading a dependency (e.g. potential breaking changes).','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','Which tool uses a ''pull-based'' synchronization model for Kubernetes clusters?','Jenkins','ArgoCD','GitLab CI (Standard)','Azure DevOps (Standard)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'In a pull model, the operator inside the cluster pulls configuration from Git, which is more secure than pushing from an external CI server.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What characterizes a ''Server-side Git Hook'' (e.g. pre-receive)?','It runs on the developer''s laptop','It is enforced on the remote Git server and can reject pushes that violate organizational policy (e.g. no secrets or linting errors)','It deletes the repository','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Server-side hooks are the most secure way to enforce standards because they cannot be bypassed by the developer.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is the primary difference between ''Helm'' and ''Kustomize'' for Kubernetes management?','Helm is faster','Helm uses templates (YAML with placeholders); Kustomize uses ''overlays'' to modify base YAML files without templates','Kustomize is only for small apps','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Helm is better for packaging complex apps for others, while Kustomize is often preferred for in-house GitOps workflows due to its ''template-less'' approach.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','In GitOps, what is a ''Reconciliation Loop''?','A ways to delete a loop','The continuous process where the operator compares the Git state (desired) to the Cluster state (actual) and applies changes to fix any ''drift''','A ways to rename a cluster','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Reconciliation ensures the environment is always self-healing back to the state defined in version control.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','How does ''Sealed Secrets'' (Bitnami) help in a GitOps workflow?','It encrypts the whole Git repo','It allows you to safely store ''encrypted'' secrets in Git which can only be decrypted by the controller running inside your Kubernetes cluster','It deletes secrets after use','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Sealed Secrets solves the problem of ''secrets in Git'' by ensuring only the cluster has the private key to read them.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is a ''Shadow Deployment'' (Traffic Mirroring)?','A deployment with no light','Sending a copy of real production traffic to a new version of the app without the users seeing the response, allowing for risk-free performance testing','A way to hide code','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Shadow deployments allow you to see how a new version handles real-world load without any risk to actual users.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is ''Artifact Attestation''?','Naming the build','A cryptographically signed statement about where and how an artifact was built, providing verifiable proof of its integrity','A list of build steps','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Attestations (using tools like Cosign) are a core part of Level 3/4 SLSA compliance.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is ''Kaniko'' used for in a Kubernetes-based CI pipeline?','Running tests','Building Docker images from a Dockerfile inside a container or cluster without needing privileged access to the host Docker daemon','Deleting old images','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Kaniko is vital for security because it avoids the ''Docker-in-Docker'' (DinD) requirement which needs hazardous elevated privileges.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is ''Incremental Building'' in a CI system?','Building the app slowly','A technique where only the parts of the application that have changed since the last build are recompiled, significantly reducing build times','Deleting the app building','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Tools like Bazel or Nx specialize in incremental builds for massive monorepos.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What characterizes ''Distributed Tracing'' (e.g. Jaeger)?','Tracing the user''s location','Tracking a single request as it flows through multiple microservices, showing exactly where time was spent and where errors occurred','Counting the logs line by line','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Tracing is essential for debugging performance bottlenecks in complex cloud-native architectures.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','How is an ''Error Budget'' typically calculated?','Counting bugs in Jira','100% minus the SLO percentage (e.g. a 99.9% availability SLO gives a 0.1% error budget)','Subtracting salary from revenue','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'The error budget determines how much ''instability'' is allowed before feature work must stop in favor of stability work.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is a ''Jenkins Shared Library''?','A ways to swap code with other companies','A separate Git repository containing Groovy code that can be imported into multiple Jenkinsfiles to avoid code duplication and standardize pipeline logic','A ways to delete old jobs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Shared libraries allow platform teams to manage ''Pipeline as Code'' at scale across an entire organization.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is the purpose of ''Gating'' in a deployment pipeline?','Closing the office','Using automated checks (e.g. error rate < 1%) or manual approvals to prevent code from automatically progressing to the next environment','A ways to name a user','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Gating provides safety barriers that prevent broad user impact from failed releases.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What characterizes ''Trunk-Based Development'' compared to ''Gitflow''?','It has more branches','It eliminates long-lived feature branches, favoring short-lived branches and frequent merges to the main ''trunk'' to enable continuous integration','It is only for small teams','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Trunk-based development is a prerequisite for reaching elite DevOps performance (DORA metrics).','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is a ''Runners'' security risk in shared CI environments?','Running too fast','Potential for code from one project to access data or environments of another project if the runner isn''t properly isolated (e.g. multi-tenant security)','A ways to see the logs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Using ephemeral, isolated runners (like per-job VMs or containers) is the best practice to prevent cross-contamination.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is ''Vulnerability Scanning'' at the Registry level?','Watching the registry for new users','Automatically scanning container images for known security vulnerabilities (CVEs) as soon as they are pushed to the registry','Deleting images that have no tags','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Registry-side scanning provides a final safety check before an image can be pulled into production.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is an ''Exponential Backoff'' strategy for retries?','Pushing the code harder','A technique where the time between retry attempts increases exponentially (e.g. 1s, 2s, 4s...) to avoid overloading a struggling system','Deleting the request','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Exponential backoff is a core principle for building resilient distributed systems that don''t cause ''thundering herd'' problems.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What does ''MTTR'' stand for and why is it important?','Mean Time To Recover: measuring how quickly you can restore service after a failure','Maximum Time To Release','Mean Time To Rename','none of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'MTTR is a key DORA metric reflecting the team''s ability to diagnose and fix production issues efficiently.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is a ''Composite Action'' in GitHub Actions?','A ways to combine files','An action that allows you to combine multiple workflow steps (scripts or other actions) into a single reusable action within one file','A ways to delete actions','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Composite actions are perfect for packaging common multi-step sequences (like setup + build + test) to simplify workflows.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What characterizes ''Reusable Workflows'' in GitHub Actions?','Copying and pasting YAML','Calling an entire workflow from another workflow, passing inputs and secrets, which allows for centralizing standard deployment logic across teams','Deleting old workflows','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Reusable workflows are the ''functions'' of the GitHub Actions ecosystem, ensuring consistency across many repositories.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is ''Configuration Drift'' and how do GitOps tools address it?','When a cloud provider moves a server','When the live environment is changed manually (via CLI or UI); GitOps tools detect this diff and automatically revert the change to match the state in Git','A ways to rename files','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Self-healing reconciliation is the primary defense against ''sneaky'' manual changes that make environments inconsistent.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is ''Mutation Testing''?','Changing the user interface','A technique where the testing tool modifies the source code (mutates it) and checks if the existing test suite fails (if it doesn''t fail, the test coverage is weak)','Deleting the code','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Mutation testing evaluates the ''quality'' of your tests, not just the ''quantity'' (coverage).','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is ''Auditability'' in a CI/CD environment?','The ability to run the pipeline','The ability to trace every production change back to a specific person, a specific ticket, and a specific commit in version control','A ways to see the user list','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Audit trails are critical for compliance (SOC2) and security forensics.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What characterizes ''A/B Testing'' through a pipeline?','Testing two versions of the name','Deploying two different feature variants and using metrics to see which one performs better for business goals (e.g. conversion rate)','Deleting either A or B','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'A/B testing allows data-driven decision making about which features are actually valuable to users.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is a ''Circuit Breaker'' pattern?','A fuse in the server room','A mechanism that detects when a service is failing and automatically ''trips'' to stop requests to that service, allowing it to recover and preventing a cascade of failures','Deleting the connection','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Circuit breakers protect the overall system health by ''failing fast'' when a dependency is down.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What characterizes ''ChatOps''?','Talking while coding','Interacting with infrastructure and pipelines directly through chat tools (like Slack/Teams) using bots that execute commands and output results for the team to see','Deleting the chat history','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'ChatOps brings visibility to operations by making actions and results public and collaborative.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is ''Image Signing'' (e.g. Notary/Cosign)?','Writing your name on an image','Using cryptographic keys to ''sign'' an image, allowing the deployment target to verify that the image hasn''t been tampered with since it was built','A ways to delete images','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Signing ensures that you only run the exact code that was produced by your trusted CI pipeline.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is ''Hydration'' in the context of GitOps (e.g. directory hydration)?','Drinking water during deployment','The process of taking abstract configurations (templates/overlays) and expanding them into the final, concrete YAML files that the cluster understands','A ways to clean the cluster','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Hydration is the final step before the ''diff/sync'' part of the GitOps loop.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is a ''Lockable Resource'' in Jenkins?','A password-protected folder','A feature that prevents multiple pipelines from accessing the same physical or virtual resource (like a specific hardware device or a database) at once','Deleting the resource','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Lockable resources prevent race conditions in pipelines that have to share non-scalable external components.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is ''Ingress Controllers'' role in a pipeline?','Controlling the gate at the office','Managing external access to services within the cluster, often providing load balancing, SSL termination, and name-based virtual hosting','Deleting the network','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Ingress controllers are the entry point for users into your cluster-hosted applications.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is ''Fuzz Testing'' (Fuzzing)?','Testing if the code is fuzzy','An automated testing technique that provides invalid, unexpected, or random data as inputs to a program to find crashes or security holes','Deleting the code errors','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Fuzzing is incredibly effective at finding deep bugs and edge cases that manual test cases would miss.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is ''Toil'' in SRE terminology?','Hard work','The kind of work that is manual, repetitive, automatable, tactical, and scales linearly as the system grows','Deleting the code','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'SREs aim to minimize toil (usually to <50% of their time) to focus on engineering and long-term improvements.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is ''Squash and Merge''?','Combining all commits from a feature branch into a single clean commit before merging into the main branch','Deleting the history','Scaling the code','none of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Squashing keeps the main branch history clean and easy to read by hiding the individual ''work-in-progress'' commits.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is ''Build Matrix'' in CI systems?','A list of developers','A feature that allows running the same job across many different configurations (e.g. different OS, different Node.js versions) simultaneously','A ways to delete a server','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Build matrices are essential for testing cross-platform compatibility without writing repetitive YAML.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is ''Rego'' in the context of pipelines?','A programming language for the web','The declarative policy language used by OPA (Open Policy Agent) to define ''Policy as Code'' (e.g. ''images must come from our registry'')','A tool to delete logs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Rego allows you to write fine-grained security policies that can be enforced at the API, container, or network levels.','pregenerated'),
('fcfab6ab-38ff-4eb4-9fa1-ad37699f38e4','What is ''Multi-cluster GitOps''?','Managing many clusters separately','A pattern where a single Git repository defines high-level configurations that are automatically ''fanned out'' to many clusters across regions','Deleting all clusters at once','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Multi-cluster management is the ultimate goal of GitOps for large, global organizations.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is the goal of ''Chaos Engineering'' in a CI/CD environment?','To create chaos in the office','To intentionally introduce failures into a system to test its resilience and build confidence in its ability to handle production incidents','To delete the cluster','To write bugs','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Chaos engineering (pioneered by Netflix''s Chaos Monkey) helps identify weaknesses before they cause real outages.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is ''Progressive Delivery''?','Deploying slowly','An umbrella term for advanced deployment techniques (Canary, Blue-Green, Feature Flags) combined with automated analysis to reduce risk','Deleting old code','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Progressive delivery uses automated metrics (e.g. error rate) to decide whether to continue a rollout.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','Which Git hook is typically used on the SERVER side to prevent unauthorized pushes?','Pre-commit','Pre-receive','Post-update','Commit-msg','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Pre-receive hooks run on the server and can reject a push if it doesn''t meet security or policy requirements.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','In Terraform, what is the ''State File'' used for?','To name the files','A file that maps real-world resources to your configuration, allowing Terraform to track what it has created and detect drift','To delete the server','To store the code','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The state file is the ''brain'' of Terraform; losing it can make managing infrastructure very difficult.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is ''Spiffe/Spire'' in a cloud-native pipeline?','A ways to delete pods','A standard and toolset for providing secure, cryptographic identities to workloads (mTLS) across heterogeneous environments','A ways to name a user','A cloud provider','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Spiffe allows services to identify each other securely without relying on static IP addresses or shared secrets.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What does ''SLSA'' (pronounced ''salsa'') stand for in the context of CI/CD?','Secure Level Services Agreement','Supply-chain Levels for Software Artifacts: A security framework to prevent tampering and improve integrity','Software Life Cycle Security Analysis','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'SLSA provides a set of standards to ensure that software was built on a trusted system with a verifiable history.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is the ''Comparison'' stage in a GitOps control loop?','Comparing two users','Calculating the difference (diff) between the desired state in Git and the actual state currently running in the cluster','Deleting the cluster','Naming the pods','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The operator uses this ''diff'' to determine what actions (create, update, delete) are needed to reach the desired state.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is ''Docker Layer Caching'' in a CI environment?','A ways to delete images','Reusing previously built layers of a Docker image to significantly speed up subsequent builds if the dependencies haven''t changed','A ways to name the layers','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Layer caching is the single most effective way to reduce build times for containerized applications.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is ''Synthetic Monitoring''?','Using simulated users (probes) to periodically test critical application paths (like login) to ensure they are functional','Fake monitoring','Deleting the logs','Naming the servers','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Synthetic monitoring acts as an ''early warning system'', detecting outages before real users do.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is the ''Git Reflog'' used for?','To name the refs','A mechanism to record when the tips of branches and other references were updated in the local repository, allowing recovery of ''lost'' commits','To delete the history','To speed up Git','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'If you accidentally delete a branch or perform a bad rebase, reflog is your safety net to find the lost work.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is ''Distroless'' images?','Images without a distro','Minimal container images that contain only the application and its runtime dependencies, excluding shell, package managers, and other OS components to reduce attack surface','Images that are free','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Distroless images are more secure because there are fewer tools for an attacker to use if they break in.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is ''Drift Detection''?','Detecting a boat','The process of identifying when the actual state of infrastructure differs from the state defined in your IaC configuration','Deleting the resources','Naming the servers','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'GitOps tools and IaC platforms (like Terraform Cloud) can automatically alert or fix drift to maintain consistency.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is ''Policy as Code''?','Writing rules','Managing and enforcing policies (secure, compliance, cost) through code that can be automatically validated in the pipeline','Deleting the code','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Tools like OPA (Open Policy Agent) allow you to define rules (e.g., ''no public buckets'') that are checked automatically.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What characterizes ''Sidecar Proxy'' performance impact in a CI/CD pipeline?','It speeds up the app','Increased overhead in terms of CPU, memory, and small network latency for every request','It deletes the app','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'While sidecars provide observability and security, they add a cost that must be balanced against their benefits.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is an ''Error Budget'' in SRE?','How much money we pay for bugs','The amount of unreliability (downtime/errors) that a service is allowed to have before development must stop and reliability work begins','Deleting the errors','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Error budgets align the interests of developers (speed) and operations (stability).','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is the ''Steady State'' hypothesis in Chaos Engineering?','A state that never changes','A measurable output of a system that indicates normal behavior, used as a baseline to determine if a chaos experiment has caused a meaningful deviation','Deleting the database','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Defining a steady state is the first step of any chaos experiment to ensure you can detect regression.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','How does ''Flagger'' automate Canary releases in a Kubernetes cluster?','By using flags in the CLI','By using a custom controller that manages traffic shifting (via Istio/Linkerd) and analyzes Prometheus metrics to automatically promote or rollback the release','By deleting the pods','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Flagger automates the ''validation'' part of progressive delivery, removing the need for manual monitoring during rollouts.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What characterizes ''Hermetic Builds'' (SLSA Level 4)?','Builds that are very fast','Builds that are executed in an environment with no network access, ensuring all dependencies are pinned and provided locally to prevent ''dependency confusion'' or tampering','Builds that delete the logs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Hermeticity is the highest level of build integrity, preventing external environment factors from influencing the build output.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','In the Git object model, what is a ''Tree'' object?','A diagram of the code','A simple list of SHA-1 pointers to ''Blob'' (file) objects and other ''Tree'' objects, representing a directory structure at a specific point in time','A ways to delete history','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Git stores the entire snapshot of the project as a Merkle tree, allowing for efficient storage and comparison.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is a ''Trust Bundle'' in the SPIFFE/SPIRE architecture?','A bundle of cash for the team','A collection of CA certificates that a workload uses to verify the identities (SVIDs) of other workloads it communicates with across different trust domains','A ways to name the users','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Trust bundles allow for ''federated'' identity, where services in different clouds can still trust each other securely.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is ''In-toto'' in a secure CI/CD pipeline?','A ways to name the build','A framework to provide end-to-end integrity of the software supply chain by defining ''layouts'' and collecting ''links'' (evidence) of every step in the process','A ways to delete old builds','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'In-toto ensures that the software hasn''t been tampered with from the first commit down to the final deployment.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is a Helm ''Library Chart''?','A chart for a library','A special type of Helm chart that does not deploy any resources itself but provides reusable templates and logic for other ''Application'' charts to use','A ways to delete charts','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Library charts are powerful for maintaining consistency in shared logic across many different microservice charts.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What characterizes ''GitOps Directory Scaling'' challenges in monorepos?','The monorepo gets too big','Excessive API pressure on Git providers and slow reconciliation times as the operator has to scan thousands of directories for changes','The monorepo deletes the history','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Optimizing repository structure and using ''webhook'' triggers instead of polling is vital for large-scale GitOps.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is ''eBPF-powered'' observability in a pipeline?','Watching the logs with a mirror','Using low-level kernel probes (via tools like Falco or Pixie) to get deep, near-zero-overhead insight into system calls and network traffic for every container','Deleting the logs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'eBPF provides unparalleled visibility without requiring any changes to the application code itself.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What characterizes ''Cattle vs Pets'' in the context of GitOps control-plane bootstrap?','Naming the servers after animals','Ensuring the initial GitOps operator and its SSH/API keys are provisioned automatically (e.g. via cloud-init or Terraform) rather than manual setup','Deleting the pets','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'True automation requires that even the ''automator'' is itself automated and easily replaceable.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','How do ''External Secrets'' operators improve pipeline security?','By storing secrets outside the cloud','By fetching secrets directly from external managers (like AWS Secrets Manager or HashiCorp Vault) and injecting them as K8s Secret objects only when needed','By deleting the secrets manager','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'External Secrets operators remove the need to store any sensitive data (even encrypted) inside the Git repository.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is the primary challenge of ''Data CI/CD'' (MLOps) compared to traditional App CI/CD?','The code is longer','Managing versioned ''Data'' and ''Models'' alongside code, where small changes in training data can lead to massive deviations in production behavior','Deleting the data','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Tools like DVC (Data Version Control) are needed to bring Git-like versioning to massive datasets.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is the goal of an ''Internal Developer Platform'' (IDP)?','A ways to host private websites','A self-service layer that allows developers to provision infrastructure, environments, and CI/CD pipelines without needing to be DevOps experts','A ways to delete the developer','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'IDPs reduce cognitive load for developers and standardize best practices across the organization.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is ''Tekton'' and how is it ''Cloud Native''?','A new cloud provider','A CI/CD framework where the pipeline components (tasks, pipelines, runs) are themselves Kubernetes Custom Resources (CRDs)','A tool to delete YAML','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Tekton allows CI/CD logic to be managed exactly like application code within the Kubernetes lifecycle.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What characterizes ''Service Mesh Federation'' in global pipelines?','Merging two companies','Connecting multiple independent service meshes across different clusters/regions to share identity, security, and traffic policies globally','Deleting the mesh','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Federation is critical for global high-availability where one region failing shouldn''t break identity trust.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is ''Continuous Compliance''?','Always following the rules','A practice where every change in the pipeline is automatically audited against regulatory requirements (like HIPAA/GDPR) in real-time, preventing non-compliant code from deploying','Deleting the audits','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Continuous compliance turns ''Audit Season'' from a manual nightmare into an automated report.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is ''Thundering Herd'' in a distributed system recovery?','A bunch of cows','An event where many clients simultaneously retry a request after a failure, overwhelming the server and causing it to fail again','Deleting the connection','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Adding ''Jitter'' to retries is the standard defense against thundering herd problems.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is ''SBOM'' (Software Bill of Materials)?','A list of materials to build a server','A formal, machine-readable inventory of all components, libraries, and dependencies included in a software package, providing transparency for security','A ways to delete files','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'SBOMs are becoming a legal requirement for government software to track upstream supply chain risks.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What characterizes ''GitOps for Database'' (GitOpsDB)?','Putting the database in Git','Managing database schema migrations and configuration through Git using tools like Liquibase or Bytebase within the CI/CD pipeline','Deleting the database','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'GitOpsDB brings the ''source of truth'' paradigm to stateful components, ensuring schemas are versioned and reviewed.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is ''Traffic Pinning'' in progressive delivery?','Pinning a server to the wall','Ensuring a specific user consistently sees the same version of an application (A or B) during a canary rollout to avoid session disruption','Deleting the user cookies','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Session affinity (pinning) is vital for user experience when the different versions have meaningful UI or data differences.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What defines a ''Dangling Object'' in Git?','An object that is hanging','An object that exists in the database but is no longer reachable from any branch or tag, usually after a rebase or delete','A ways to name a file','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Dangling objects are eventually cleaned up by Git''s garbage collection (gc).','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is ''Cardinality'' in the context of metrics/logs?','The number of birds','The number of unique label/value combinations in your metric data; high cardinality (e.g. using User IDs as labels) can crash observability systems','Deleting the tags','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Careful label design is crucial when sending metrics from massive production clusters.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What characterizes ''GameDay'' exercises in SRE?','Playing video games','A scheduled event where a team purposely triggers a production-like failure in a controlled environment to practice their incident response skills','Deleting the game','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'GameDays build muscle memory for SRE teams, ensuring they can react calmly during real outages.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is ''Multi-Region Cell'' architecture?','A jail for servers','Dividing the infrastructure into independent, identical ''Cells'' where one cell failing doesn''t impact others, enabling massive scalability and reliability','Deleting the regions','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Cell-based architecture (used by Amazon/Google) prevents ''blast radius'' expansion from a single region outage.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What characterizes ''Poisoned Pipeline Execution'' (PPE)?','Putting poison on the cables','An attack where a malicious pull request modifies the pipeline definition (e.g. YAML) to steal secrets or execute code on the runner','Deleting the pipeline','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Hardening CI configurations (like preventing PRs from accessing secrets) is vital for repository security.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is ''GitOps Engine''?','The motor of a car','A library (used by ArgoCD) that provides the core logic for syncing, resource monitoring, and diffing between Git and Kubernetes','A tool to delete repositories','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The engine provides the heavy-lifting logic that allows GitOps tools to handle thousands of resources reliably.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is ''Graceful Degradation''?','Being polite while failing','Designing a system so that if some parts fail, the overall system remains functional (e.g. returning a cached result if the database is down)','Deleting the system','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Graceful degradation ensures that a partial failure doesn''t turn into a total blackout for the user.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What characterizes ''Release Candidate'' (RC) in a pipeline?','A person running for office','A version of the application that is believed to be stable and is undergoing final production-readiness testing before official release','Deleting the version','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'RCs allow for late-stage discovery of minor bugs that were missed during earlier testing phases.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is ''Remote Backend'' in Terraform?','A server in the back of the room','Storing the Terraform state file in a centralized, secure location (like S3 or GCS) rather than on the local machine where the CLI is run','A ways to delete files','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Remote backends are mandatory for team collaboration to ensure everyone is working with the same infrastructure state.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is the ''CIS Benchmark'' for Kubernetes?','A ways to mark the code','A set of globally recognized best-practice standards for securing Kubernetes clusters (control plane, nodes, and network)','A tool to delete the pods','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Running a ''kube-bench'' scan against your cluster is the standard way to check for CIS compliance.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What characterizes ''Deployment vs Release'' in elite DevOps teams?','They are the same thing','Deployment is the technical act of moving code to a production environment; Release is the business act of exposing that code to users (using flags)','Deployment is faster','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Decoupling deployment from release allows for safer, risk-free testing in true production environments.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What does `git worktree` do?','Plants a tree in the repo','Allows you to have multiple working directories for a single repository attached to different branches simultaneously','Deletes the Git files','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Worktrees are incredibly helpful for developers who need to work on multiple branches without constantly stashing or switching.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is a ''Jenkins Global Security Configuration'' for CSRF?','A password for Jenkins','A protection mechanism that ensures requests made to the Jenkins API are legitimate and not Cross-Site Request Forgery attacks','Deleting the security logs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Enabling the ''Crumb'' issuer is a mandatory security hardening step for production Jenkins instances.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What is an ''OCI Runtime Specification''?','A way to name containers','The industry standard that defines how a container runtime (like runc) should start, stop, and manage a container process given a configuration file','A tool to delete images','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The OCI spec ensures interoperability across different container runtimes and platforms.','pregenerated'),
('1f2d5c26-d873-4d02-90ed-6c3c777c0262','What characterizes ''DORA Metrics''?','Metrics about the explorer','Deployment Frequency, Lead Time for Changes, Change Failure Rate, and Time to Restore Service','A ways to delete old code','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'DORA metrics are the industry-standard way to measure the performance and maturity of a DevOps organization.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','Which logic gate returns 1 only if all its inputs are 1?','OR','AND','XOR','NAND','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The AND gate requires every input to be true for the output to be true.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','What is the decimal equivalent of the binary number 1011?','9','10','11','13','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'1*2^3 + 0*2^2 + 1*2^1 + 1*2^0 = 8 + 0 + 2 + 1 = 11.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','What is the minimum number of variables required for a Karnaugh Map (K-map) to show 16 cells?','2','3','4','5','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'A K-map with ''n'' variables has 2^n cells. 2^4 = 16.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','According to De Morgan''s Laws, NOT (A AND B) is equivalent to:','(NOT A) AND (NOT B)','(NOT A) OR (NOT B)','A OR B','NOT (A OR B)','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',35,'De Morgan''s law states that the negation of a conjunction is the disjunction of the negations.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','Which of the following are considered ''Universal Gates''?','AND','NAND','NOR','XOR','["B","C"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',30,'NAND and NOR gates are universal because any other logic function can be realized using only those gates.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','Which part of the CPU is responsible for coordinating all activities within the processor?','ALU','Control Unit','Registers','Cache','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The Control Unit (CU) directs the flow of data and instructions within the CPU.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','What does ALU stand for?','Arithmetic Logic Unit','Advanced Logical Unit','Array Logic Universal','Application Layer Utility','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'ALU performs arithmetic and logical operations.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','Which memory is the fastest in a computer system?','RAM','Hard Disk','Cache Memory','Registers','["D"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Registers are located inside the CPU and provide the fastest access.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','In which stage of the instruction cycle is the instruction decoded?','Fetch','Decode','Execute','Store','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Decoding determines which operation the instruction is meant to perform.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','What is the hexadecimal equivalent of binary 1111?','E','F','10','A','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Binary 1111 is 15 in decimal, which is F in hexadecimal.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','How many bits are in one byte?','4','8','16','32','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'A byte is a unit of digital information that most commonly consists of eight bits.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','Which bus is used to specify a physical address in memory?','Data Bus','Control Bus','Address Bus','Expansion Bus','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'The Address Bus carries the address of the data that the CPU wants to access.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','Which register holds the memory address of the next instruction to be fetched?','MAR','MDR','Program Counter (PC)','Accumulator','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'The PC keeps track of the next instruction in memory.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','Which gate is known as an inverter?','OR','AND','NOT','XOR','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The NOT gate flips the input bit.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','RAM is ________ computer memory.','Volatile','Non-volatile','Secondary','Permanent','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'RAM loses its data when the power is turned off.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','In Von Neumann architecture, where are instructions and data stored?','Separate memories','Same memory','Registers only','Hard drive only','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Von Neumann architecture uses a single storage system for instructions and data.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','What does DMA stand for?','Data Memory Access','Direct Memory Access','Dual Master Architecture','Direct Module Access','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'DMA allows hardware subsystems to access main memory independently of the CPU.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','What is the 2''s complement of the binary number 0110?','1001','1010','1100','0111','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'1''s complement of 0110 is 1001. Adding 1 gives 1010.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','Which register holds the data being fetched from or stored into memory?','Accumulator','Instruction Register','Memory Data Register (MDR)','Flag Register','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'MDR (or MBR) holds the content of the memory word currently being accessed.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','How many outputs does a half adder have?','1','2','3','4','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'A half adder has two outputs: Sum and Carry.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','Which method of generating control signals uses a small memory called control store?','Hardwired control','Microprogrammed control','Software control','Direct control','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Microprogrammed control units store control sequences in a microcode memory.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','1 Gigabyte (GB) is equivalent to how many Megabytes (MB) in standard binary prefix?','100','1000','1024','512','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'In binary, 1 GB = 1024 MB.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','An instruction consists of two main parts: Opcode and ________.','Mnemonic','Operand','Variable','Comment','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Opcode specifies the operation, and Operand specifies the data or its address.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','What type of computers are primarily used for scientific research and weather forecasting?','Mainframes','Microcomputers','Supercomputers','Workstations','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Supercomputers have extremely high calculation speeds.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','What is the output of XOR gate if both inputs are 1?','0','1','High impedance','Undefined','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'XOR gate returns 1 only if inputs are different.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','What is a main characteristic of RISC architecture?','Complex instructions','Large instruction set','Small, simple instruction set','Variable length instructions','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Reduced Instruction Set Computer (RISC) focuses on simplified instructions for faster execution.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','A CPU flag that indicates a zero result from an arithmetic operation is called:','Carry flag','Sign flag','Zero flag','Overflow flag','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The zero flag is set to 1 if the ALU result is zero.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','Cache memory works on the principle of:','Locality of reference','Parallelism','Virtualization','Random distribution','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Locality of reference refers to the tendency of processors to access same set of memory locations repeatedly.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','According to IEEE 754 standard, a single-precision float uses how many bits?','16','32','64','80','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Single-precision is 32-bit, double-precision is 64-bit.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','The width of the data bus determines the ________ bit size of the processor.','Internal','External','Word','Cache','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Word size is often matched to the data bus width.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','A full adder adds how many bits at a time?','2','3','4','1','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'A full adder adds two significant bits and an incoming carry bit (total 3).','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','Which architecture is known for having a bottle neck between CPU and Memory?','Harvard','Von Neumann','Parallel','Distributed','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The ''Von Neumann Bottleneck'' occurs because instructions and data share the same bus.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','Which of these is an example of primary storage?','USB Drive','Magnetic Tape','RAM','CD-ROM','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'RAM is the main internal memory accessed directly by the CPU.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','A Multiplexer (MUX) is also known as a:','Data decoder','Data selector','Data encoder','Data multiplier','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'A MUX selects one of many inputs and forwards it to a single output line.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','In which addressing mode is the operand specified in the instruction itself?','Direct','Indirect','Immediate','Register','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Immediate addressing includes the actual constant value in the instruction.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','What is the result of binary addition 1010 + 0101?','10000','1111','1100','1011','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'1010 (10) + 0101 (5) = 1111 (15).','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','Virtual memory is a technique used to:','Simulate faster RAM','Allow execution of programs larger than physical memory','Speed up the cache','Create more registers','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',40,'Virtual memory maps logical addresses to physical disk or RAM locations.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','Which of these gates have exactly TWO inputs?','NOT','XOR','Standard AND','Three-input NOR','["B","C"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',30,'XOR and standard AND are binary operations (2 inputs). NOT is unary (1 input).','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','The time taken to fetch, decode and execute an instruction is called:','Cycle time','Instruction time','Access time','Response time','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Instruction time refers to the full lifetime of one instruction in the pipeline.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','The register that stores the result of ALU operations is the:','Program Counter','Instruction Register','Accumulator','Stack Pointer','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The Accumulator is a general-purpose register for intermediate results.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','Which signals are handled by the Control Bus?','Read/Write signals','Data bits','Memory addresses','File contents','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'The Control Bus carries synchronization and operational signals like ''Clock'', ''Read'', ''Write''.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','Pipelining improves CPU performance by:','Increasing clock speed','Decreasing instruction count','Allowing multiple instructions to be in different stages of execution','Reducing memory size','["C"]'::jsonb,'tricky',45,'Pipelining increases throughput by overlapping instruction execution phases.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','CISC stands for:','Complex Instruction Set Computer','Control Instruction System Central','Combined Instruction Software Computer','Central Internet System Connector','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'CISC focuses on complex instructions that can perform multiple steps.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','Which gate is known as the ''All or Nothing'' gate for its 0 output?','OR','NAND','AND','NOR','["D"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'A NOR gate outputs 1 ONLY if all inputs are 0.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','Who is considered the father of modern computer architecture?','Bill Gates','John von Neumann','Steve Jobs','Alan Turing','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Von Neumann architecture is the basis for most modern computers.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','A Decoder converts ''n'' input lines into ________ output lines.','n^2','2n','2^n','log n','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'A decoder has n inputs and 2^n outputs.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','Harvard architecture differs from Von Neumann by having ________.','More CPUs','Separate data and instruction memories','Larger registers','Wireless memory','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Harvard architecture allows simultaneous fetching of data and instructions.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','The time delay between memory request and data arrival is called:','Cycle time','Latency','Bandwidth','Refresh rate','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Memory latency is the lag time from request to fulfillment.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','In Boolean algebra, A + 0 is equal to:','0','1','A','NOT A','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'Adding 0 (OR with 0) to a Boolean variable does not change its value.','pregenerated'),
('503a2bc3-cfed-4fab-88da-923f60d7939a','If you connect both inputs of a NAND gate together, what gate is formed?','AND','OR','NOT','XOR','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'NAND(A, A) results in NOT A.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('9d8e22b4-23b6-410a-9a56-70e4071bd06d','Which level of memory hierarchy is the fastest and closest to the CPU core?','Main Memory (RAM)','L1 Cache','Registers','L2 Cache','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Registers are located inside the CPU and provide almost instantaneous access compared to other memory types.','pregenerated'),
('9d8e22b4-23b6-410a-9a56-70e4071bd06d','In CPU pipelining, what is the goal of overlapping instruction execution?','To reduce the clock cycle time','To increase instruction throughput (instructions per second)','To simplify the control unit','To eliminate the need for a clock','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Pipelining doesn''t speed up a single instruction (latency) but increases the number of instructions finished per second (throughput).','pregenerated'),
('9d8e22b4-23b6-410a-9a56-70e4071bd06d','What does RAM stand for, and what is its primary characteristic?','Read-Always Memory; Persistent','Random Access Memory; Volatile','Rapid Access Module; Volatile','Real-time Array Management; Persistent','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'RAM is Random Access Memory, meaning any byte can be accessed directly. It is volatile, losing data when power is removed.','pregenerated'),
('9d8e22b4-23b6-410a-9a56-70e4071bd06d','Which of the following are types of locality that caches exploit?','Temporal Locality','Spatial Locality','Logical Locality','Physical Locality','["A","B"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',35,'Temporal locality means recently accessed data is likely to be accessed again soon. Spatial locality means nearby data is likely to be accessed soon.','pregenerated'),
('9d8e22b4-23b6-410a-9a56-70e4071bd06d','A situation where the next instruction cannot execute because of a dependency on a previous instruction''s data is called:','Control Hazard','Structural Hazard','Data Hazard','Memory Leak','["C"]'::jsonb,'tricky',40,'Data hazards occur when instructions that exhibit data dependence overlap in execution.','pregenerated'),
('9d8e22b4-23b6-410a-9a56-70e4071bd06d','An instruction with zero addresses is commonly found in which type of architecture?','Stack-based architecture','Register-based architecture','Accumulator architecture','Memory-to-memory architecture','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Stack architectures use implicit operands from the top of the stack.','pregenerated'),
('9d8e22b4-23b6-410a-9a56-70e4071bd06d','Which I/O technique allows a device to transfer data directly to memory without constant CPU intervention?','Programmed I/O','Interrupt-initiated I/O','Direct Memory Access (DMA)','Polling','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'DMA controllers handle the data transfer, freeing the CPU for other tasks.','pregenerated'),
('9d8e22b4-23b6-410a-9a56-70e4071bd06d','In auto-increment addressing mode, when is the register incremented?','Before fetching the operand','After fetching the operand','During instruction fetch','Only on branch instructions','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The effective address is the register''s current value, which is then incremented for the next use.','pregenerated'),
('9d8e22b4-23b6-410a-9a56-70e4071bd06d','Which cache mapping technique allows a block of main memory to be loaded into any line of the cache?','Direct mapping','Fully associative mapping','Set-associative mapping','Sector mapping','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Fully associative mapping provides the most flexibility but requires complex hardware for searching.','pregenerated'),
