('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','Which component of the CPU is responsible for coordinating the activities of all other components?','ALU (Arithmetic Logic Unit)','Control Unit','Register File','Bus Interface','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'The Control Unit directs the operation of the processor by providing timing and control signals.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is a defining characteristic of a RISC (Reduced Instruction Set Computer) architecture?','Highly complex instructions that take many cycles','A small set of simple, uniform-length instructions optimized for high-speed execution','No use of pipelining','Direct hardware support for high-level language constructs','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'RISC focuses on simple instructions that can be executed in a single clock cycle, enabling efficient pipelining.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','In a Hardwired Control Unit, how are control signals generated?','By executing microcode stored in ROM','By fixed combinational and sequential logic circuits','By the operating system','By a software interpreter','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Hardwired control units use physical circuits to generate signals, which is faster but less flexible than microprogrammed control.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','Which of the following are generally associated with CISC (Complex Instruction Set Computer) architectures?','Variable length instructions','Rich set of addressing modes','Large number of general-purpose registers','Emphasis on hardware complexity to simplify software','["A","B","D"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',40,'CISC (like x86) uses complex instructions and many addressing modes. RISC typically uses more registers to offset its simpler instruction set.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','Which register holds the address of the next instruction to be fetched?','Instruction Register (IR)','Program Counter (PC)','Memory Address Register (MAR)','Accumulator','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The PC keeps track of where the CPU is in its program execution.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is a ''Data Hazard'' in a CPU pipeline?','The CPU catching fire','A situation where an instruction depends on the result of a previous instruction that hasn''t completed yet','Deleting the wrong file','A power surge','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Data hazards occur when the pipeline must stall or forward data because of dependencies.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','How does ''Branch Prediction'' improve pipeline performance?','By doubling CPU speed','By guessing the outcome of conditional branches to avoid pipeline stalls (flushes)','By increasing memory size','By deleting old code','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Effective branch prediction keeps the pipeline full of useful instructions.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is ''Direct Mapping'' in cache memory?','A ways to name files','A technique where each block of main memory is mapped to exactly one possible cache location','Cache that only stores addresses','A ways to delete cache','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Direct mapping is simple to implement but can lead to high conflict misses.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What defines ''Set-Associative Mapping''?','Grouping files','Dividing the cache into sets, where each memory block can be placed in any line within its designated set','Only allowing 2 cache lines total','A ways to encrypt cache','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Set-associative is a compromise between direct and fully associative mapping, balancing complexity and performance.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is ''Programmed I/O''?','I/O that uses AI','A method where the CPU manually checks the status of an I/O device and transfers data, wasting CPU cycles in polling','I/O that only works with Java','Automatic data transfer','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Programmed I/O is simple but inefficient as the CPU is tied up waiting for the device.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','How does ''Interrupt-Driven I/O'' improve efficiency?','By turning off the screen','By allowing the CPU to perform other tasks until the I/O device signals that it is ready for data transfer','By deleting old tasks','By increasing clock speed','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The CPU doesn''t need to poll the device; the device ''interrupts'' the CPU when ready.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is the primary role of a ''DMA Controller''?','Managing internet speed','Managing data transfers between I/O devices and main memory without continuous CPU involvement','Encrypting hard drives','Controlling the monitor','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Direct Memory Access (DMA) frees the CPU for other tasks during large data transfers.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is ''Cycle Stealing'' in DMA?','Deleting CPU cycles','A process where the DMA controller takes control of the system bus for one clock cycle to transfer a data word','Clock speed manipulation','A virus','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'The DMA controller ''steals'' a cycle from the CPU to perform a transfer.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is the purpose of the ''TLB'' (Translation Lookaside Buffer)?','To cache file names','To act as a high-speed cache for page table entries, speeding up the translation of virtual addresses to physical addresses','To store internet passwords','To encrypt RAM','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'The TLB avoids slow lookups in the full page table stored in main memory.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is a ''Page Fault''?','A bug in a web page','An interrupt that occurs when a requested page is not currently in physical memory','A ways to delete a page','A printing error','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'When a page fault occurs, the OS must fetch the page from disk into RAM.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What are the four basic stages of the instruction cycle?','Write, Read, Delete, Repeat','Fetch, Decode, Execute, Store','Start, Process, End, Shutdown','Input, Logic, Output, Storage','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'These stages define how any instruction is handled by the CPU.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is the difference between a synchronous and asynchronous bus?','Color of the wires','Synchronous buses use a common clock signal for all devices; asynchronous uses handshaking protocols','Asynchronous is only for printers','There is no difference','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Synchronous is faster for fixed speeds; asynchronous is more flexible for different device speeds.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is ''Micro-operations''?','Small CPU chips','Functional or atomic operations that are performed to execute a microcode instruction','Calculating very small numbers','A ways to delete registers','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'A single machine instruction is broken down into a sequence of micro-operations.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is a ''Vectored Interrupt''?','An interrupt with a direction','An interrupt where the device provides the memory address (vector) of the service routine to the CPU','A ways to cancel interrupts','A circular interrupt','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Vectored interrupts allow for faster handling as the CPU doesn''t have to poll to find the source.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is ''Interrupt Latency''?','Clock speed','The time elapsed from the arrival of an interrupt signal to the start of the execution of its service routine','The duration of an interrupt','CPU cooling time','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Lower latency is critical for real-time systems.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is the function of the ''Instruction Register'' (IR)?','Counting instructions','Holding the instruction that is currently being decoded or executed','Holding the result of addition','managing memory','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Once fetched from memory, an instruction must stay in the IR until it is finished.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is ''Indirect Addressing''?','Addressing a friend','An addressing mode where the address field of the instruction contains the memory address where the effective address is stored','Directly using a register','A ways to delete memory','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Indirect addressing requires two memory accesses to get the data.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','How can ''Structural Hazards'' in a pipeline be minimized?','Building a better case','By duplicating functional units or using separate caches for data and instructions (Harvard architecture)','By lowering the voltage','By deleting old code','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Structural hazards occur when two instructions need the same hardware resource at the same time.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is ''Daisy Chaining'' in bus arbitration?','Planting flowers','A centralized arbitration method where a grant signal is passed sequentially through each device in order of priority','A ways to delete devices','Random device selection','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Daisy chaining is simple but can lead to unfairness if many devices are connected.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What defines ''Memory-Mapped I/O''?','Mapping the hard drive','A technique where I/O devices are assigned addresses in the same address space as main memory, allowing memory instructions to access I/O','I/O that only uses RAM','A ways to delete BIOS','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Memory-mapped I/O simplifies instruction sets but reduces available memory address space.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is ''Amdahl''s Law'' used for in COA?','Calculating electricity cost','Calculating the theoretical speedup in latency of the execution of a task at fixed workload that can be expected of a system whose resources are improved','A ways to delete users','Measuring weight of components','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'It highlights that the speedup is limited by the serial portion of the task.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is ''Cache Coherency'' in a multi-core processor?','Making cache look nice','The uniformity of shared resource data that ends up stored in multiple local caches','Deleting all cache','A clock speed sync','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Protocols like MESI are used to ensure all cores see the same data for a shared memory location.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is an ''Opcode''?','An opening code','The portion of a machine language instruction that specifies the operation to be performed','The name of the CPU','A ways to delete registers','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Opcode (Operation Code) tells the CPU whether to add, subtract, load, etc.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is the ''Accumulator'' register?','A register for counting dust','A register in which intermediate arithmetic and logic results are stored','The main clock','naming variables','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'In many simple processors, the accumulator is the primary work area for calculations.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is ''Memory Interleaving''?','Folding memory','Slicing memory into multiple modules so that consecutive addresses are in different modules, allowing parallel access to increase throughput','A ways to delete RAM','Using two keyboards','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Interleaving hides the latency of individual memory chips.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is ''Microprogramming''?','Programming small apps','The implementation of a control unit by using a small internal memory to store sequences of micro-instructions','Coding in C','A training system','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Microprogramming makes it easier to update or add new machine instructions to a CPU.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is the purpose of a ''Multiplexer'' (MUX) in computer architecture?','To multiply numbers','To select one of many input signals and forward it to a single output line','To delete old data','A security gate','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'MUXes are essential for choosing which data source (register, ALU, etc.) goes to a specific destination.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is ''Isolated I/O''?','I/O in a box','A technique where I/O devices have a separate address space from main memory, requiring special instructions like IN and OUT','I/O that is broken','A training dashboard','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Isolated I/O leaves more address space for RAM but requires a more complex CPU.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is a ''Full Adder'' circuit?','Something that adds everything','A logical circuit that performs an addition operation on three one-bit binary numbers (two bits and a carry-in)','A calculator app','A way to delete bits','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Full adders can be chained together to add multi-bit binary numbers.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is a ''Control Hazard''?','Loosing the remote','A situation where the pipeline doesn''t know which instruction to fetch next due to a branch or jump','A power failure','Too many users','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Control hazards (or branch hazards) break the flow of the pipeline.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is ''Instruction-Level Parallelism'' (ILP)?','Using many CPUs','The overlap of individual instruction executions to perform more than one operation at a time within a single CPU core','Running two apps','naming variables','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'ILP is achieved through techniques like pipelining and superscalar execution.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','In Flynn''s Taxonomy, what does ''SIMD'' stand for?','Simple Instruction Multi Data','Single Instruction, Multiple Data','Secure Inter-Memory Device','Some Information More Data','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'SIMD describes architectures like GPUs where the same operation is applied to an array of data simultaneously.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is ''Speculative Execution''?','Buying servers cheap','An optimization where a computer system performs some task that is not yet prompted, to improve performance if the task is eventually needed','A ways to delete code','managing memory','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Speculative execution helps hide branch latency but can lead to security vulnerabilities like Spectre.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is ''Average Memory Access Time'' (AMAT) formula?','Size / Speed','Hit Time + (Miss Rate * Miss Penalty)','Clock Speed * 2','Total RAM / 10','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'AMAT is the standard metric used to evaluate the efficiency of a cache system.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is the ''LRU'' (Least Recently Used) replacement policy?','Deleting random files','Replacing the cache line that has not been accessed for the longest period of time','Replacing the first file always','Keep everything forever','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'LRU is a common and effective cache replacement algorithm based on temporal locality.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What characterizes ''Write-Through'' cache policy?','Writing through paper','Information is written to both the cache and the main memory simultaneously','Only writing to RAM','A training system','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Write-through is simple and keeps memory consistent but is slower than write-back.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What characterizes ''Write-Back'' cache policy?','Writing backwards','Information is only written to the cache; memory is updated only when the cache line is evicted','A ways to delete files','Calculations on paper','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Write-back is faster as it reduces memory traffic, but requires a ''dirty bit'' to track changes.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is ''Cycle Stealing'' in the context of I/O?','A bug in the BIOS','The DMA controller pausing the CPU''s bus access to perform a data transfer','Deleting clock cycles','A ways to rename devices','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'It minimizes CPU interruption during slow I/O operations.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is ''Booth''s Algorithm'' used for?','Connecting booths','A multiplication algorithm that multiplies two signed binary numbers in two''s complement notation','Dividing floats','A ways to delete registers','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Booth''s algorithm is efficient because it reduces the number of additions required for multiplication.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is the ''Control Store'' in a microprogrammed CPU?','A local hardware shop','A high-speed memory area where the microinstructions (control words) are stored','The main RAM','A ways to delete data','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'The control store allows for easy updates to the CPU''s machine instruction behaviors.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','In IEEE 754 floating point representation, what is the ''bias'' used for?','Ignoring small numbers','To represent both positive and negative exponents without using a separate sign bit for the exponent itself','To delete errors','Increasing precision','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'A bias allows the exponents to be treated as unsigned numbers, simplifying comparisons.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is a ''Vector Processor''?','A CPU that likes math','A CPU designed specifically to perform the same operation on large sets of data (vectors) simultaneously','A ways to delete files','An old version of RISC','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Vector processors were the precursors to modern GPU computing architectures.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is ''Associative Memory'' (or Content-Addressable Memory)?','Memory that remembers everything','A type of memory where data is accessed by its content rather than its physical address','A ways to delete RAM','A backup tool','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'CAM is extremely fast for searching (like in TLBs) but very expensive compared to standard RAM.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What is ''Bus Master''?','The person driving the bus','A device that is currently in control of the system bus and can initiate data transfers','The CPU always','The power supply','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'While the CPU is usually the bus master, DMA controllers can also become bus masters.','pregenerated'),
('9439573b-aa8f-40d3-b201-f3badae44cef','What does ''MIPS'' stand for in computer performance?','Memory In Primary Storage','Millions of Instructions Per Second','Managing Internal Processing Speed','Max Input Power Supply','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'MIPS was a common but often misleading metric of CPU performance.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What is the primary purpose of DMA (Direct Memory Access)?','To allow the CPU to access memory faster','To allow I/O devices to transfer data directly to/from memory without constant CPU involvement','To increase the size of the hard drive','To encrypt data in transit','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'DMA offloads data transfer tasks from the CPU, significantly improving system performance during large data moves.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','In a ''Fully Associative'' cache mapping, where can a main memory block be placed?','Only in one specific cache line determined by its index','In any available cache line','Only in even-numbered cache lines','In a specific set of cache lines','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Fully associative mapping is flexible but requires complex hardware to search all lines simultaneously for a hit.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','Which cache mapping technique suffers from ''Conflict Misses'' because multiple memory blocks map to the same single cache line?','Direct Mapping','Fully Associative','Set Associative','LRU Mapping','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Direct mapping uses a simple ''memory_addr % num_cache_lines'' formula, which is fast but leads to thrashing if multiple frequently used blocks map to the same index.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What is a ''Vectored Interrupt''?','An interrupt that is ignored by the CPU','An interrupt where the device provides the CPU with the address (vector) of its service routine','An interrupt caused by a math error','An interrupt that happens every clock cycle','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Vectored interrupts allow for faster response because the CPU doesn''t have to poll all devices to find the source.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','Which of the following are valid methods of I/O communication between a CPU and a peripheral?','Programmed I/O (Polling)','Interrupt-driven I/O','Direct Memory Access (DMA)','Pipelined I/O','["A","B","C"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',40,'Programmed, Interrupt-driven, and DMA are the three standard I/O communication techiques. Pipelining is a CPU-internal instruction processing technique.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What is the primary mechanism that allows a ''Superscalar'' processor to execute multiple instructions per clock cycle?','A faster clock','Multiple independent execution units (ALUs, FPUs) and hardware that can issue multiple instructions simultaneously','Deleting old instructions','A larger motherboard','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Superscalar processors use multiple pipelines to achieve instruction-level parallelism.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What defines a ''VLIW'' (Very Long Instruction Word) architecture?','Instructions that are very long to read','A design where the compiler is responsible for grouping independent instructions into a single large instruction word to be executed in parallel','A ways to delete registers','A CPU with many fans','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Unlike superscalar, VLIW relies on the compiler, not the hardware, to find parallelism.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What is the ''Sequential Consistency'' model in multiprocessor systems?','Counting numbers in order','A property that ensures the result of any execution is the same as if the operations of all processors were executed in some sequential order','Deleting old memory','A backup tool','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Sequential consistency is the most intuitive but often the most restrictive memory model for performance.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','How does a ''Snooping Protocol'' maintain cache coherence?','By watching the user','By having every cache controller monitor (snoop) the bus for memory transactions related to cache blocks it holds','By deleting all cache daily','By using 2 buses','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Snooping is common in small-scale multiprocessors where a shared bus is available.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What characterizes a ''Directory-Based'' cache coherence protocol?','Storing files in folders','Maintaining a central directory that tracks which caches have copies of each memory block','naming variables','A training system','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Directory-based protocols scale better than snooping as they don''t require broadcast on a bus.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What is a ''Crossbar Switch'' in a multiprocessor system?','A literal switch in the hardware','A non-blocking interconnection network that provides a direct path between every processor and every memory module','A ways to delete data','An internet router','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Crossbar switches provide the highest bandwidth but are very complex to scale.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What defines a ''Hypercube'' interconnection topology?','A 4D cube','A network where N nodes are connected such that each node has log2(N) neighbors, providing low diameter for communication','A cloud server','naming variables','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Hypercubes provide a good balance between the number of links and the distance between nodes.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What is ''Tomasulo''s Algorithm'' used for?','Sorting numbers','A hardware algorithm for dynamic instruction scheduling that allows out-of-order execution by using reservation stations','A ways to delete records','A backup tool','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Tomasulo''s algorithm effectively handles data dependencies and increases pipeline throughput.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What is ''Register Renaming'' designed to prevent?','Naming variables ''x''','False dependencies (WAW and WAR hazards) caused by using a limited number of architectural registers','Deleting registers','A slow clock','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'By mapping architectural registers to a larger pool of physical registers, the CPU can execute more instructions in parallel.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What is ''NUMA'' (Non-Uniform Memory Access) architecture?','Memory that is random','A multiprocessor architecture where memory access time depends on the memory location relative to the processor','A ways to delete RAM','An old version of cache','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'NUMA allows for large-scale multiprocessing by providing local memory to every CPU node.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What is ''Simultaneous Multithreading'' (SMT)?','Running 10 apps at once','A technique that permits multiple independent threads of execution to better utilize the resources provided by modern processor architectures','A ways to delete threads','A training system','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Intel''s Hyper-Threading is a well-known implementation of SMT.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What does ''CPI'' (Cycles Per Instruction) measure?','How many seconds one instruction takes','The average number of clock cycles a processor takes to execute an instruction','The size of the instruction','naming variables','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Lower CPI indicates higher efficiency in instruction execution.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What characterizes a ''Side-Channel Attack'' in computer architecture?','Attacking the side of the server','An attack based on information gained from the physical implementation of a system (e.g. power consumption, timing, electromagnetic leaks)','Deleting hard drives','A ways to name a user','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Side-channel attacks can bypass traditional logical security barriers.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What is the ''Carry Lookahead Adder'' designed to improve?','Carrying heavy parts','Speeding up addition by calculating carry signals simultaneously for all bits rather than waiting for them to ripple through','Deleting carry bits','A training dashboard','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Lookahead adders significantly reduce the gate delay compared to ripple carry adders.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What is the benefit of ''ECC'' (Error Correction Code) memory?','It makes the computer look better','It can detect and fix single-bit memory errors and detect multi-bit errors to prevent system crashes and data corruption','It is cheaper','naming variables','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'ECC is essential for servers and high-reliability computations.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What characterizes ''In-Order Execution''?','Ordering products','Instructions are fetched, decoded, and executed in the exact sequence they appear in the program','A ways to delete code','naming variables','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'In-order execution is simpler to implement but often results in many pipeline stalls.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What is ''Branch Target Buffer'' (BTB) used for?','Buffering internet videos','Storing the predicted target addresses of branch instructions to allow fetching from the target address immediately','A ways to delete branches','A backup tool','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'The BTB works with branch predictors to minimize the penalty of control hazards.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What characterizes ''Memory-Level Parallelism'' (MLP)?','Using 10 RAM sticks','The ability of a processor to handle multiple outstanding memory requests simultaneously (e.g. through a miss status handling register)','A ways to delete files','naming variables','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'MLP helps hide long memory latencies by overlapping them.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What is ''Victim Cache''?','A cache for deleted files','A small, fully associative cache that stores blocks recently evicted from the main cache to reduce conflict misses','A training system','A way to name a user','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Victim caches are a cost-effective way to improve the performance of direct-mapped caches.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What characterizes ''RAID 5''?','5 redundant hard drives','Block-level striping with distributed parity, offering a balance between performance, capacity, and fault tolerance','Deleting 5 records','A security attack','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'RAID 5 can survive the failure of a single drive in the array.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What is ''Trace Cache'' used for in older Pentium 4 CPUs?','Tracing users','Storing sequences of decoded micro-instructions to avoid the need for decoding every time a branch is taken','A ways to delete code','managing memory','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Trace cache optimized the performance of complex instruction decoding.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What defines the ''Roofline Model'' in architecture analysis?','Measuring the roof of a data center','A visual performance model used to provide performance estimates of a given compute kernel running on multi-core, many-core, or accelerator platforms','A ways to delete records','A training system','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It helps determine whether an application is memory-bound or compute-bound.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What is ''InfiniBand'' used for in supercomputers?','Playing music','A high-throughput, low-latency interconnection network used for both internal system communication and external storage connectivity','A ways to delete files','A backup tool','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'InfiniBand is the dominant interconnect for high-performance computing clusters.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','Which component is responsible for power management and thermal monitoring in modern CPUs?','ALU','Integrated Microcontroller (System Management Unit)','RAM controller','The case','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Modern CPUs have dedicated controllers to optimize power based on real-time temperature and load.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What is ''Hardware Multithreading'' (Temporal Multithreading)?','Running two threads at once literally','The ability of a CPU to switch between different thread contexts on a single core to hide stalls','A ways to delete code','A training dashboard','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Temporal multithreading switches when a thread is idle, e.g. waiting for memory.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What characterizes ''Out-of-Order Execution''?','ordering things wrong','A paradigm where a processor executes instructions as soon as their operands are available, instead of in the program''s original sequence','A ways to delete records','A security gate','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Out-of-order execution allows the CPU to work ahead while waiting for slow data fetches.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What is a ''Non-blocking Cache''?','A cache that never fills up','A cache that can continue to supply data for hits while it is busy processing earlier misses','A ways to delete cache','A training system','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Non-blocking caches are essential for out-of-order execution processors.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What characterizes ''Load/Store Architecture''?','Loading stores manually','An instruction set architecture where all memory access is done through explicit load and store instructions between memory and registers','A ways to delete code','naming variables','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'RISC architectures are almost exclusively load/store.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What does ''ILP'' stand for in computer architecture?','Instruction-Level Parallelism','Internet Logic Protocol','Internal L1 Processing','none of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'ILP is a measure of how many operations can be performed simultaneously at the instruction level.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','In IEEE 754, what is a ''NaN'' (Not a Number)?','An error in the UI','A symbolic representation in the floating point standard for indefinite or unrepresentable values (e.g. 0/0)','A ways to delete numbers','naming variables','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'NaN allows calculations to continue without crashing while signaling an invalid operation.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What is the ''Wallace Tree'' multiplier?','A multiplier made of wood','An efficient hardware implementation of a digital circuit that multiplies two integers using a tree of adders to reduce partial products','A ways to delete bits','A training dashboard','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Wallace trees are much faster than ripple-carry based multipliers for large numbers.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What is ''Mesh Topology'' in parallel computing?','A messy network','A grid-like network topology where nodes are connected to their nearest horizontal and vertical neighbors','A ways to delete connections','naming variables','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Mesh networks are simple to implement on 2D chips for many-core systems (NoCs).','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What characterizes ''Weak Consistency'' models?','failing often','Models where memory operations do not appear to be performed in the program''s order, requiring explicit ''fence'' or ''sync'' instructions to ensure visibility','A ways to delete files','A backup tool','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Weak consistency allows for aggressive hardware and compiler optimizations.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What is ''Write Atomicity''?','Small writes','A property ensuring that a write by one processor becomes visible to all other processors simultaneously (or in a consistent way)','A ways to delete records','managing memory','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Write atomicity is a key component of strong memory consistency models.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What does a ''Branch Predictor''s Confidence'' indicate?','How brave the CPU is','A metric that estimates how likely a specific branch prediction is to be correct, allowing the CPU to throttle speculation','A ways to delete branches','naming variables','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Confidence bits help prevent expensive mispredictions in complex branch histories.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What is ''NVMe'' (Non-Volatile Memory Express)?','A new brand of RAM','An interface specification optimized for accessing non-volatile storage media attached via a PCIe bus','A ways to delete files','A training dashboard','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'NVMe significantly reduces overhead compared to legacy SATA interfaces.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What characterizes ''Harvard Architecture''?','A school in Boston','A computer architecture with separate storage and signal pathways for instructions and data','A ways to delete data','An old version of RISC','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Harvard architecture allows the CPU to fetch both an instruction and data simultaneously.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What defines ''Von Neumann Bottleneck''?','A literal bottle on the desk','The shared bus between the CPU and memory, which limits the rate of instruction fetch and data transfer','A ways to delete code','managing memory','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'This bottleneck is the primary driver for high-performance cache and complex bus architectures.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','How does ''Address Space Layout Randomization'' (ASLR) work in architecture context?','Randomly deleting files','A security technique that randomly arranges the address space positions of key data areas of a process to prevent exploits like buffer overflows','A ways to rename users','A training system','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'ASLR makes it difficult for an attacker to predict the location of target code/data in memory.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What is ''SPEC'' in the context of computer architecture?','A set of glasses','Standard Performance Evaluation Corporation: a non-profit that develops standardized benchmark suites to evaluate computer performance','A ways to delete records','A training dashboard','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'SPEC benchmarks are the industry standard for reporting CPU and system performance.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What is the ''Division by Subtraction'' method?','Subtracting numbers randomly','An algorithm for binary division that uses repeated subtraction of the divisor from the dividend (e.g. Restoring or Non-Restoring division)','A ways to delete bits','A training system','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'This iterative process is how hardware dividers are typically implemented.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What is ''Memory Protection''?','A case for RAM','Hardware features that control memory access rights on a computer, preventing processes from accessing unauthorized memory','A ways to delete files','naming variables','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Memory protection is critical for multi-user operating systems and overall system security.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What characterizes ''Clock Skew'' in digital circuits?','A broken clock','The difference in arrival time of the clock signal at various parts (flip-flops) of a synchronous digital circuit','A ways to delete data','A battery issue','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Clock skew must be carefully managed in high-speed CPU design to avoid synchronization failures.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What is ''Dynamic Voltage and Frequency Scaling'' (DVFS)?','Changing the clock color','A power management technique where the voltage and frequency of a processor are adjusted in real-time to conserve energy or reduce heat','A ways to delete files','naming variables','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'DVFS is the primary ways modern processors balance performance and power consumption.','pregenerated'),
('2757bb26-7e2f-4e30-9e36-67f20f8c6f5b','What is ''Dark Silicon''?','Silicon that is painted black','A phenomenon where the majority of an integrated circuit''s area cannot be powered simultaneously due to thermal constraints','Broken chips','A ways to name a user','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'It forces designers to use specialization (accelerators) rather than just adding more general cores.','pregenerated')
