INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','What is the time complexity of Binary Search in the worst case?','O(n)','O(log n)','O(n^2)','O(1)','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Binary Search divides the search space in half at each step, leading to logarithmic time complexity.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','Which of the following growth rates is the slowest?','O(n log n)','O(n^2)','O(2^n)','O(log n)','["D"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Logarithmic growth is slower than linear, polynomial, or exponential growth.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','What is the best-case time complexity of Bubble Sort when the array is already sorted?','O(n^2)','O(n log n)','O(n)','O(1)','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'If an optimized version of Bubble Sort is used, it can detect a sorted array in a single pass.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','Which searching algorithm requires the data to be sorted?','Linear Search','Binary Search','Hash Search','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Binary Search relies on the order of elements to eliminate half of the search space.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','What is the primary risk of a recursive function without a proper base case?','Infinite loop','Stack overflow','Memory leak','Compilation error','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'Each recursive call consumes stack space; without a base case, the stack eventually overflows.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','Which of these algorithms uses the Divide and Conquer strategy?','Selection Sort','Merge Sort','Insertion Sort','Bubble Sort','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Merge sort divides the array into halves, sorts them, and then merges them back.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','What is the space complexity of an algorithm that uses an auxiliary array of the same size as the input?','O(1)','O(log n)','O(n)','O(n^2)','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'If the space used scales linearly with the input size, the space complexity is O(n).','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','Which of these is a characteristic of Greedy algorithms?','Always finds the globally optimal solution','Makes the locally optimal choice at each step','Explore all possible paths','Uses backtracking','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Greedy algorithms make immediate choices that look best at the moment, hoping to reach a global optimum.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','What does O(1) represent?','Linear time','Logarithmic time','Constant time','Quadratic time','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Constant time means the execution time does not depend on the input size.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','Which sorting algorithm is known for its worst-case performance of O(n^2) but is very fast on average?','Merge Sort','Heap Sort','Quick Sort','Counting Sort','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Quick sort''s worst case is O(n^2) (e.g., when the pivot is the smallest or largest element), but its average case is O(n log n).','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','In Selection Sort, how many swaps are performed in the worst case for an array of size n?','O(n^2)','O(n)','O(n log n)','O(1)','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'Selection sort performs at most n-1 swaps, even if it does O(n^2) comparisons.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','What is the time complexity of the following code? `for(int i=1; i<n; i*=2) { ... }`','O(n)','O(log n)','O(n^2)','O(sqrt(n))','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'A loop index that multiplies/divides by a constant factor results in logarithmic complexity.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','What are the two main properties that a problem must have to be solved using Dynamic Programming?','Greedy choice and optimal substructure','Overlapping subproblems and optimal substructure','Large input and small output','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'DP requires dividing the problem into subproblems that repeat (overlapping) and can be combined to solve the larger problem (optimal substructure).','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','What is the average time complexity of searching in a Hash Table?','O(1)','O(log n)','O(n)','O(n log n)','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'With a good hash function and minimal collisions, hash table lookups take constant time on average.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','How do you represent ''linearithmic'' complexity?','O(n)','O(log n)','O(n log n)','O(n^2)','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'O(n log n) is known as linearithmic time complexity.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','Which sorting algorithm maintains the relative order of equal elements?','Heap Sort','Merge Sort','Quick Sort','Selection Sort','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'A stable sorting algorithm like Merge Sort preserves the original order of items with identical keys.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','What is the time complexity of building a heap from an unsorted array of size n?','O(n log n)','O(n)','O(log n)','O(n^2)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'While inserting one element is log n, building the entire heap from scratch using the bottom-up approach is O(n).','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','Prim''s and Kruskal''s algorithms are used to find which of the following?','Shortest path in a graph','Minimum Spanning Tree (MST)','Maximum flow in a network','Biconnected components','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Both utilize greedy strategies to connect all vertices of a graph with the minimum total edge weight.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','Which algorithm is commonly used for level-order traversal of a tree?','Depth First Search (DFS)','Breadth First Search (BFS)','Dijkstra''s Algorithm','Binary Search','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'BFS explores nodes layer by layer using a queue, making it perfect for finding the shortest path in an unweighted graph.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','What is the time complexity of accessing an element at a given index in an array?','O(1)','O(n)','O(log n)','O(n^2)','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Arrays provide direct memory access to elements via indices, which takes constant time.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','In a singly linked list, what is the time complexity of inserting an element at the beginning?','O(log n)','O(1)','O(n)','O(n log n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'You only need to update the new node''s pointer and the head pointer, which takes constant time.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','What is the worst-case time complexity for searching an element in a binary search tree (BST)?','O(log n)','O(n)','O(1)','O(n log n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'If the BST is skewed (like a linked list), searching takes O(n) because you may have to traverse every node.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','Using Master Theorem, what is the complexity of T(n) = 2T(n/2) + n?','O(n)','O(n log n)','O(log n)','O(n^2)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'This corresponds to Case 2 of the Master Theorem (a=2, b=2, f(n)=n^1), resulting in O(n log n), the same as Merge Sort.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','Which of these is a typical example of a problem solved efficiently via Tail Recursion?','Matrix Multiplication','Factorial','Binary Search','Traveling Salesman Problem','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Tail recursion allows the compiler to optimize calls to avoid creating new stack frames.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','Dijkstra''s algorithm may fail or produce incorrect results if the graph contains:','Cycles','Negative edge weights','Disconnected components','Weighted edges','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Dijkstra''s assumes that once a node is visited, its shortest distance is found; negative edges can invalidate this greedy approach.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','What is the time complexity to find the maximum element in an unsorted array of size n using Divide and Conquer?','O(log n)','O(n)','O(n log n)','O(1)','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'You must still check every element at least once, so it is O(n).','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','What does Omega (Ω) notation describe?','Average case complexity','Lower bound performance','Upper bound performance','The fastest the code can possibly run on any input','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Ω(g(n)) provides a simplified lower bound for the growth rate of a function.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','What does Theta (Θ) notation describe?','A tight bound (both upper and lower)','Only the worst case','The space complexity only','The number of loops','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Θ(g(n)) means the function is bounded both above and below by g(n) for large n.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','What is the time complexity of Strassen''s matrix multiplication algorithm?','O(n^3)','O(n^2.81)','O(n^2)','O(2^n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Strassen''s reduces the number of recursive multiplications from 8 to 7, improving complexity from O(n^3) to approx O(n^2.81).','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','Which sorting algorithm is often used when the range of input values (k) is not significantly larger than the number of elements (n)?','Heap Sort','Counting Sort','Quick Sort','Merge Sort','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'Counting sort is a non-comparison based sort with O(n + k) complexity.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','What is the worst-case time complexity of Insertion Sort?','O(n)','O(n^2)','O(n log n)','O(log n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Worst case happens when the array is sorted in reverse order.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','A queue follows which rule for element processing?','LIFO (Last-In First-Out)','FIFO (First-In First-Out)','Random Access','Highest Priority First','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'In a queue, elements are added at the back and removed from the front.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','A stack follows which rule for element processing?','FIFO','LIFO','Linear Access','Circular Access','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The last element pushed onto a stack is the first one to be popped off.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','Which of these is a classic problem solved using Backtracking?','Fibonacci Numbers','N-Queens Problem','Finding the max in an array','Linear Search','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Backtracking is an algorithmic-technique for solving problems recursively by trying to build a solution incrementally while removing those that fail.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','What is the space complexity of an iterative Factorial algorithm?','O(n)','O(1)','O(log n)','O(2^n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Iteration only uses a constant amount of extra space for variables, unlike recursion which uses stack space.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','What is the space complexity of a recursive Factorial algorithm (without tail optimization)?','O(1)','O(n)','O(n^2)','O(log n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The recursion stack grows linearly with n.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','Which data structure is most suitable for implementing the ''Undo'' feature in applications?','Queue','Stack','Array','Linked List','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The LIFO nature of a stack allows reversing the last action easily.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','What is a ''Collision'' in a Hash Table?','When the program crashes','When two different keys produce the same hash index','When the table is full','When keys are deleted','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Methods like Chaining or Open Addressing are used to resolve these collisions.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','In a graph, which traversal discovers all nodes reachable from a starting node by exploring neighbors first?','DFS','BFS','Topological Sort','Binary Search','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'BFS uses a Queue to explore adjacent nodes before moving deeper.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','Which data structure is primarily used by Depth First Search (DFS)?','Queue','Stack','Hash Table','Heap','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'DFS can be implemented using an explicit stack or implicitly via the call stack (recursion).','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','If f(n) = 3n^2 + 10n + 5, what is its Big O complexity?','O(n)','O(n^2)','O(1)','O(n^3)','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'In Big O, we ignore constant factors and focus on the highest-order term.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','Can Master Theorem be used to solve T(n) = 2T(n/2) + n log n?','Yes, directly','No, it doesn''t fit the standard cases','Yes, using the extended version','Only for n=2','["C"]'::jsonb,'tricky',40,'Standard Master Theorem doesn''t cover f(n) = n log n, but an extension (Case 2 generalized) shows it is O(n log^2 n).','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','In the Fractional Knapsack problem, which greedy strategy is correct?','Sort items by weight','Sort items by high value only','Sort items by value/weight ratio','No greedy strategy works','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Taking the item with highest ''density'' (value per unit weight) leads to the optimal result for the fractional version.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','Which sorting algorithm is known for being performant on small data sets and is used in hybrid algorithms like Timsort?','Quick Sort','Insertion Sort','Bubble Sort','Selection Sort','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Insertion sort is efficient for very small lists (n < 20) or nearly sorted lists.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','What does it mean if an algorithm is ''In-place''?','It uses no memory at all','It requires only a small, constant amount of extra memory regardless of input size (O(1) extra space)','It runs very fast','It doesn''t move elements','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Quick Sort and Heap Sort are in-place; Merge Sort is typically not.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','The ''Average Case'' of an algorithm refers to performance on:','The best possible data','The worst possible data','A random or typical distribution of possible inputs','Small data sets only','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Average case analysis often involves complex probability but is more realistic for real-world use.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','Which of these allows O(1) time complexity for both Insertion and Deletion at both ends?','Singly Linked List','Doubly Linked List','Sorted Array','Binary Search Tree','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'With pointers to both head and tail, doubly linked lists handle extremes instantly.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','What is the time complexity to solve the Tower of Hanoi problem for n disks?','O(n)','O(2^n)','O(n^2)','O(log n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The number of moves required is 2^n - 1, making it exponential.','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','Is O(n!) faster or slower than O(2^n)?','Faster','Slower','Same speed','Not comparable','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Factorial growth O(n!) is extremely fast and much worse than exponential growth O(2^n).','pregenerated'),
('6e5df2b8-329e-4c2a-a042-67a11da56a99','An ''Edge'' in a graph connects two:','Processes','Vertices (or Nodes)','Stacks','Lists','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Vertices represent objects, and Edges represent relationships between them.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','Which sorting algorithm is ''stable'' by default?','Quick Sort','Merge Sort','Heap Sort','Selection Sort','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Merge sort preserves the relative order of elements with equal values.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','Which of the following problems can be solved optimally using a Greedy approach?','0/1 Knapsack Problem','Fractional Knapsack Problem','Longest Common Subsequence','Matrix Chain Multiplication','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Fractional Knapsack can be solved greedily by taking items with the highest value-to-weight ratio first.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','In the Master Theorem, if T(n) = 2T(n/2) + O(n), what is the complexity?','O(n)','O(n log n)','O(log n)','O(n^2)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'This corresponds to the case where the divide-and-conquer work matches the work done at each level, specifically merge sort.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','What is the time complexity to build a Max-Heap from an unsorted array of size n?','O(n log n)','O(n)','O(1)','O(log n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Although it seems like O(n log n), the mathematical evaluation of build-heap results in linear time complexity O(n).','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','Which search strategy does Backtracking typically follow?','Breadth-First Search','Depth-First Search','Best-First Search','Random Search','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Backtracking explores paths deeply and retreats (backtracks) when it hits a dead end, which is DFS-like.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','What is ''Memoization'' in Dynamic Programming?','A bottom-up approach','A top-down approach that stores results of expensive function calls','A ways to sort elements','A ways to visualize graph','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Memoization saves computed values in a cache (like a map or array) to avoid redundant calculations in recursion.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','What is the time complexity of Dijkstra''s algorithm using a simple binary heap?','O(V^2)','O(E log V)','O(V + E)','O(E log E)','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'With a priority queue (binary heap), each edge can trigger an update taking O(log V) time.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','The class ''P'' in computational complexity refers to problems that can be solved in:','Parallel time','Polynomial time','Probabilistic time','Prime time','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'P stands for Polynomial time solvable on a deterministic Turing machine.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','If a problem is ''NP-Complete'', what does it mean?','It cannot be solved','It is in NP and every problem in NP can be reduced to it in polynomial time','It is solvable in constant time','It has no solution','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'NP-complete problems are the hardest problems in NP; if any one of them is solved in P, then P = NP.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','What is the time complexity of Strassen''s matrix multiplication?','O(n^3)','O(n^2.81)','O(n^2)','O(n log n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Strassen''s algorithm reduces the number of multiplications required for 2x2 matrices from 8 to 7, bringing complexity down from O(n^3).','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','Which sorting algorithm uses a divide and conquer approach and is NOT in-place?','Quick Sort','Merge Sort','Selection Sort','Insertion Sort','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Standard merge sort requires O(n) auxiliary space for merging.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','In Huffman coding, what type of tree is used to represent the codes?','Binary Search Tree','Binary Tree where characters are leaf nodes','AVL Tree','Heap','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Huffman coding uses a binary tree where frequently occurring characters stay closer to the root for shorter codes.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','What is the amortized time complexity of an ''append'' operation in a dynamic array (like std::vector in C++)?','O(n)','O(1)','O(log n)','O(n log n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Although some appends take O(n) due to resizing, the total work for n appends is O(n), so each is O(1) on average.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','What is the result of applying Topological Sort on a graph with cycles?','A correctly sorted list','An error; topological sort is only for DAGs (Directed Acyclic Graphs)','A random list','A reversed list','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Topological sorting requires dependencies to be acyclic; cycles create contradictions.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','Which algorithm is used to find the maximum flow in a flow network?','Dijkstra''s Algorithm','Ford-Fulkerson Algorithm','Kruskal''s Algorithm','Bellman-Ford Algorithm','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The Ford-Fulkerson method (or Edmonds-Karp implementation) calculates max flow using augmenting paths.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','Which algorithm is used to find all-pairs shortest paths in a weighted graph?','Dijkstra''s Algorithm','Bellman-Ford Algorithm','Floyd-Warshall Algorithm','Prim''s Algorithm','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Floyd-Warshall is a dynamic programming algorithm with O(V^3) complexity.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','What is the time complexity of Kruskal''s algorithm using the Union-Find data structure with path compression?','O(E log V)','O(V^2)','O(E log E)','O(V + E)','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The bottleneck is sorting the edges, which takes O(E log E) or O(E log V) time.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','Which of these sorting algorithms is NOT a comparison-based sort?','Radix Sort','Quick Sort','Merge Sort','Heap Sort','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Radix sort sorts numbers digit by digit and doesn''t directly compare elements as wholes.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','What is the time complexity of the Matrix Chain Multiplication problem solved via DP?','O(n^2)','O(n^3)','O(2^n)','O(n log n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Calculating the minimum number of scalar multiplications for n matrices takes O(n^3) time.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','What is the space complexity of Depth First Search (DFS)?','O(V)','O(E)','O(V^2)','O(1)','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'In the worst case, the recursion stack can go as deep as the number of vertices.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','Which property allows Dijkstra''s algorithm to work?','Optimal Substructure','Overlapping Subproblems','Greedy Choice Property','None of the above','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Dijkstra''s is a greedy algorithm that assumes locally optimal choices lead to globally optimal shortest paths.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','What is ''Double Hashing'' used for?','Encrypting data twice','Resolving collisions in open-addressing hash tables','Making the hash table larger','Sorting the keys','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'It uses a second hash function to calculate the offset for probing.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','What is the height of a Red-Black tree with n nodes?','O(n)','O(log n)','O(sqrt(n))','O(n log n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Red-Black trees are self-balancing binary search trees that guarantee logarithmic height.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','Which of these is TRUE about NP-Hard problems?','They are all in P','They are at least as hard as the hardest problems in NP','They always have a solution in polynomial time','They must be in NP','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'NP-Hard problems don''t necessarily have to be in NP themselves, but every problem in NP reduces to them.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','Branch and Bound is commonly used for what type of problems?','Linear search','Combinatorial optimization (e.g., TSP)','Simple sorting','Calculating square roots','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It systematically explores branches of a search space and prunes them using bounds.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','What is the time complexity of Breadth First Search (BFS) given adjacent list representation?','O(V)','O(V + E)','O(E^2)','O(V log V)','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Every vertex and every edge is explored exactly once.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','In Huffman Coding, which characters get the shortest bit representation?','Characters encountered first','Most frequent characters','Least frequent characters','Vowels','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Huffman coding is a prefix coding system that assigns shorter codes to higher-frequency symbols.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','What is the complexity of finding the Median of an unsorted array using the ''Median-of-Medians'' algorithm?','O(n log n)','O(n)','O(n^2)','O(log n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'It is a deterministic selection algorithm that finds the kth smallest element in linear time.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','Which algorithm finds the strongly connected components (SCCs) of a directed graph?','Dijkstra''s','Tarjan''s Algorithm','Prim''s','Boruvka''s','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Tarjan''s and Kosaraju''s are the two most common algorithms for finding SCCs.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','What is the time complexity of the Longest Common Subsequence (LCS) problem for two strings of length m and n?','O(m+n)','O(mn)','O(2^(m+n))','O(log(m+n))','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'The DP table requires filling m * n cells.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','Which tree is strictly balanced such that the height difference between any two sibling subtrees is at most 1?','Binary Search Tree','AVL Tree','B-Tree','Trie','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'AVL trees perform rotations during insertion and deletion to maintain this balance.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','In a max-heap stored in an array, if a node is at index ''i'', where is its left child located?','i + 1','2i','2i + 1','i/2','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Assuming 1-based indexing, the left child is at 2i. (For 0-based indexing, it is 2i + 1).','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','The ''Bottom-Up'' approach to Dynamic Programming is also known as:','Memoization','Tabulation','Recursion','Greedy strategy','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Tabulation systematically fills a table from the smallest subproblems up to the target problem.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','In the 8-Queens problem, what does a ''Dead End'' represent in the search tree?','Finding a solution','A state where no further queen can be placed without violating rules','Completing the first row','The end of the code','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'When a dead end is reached, the algorithm must backtrack to the previous row and try a different column.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','What is the time complexity of adding an element into a Heap of size n?','O(1)','O(log n)','O(n)','O(n log n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The element is added at the end and then ''bubbled up'' (heapiy up), which takes time proportional to the height.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','Which sorting algorithm''s average time complexity is O(n + k), where k is the range of input?','Merge Sort','Counting Sort','Quick Sort','Selection Sort','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Counting sort is extremely fast if the range of values is small.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','Which algorithm should you use if your graph contains negative edge weights but no negative cycles?','Dijkstra''s','Bellman-Ford','BFS','Kruskal''s','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Bellman-Ford handles negative weights and can even detect negative cycles.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','What is an ''Articulating Point'' in a graph?','An edge that connects two nodes','A vertex which, if removed, increases the number of connected components','A node with zero degree','A node in a cycle','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Removing an articulation point splits the graph into multiple pieces.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','Which sorting algorithm is commonly used in practice as it is often faster than other O(n log n) sorting algorithms due to its low constant factors?','Merge Sort','Quick Sort','Selection Sort','Insertion Sort','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Quick Sort is typically very fast and is used as the default sort (often as Introsort) in many libraries.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','Complexity used by an algorithm in addition to input and output space is called:','Total Space','Auxiliary Space','Working Space','Heap Space','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Auxiliary space is the extra space or temporary space used by an algorithm.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','In the 0/1 Knapsack problem, what does ''0/1'' signify?','The item must be weighted either 0 or 1','An item cannot be split; it must be taken as a whole or left behind','Binary code is used','Only two items exist','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Unlike the fractional version, you can''t take a piece of an item.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','Prim''s algorithm starts from:','The shortest edge in the entire graph','Any starting vertex (root)','The destination vertex','A random edge','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Prim''s grows the MST from a single starting node by picking the nearest neighbor.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','What is the lower bound for comparison-based sorting algorithms?','O(n)','O(n log n)','O(log n)','O(n^2)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'It has been mathematically proven that any comparison sort requires Ω(n log n) operations.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','How many comparisons are made in Binary Search in the worst case for an array of size 1024?','10','11','1024','512','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'log2(1024) = 10; including the final check, it''s approximately 11 comparisons.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','Which greedy algorithm is used to find the shortest path from a single source in a graph with non-negative edges?','Bellman-Ford','Dijkstra''s','Floyd-Warshall','Johnson''s','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Dijkstra''s is the standard greedy approach for this problem.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','In backtracking, ''Pruning'' refers to:','Deleting the code','Removing branches from the search space that are known not to contain a solution','Sorting the input','Adding more nodes','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Pruning increases efficiency by skipping unnecessary computations.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','What is the time complexity of the most efficient algorithm to check if a number is prime (probabilistic)?','O(n)','O(k log^3 n)','O(sqrt(n))','O(n^2)','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'The Miller-Rabin primality test is very efficient and runs in polynomial time relative to number of bits.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','A ''Recursive'' algorithm is one that:','Uses a loop','Calls itself to solve smaller subproblems','Runs in O(1) time','Does not use a stack','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Recursion involves breaking a problem down until reaching a base case.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','Which traversal of a Binary Search Tree (BST) visits nodes in ascending order?','Pre-order','In-order','Post-order','Level-order','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'In-order traversal (Left, Root, Right) naturally sorts a BST.','pregenerated'),
('37ae2bd8-0ac5-4f3e-9b71-397bb13dc27c','If f(n) = O(g(n)) and h(n) = O(i(n)), then f(n) * h(n) is:','O(g(n) + i(n))','O(g(n) * i(n))','O(g(n))','O(1)','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Standard property of asymptotic notations: complexities multiply when the operations multiply.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','What is the time complexity of the Matrix Chain Multiplication problem using DP?','O(n^2)','O(n^3)','O(2^n)','O(n log n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Solving matrix chain multiplication involves computing values for all sub-chains of length 2 to n, taking O(n^3) time.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','In the Floyd-Warshall algorithm, what does the table `dp[i][j]` represent after the k-th iteration?','Shortest path from i to j using all nodes as intermediates','Shortest path from i to j using only nodes {1, 2, ..., k} as intermediate points','Shortest path from i to j with exactly k edges','Max flow from i to j','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Floyd-Warshall is a DP algorithm that progressively includes nodes in the set of allowed intermediates.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','Which algorithm is used to find the ''Convex Hull'' of a set of points?','Graham Scan','Kruskal''s Algorithm','Dijkstra''s Algorithm','Prim''s Algorithm','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Graham Scan is a classic O(n log n) algorithm for finding the convex hull.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','What is the purpose of an ''Approximation Algorithm''?','To find an approximate solution for a problem in P','To find a solution that is guaranteed to be within a certain factor of the optimal for NP-hard problems','To guess the answer','To speed up sorting','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'For NP-hard problems, we often settle for solutions that are ''close'' to optimal but can be found in polynomial time.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','What is the primary advantage of a B-Tree over a standard Binary Search Tree in disk-based storage?','Faster CPU processing','Reduced number of disk reads due to high branching factor (broad and shallow tree)','Less memory usage','Simpler implementation','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'B-Trees keep the tree height low, minimizing expensive disk I/O operations.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','What is a ''Las Vegas Algorithm''?','An algorithm that sometimes returns an incorrect answer','An algorithm that always returns the correct answer but whose running time is a random variable','An algorithm used for gambling','An algorithm that is always fast but may fail','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Las Vegas algorithms (like Quick Sort with random pivot) are guaranteed to be correct; Monte Carlo algorithms might be wrong.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','Which string matching algorithm uses a ''prefix function'' (or failure function) to avoid redundant comparisons?','Brute Force','Knuth-Morris-Pratt (KMP)','Rabin-Karp','Boyer-Moore','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'KMP''s prefix function allows the search to skip ahead based on what has already been matched.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','What is the worst-case height of an AVL tree with n nodes?','O(n)','O(log n)','O(sqrt(n))','O(n log n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'AVL trees are self-balancing BSTs that maintain a height of approximately 1.44 log n.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','What is the relationship between NP-Hard and NP-Complete classes?','NP-Complete is a subset of NP-Hard','NP-Hard is a subset of NP-Complete','They are exactly the same','They have nothing in common','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'A problem is NP-Complete if it is both NP-Hard and in NP.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','What does the expression `n & (n-1)` check for if n is a positive integer?','If n is even','It clears the lowest set bit of n','If n is prime','If n is negative','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'This bitwise operation is commonly used to clear the lowest set bit or check if n is a power of 2 (if the result is 0).','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','What is the complexity of the Bellman-Ford algorithm?','O(V + E)','O(VE)','O(V^2)','O(E log V)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Bellman-Ford relaxes all edges V-1 times, resulting in O(VE) complexity.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','What does the Max-Flow Min-Cut Theorem state?','The maximum flow is always equal to the total weight of the graph','The maximum flow in a network is equal to the capacity of the minimum cut','The minimum cut is always 0','Flow cannot be calculated','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'This fundamental theorem relates the capacity of the bottlenecks (cuts) to the total throughput (flow).','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','Which problem can be solved in O(n log n) using divide and conquer in a 2D plane?','Travelling Salesperson Problem','Closest Pair of Points','3-SAT','Graph Coloring','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Closest pair of points uses a clever recursive approach with a strip-check to achieve O(n log n).','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','What is ''Theta notation'' (Θ-notation) used for?','Upper bound of a function','Lower bound of a function','Tight bound of a function (both upper and lower)','Average case only','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Θ-notation provides a tight asymptotic bound on the growth rate of an algorithm.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','What is the amortized complexity of ''union'' and ''find'' operations in a Disjoint Set with path compression and union by rank?','O(log n)','O(α(n)), where α is the inverse Ackermann function','O(1)','O(n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'The inverse Ackermann function grows extremely slowly, making it nearly constant (O(1)) for all practical purposes.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','What is the primary constraint of the ''Optimal Binary Search Tree'' problem?','Minimizing the height of the tree','Minimizing the total search cost given access frequencies of keys','Keeping all nodes as leaf nodes','Maximizing the number of nodes','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'DP is used to construct a tree such that frequently accessed nodes move closer to the root.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','What is the time complexity of the Edmonds-Karp implementation of the Max-Flow problem?','O(VE)','O(VE^2)','O(V^3)','O(E log V)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'Edmonds-Karp always uses BFS to find the shortest augmenting path, ensuring O(VE^2) performance.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','Which condition must be met for a graph to have an ''Eulerian Circuit''?','All nodes must have an odd degree','The graph must be connected and every node must have an even degree','The graph must be a tree','No node can have more than two neighbors','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'An Eulerian circuit visits every edge exactly once and returns to the start; even degrees ensure an entry and exit for every visit.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','Rabin-Karp algorithm uses which technique to improve string searching?','Finite Automata','Rolling Hash','Prefix mapping','Suffix arrays','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Rabin-Karp compares the hash of the pattern with hashes of overlapping substrings of the text in O(1) time after precomputation.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','Cook''s Theorem proves that which of the following problems is NP-Complete?','Halting Problem','Boolean Satisfiability Problem (SAT)','Tower of Hanoi','Binary Search','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'This was the first problem proven to be NP-complete, forming the basis for later reductions.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','What is the approximation ratio of the standard greedy algorithm for the Vertex Cover problem?','1.5','2','log n','n','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'The simple edge-selection greedy algorithm guarantees a solution no worse than twice the optimal size.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','Which algorithm is most efficient for All-Pairs Shortest Path in a sparse weighted graph with some negative edges?','Floyd-Warshall','Johnson''s Algorithm','Dijkstra''s (repeated)','Kruskal''s','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Johnson''s algorithm uses Bellman-Ford for reweighting and then repeated Dijkstra''s, performing better than O(V^3) on sparse graphs.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','The ''Simplex Method'' is primarily used to solve which type of problems?','Sorting large arrays','Optimizing linear objective functions subject to linear constraints','Finding cycles in a graph','Searching hashed values','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Simplex is an efficient (in practice) algorithm for solving Linear Programming problems.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','In a Splay Tree, what happens when an element is accessed?','It is deleted','It is moved to the root via a series of rotations','The tree is rebuilt from scratch','Its subtree is balanced only','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Splaying provides amortized O(log n) efficiency by keeping recently accessed items near the top.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','Which algorithm finds the Convex Hull in O(nh) time, where h is the number of vertices in the hull?','Graham Scan','Jarvis March (Gift Wrapping)','QuickHull','Monotone Chain','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Jarvis March is an ''output-sensitive'' algorithm; it is fast if the final hull has few points.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','A ''Segment Tree'' is most useful for which type of scenario?','Sorting strings','Frequent range queries (e.g., sum, min) and range updates in fixed data','Storing user records','Hashing passwords','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Segment trees allow for O(log n) performance for both query and modification operations over an interval.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','The ''Accounting Method'' of amortized analysis involves:','Paying a CPA to check the code','Assigning artificial costs to operations to ''save'' credit for future expensive operations','Summing all actual times and dividing','Using potential energy functions','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'It helps in proving that overall performance is efficient even if individual steps are slow.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','According to Amdahl''s Law, what limits the speedup of a program when using parallel computing?','The number of processors available','The serial (non-parallelizable) portion of the algorithm','The speed of the network','The type of programming language','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Even with infinite processors, the total speedup is limited by the sequential code that cannot be parallelized.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','What is the complexity of Tarjan''s Strongly Connected Components algorithm?','O(V + E)','O(VE)','O(V log V)','O(V^2)','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Tarjan''s algorithm uses a single DFS pass with extra metadata (discovery time, low-link values) for linear efficiency.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','In the Floyd-Warshall algorithm, if the diagonal element dp[i][i] becomes negative, what does it indicate?','An error in the input scale','The presence of a negative cycle reachable from node i','A terminal state','The graph is not connected','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'A negative diagonal means a path starting and ending at the same node now has a total weight less than zero.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','The AKS primality test is significant because it is:','Very fast in practice','The first deterministic, unconditional, and polynomial-time sorting of primes','A probabilistic check like Miller-Rabin','An extension of the Sieve of Eratosthenes','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The AKS test proved that ''Primes is in P'' (deterministic polynomial time).','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','Which string searching algorithm is generally considered the most efficient for large alphabets and avoids checking many characters of the text by scanning the pattern from right to left?','KMP','Boyer-Moore','Brute Force','Aho-Corasick','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'Boyer-Moore uses ''Good Suffix'' and ''Bad Character'' rules to skip large blocks of text.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','In a B-Tree of order m, every node except the root must contain at least how many keys?','1','ceil(m/2) - 1','m - 1','m/2','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'B-Tree properties ensure the tree remains dense and height is minimized.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','What is the time complexity of a naive backtracking algorithm for the Traveling Salesman Problem (TSP)?','O(n^2)','O(n!)','O(2^n)','O(n^n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Trying all possible permutations of n vertices takes O(n!) time.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','How does Held-Karp algorithm solve the Traveling Salesman Problem?','Using greedy edge selection','Using dynamic programming and bitmasking with complexity O(n^2 2^n)','Using a simple DFS','Using sorting','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Held-Karp is significantly faster than n! but still exponential, solving TSP via memoized sub-structures.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','What is a ''Metric TSP''?','TSP with distances in kilometers only','A version of TSP where edge weights satisfy the triangle inequality','A TSP with no cycles','A TSP where all weights are 1','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'If distance(a,c) <= distance(a,b) + distance(b,c), it is Metric TSP, which allows for better approximation bounds.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','What is the time complexity of building a Suffix Tree for a string of length n using Ukkonen''s algorithm?','O(n^2)','O(n)','O(n log n)','O(log n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Ukkonen''s is a complex but linear-time algorithm for constructing suffix trees online.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','A ''Fenwick Tree'' (Binary Indexed Tree) is most efficient for:','Finding all-pairs shortest paths','Prefix sums and point updates on an array','Sorting strings','Balanced search operations','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It provides O(log n) for both updates and prefix sum queries with very low constant overhead.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','What does the notation co-NP represent?','Problems not in NP','The class of problems whose complement is in NP','Polynomial time solvable problems','Concurrent NP','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'If a problem ''Is this true?'' is in NP, its ''Is this false?'' version is in co-NP.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','What is the benefit of ''Bloom Filters'' in distributed systems?','Perfectly accurate searching','Extremely space-efficient probabilistic set membership checks (No false negatives, possible false positives)','Deleting unwanted data','Encrypting data','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Bloom filters tell you if an element is ''definitely not'' in a set or ''possibly'' in it.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','What is the bottleneck step in the Boruvka''s MST algorithm?','Finding the minimum weight edge for each component in parallel','Sorting all edges','Calculating degrees','None of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Boruvka''s algorithm is inherently parallelizable and efficient for dense graphs.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','What is ''Adversarial Analysis'' of an algorithm?','Testing against hackers','Assuming the input is chosen by an ''adversary'' to produce the worst possible performance','Deleting the database','Comparing two algorithms','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'It helps determine lower bounds for problems by showing that an adversary can always force a certain number of operations.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','The ''Minimum Cut'' in a network is used to solve which problem?','Finding shortest path','Finding the smallest set of edges that disconnects the source from the sink','Sorting numbers','Finding cycles','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'The weight of this cut is exactly equal to the maximum flow.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','Which technique converts a multi-argument function into a series of single-argument functions?','Recursion','Currying','Backtracking','Divide and conquer','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Currying is common in functional programming for partial application of functions.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','The Master Theorem case for T(n) = 8T(n/2) + n^2 results in which complexity?','O(n^2)','O(n^3)','O(n log n)','O(2^n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'log2(8) = 3 and since 3 > 2, Case 1 applies, giving O(n^3).','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','What is the time complexity of ''Interpolation Search'' in the best case (when data is uniformly distributed)?','O(log n)','O(log log n)','O(1)','O(n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Interpolation search estimates the position based on values, achieving O(log log n) for uniform distributions.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','What is the maximum number of keys in a B-Tree node of order m?','m','m - 1','2m','log m','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Each node has at most m children and m-1 keys.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','What is the time complexity of the Bipartite Matching problem using Max-Flow on a graph with V vertices and E edges?','O(VE)','O(E sqrt(V))','O(V^3)','O(log E)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'The Hopcroft-Karp algorithm solves this in O(E sqrt(V)) time.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','What is the time complexity to find the Greatest Common Divisor (GCD) of two numbers a and b using the Euclidean algorithm?','O(a+b)','O(log(min(a,b)))','O(1)','O(sqrt(a))','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'The number of steps in the Euclidean algorithm is proportional to the number of digits.','pregenerated'),
('cf4fa23e-a4b1-4b1a-884b-5a500408e5d8','A ''Non-deterministic Turing Machine'' (NTM) is primarily used in which context?','Building faster PCs','A theoretical model defining the class NP','Encrypted searches','Sorting in parallel','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'NP is the set of problems solvable in polynomial time on an NTM.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','What is the primary open question in computational complexity theory?','Does P = NP?','Is 1+1=2?','Are all algorithms O(n)?','Can we solve TSP in O(n)?','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The P vs NP problem asks whether every problem whose solution can be quickly verified by a computer can also be quickly solved by a computer.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','If Problem A is reducible to Problem B in polynomial time, what can we say about their relative difficulty?','A is at most as hard as B','B is at most as hard as A','A and B are equally hard','A is harder than B','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Reduction `A ≤p B` means that if we can solve B efficiently, we can also solve A efficiently by converting A to B.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','What is a ''Fibonacci Heap'' primarily used for to optimize certain graph algorithms?','Sorting numbers','Dijkstra''s and Prim''s algorithm (improving decrease-key operation to O(1) amortized)','String matching','Dynamic programming','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Fibonacci heaps offer better amortized performance for many priority queue operations than binary or binomial heaps.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','Which of these is a classic NP-Hard optimization problem?','Shortest Path (Source to Destination)','Minimum Spanning Tree','Travelling Salesperson Problem (TSP)','Sorting an array','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'TSP involves finding the shortest cycle that visits every node once; it''s a fundamental problem in optimization and complexity.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','Which quantum algorithm is used for factoring large integers efficiently?','Grover''s Algorithm','Shor''s Algorithm','Deutsch-Jozsa Algorithm','QuickSort','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Shor''s algorithm can factor integers in polynomial time on a quantum computer, threatening RSA encryption.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','What is the approximation ratio of the standard greedy algorithm for the Vertex Cover problem?','1.5','2','log n','n','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The simple 2-approximation algorithm for vertex cover picks an edge and includes both endpoints in the cover.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','What is the time complexity of the Edmonds-Karp algorithm?','O(VE)','O(VE^2)','O(V^2E)','O(E log V)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Edmonds-Karp uses BFS to find augmenting paths, ensuring termination even for irrational capacities and achieving O(VE^2).','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','What is ''Fixed-Parameter Tractability'' (FPT)?','A ways to delete parameters','A class of problems that can be solved in a running time where the exponent doesn''t depend on the parameter k','Constant time for any k','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'FPT problems can be solved in O(f(k) * n^c) time, where k is a small parameter (like tree width).','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','Which algorithm is capable of finding ALL occurrences of a set of patterns in a text simultaneously?','KMP','Aho-Corasick','Rabin-Karp','Boyer-Moore','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Aho-Corasick builds an automaton from the patterns, allowing for efficient multi-pattern matching.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','What is ''Brent''s Theorem'' used for?','Complexity of sorting','Relating the number of processors to the time required for a parallel computation','Naming the nodes','Deleting threads','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Brent''s theorem provides an upper bound on the time to simulate a parallel algorithm with p processors.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','What does the ''FLP Impossibility'' result state?','Consensus is impossible in asynchronous systems if even one process fails','All nodes must agree','Internet is slow','Messages are always lost','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Named after Fischer, Lynch, and Paterson, this is a cornerstone result in distributed systems theory.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','What is the complexity of constructing a Voronoi Diagram of n points in 2D?','O(n^2)','O(n log n)','O(n)','O(log n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Fortune''s Algorithm (sweep-line) constructs Voronoi diagrams in O(n log n) time.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','What is the lower bound of comparison-based sorting algorithms in terms of number of comparisons?','Ω(n)','Ω(n log n)','Ω(n^2)','Ω(1)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'By decision tree theory, any comparison-based sort must make at least log(n!) comparisons, which is Ω(n log n).','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','What is ''Knuth''s Optimization'' in DP used for?','Sorting strings','Reducing the complexity of certain O(n^3) DP problems (like Optimal BST) to O(n^2)','Naming variables','Deleting subproblems','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'If the optimal split point for a range [i, j] lies between the optimal split points of [i, j-1] and [i+1, j], we can narrow the search range.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','Which class contains problems that can be solved in polynomial time by a quantum computer?','P','NP','BQP','PSPACE','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'BQP (Bounded-error Quantum Polynomial time) is the class of decision problems solvable by a quantum computer.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','A problem is in the ''PSPACE'' class if it can be solved by a Turing machine using:','Polynomial time','Polynomial amount of memory space regardless of time','Constant space only','Exponential time and exponential space','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'PSPACE is the set of all decision problems that can be solved by a Turing machine using a polynomial amount of space.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','What is the ''Ladner''s Theorem'' concern?','Proof that P = NP','If P ≠ NP, then there exist problems in NP that are neither in P nor NP-complete (NP-Intermediate)','Complexity of sorting','Halting problem solution','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'It shows that if P != NP, the world is more complex than just P and NP-Complete.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','What is a ''Monte Carlo'' algorithm?','Always correct, random time','Fast, but has a non-zero probability of giving an incorrect answer','Used for encryption','A type of sorting','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Monte Carlo algorithms are useful when a small error probability is acceptable for a big speedup.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','Which property defines a ''Van Emde Boas tree''?','It sorts in O(n log n)','It supports search, insert, and delete in O(log log U) where U is the universe size','It is a type of hash table','It uses exponential space','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'vEB trees are extremely fast for small, fixed integers.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','What is the time complexity of Dinic''s algorithm for finding maximum flow?','O(VE^2)','O(V^2E)','O(VE)','O(E sqrt(V))','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Dinic''s uses ''level graphs'' and ''blocking flows'' to achieve better performance than Edmonds-Karp.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','In the External Memory model, what is the bottleneck for algorithm performance?','CPU instructions','Number of Block I/O operations (accessing disk)','Network latency','Amount of RAM','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Since disk access is orders of magnitude slower than RAM, minimizing I/O is the goal.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','Which algorithm finds the ''Minimum Enclosing Circle'' of n points in expected O(n) time?','Graham Scan','Welzl''s Algorithm','Gift Wrapping','Binary Search','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Welzl''s is a randomized recursive algorithm with linear expected time.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','What is a ''PTAS'' (Polynomial-Time Approximation Scheme)?','A ways to sort primes','An algorithm that, for any ε > 0, returns a solution within a factor (1 + ε) of optimal in polynomial time','A constant time algorithm','A randomized approach to SAT','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The runtime may be exponential in 1/ε but must be polynomial in n.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','In online algorithms, ''Competitive Ratio'' compares the online algorithm''s performance to:','The best possible offline algorithm (with full knowledge of the future)','A random guesser','Its own best-case','The speed of light','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'It measures how much we ''lose'' by not knowing future inputs.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','What is the complexity of finding the ''Max Clique'' in a general graph?','Polynomial','NP-Hard','O(1)','Constant','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Finding the largest set of pairwise adjacent vertices is a classic NP-hard problem.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','The ''Ellipsoid Method'' was significant because it was the first algorithm to prove that Linear Programming is in:','NP','P (Polynomial time)','EXP','L','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Developed by Khachiyan, it proved that LP is solvable in polynomial time (unlike Simplex''s worst case).','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','Which hard algorithmic problem provides the security foundation for ElGamal and Diffie-Hellman?','Integer Factorization','Discrete Logarithm Problem','Traveling Salesman','Sorting large sets','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Finding ''x'' given ''g^x mod p'' is computationally difficult on current hardware.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','What is the ''Population Count'' (popcount) operation?','Counting users in a database','Counting the number of set bits (1s) in a binary representation','Multiplying by powers of 2','Dividing the array in half','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Many CPUs have a hardware instruction for this; otherwise, algorithms like Hamming Weight are used.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','What is the ''Misra-Gries'' algorithm used for in data streams?','Compressing the stream','Finding ''Heavy Hitters'' (Frequent elements)','Encrypting the stream','Sorting the stream','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'It finds elements that appear more than n/k times using k counters.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','In complexity theory, what does ''BPP'' stand for?','Below Polynomial Performance','Bounded-error Probabilistic Polynomial time','Binary Parallel Processing','Basic Prime Path','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The class of problems solvable by a randomized Turing machine with error probability at most 1/3.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','What do ''Chernoff Bounds'' provide for randomized algorithms?','Exact results','Exponentially decreasing bounds on tail distributions of sums of independent random variables','A ways to sort data','Memory limits','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'They prove that randomized algorithms with independent trials practically never deviate far from their average case.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','Which algorithm solves the ''All-Pairs Shortest Paths'' for a graph with NO negative edges in O(V^2 log V + VE)?','Floyd-Warshall','Johnson''s Algorithm','Repeated Dijkstra''s with Fibonacci Heaps','Bellman-Ford','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Johnson''s algorithm uses this repeated Dijkstra approach after an initial reweighting step.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','The ''Polynomial Hierarchy'' (PH) is a hierarchy of complexity classes that collapses if:','P = NP','P = L','V^2 = E','Recursion limit is reached','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'If P = NP, the entire hierarchy collapses to P.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','What is ''Christofides'' Algorithm'' used for?','Factoring numbers','Finding a 3/2-approximation for the Metric Traveling Salesman Problem','Sorting strings','Drawing graphs','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'It''s one of the most famous approximation algorithms for TSP, using MST and matching.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','What is ''Convex Hull Trick'' in DP optimization?','Drawing hulls in code','A technique to optimize DP transitions of the form dp[i] = min(m[j]*x[i] + b[j]) using geometric properties','Deleting subproblems','Recursive sorting','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'It reduces O(n^2) DP to O(n log n) or O(n) by maintaining a set of lines and finding the extreme point.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','What is a ''Cache-Oblivious'' algorithm?','One that uses no cache','An algorithm designed to perform well on hierarchies of caches without knowing the specific cache sizes or line lengths','Deleting the cache manually','A very slow algorithm','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'They typically use divide-and-conquer to fit problems into cache at every level of the hierarchy automatically.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','What distinguishes a ''Persistent Data Structure''?','It never deletes data from disk','It preserves the previous version of itself when it is modified','It uses only immutable variables','It is saved in a database automatically','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Functional programming languages rely heavily on persistent data structures.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','What is ''Skip List'' complexity for search, insert, and delete?','O(n)','O(log n) average','O(1)','O(n log n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Skip lists are probabilistic data structures that are simpler to implement than balanced trees but offer similar expected performance.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','In the context of ''Self-Organizing Lists'', what does the ''Move-To-Front'' heuristic do?','Moves the largest item to the front','Moves the requested item to the front of the list','Deletes the last item','Sorts the list','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'It is highly effective when access patterns show high temporal locality.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','The ''Sweep-Line'' algorithm for line segment intersection has what complexity?','O(n^2)','O((n+k) log n) where k is the number of intersections','O(n)','O(1)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Bentley-Ottmann algorithm is much faster than checking all pairs if intersections are sparse.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','The ''Decision Problem'' version of TSP is in which class?','P','NP-Complete','L','BPP','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Given a graph and a budget K, deciding if a tour exists with cost <= K is NP-complete.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','Which algorithm handles the ''Minimum Cost Maximum Flow'' problem?','Dijkstra''s with potentials (Successive Shortest Path)','Standard BFS','Merge Sort','Binary Search','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'It finds augmenting paths of minimum cost using algorithms like Bellman-Ford or Dijkstra with node potentials.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','What is ''Introsort'' primarily used for in system libraries (like C++ std::sort)?','Sorting integers specifically','A hybrid sort that starts with QuickSort and switches to HeapSort if recursion depth exceeds a limit','Deleting duplicates','A ways to sort strings','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'It combines the average-case speed of QuickSort with the worst-case guarantee of HeapSort.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','What is the complexity of the Ackermann function A(m, n)?','Polynomial','Exponential','Non-primitive recursive (grows faster than any fixed power of 2)','Constant','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'It is a famous example of a computable function that is not primitive recursive.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','In complexity theory, ''P CP'' (Probabilistically Checkable Proofs) theorem relates to:','Parallel computing','The hardness of approximating certain optimization problems','Cryptographic hashing','Network flow','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The PCP theorem is a profound result showing that some NP-hard problems are hard to approximate even within a small constant.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','What is ''Garbage Collection'' overhead in algorithmic analysis?','The time spent taking out trash','The amortized cost of memory deallocation that can interrupt application threads','Deleting the source code','Memory leaks in C++','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Modern GCs aim to minimize ''Stop-the-world'' pauses.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','A ''Reduction'' from A to B is ''Polynomial'' if:','The transformation takes polynomial time','B is faster than A','A is O(1)','It uses a for loop','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'A polynomial reduction ensures that an efficient solution for B implies an efficient solution for A.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','Which algorithm is the currently fastest known for general matrix multiplication (theoretically)?','Standard (n^3)','Strassen''s','Coppersmith-Winograd (or improved variants)','Held-Karp','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'It has a complexity of approximately O(n^2.37), though it is not used in practice due to gargantuan constant factors.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','What is ''Min-Wise Hashing'' (MinHash) used for?','Sorting numbers','Estimating the Jaccard similarity between two large sets efficiently','Password encryption','Matrix inversion','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Commonly used in web search to detect ''near-duplicate'' documents.','pregenerated'),
('b3401f7d-36f5-4f64-91d6-d1616b1c19b6','Which property is REQUIRED for an A* search heuristic h(n) to be ''Admissible''?','h(n) must be O(1)','h(n) must never overestimate the actual cost to reach the goal','h(n) must be calculated using BFS','h(n) must be prime','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Admissibility guarantees that A* will find the optimal solution.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','In an ER diagram, what shape represents an ''Entity''?','Ellipse','Rectangle','Diamond','Triangle','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'In Entity-Relationship modeling, rectangles represent entities, ellipses represent attributes, and diamonds represent relationships.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','Which SQL keyword is used to remove duplicate rows from the result set?','UNIQUE','DIFFERENT','DISTINCT','FILTER','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'The DISTINCT keyword is used to return only unique values in a SELECT statement.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','What type of relationship exists between ''Students'' and ''Courses'' in a typical university system?','One-to-One','One-to-Many','Many-to-Many','Many-to-One','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'A student can enroll in many courses, and a course can have many students, making it a many-to-many relationship.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','Which JOIN returns all records from the left table and the matched records from the right table?','INNER JOIN','RIGHT JOIN','LEFT JOIN','FULL OUTER JOIN','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'A LEFT JOIN (or LEFT OUTER JOIN) returns all rows from the left table, even if there are no matches in the right table.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','Which of these are DDL (Data Definition Language) commands?','CREATE','DROP','SELECT','ALTER','["A","B","D"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',35,'CREATE, DROP, and ALTER are DDL commands because they define/modify the structure. SELECT is a DQL (Data Query Language) command.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','Which key uniquely identifies a record in a table and cannot contain NULL values?','Foreign Key','Primary Key','Composite Key','Candidate Key','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The Primary Key is a unique identifier that enforces entity integrity.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','What is the primary advantage of a DBMS over a traditional file system?','Reduces data redundancy','Allows manual data entry','Uses more disk space','Does not require a schema','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'DBMS centralizes data, minimizing duplication and inconsistency.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','In an ER diagram, how is a ''Derived Attribute'' represented?','Solid Ellipse','Dashed Ellipse','Double Ellipse','Triangle','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Derived attributes (like ''Age'' calculated from ''DOB'') are shown with dashed ellipses.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','What is a ''Tuple'' in a relational database?','A column','A row (record)','A table name','A data type','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'A tuple represents a single instance of an entity in a relation.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','Which key is used to establish a relationship between two tables?','Primary Key','Foreign Key','Candidate Key','Super Key','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'A Foreign Key in one table points to the Primary Key of another table.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','Which SQL command is used to change existing data in a table?','MODIFY','UPDATE','CHANGE','ALTER','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The UPDATE command modifies values within existing rows.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','In SQL, which operator is used for pattern matching using wildcards?','EQUALS','LIKE','MATCH','BETWEEN','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The LIKE operator is used in a WHERE clause to search for a specified pattern in a column.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','What does ''Referential Integrity'' ensure?','That a table has a primary key','That values in a foreign key column must match values in the referenced primary key column','That data is encrypted','That only users can see the data','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Referential integrity maintains consistent relationships between tables.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','What is a ''Weak Entity''?','An entity with few attributes','An entity that cannot be uniquely identified by its own attributes alone and depends on a strong entity','An entity that is not and primary key','A table with no rows','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Weak entities are identified by using the primary key of an identifying owner entity.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','Which SQL clause is used to filter the results of an aggregate function?','WHERE','HAVING','FILTER','GROUP BY','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'HAVING is applied after the GROUP BY clause to filter groups.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','What is the ''Three-Schema Architecture'' primarily used for?','To speed up queries','To achieve data independence','To provide three copies of the database','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'It separates the physical view from the logical and external views, protecting apps from storage changes.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','What is a ''Candidate Key''?','A key that is not yet used','Any set of attributes that can uniquely identify a tuple in a relation','The key that the user likes best','A key that only has numbers','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Candidate keys are minimal superkeys that are eligible to become the Primary Key.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','In ER modeling, what is a ''Multivalued Attribute''?','An attribute with many names','An attribute that can have more than one value for a single entity (e.g., Phone Numbers)','A primary key','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Multivalued attributes are represented by double ellipses in ER diagrams.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','Which SQL command is used to remove all records from a table without deleting the table structure?','DELETE','TRUNCATE','REMOVE','DROP','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'TRUNCATE is a DDL operation that removes all data but keeps the schema.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','Which relational algebra operator is used to select specific columns (attributes) from a relation?','Selection (σ)','Projection (π)','Join (⨝)','Union (∪)','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Projection focuses on columns, while Selection focuses on rows (tuples).','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','What is the main goal of database normalization?','To make the database bigger','To eliminate data redundancy and anomalies (Insert, Update, Delete)','To encrypt the data','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Normalization organizes data into multiple related tables for efficiency.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','Which of these is a TCL (Transaction Control Language) command?','SELECT','GRANT','COMMIT','DELETE','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'COMMIT and ROLLBACK are used to manage changes perfectly made by DML statements.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','In a relational model, the number of columns in a table is called its:','Cardinality','Degree','Dimension','Domain','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'The degree is the count of attributes. Cardinality is the count of tuples (rows).','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','What does the SQL ''CASCADE'' constraint do during a DELETE operation?','Stops the deletion','Automatically deletes related offspring records in child tables','Asks for confirmation','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'ON DELETE CASCADE maintains referential integrity by cleaning up dependent records.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','Which data model uses a parent-child structure like a tree?','Relational Model','Hierarchical Model','Network Model','Object-Oriented Model','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'The legacy hierarchical model organizes data in a strict tree hierarchy.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','Which function is used to calculate the total number of records in a table?','SUM()','COUNT()','TOTAL()','AVG()','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'COUNT(*) returns the number of rows that match specified criteria.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','In SQL, what is the default sort order for ORDER BY?','Descending (DESC)','Ascending (ASC)','Random','By primary key','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Values are sorted from lowest to highest by default.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','What does ''NULL'' represent in a database?','Zero','An empty string','Unknown or missing data','A space character','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'NULL is a marker, not a value. It indicates the absence of data.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','What is a ''Super Key''?','A key with special powers','Any set of one or more attributes that can uniquely identify tuples in a relation','The primary key only','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Every candidate key is a super key, but not every super key is a candidate key (some are redundant).','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','Which SQL operator is used to check for a range of values?','IN','BETWEEN','RANGE','LIKE','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'BETWEEN is inclusive of the start and end values.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','In an ER diagram, how is a ''Total Participation'' constraint represented?','Single line','Double line','Dashed line','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Double lines between an entity and a relationship indicate that every entity instance must participate.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','Which level of the 3-Schema architecture describes how data is actually stored on the hardware?','External level','Conceptual level','Internal (Physical) level','User level','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The internal level deals with byte layouts, blocks, and indexes on disk.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','Which SQL keyword is used to sort the result-set?','SORT BY','ARRANGE BY','ORDER BY','GROUP BY','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'ORDER BY allows sorting by one or more columns.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','What is an ''Alternate Key''?','A key that changes daily','Any candidate key that was NOT chosen as the primary key','A foreign key','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Alternate keys are valid unique identifiers that are not the main primary key.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','Which operation in relational algebra combines two relations into a single relation containing all possible combinations of tuples?','Union','Intersection','Cartesian Product (X)','Join','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'The Cartesian Product results in a table with row_count1 * row_count2 tuples.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','What is a ''Self Join''?','Joining two different databases','A regular join where a table is joined with itself to compare rows within the same table','Automatic join by the OS','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Self joins often use table aliases to differentiate the ''left'' and ''right'' instances of the same table.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','What is a ''Database View''?','The physical screen showing data','A virtual table based on the result-set of an SQL statement, which doesn''t store data itself','A copy of the whole table','A user''s login history','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Views provide security and simplify complex queries by abstracting the underlying tables.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','Which command is used to add a new column to an existing table?','ADD COLUMN','ALTER TABLE ... ADD','UPDATE TABLE ... NEW','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'ALTER TABLE is the DDL command for structural changes.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','A table is in 1st Normal Form (1NF) if:','It has no primary key','All its attributes contain only atomic (indivisible) values','It is sorted','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'1NF requires no multivalued or composite attributes.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','What does ''Entity Integrity'' rule state?','No data can be deleted','Primary key attributes cannot be NULL','Everything must be a number','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Since PK identifies a row, it must have a value.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','Which relationship mapping has ''many'' on both sides?','1:1','1:N','M:N','N:1','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Many-to-Many relationships usually require an associative (bridge) table in implementation.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','Which SQL command is used to add new rows into a table?','ADD RECORD','INSERT INTO','CREATE','UPDATE','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'INSERT INTO is one of the core DML commands.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','What is ''Physical Data Independence''?','Deleting the hard drive','The ability to change the physical storage structure without needing to change the conceptual schema','Changing the programming language','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'This allows the DBA to improve performance (e.g., adding an index) without breaking existing apps.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','Which relational algebra operation is equivalent to a ''Cartesian Product followed by a selection''?','Intersection','Join','Union','Difference','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'A join uses a condition to filter the cross product of two relations.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','Who is the person responsible for the overall management of a database system?','Software Engineer','Database Administrator (DBA)','System Analyst','Project Manager','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The DBA handles installation, configuration, security, and performance tuning.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','Which wildcard character represents ''any sequence of characters'' in SQL LIKE?','_ (underscore)','% (percent sign)','* (asterisk)','# (hash)','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Underscore represents a single character; percent represents zero or more characters.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','What is the ''Metadata'' in a database?','The data that is encrypted','Data about data, stored in the Data Dictionary (Schema definitions, constraints, etc.)','Old data that is archived','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Metadata governs how the actual data is understood and managed by the system.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','Which Relational Algebra operation is NOT part of the ''Fundamental'' set?','Selection','Projection','Join','Union','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Join can be expressed using fundamental operations like Cartesian product and Selection.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','Which SQL aggregate function finds the highest value in a column?','TOP()','MAX()','HIGH()','GREATEST()','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'MAX() returns the maximum value ignoring NULLs.','pregenerated'),
('bccf8ca7-3a76-4cc0-a48b-763ff8fa90d9','What does ''SQL'' stand for?','System Query Logic','Structured Query Language','Simple Queue Layout','Shared Query Level','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'SQL is the standard language for relational database interaction.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','A table is in 2nd Normal Form (2NF) if it is in 1NF and:','Has no primary key','Every non-prime attribute is fully functionally dependent on the primary key (no partial dependency)','Has no transitive dependencies','Is sorted','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'2NF eliminates dependencies on part of a composite primary key.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','A table is in 3rd Normal Form (3NF) if it is in 2NF and:','Has no multi-valued attributes','Has no transitive functional dependencies (non-prime attributes shouldn''t depend on other non-prime attributes)','Is always sorted by primary key','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'3NF ensures that non-key attributes are dependent ONLY on the primary key.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','In ACID properties, what does ''Atomicity'' mean?','All operations in a transaction succeed, or none of them do','The database is always fast','Data is stored on atoms','Users cannot see each other''s data','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Atomicity ensures ''all-or-nothing'' execution for database transactions.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','In ACID properties, what does ''Durability'' ensure?','Data stays for a long time','Once a transaction is committed, its changes are permanent, even in the event of a system failure','The database never crashes','Encryption','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Durability is usually guaranteed by writing changes to non-volatile storage (disk).','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What is ''Partial Functional Dependency''?','When only half the data is dependent','When a non-prime attribute depends on only a part of a composite candidate key','Dependency on null values','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Partial dependency violates 2NF and causes anomalies.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','When is a table in BCNF (Boyce-Codd Normal Form)?','When it is in 3NF and every determinant is a candidate key','When it has no keys','When all attributes are prime','None of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'BCNF is a stricter version of 3NF that handles overlapping candidate keys.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What is a ''Dirty Read'' anomaly?','Reading data that is unencrypted','When a transaction reads data that has been modified by another concurrent transaction that hasn''t committed yet','Reading from a deleted table','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'If the modifying transaction rolls back, the first transaction''s data becomes invalid (dirty).','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What is ''Phantom Read'' anomaly?','A transparent reading mode','When a transaction re-executes a query and finds new rows that were not there before because of a commit by another transaction','Reading deleted data','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Phantom reads affect collective results like COUNT or SUM.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What is the difference between UNION and UNION ALL?','UNION ALL is faster because it does not remove duplicates','UNION is for only two tables','There is no difference','UNION ALL is more secure','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'UNION performs an additional step to filter out duplicates, which is more expensive.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What is a ''Natural Join'' (⨝)?','Joining two tables with No common columns','A join that automatically matches columns with the same name and eliminates the redundant duplicate column from the result','A join defined by the user manually','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Natural join is a shorthand for an Inner Join on all identical field names.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What does ''ROLLBACK'' do in a transaction session?','Restarts the server','Undoes all changes made during the current transaction, returning the database to its previous stable state','Deletes the logs','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Rollback is used when an error occurs to maintain database consistency (Atomicity).','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What are ''Armstrong''s Axioms'' used for?','Measuring the distance between servers','A set of rules (Reflexivity, Augmentation, Transitivity) used to derive all functional dependencies that hold in a relation','A way to encrypt passwords','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'These axioms form the foundation of logical inference for database design.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What is ''Attribute Closure'' (X+)?','Closing the table for editing','The set of all attributes that can be functionally determined by a given attribute set X','Deleting an attribute','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Closure is used to find candidate keys and check if a dependency holds.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What is ''Conflict Serializability''?','When two users have a conflict','A property of a schedule that means it can be transformed into a serial schedule by swapping non-conflicting concurrent operations','Sorting data after an error','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'Serializable schedules ensure that concurrent execution is equivalent to some serial ordering.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What is ''Transitive Dependency''?','Dependency on a primary key','When a non-prime attribute depends on another non-prime attribute (X -> Y and Y -> Z where Z is non-prime)','Dependency on a foreign key','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Transitive dependencies must be removed to achieve 3NF.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','In SQL, which operator is used to get the intersection of two result sets?','UNION','INTERSECT','AND','CROSS','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'INTERSECT returns only the rows that are present in both queries.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','In SQL, which operator returns the rows from the first query that are NOT present in the second query?','NOT IN','EXCEPT / MINUS','DIFFERENCE','NOT EXIST','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'EXCEPT (Postgres/SQL Server) or MINUS (Oracle) performs set subtraction.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What is a ''Precedence Graph'' (Serialization Graph) used for?','To draw beautiful charts','To determine whether a schedule is conflict serializable by checking for cycles in the graph','To map user permissions','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'If a cycle exists in the precedence graph, the schedule is NOT conflict serializable.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What is a ''Consistent'' database state?','A state that changes every second','A state where all integrity constraints are satisfied','A state where the web server is online','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Consistency ensures the database transitions from one valid state to another.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What is ''Domain Integrity''?','The address of the website','A constraint that defines the allowable values for a column (data type, range, format)','The security of the domain','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Domain integrity ensures that data values fall within defined valid boundaries.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What is a ''Trivial Functional Dependency''?','A dependency that is unimportant','A dependency X -> Y where Y is a subset of X (e.g., {ID, Name} -> ID)','A dependency on a null value','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Trivial dependencies always hold by definition and don''t provide useful design info.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','In SQL Joins, what is an ''Outer Join''?','A join for tables in different databases','A join that includes unmatched rows from one or both tables, filling missing values with NULL','A faster join','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Outer joins (Left, Right, Full) ensure no data is lost even if there''s no match.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What characterizes a ''Correlated Subquery''?','It uses more than one table','It is a subquery that depends on values from the outer query, executing once for each row of the outer query','It is encrypted','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Correlated subqueries are often powerful but can be slower than standard joins or non-correlated queries.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','Decomposition of a relation should ideally be:','Lossy','Lossless and Dependency Preserving','Random','One table only','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Lossless ensures you can recreate the original table; preserve dependency ensures constraints still check locally.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What is ''Lost Update'' anomaly?','The computer loses power','When two transactions override each other''s changes because they read the same initial value, resulting in only one change being saved','A deleted update','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Lost updates are a major concurrency problem that requires locking or isolation levels.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','Which integrity constraint prevents a user from entering a NULL value in a column?','UNIQUE','NOT NULL','CHECK','PRIMARY KEY','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'While PK implies NOT NULL, you can apply NOT NULL to regular columns too.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','A dependency X -> Y is a ''Full Functional Dependency'' if:','Y depends on all of X','Removal of ANY attribute from X causes the dependency to no longer hold','X is only one attribute','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'This is a key requirement for 2NF.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What is the typical result of a ''Schedule'' that is NOT serializable?','Faster processing','Database inconsistency and incorrect results','Deleted tables','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Non-serializable schedules allow data races and logical errors.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','In FD notation X -> Y, what is ''X'' called?','Determinant','Dependent','Product','Sum','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'X determines the value of Y, so X is the determinant.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What is ''Theta Join'' (θ-join)?','A join in a Greek database','A general join that uses various comparison operators (like <, >, <=, >=) instead of just equality','Joining 3 tables','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Equijoin is a specific type of Theta Join where θ is ''=''.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What is a ''Transaction State'' called when it is executing?','Active','Ready','Processing','Running','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'A transaction stays in ''Active'' state while its operations are being performed.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','Why do we rarely normalize beyond BCNF in many practical applications?','Higher levels are impossible','It often leads to too many small tables and excessive joins, which can hurt performance and query complexity','Normal forms are secrets','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Designers often balance normalization with performance (sometimes even denormalizing for speed).','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What characterizes ''Non-trivial'' functional dependency?','Important dependencies','A dependency X -> Y where Y is NOT a subset of X','Dependency on many tables','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Non-trivial dependencies are the ''meat'' of the database design rules.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','How many tables are involved in a ''Self Join''?','One','Two','Three','Many','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'A table is joined with its own copy.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What is ''Isolation'' in ACID properties?','Separating users physically','The property that concurrent execution of transactions results in a system state that would be obtained if transactions were executed serially','Keeping the data in its own folder','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Isolation prevents transactions from interfering with each other''s intermediate steps.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What does a ''Full Outer Join'' return?','Only matching rows','All records from both tables, with NULLs in place of unmatched rows','The whole database','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Full joins provide a complete view of data from both sides.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','If A -> B and B -> C, then A -> C is an example of which rule?','Reflexivity','Augmentation','Transitivity','Union','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Transitivity allows inferring a relationship across a middle attribute.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','A ''Serial Schedule'' is one where:','Transactions run at the same time','Transactions are executed execution one after another, with no overlap','The data is sorted','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Serial schedules are always consistent but offer poor performance for concurrent users.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What is the ''Partially Committed'' state?','When the user thinks they are done','After the final statement in a transaction has been executed but before changes are made durable to disk','A failed transaction','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Final safety checks occur here before the permanent COMMIT.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','Which SQL constraint ensures that all values in a column are unique?','PRIMARY KEY','UNIQUE','CHECK','NOT NULL','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'UNIQUE constraint prevents multiple rows from having same value, but allows NULLs unless specified otherwise.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','In SQL, what is the ''IN'' operator used for?','Finding the inner join','Checking if a value matches any value in a list of specified values or results from a subquery','Logging in as a user','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'IN is a cleaner alternative to multiple OR conditions.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','True or False: Every relation is in 1NF by definition in the relational model.','True','False','Only for MySQL','None of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'tricky',40,'The relational model fundamentally requires atomic values (no sets in cells), which is 1NF.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What is the ''Aborted'' state in a transaction?','A transaction that was forgotten','When a transaction has been rolled back and the database restored to its state before the transaction started','A committed transaction','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Abortion happens after a failure to ensure data integrity.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','Which JOIN is the base case and only returns common rows?','FULL JOIN','INNER JOIN','OUTER JOIN','CROSS JOIN','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Inner joins filter out rows that don''t have a match in the other table.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','If closure of {A, B} is {A, B, C, D}, can {A, B} be a candidate key?','Yes, if no subset of {A, B} is a super key','No, it must have all attributes','Only if it is a primary key','none of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Candidate keys must be MAS (Minimal Superkeys).','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What is ''Logical Data Independence''?','Changing the database password','The capacity to change the conceptual schema without having to change external schemas or applications','A way to use multiple databases','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'This allows changing the table structures without breaking the end-user queries (often using views).','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What does ''EXISTS'' check for in SQL?','If the table exists','If the subquery returns ANY result rows','If the user exists','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'EXISTS is typically more efficient for existence checks than COUNT(*) > 0.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What happens if a Primary Key is updated and ''ON UPDATE CASCADE'' is set?','The update fails','All matching foreign key values in related tables are automatically updated','The old data is deleted','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Cascading updates maintain synchronization across related records.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What is the ''Buffer Pool'' in a DBMS?','A place for swimming','A region of main memory used to cache data blocks from disk to speed up read/write operations','A list of logged-in users','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The buffer pool minimizes expensive disk I/O.','pregenerated'),
('1bf8d5e4-67ae-4b2d-b09b-abf78242f866','What is ''Recoverable Schedule''?','A schedule that can be printed','A schedule where if transaction T1 reads data modified by T2, then T2 must commit before T1 commits','A schedule with no errors','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Recoverability prevents ''cascading rollbacks'' and permanent data loss during failures.','pregenerated')
