('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is the primary difference between a B-Tree and a B+ Tree index?','B-Trees are only for numbers','B+ Trees store data pointers only in the leaf nodes, creating a linked list for faster range queries, whereas B-Trees store pointers in all nodes','B-Trees are faster for deletes','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'B+ trees are the industry standard for database indexing because of their efficient range scanning and predictable height.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is a ''Clustered Index''?','An index for groups of people','An index that defines the physical order of data in the table (a table can have only one)','An index that is encrypted','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'The table data itself is stored in the leaf nodes of a clustered index.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What characterizes ''Extendible Hashing''?','Adding more space manualy','A dynamic hashing technique that uses a directory of pointers to buckets, allowing the file to grow and shrink gracefully','Using a very long hash key','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Extendible hashing avoids the rehashing of the entire database by splitting only one bucket at a time.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is the ''Two-Phase Locking'' (2PL) protocol?','Locking the table twice','A protocol where a transaction has a Growing phase (acquiring locks) and a Shrinking phase (releasing locks), and it cannot acquire new locks after releasing one','Using two different keys for one row','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'2PL ensures conflict serializability but does not prevent deadlocks.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is ''Strict 2PL'' and why is it used?','A 2PL with no shrinkage','A variation where all exclusive (write) locks are held until the transaction commits or aborts to ensure recoverability','A way to delete all locks','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'Strict 2PL avoids cascading rollbacks and is used by most commercial databases.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What does ''Thomas'' Write Rule'' optimization do in timestamp-based concurrency?','Writes everything twice','It allows a write to be ignored if a newer write has already occurred (obsolescence), helping to improve concurrency without violating view serializability','Deletes the logs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Thomas'' Write Rule allows some non-conflict serializable schedules to be view serializable.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','In a ''Wait-Die'' deadlock prevention scheme, what happens if an older transaction requests a resource held by a younger one?','Older waits','Older dies','Younger dies','none of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Wait-Die uses timestamps to build a non-circular wait dependency (old waits for young; young dies if requesting old).','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','In a ''Wound-Wait'' deadlock prevention scheme, what happens if an older transaction requests a resource held by a younger one?','Older waits','Older ''wounds'' (aborts) the younger transaction to get the resource','Older dies','Younger waits','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Wound-Wait is generally more efficient than Wait-Die as it preempts younger transactions.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is ''Shadow Paging''?','Creating a shadow for the database','A recovery technique where the database remains consistent by maintaining dual versions of the page table; updates are written to a ''shadow'' version','Deleting the database shadow','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'Shadow paging avoids the overhead of log-based recovery but can lead to disk fragmentation.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is the purpose of ''Checkpoints'' in log-based recovery?','To check for bugs','To reduce the time for recovery after a crash by flushing dirty buffers to disk and marking a safe point in the log','To count the number of users','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Recovery only needs to process the log from the last checkpoint rather than from the beginning of time.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is a ''Database Trigger''?','An error that stops the database','A procedural piece of code that automatically executes in response to certain events (INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE) on a particular table','A user manual for the DB','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Triggers are used for complex integrity checks and auditing.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is a ''Stored Procedure''?','A way to store data faster','A prepared SQL code that you can save and reuse, allowing for complex logic and better performance (via pre-compilation)','The bios setup for DB','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Stored procedures reduce network traffic by executing complex logic on the server side.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','Which SQL Window function provides a unique sequence number for each row within a partition, regardless of ties?','RANK()','DENSE_RANK()','ROW_NUMBER()','PARTITION()','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'ROW_NUMBER() always increments, while RANK() can have gaps if ties occur.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','How does ''DENSE_RANK()'' differ from ''RANK()''?','Dense rank is for text only','DENSE_RANK() does not leave gaps in the rank sequence after a tie (e.g., 1, 2, 2, 3), whereas RANK() would skip (e.g., 1, 2, 2, 4)','Rank is faster','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'DENSE_RANK ensures every number is used in a consecutive sequence.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is ''Query Optimization'' in a DBMS engine?','The user writing better code','The component that analyzes a query and chooses the most efficient execution plan (lowest cost) considering indexes and table statistics','Deleting unused tables','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Optimization is the ''brain'' of the DBMS, determining whether to use a full table scan or an index.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What characterizes ''MVCC'' (Multi-Version Concurrency Control)?','Deleting old versions of the DB','Maintaining multiple versions of data items to allow ''readers'' to see a consistent snapshot of the DB without blocking ''writers''','Using multiple databases at once','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'MVCC provides high performance for read-heavy workloads (Postgres and InnoDB use it).','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is ''Index Fan-out''?','The number of fans in the server room','The number of pointers (entries) that can fit in a single index block','The depth of the tree','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Higher fan-out leads to shallower B+ trees and faster lookups.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is a ''Heap File'' organization?','Sorting everything by price','An unorganized collection of records where data is simply appended to the end of the file','Storing data only in RAM','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Heap files are fast for writes but slow for searches without an index.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is ''ISAM'' (Indexed Sequential Access Method)?','A high-speed internet protocol','A static multi-level index structure where data is stored in sorted order on disk','A way to delete database logs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'ISAM is efficient for static data but performs poorly when there are many inserts/deletes.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','In Log-based recovery, what is ''Deferred Update''?','Updating at the end of the day','Actual database updates are postponed until after the transaction is successfully committed, writing only to the log until then','A way to speed up the disk','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Deferred updates eliminate the need for ''Undo'' operations during recovery.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','In Log-based recovery, what is ''Immediate Update''?','Updating without writing a log','A technique where database updates are immediately reflected on disk even before the transaction commits','Updating only one table','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Immediate updates require both ''Undo'' and ''Redo'' operations during recovery.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is ''Lock Downgrading'' in 2PL?','Removing a password','Transitioning from an exclusive (write) lock to a shared (read) lock in the shrinking phase','Deleting the locks','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'Downgrading is allowed during the shrinking phase to improve concurrency.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is ''SQL Injection''?','Adding data using a syringe','A vulnerability where an attacker can execute arbitrary SQL code by manipulating input untrusted by the application','A way to speed up database queries','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Using ''Prepared Statements'' or ''Parameterized Queries'' is the primary defense against SQL injection.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is the ''Height'' of a B+ Tree?','The physical size of the disk','The number of levels from the root node to the leaf nodes','The number of users on the site','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Most production B+ trees have a height of 3 or 4, even with millions of records.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is ''Linear Hashing''?','Hashing in a straight line','A dynamic hashing method that grows the file by splitting buckets in a predictable, linear order, avoiding a global directory','Hashing only the primary key','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Linear hashing avoids the directory overhead of extendible hashing.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is an ''Index Scan'' vs ''Full Table Scan''?','Index scan only looks at the book cover','Index scan traverses an index tree to find rows; Full Table scan reads every single page of the table from disk','Full table scan is always faster','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Index scans are drastically faster for selective queries (e.g., finding 1 user out of 1 million).','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is the ''Log'' in log-based recovery?','A piece of wood','A sequential file that records all data-modification operations (and their outcomes) for the purpose of ensuring ACID properties','A list of table names','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The log (or WAL - Write Ahead Log) is the primary tool for database durability.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is ''Lock Starvation''?','The computer is hungry','When a transaction is never granted a lock it needs because other transactions keep getting the lock first (e.g., constant readers blocking a writer)','The database is empty','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Lock scheduling must use fairness (like a FIFO queue for locks) to avoid starvation.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is the ''Cascading Rollback'' problem?','Rolling down a hill','When the rollback of one transaction forces the rollback of many other dependent transactions due to uncommitted data being read','Deleting the database backup','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Avoiding cascading rollbacks is a key goal for practical database isolation.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is a ''Database Catalog''?','A magazine for DBs','The part of the metadata that contains info about users, privileges, table structures, and physical storage stats','A list of all users on the internet','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'The catalog is accessible via ''Information Schema'' queries in many SQL systems.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is ''Cursor'' in SQL processing?','The mouse on the screen','A database object that allows for row-by-row processing of a result-set','An error code','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Cursors should be used sparingly as they are generally slower than set-based SQL operations.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is a ''Hash Collision''?','When the computer crashes during hashing','When two different search keys hash to the same bucket address','Hiding the hash key','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Collisions are inevitable and are handled by techniques like Overflow Chaining or Open Addressing.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is ''RAID 6'' known for?','Speed only','Using dual parity to provide protection against the simultaneous failure of any two drives','Triple mirroring','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'RAID 6 is very safe but has high write overhead due to calculating complex syndromes.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is the purpose of the ''WITH RECURSIVE'' clause in SQL?','To delete files recursively','To perform recursive queries, such as navigating hierarchical data like an organizational chart or family tree','To repeat the same query forever','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Recursive CTEs (Common Table Expressions) are powerful for processing graph-like or hierarchical data structures.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is ''Role-Based Access Control'' (RBAC)?','Granting rights to individuals','Defining permissions for roles and then assigning users to those roles, simplifying maintenance','Using a role-play game to secure data','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'RBAC is the standard for enterprise security management.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is the result of ''Thomas Write Rule'' regarding serialization?','It makes all schedules conflict serializable','It allows some schedules that are NOT conflict serializable but ARE view serializable','It deletes all writes','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'By ignoring obsolete writes, it relaxes the strict conflict rules while maintaining logical correctness.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is ''Data Scrubbing'' in large storage systems?','Deleting all the data','Background background background background scanning for data corruption and fixing it using parity or ECC','Cleaning the hardware with soap','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Data scrubbing prevents silent errors (bit rot) from accumulating.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is ''Cost-Based Optimization''?','Making the database cheaper to buy','The strategy where the engine evaluates multiple plans and chooses one with the lowest estimated cost in terms of I/O, CPU, and memory','Paying the developer to write code','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Cost is estimated using table statistics (row count, selectivity, etc.).','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is ''Buffer Pinning''?','Adding a pin to the board','Forcing a page to stay in the buffer pool until a specific operation completes to prevent it from being swapped out','A way to backup the computer','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Pinning is required for active data manipulation by the engine.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is ''Snapshot Isolation''?','Taking a picture of the server','An isolation level where each transaction sees a consistent snapshot of the whole database from when it started, usually implemented via MVCC','Hiding the data from users','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Snapshot isolation eliminates many anomalies like Dirty Reads and Unrepeatable Reads.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','In a B+ Tree, what is ''Leaf Level'' chaining?','Chaining the leaves to the root','Connecting leaf nodes via pointers to form a doubly linked list for efficient range scans','A way to encrypt data','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'This allows the engine to satisfy a ''WHERE value BETWEEN x AND y'' query by jumping to x and following the links to y.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What happens if a transaction violates a ''CHECK'' constraint in SQL?','The computer reboots','The operation fails and the transaction is typically aborted/rolled back','The data is automatically fixed','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Constraints preserve data integrity; violations are rejected.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is ''Record Blocking'' in storage?','Blocking a user from a record','Grouping multiple logical records into a single physical block on disk to improve I/O efficiency','Splitting a file into many parts','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Larger blocks use less overhead and fewer IO operations.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What characterizes ''View Serializability''?','A schedule that looks like a serial one','A weaker isolation level than conflict serializability that allows the same final view of the database','A stronger version of serializability that handles obsolete writes correctly','None of the above','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'View serializability is more permissive than conflict serializability but difficult to check efficiently (NP-hard).','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','Which operation in relational algebra is used to find records that exist in R but NOT in S?','Union','Set Difference (-)','Intersection','Projection','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Set difference yields R - S.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is the ''Rename'' operator (ρ) used for in relational algebra?','Changing the name of the database','A way to provide a temporary name for a relation or its attributes during a query (e.g., in a self-join)','Deleting a table name','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Rename allows for unambiguous reference in complex joins.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is ''Write Ahead Logging'' (WAL)?','Writing at the beginning of the day','A fundamental rule that a log record describing a change MUST be written to stable storage before the actual change is applied to the database on disk','A security scan of the logs','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'WAL is required to survive system failures reliably.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','Can a transaction acquire a ''Shared Lock'' if an ''Exclusive Lock'' held by someone else exists on the same item?','Yes','No','Only on Tuesdays','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Exclusive locks are incompatible with any other locks (shared or exclusive).','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is ''Materialized View''?','An index on a view','A view whose query result is physically stored on disk, and updated when the base tables change, to speed up expensive queries','A view for only prime attributes','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Materialized views trade storage and update time for ultra-fast read performance.','pregenerated'),
('b210b9d0-c54b-4abe-8ee6-09a580929c2e','What is ''Lock Escalation''?','Making the lock harder to break','When the OS converts hundreds of individual row-level locks into a single table-level lock to save memory when a transaction is affecting many rows','A way to backup the computer','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Lock escalation saves RAM but significantly reduces concurrency (other users are blocked from the whole table).','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is the primary role of the ''Two-Phase Commit'' (2PC) protocol?','To commit the data twice','To ensure atomicity in distributed transactions by having all participating nodes agree to either commit or abort the transaction together','To backup the database to two different clouds','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'2PC involves a coordinator and participants in ''Prepare'' and ''Commit'' phases.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is the ''CAP Theorem'' in distributed systems?','Consistency, Availability, and Partition Tolerance: You can only have two out of three in a distributed database when a network partition occurs','Computers, Applications, and Programs must work together','Cloud, APIs, and Parallelism are the keys to success','None of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'CAP theorem highlights the unavoidable trade-offs in distributed data storage design.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What does ''BASE'' property stand for in NoSQL databases?','Basic Atomic Storage Entry','Basically Available, Soft-state, Eventually consistent','Binary Access System Engine','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'BASE is a relaxed consistency model used by NoSQL to achieve high availability and scale.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is ''Bitmap Indexing'' primarily used for?','Storing photos in the database','Indexing columns with low cardinality (few unique values, e.g., Gender, Marital Status) for highly efficient bitwise queries','Speeding up primary key lookups','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Bitmap indexes are extremely space-efficient and fast for complex search filtering in data warehouses.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','How does ''OLAP'' differ from ''OLTP''?','OLAP is for daily sales (short queries); OLTP is for long-term reports (long queries)','OLTP is for transaction processing (many short writes/reads); OLAP is for analytical processing (complex aggregate queries on historical data)','They are the same','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'OLTP optimizes for operational speed; OLAP optimizes for deep insightful analysis.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is ''Horizontal Fragmentation'' (Sharding)?','Splitting a table into many columns','Splitting a table into groups of rows and storing them on different servers based on a shard key','Deleting half of the data','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Sharding is the most common way to horizontally scale relational databases.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is ''Vertical Fragmentation'' in a distributed DBMS?','Splitting the rows of a table','Splitting the columns of a table across different sites, keeping only the primary key in each fragment to allow reconstruction','Putting data in a vertical folder','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Vertical fragmentation can be used to store personally identifiable info on a more secure server.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is a ''Vector Database'' primarily used for in modern AI applications?','Storing mathematical formulas','Storing and performing similarity search on high-dimensional vectors (embeddings) generated by Large Language Models','Calculating physics vectors','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Vector databases (like Pinecone, Milvus) empower AI with ''long-term memory'' via semantic search.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is ''ARIES'' algorithm in database recovery?','A security scan from the cloud','A sophisticated recovery algorithm based on ''Write-Ahead Logging'' that repeats history, undoes uncommitted transactions, and handles multiple crashes during recovery','A way to delete all logs after commit','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'ARIES (Algorithm for Recovery and Isolation Exploiting Semantics) is implemented in many industrial databases.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What characterizes a ''Snowflake Schema'' compared to a ''Star Schema''?','It looks like a snow flake','Dimension tables are normalized into multiple related tables, whereas a Star Schema uses single large denormalized dimension tables','There is no difference','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Snowflake schema saves space through normalization but requires more complex joins.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','How does ''Three-Phase Commit'' (3PC) improve upon Two-Phase Commit?','It adds a third Cloud backup','It eliminates the ''Blocking'' problem of 2PC by introducing a ''Pre-commit'' phase that allows participants to safely abort if the coordinator fails','It is exactly the same','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'3PC is non-blocking but more expensive in terms of network communication.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is ''Polyalphabetic Substitution'' in the context of database column encryption?','A type of database indexing','An encryption technique that uses multiple substitution alphabets, making frequency analysis attacks much harder for attackers','Using many fonts in SQL','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'This is a classic cryptographic principle used in secure data storage.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','How does ''MapReduce'' handle massive data processing in a cluster?','By using a large map of the world','By dividing a large task into smaller units (Map), processing them in parallel on many nodes, and then combining the results (Reduce)','By compressing the data','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'MapReduce allows for distributed computation on Petabytes of data across thousands of machines.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','When would you prefer a ''Graph Database'' (like Neo4j) over a Relational database?','For storing simple user lists','When the data has complex, interconnected relationships that are more important than the data points themselves (e.g., social networks, fraud detection)','For storing image files','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Graph databases excel at ''relationship traversal'' which is expensive in relational SQL (many joins).','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is ''Distributed Deadlock Detection'' via a Global Wait-for Graph?','Asking every user to wait','Maintaining a graph representing all dependencies across all nodes to find and resolve cycles that span multiple machines','Deleting all transactions and starting over','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Global deadlock occurs when T1 on Site A waits for T2, and T2 on Site B waits for T1.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','Why are ''Column-oriented'' databases (like BigQuery or ClickHouse) much faster for big analytical queries?','They use fewer columns','They read only the columns required for the query from disk, minimizing I/O for large-scale aggregations','They are in the cloud','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Columnar storage is optimized for data warehousing where you might read 10 columns out of 500.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is ''Shared Nothing'' architecture in parallel databases?','Computers that don''t share data','An architecture where each processor has its own private memory and its own private disk storage, communicating via an interconnection network','Deleting no data','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Shared nothing is highly scalable and is used by almost all modern web-scale data systems.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is an ''Inverted Index'' used for most commonly?','Sorting data backwards','Full-text search, where it maps words to the documents (or rows) where they appear','Indexing the primary key','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Inverted index (used in Elasticsearch) allows for lightning-fast keyword search across large text corpora.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is ''Consensus Replication'' using the ''Raft'' or ''Paxos'' protocol?','Asking everyone to vote on what to eat','A leader-follower algorithm that ensures a group of distributed servers agree on a sequence of state changes even if some fail','Deleting all copies of the data','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Raft/Paxos form the basis of highly available, consistent distributed systems like etcd (used in K8s).','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is ''5th Normal Form'' (5NF) / Join-Project Normal Form?','A high level of security','A advanced normalization level that handles join dependencies, where a table cannot be reconstructed from several smaller tables without losing data integrity','A way to backup the database','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'5NF is rare in practice but theoretically important for multi-valued multi-table dependencies.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is an ''R-Tree'' primarily used for?','Sorting text','Indexing spatial and geographic data (points, polygons, lines) for proximity queries','Storing family trees','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'R-Trees allow you to find ''all coffee shops within 1km'' very quickly.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is a ''Merkle Tree'' in distributed ledger technologies?','A type of family tree','A cryptographic hash tree where each leaf node is a hash of a block of data, used for efficient and secure verification of data integrity','A way to grow computer trees','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Merkle trees ensure that if one bit of data changes in 100GB of storage, the root hash will detect it instantly.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','In Vector Databases, what is ''HNSW'' (Hierarchical Navigable Small World)?','A map of the whole world','A state-of-the-art graph-based algorithm for Approximate Nearest Neighbor (ANN) search, providing sub-linear search time in high-dimensional spaces','A way to encrypt passwords','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'HNSW is one of the most popular algorithms for implementing fast RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) in AI apps.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is ''Quorum'' in distributed consistency models (R+W > N)?','The maximum number of users','A configuration where the number of successful reads (R) and writes (W) plus the total replicas (N) ensure you always read the latest data','A tool to delete logs','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Quorum-based systems allow you to tune for either higher read speed or higher write consistency.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is a ''Document Store'' (like MongoDB) database?','A system to store PDF files only','A NoSQL database that stores data in flexible semi-structured JSON or BSON documents, allowing for dynamic schemas','A way to backup MS Word documents','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Document stores are preferred for fast prototyping and hierarchical data that changes often.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is the ''Lambda Architecture'' in data engineering?','A high-speed networking cable','A design pattern that processes massive amounts of data using both a batch layer (high accuracy) and a speed layer (low latency) for real-time analysis','An encryption standard','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Lambda architecture attempts to provide the best of both worlds: robust history and near-real-time insights.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is ''Database Hardening''?','Freezing the server with liquid nitrogen','A series of actions (like disabling unused features, changing default accounts, and encrypting connections) to reduce the attack surface of the DB instance','Adding more RAM to the computer','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Hardening is a critical step before putting a database into production on the internet.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is the ''Object-Relational Impedance Mismatch''?','When the programmer is tired','The conceptual and technical difference between how data is represented in Object-Oriented code (objects) vs Relational Tables','A hardware cable mismatch','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'ORM libraries (like Hibernate or Prisma) bridge this gap but can introduce performance issues if not careful.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is ''NewSQL'' (e.g., CockroachDB, Google Spanner)?','A newer version of MySQL','Modern scalable databases that provide the ACID guarantees of traditional RDBMS with the horizontal scalability of NoSQL systems','A database that only saves data once','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'NewSQL systems are ideally suited for global-scale mission-critical financial applications.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is ''Cardinality Estimation'' in query optimization?','Counting the stars','The process of predicting how many rows will be returned by various parts of a query plan, allowing for accurate cost prediction','A way to delete database logs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Poor cardinality estimates (due to outdated statistics) lead to the engine picking extremely slow query plans.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is ''Multi-Master Replication''?','Using many computers as monitors','A system where data can be both read and written to multiple database nodes simultaneously, with the system handling synchronization','Copying data to a master disk','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Multi-master allows for ultra-high write availability but introduces complex conflict resolution (e.g., ''Last Write Wins'').','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is ''Erasure Coding'' used for in large-scale storage (like HDFS or S3)?','Deleting the code for better performance','A highly efficient way to provide fault tolerance by splitting data into fragments and calculating redundant data chunks, allowing for recovery from multiple drive failures','Hiding passwords','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Erasure coding is more space-efficient than simple replication (3x mirrored) for giant cloud systems.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is a ''Business Rule'' in database constraints?','A law for the economy','A complex constraint that defines specific data logic (e.g., ''Total balance cannot be less than zero'') that is often enforced via triggers or stored procedures','A rule for the boss','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'DBMS-enforced business rules are more reliable than application-level checks which can be bypassed via other tools.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is a ''JSONB'' data type in Postgres?','A JSON file that is blue','A binary representation of JSON that is pre-parsed and can be indexed, making it much faster for querying than plain JSON text','A way to encrypt data','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'JSONB bridges the gap between relational and document-oriented databases.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is ''Database Grooming'' (Vacuuming)?','Cleaning the database with soap','The process of reclaiming space from deleted rows and updating statistics to keep the database running efficiently','Replacing the hard drive','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'In MVCC systems (like Postgres), ''Vacuuming'' is essential to prevent ''bloat'' and maintain speed.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is ''Predicate Pushdown'' in distributed query engines?','Pushing the button for data','Sending filtering logic (WHERE clauses) as close to the data source as possible to minimize the amount of data transferred over the network','A way to delete database logs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Predicate pushdown is critical for performance in systems like Spark or Hadoop.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is ''Row-Level Security'' (RLS)?','Locking the whole table','A security feature that restricts which rows a user can see based on their identity or a boolean condition (e.g., ''manager can only see their department'')','Encryption for only one row','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'RLS allows building multi-tenant applications securely at the database level.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What characterizes ''Linearizability'' in distributed consistency?','Drawing data in a line','The strongest form of consistency where every operation appears to occur atomically and instantaneously at some point between its start and finish','Deleting data after it is read','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Linearizability provides users with the most intuitive view of a distributed system, as if it were a single machine.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is ''Tiered Storage''?','Buying many hard drives','Moving data automatically between different storage media (e.g., NVMe SSD, SATA SSD, HDD) based on how frequently it is accessed','Using multiple cloud accounts','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Tiered storage (or HSM) optimizes for both high speed and low cost for massive datasets.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is the ''Write-Write Conflict'' problem?','Writing at night','When two transactions attempt to update the same record at the same time, necessitating a resolution strategy','Using two different pens for code','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Write-write conflicts are the hardest part of distributed multi-master synchronization.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is a ''Data Lakehouse''?','A house for data','A modern architecture that combines the flexible storage of a Data Lake with the management and performance of a Data Warehouse','A floating server on water','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Data lakehouses (like Databricks) allow for both AI/ML exploration and structured reporting in one place.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is ''Saga Pattern'' for long-running transactions?','A very long story about data','A sequence of local transactions where each one updates the DB and publishes an event; if one fails, ''compensating'' transactions are run to undo previous steps','Deleting the database and starting over','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Sagas are the standard for maintaining ''eventual consistency'' in microservices where ACID 2PC is too expensive.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is ''Disaster Recovery'' (DR) in database management?','The computer breaking','The technical process of restoring database service after a catastrophic event, usually involving failover to a georeplicated site','A error in the code','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'D/R recovery time objective (RTO) and recovery point objective (RPO) are key business metrics.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is ''Join Reordering'' in a query optimizer?','Sorting the columns by name','A complex task of finding the sequence of joins (e.g., (A⨝B)⨝C vs A⨝(B⨝C)) that results in the minimum total disk reads','Deleting unused tables from a join','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The difference between join orders can mean the difference between a 1-second query and a 1-hour query.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is ''TF-IDF'' in the context of full-text search indexing?','A new database brand','Term Frequency-Inverse Document Frequency: A statistical measure used to evaluate how important a word is to a document in a collection or corpus','A way to encrypt data','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'TF-IDF is used to rank search results by relevance.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','In ARIES recovery, what is the ''Analysis'' pass?','Analyzing the user''s code','The first phase after a crash that identifies which transactions were active and which pages were ''dirty'' (not yet on disk) at the time of failure','Deleting all database logs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Analysis pass sets the stage for Redo and Undo phases.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What characterizes ''Optimistic Concurrency Control'' (OCC)?','Hoping the computer won''t crash','Checking for conflicts only at the end (commit) of a transaction rather than locking data up front, assuming conflicts are rare (optimism)','Always using a password','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'OCC is efficient for high-scale systems where most transactions don''t touch the same data rows.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is ''Direct I/O'' in a DBMS?','I/O that skips the cable','Bypassing the OS kernel''s file system cache so the DBMS can manage its own buffer pool entirely, giving it more predictable performance','Using a faster internet port','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Most expert-level databases (like SQL Server or Oracle) use Direct I/O to avoid ''double buffering'' memory waste.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is ''Bit-Slicing'' in column databases?','Cutting the CPU into parts','A high-performance aggregation technique where data is stored in slices of bits to allow for ultra-fast parallel calculations in the CPU''s SIMD registers','A way to hide passwords','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Bit-slicing can significantly speed up massive analytical summations.','pregenerated'),
('6ec13e5f-54d8-4d31-a205-c8acabb8209f','What is ''Serverless Database'' (e.g., Aurora Serverless, PlanetScale)?','A database for people without servers','A cloud-native database that automatically scales capacity based on real-time application demand, with the user paying only for what they use','A way to use a different cloud for free','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Serverless databases simplify operations for modern reactive applications.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('34b1aaf4-006b-4f08-a3bc-268db959f342','Which OSI layer is responsible for routing and logical addressing?','Data Link Layer','Network Layer','Transport Layer','Physical Layer','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The Network Layer (Layer 3) handles IP addressing and routing packets between different networks.','pregenerated'),
('34b1aaf4-006b-4f08-a3bc-268db959f342','What is the primary difference between the OSI model and the TCP/IP model regarding layers?','OSI has 4 layers, TCP/IP has 7','OSI has 7 layers, TCP/IP has 4 (or 5 standard)','OSI is practical, TCP/IP is theoretical','There is no difference in the number of layers','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'The OSI model is a 7-layer theoretical framework, while the practical TCP/IP model is generally interpreted as 4 or 5 layers.','pregenerated'),
('34b1aaf4-006b-4f08-a3bc-268db959f342','Calculate the number of usable hosts in a /27 subnet.','32','30','14','62','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'A /27 subnet has 32 addresses total. 30 are usable (32 - 2 for Network and Broadcast).','pregenerated'),
