('fbc440c7-dd74-42e0-99bb-f13a2bf930ca','What is ''Bit Stuffing'' in framing?','Adding extra bits to make the data longer','Inserting a 0 after five consecutive 1s in data to avoid it being mistaken for a flag sequence','Deleting bits to compress data','Encrypting the bits during transmission','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Bit stuffing ensures the frame delimiter (flag) only appears at the start and end of a frame.','pregenerated'),
('fbc440c7-dd74-42e0-99bb-f13a2bf930ca','In a ''Go-Back-N'' protocol, if the window size is 7 and packet 4 is lost, which packets must be retransmitted?','Only packet 4','All packets from 4 onwards in the current window','No packets; it waits for 10 seconds','Only the last packet','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Go-Back-N retransmits the lost packet and all subsequent packets that were sent after it in the window.','pregenerated'),
('fbc440c7-dd74-42e0-99bb-f13a2bf930ca','In ''Selective Repeat'' ARQ, if packet 4 is lost, which packets are retransmitted?','Only packet 4','All packets starting from 4','The entire window','Nothing is retransmitted','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Selective Repeat is more efficient as it only retransmits the specific frames that were lost or damaged.','pregenerated'),
('fbc440c7-dd74-42e0-99bb-f13a2bf930ca','What is the primary characteristic of ''Distance Vector'' routing?','Each router has a full map of the network','Each router shares its routing table with its immediate neighbors periodically','It uses the Dijkstra algorithm','It never has loops','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Distance Vector protocols (like RIP) calculate the best path based on reports from neighbors.','pregenerated'),
('fbc440c7-dd74-42e0-99bb-f13a2bf930ca','Dijkstra''s algorithm is commonly used in which type of routing?','Distance Vector','Link State','Static Routing','Flooding','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Link State protocols (like OSPF) use Dijkstra to find the shortest path after building a full topology map.','pregenerated'),
('fbc440c7-dd74-42e0-99bb-f13a2bf930ca','What is the ''Stop-and-Wait'' protocol''s main efficiency limitation?','It uses too much memory','The sender must wait for an ACK for every single frame, wasting time on high-latency links','It is hard to code','It doesn''t detect errors','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'It has very low bandwidth utilization because it only allows one pending frame at a time.','pregenerated'),
('fbc440c7-dd74-42e0-99bb-f13a2bf930ca','What is the ''TTL'' field in an IPv4 header used for?','To speed up packet arrival','To prevent packets from looping infinitely in a network','To tell the user how long wait','To encrypt the payload','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Time To Live (TTL) is decremented by 1 at each router; if it reaches 0, the packet is discarded.','pregenerated'),
