('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What does SAST analyze to find vulnerabilities?','The running application','The static source code, before compilation','Network traffic','User logs','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Static Application Security Testing (SAST) scans the code itself for vulnerabilities like hardcoded secrets or poor design.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What does DAST analyze to find vulnerabilities?','The source code',' The running application, by simulating attacks','The developer''s laptop','Only the documentation','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Dynamic Application Security Testing (DAST) interacts with the app while it''s active to find runtime security issues.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is ''SCA'' in the context of DevSecOps?','Secure Code Analysis','Software Composition Analysis: Identifying vulnerabilities in third-party libraries and dependencies','Social Communication Audit','System Control Access','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'SCA helps manage the risk of using open-source components that might have known security flaws.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What does the principle of ''Least Privilege'' mean?','Giving everyone full access to everything','Giving users and services ONLY the minimum permissions they need to perform their job','Developing with the cheapest tools','Deleting all users frequently','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Least privilege reduces the ''blast radius'' if a specific account is compromised.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is RBAC?','Remote Backup and Coding','Role-Based Access Control: Managing permissions based on the roles within an organization','Randomly Based Access Control','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'RBAC simplifies security management by grouping permissions into roles rather than assigning them to individual users.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','Why should you use ''minimal'' base images for Docker containers?','To make them look smaller on screen','To reduce the ''attack surface'' by excluding unnecessary tools like shells and package managers','To save money on internet bandwidth only','Because they are faster to download only','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Fewer installed packages means fewer vulnerabilities and fewer tools for an attacker to use.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','How should database passwords be handled in a CI/CD pipeline?','Stored as plain text in the repo','Injected at runtime as encrypted environment variables or from a dedicated Secret Management service','Hardcoded in the Dockerfile','Shared in the team Slack channel','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Tools like HashiCorp Vault, AWS Secrets Manager, or GitHub Secrets keep sensitive data secure while allowing automation.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is ''GDPR''?','General Data Protection Regulation: A regulation on data protection and privacy in the EU','Global Data Pattern Recognition','A programming language','A ways to name servers','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Compliance involves ensuring your systems meet legal standards for protecting user data.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is ''SOC 2''?','A brand of security camera','A compliance standard for service organizations, focusing on security, availability, and privacy','The second version of the cluster','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'SOC 2 audits verify that an organization has strong internal security controls.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is a ''DDoS'' attack?','Deleting the Data of Users','Distributed Denial of Service: Overwhelming a target system with traffic from many sources to make it unavailable','Directly Downloading Software','A ways to hack a password','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'DDoS attacks use many computers (botnets) to flood a network or server, causing an outage.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is ''TLS'' (Transport Layer Security) used for?','To speed up the network','To provide secure, encrypted communication between a client and a server (e.g. HTTPS)','To rename the internet','To delete old messages','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'TLS ensures that data being sent over the network cannot be intercepted or modified by others.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is ''Audit Logging''?','Logging the weight of the server','Recording a chronological history of who did what and when in a system','Deleting old files','Naming the pods','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Logs are essential for investigating security incidents and proving compliance.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is an ''Incident Response Plan''?','A plan to write code faster','A set of procedures for detecting, responding to, and recovering from security incidents','A ways to delete users','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Having a plan ensures that the organization can act quickly and effectively when an attack occurs.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What does ABAC stand for?','Always Be Accessing Code','Attribute-Based Access Control: Granting access based on attributes of the user, resource, and environment','Automated Backup and Control','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'ABAC is more flexible than RBAC, allowing for complex rules (e.g. ''can only access data during office hours'').','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is a ''DMZ'' (Demilitarized Zone) in networking?','A place where there is no internet','A physical or logical subnetwork that contains and exposes an organization''s external-facing services to an untrusted network','A ways to delete servers','Naming the nodes','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'DMZ adds an extra layer of security to an organization''s LAN; an external attacker only has access to equipment in the DMZ.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is the purpose of ''GPG Signing'' your Git commits?','To make the commit messages look professional','To verify that the commit actually came from you and hasn''t been altered','To encrypt the source code in Git','To speed up the Git push process','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Signing commits prevents ''identity spoofing'' where an attacker pretends to be a trusted developer.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','How can ''Pre-commit hooks'' improve security in a DevSecOps pipeline?','By deleting the code before it is committed','By automatically running security checks (like secret scanning or linting) locally before the code is even committed to Git','By asking for the developer''s password more often','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Hooks catch issues early (Shift Left), preventing sensitive data from ever reaching the central repository.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is a ''False Positive'' in the context of security scanning?','A bug that is actually a feature','When a scanner incorrectly identifies a piece of code as dynamic when it is static','When a scanner reports a security vulnerability that does not actually exist or is not exploitable','none of the above','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'False positives can lead to ''alert fatigue'' and waste developer time; tuning scanners is essential.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What does ''CVSS'' stand for in vulnerability assessment?','Common Vulnerability Scoring System','Central View Security Solution','Code Verification Safety Standard','none of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'CVSS provides a numerical score (0-10) to reflect the severity of a vulnerability.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is ''IaC Scanning''?','Scanning the computer for viruses','Analyzing configuration files (like Terraform or CloudFormation) for security misconfigurations before they are deployed','Checking the internet speed','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'IaC scanning prevents deploying insecure infrastructure, such as S3 buckets with public read access.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is ''Image Layering'' in the context of security scanning?','Drawing pictures of the server','The process where a scanner inspects each layer of a Docker image for vulnerabilities, rather than just the final state','Naming the folders in order','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Security issues can be hidden in intermediate layers even if they are ''cleaned up'' in the final layer.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What characterizes ''Fuzz Testing'' (Fuzzing)?','Writing blurry code','Providing large amounts of random, malformed, or unexpected data to an application to see if it crashes or behaves unexpectedly','Deleting old logs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Fuzzing is excellent for finding memory leaks, crashes, and unhandled edge cases.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is ''CSRF'' (Cross-Site Request Forgery)?','A ways to hack a password','An attack that tricks a logged-in user into performing an action they did not intend to do on a different website','Deleting the database','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'CSRF exploits the trust a site has in a user''s browser (usually via cookies).','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','How does an ''Anti-CSRF Token'' protect an application?','It encrypts the whole website','It is a unique, secret, and unpredictable value generated by the server and required in every state-changing request from the client','It is a ways to name a user','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Because an attacker cannot predict the token, they cannot forge a valid request on behalf of the user.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is the ''Same Origin Policy'' (SOP)?','A policy that says all users must be the same','A critical browser security mechanism that restricts how a document or script loaded from one origin can interact with a resource from another origin','A ways to name a server','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'SOP is a foundational security property that prevents scripts on one site from reading sensitive data on another site.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is ''CSP'' (Content Security Policy)?','A protocol for streaming video','An added layer of security that helps detect and mitigate certain types of attacks, including XSS and data injection, by declaring which origins are trusted','A ways to delete old images','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'CSP is implemented via HTTP headers and can block inline scripts or unauthorized domains from loading resources.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','Why should you NOT store sensitive user data (like passwords) inside a ''JWT'' (JSON Web Token) payload?','JWTs are too small','The payload is standard base64 encoded, and anyone with the token can easily read the contents (unless it is explicitly encrypted)','JWTs delete themselves','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Standard JWTs provide ''Integrity'' (via signature) but NOT ''Confidentiality'' for the payload content.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is ''Rate Limiting'' used for in API security?','To slow down the developers','To limit the number of requests a user can make in a given timeframe, protecting against brute-force and DoS attacks','To rename the API','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Rate limiting ensures systems aren''t overwhelmed and prevents automated tools from scraping data too quickly.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What characterizes a ''Man-in-the-Middle'' (MitM) attack?','A ways to catch two people talking','An attack where the attacker secretly relays and possibly alters the communications between two parties who believe they are directly communicating','A ways to delete a server','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Encryption (TLS) and certificate validation are the primary defenses against MitM attacks.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is ''Secure by Default''?','A ways to name a user','The concept that software should be secure out-of-the-box, without requiring users to change settings to protect themselves','A ways to delete old code','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Examples include passwords being forced to change on first login or closing all ports by default on a firewall.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is ''Data Masking''?','Putting a mask on the server','A method of creating a structurally similar but inauthentic version of an organization''s data (e.g. for testing) to protect PII','Deleting the data','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Masking allows developers to work with realistic data without seeing actual customer secrets.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is a ''SIEM'' tool?','Software for writing code','Security Information and Event Management: A solution that aggregates and analyzes log data from across an entire organization to identify threats','A tool to delete logs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'SIEMs (like Splunk or ELK) help security teams see the ''big picture'' by connecting dots across multiple systems.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What does the ''S'' in the STRIDE threat modeling framework stand for?','Secrecy','Spoofing','Simple','Source','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Spoofing is an attempt to gain access to a system by using a false identity.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is ''Security Debt''?','Money owed to a security company','The accumulation of known vulnerabilities and weak security designs that have not been addressed in favor of feature delivery','A ways to delete code','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Ignoring security issues creates ''debt'' that becomes increasingly expensive and dangerous to fix later.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','In the ''Shared Responsibility Model'', who is typically responsible for ''Security OF the Cloud''?','The Customer','The Cloud Service Provider (e.g. AWS, GCP)','The Internet Provider','The Developer','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The provider handles physical security and hardware; the customer handles data, OS, and app security.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is the core idea of ''Zero Trust'' architecture?','Trusting no one, even users inside the corporate network','Trusting only the boss','Trusting only the server','A ways to delete a user','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Zero Trust means every request must be authenticated and authorized, regardless of where it originates.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is ''Directory Traversal'' (or Path Traversal)?','A ways to find files in a folder','A vulnerability that allows an attacker to read arbitrary files on the server that is running an application','Deleting the folders','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Attackers use `../` patterns to move out of the intended folder and access sensitive OS files like `/etc/passwd`.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What which port is commonly used for ''SSH''?','80','22','443','21','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Secure Shell (SSH) is used for secure remote administration of systems.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What which port is commonly used for ''HTTPS''?','80','443','8080','22','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'HTTPS traffic is encrypted and typically served on port 443.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is an ''Open Redirect'' vulnerability?','A ways to name a user','When a web application accepts a user-controlled input that specifies a link to an external site, and uses that in a redirection','Deleting the URL','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Attackers use open redirects to make a link appear to go to a trusted site, when it actually goes to a phishing site.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What characterize ''Business Logic'' vulnerabilities?','Bugs in the code that make it slow','Flaws in the design and implementation of an application that allow an attacker to elicit unintended behavior (e.g. buying a $1000 item for $1)','Deleting the code','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Business logic flaws are hard for automated scanners to find and usually require manual penetration testing.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is ''Account Lockout'' policy?','A policy that deletes the account','A security feature that temporarily disables a user account after a pre-defined number of failed login attempts','A ways to name a user','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Lockout policies prevent brute-force attacks from trying thousands of passwords on a single account.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is ''File Integrity Monitoring'' (FIM)?','Checking if the file is pretty','A process that alerts when changes are made to critical system files or configurations','A tool to delete old files','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'FIM is a core security control to detect tampered systems after a breach.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is ''Perfect Forward Secrecy'' (PFS)?','Deleting the past','A security property of key agreement protocols that ensures that a session key will not be compromised even if the long-term private key is stolen later','A ways to name a key','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'PFS ensures that past encrypted communications cannot be decrypted even if the server key is later compromised.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is a ''Distroless'' image?','An image with no name','A container image that contains ONLY the application and its runtime dependencies, and nothing else (no shell, no package manager)','A image that is free to use','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Distroless images are the current ''Gold Standard'' for secure container deployments.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is ''Exploitability''?','A ways to sell a vulnerability','The measure of how easily a particular security vulnerability can be used by an attacker to gain unauthorized access or cause damage','A ways to delete code','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'High severity but zero exploitability (e.g. no network path) may lower the priority of a fix.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What characterizes ''Gray Box'' testing?','Testing only the colors of the app','Security testing where the evaluator has limited knowledge of the system (e.g. they have an account but not source code access)','A ways to delete logs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Gray box testing simulates an authenticated user attempting to escalate privileges.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is an ''ISMS''?','Internal Security Management Software','Information Security Management System: A systematic approach to managing sensitive company information','Internet Safety Monitoring Service','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'ISO/IEC 27001 is a leading international standard for an ISMS.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is a ''Rootkit''?','A ways to name a user','A collection of computer software designed to enable access to a computer or an area of its software that is not otherwise allowed, while masking its existence','A tool to delete old files','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Rootkits are very dangerous as they can hide from standard anti-virus and operating system tools.','pregenerated'),
('ed60bff1-55f9-49f0-bc82-043de4275811','What is ''Credential Stuffing''?','Eating the passwords','A type of attack where a large number of spilled credentials (username/password pairs) are automatically tried against a website','A ways to name a user','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'This attack relies on the fact that many users reuse the same password across multiple sites.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','In a DevSecOps pipeline, what is a ''Security Gate''?','A literal gate','An automated check (e.g. no High vulnerabilities allowed) that stops the pipeline if failed','A ways to delete pods','Naming the servers','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Security gates ensure that insecure code never reaches production.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is ''CVE''?','Common Visibility Entry','Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures: A list of publicly disclosed cybersecurity vulnerabilities','Critical Vulnerability Engine','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'CVE IDs (e.g. CVE-2021-44228) are used to uniquely identify and track specific security flaws.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is the ''Shared Responsibility Model'' in cloud computing?','The cloud provider is responsible for everything','Security ''of'' the cloud is the provider''s responsibility; security ''in'' the cloud is the customer''s responsibility','The customer is responsible for everything','Nobody is responsible','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Customers must still secure their data, apps, and OS even when using a managed cloud platform.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is ''Identity Federation''?','A ways to delete users','Sharing identity information across multiple trust domains (e.g. logging into an app using a Google account)','Naming the users','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Federation (using protocols like SAML or OIDC) simplifies access management across different systems.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is the ''OWASP Top 10''?','Top 10 developers','A standard awareness document for developers and web application security, listing the most critical web security risks','A list of 10 hackers','A ways to delete code','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'OWASP Top 10 includes risks like SQL Injection, Broken Access Control, and SSRF.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is ''Golden Image'' in the context of server deployment?','An image made of gold','A pre-configured, hardened, and tested server template used for deploying all new instances','A ways to name a server','A ways to delete a server','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Using golden images ensures consistency and security across the entire infrastructure fleet.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is ''mTLS'' (Mutual TLS)?','A ways to speed up the internet','A protocol where BOTH the client and server present certificates to verify each other''s identity','A ways to delete messages','Naming the servers','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'mTLS is commonly used in service meshes (like Istio) to provide zero-trust security between microservices.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is ''Threat Modeling''?','A ways to predict the weather','A proactive process for identifying, quantifying, and addressing potential security threats to an application or system','Deleting the code','Naming the pods','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Threat modeling (e.g. using the STRIDE model) helps teams design more secure systems from the start.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What characterizes ''Asymmetric Encryption'' (Public Key Cryptography)?','Using the same key for encryption and decryption','Using a pair of keys (Public and Private); data encrypted with the public key can only be decrypted by the private key','A ways to speed up encryption','Deleting the keys','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Asymmetric encryption (e.g. RSA) allows for secure communication without needing to share a secret key beforehand.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is an ''SSID'' vulnerability in the context of cloud IAM?','A ways to name a user','A vulnerability in cross-account role assumption (Confused Deputy problem in AWS)','A wireless network flaw','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Securing cross-account resource access is a complex but vital part of cloud security.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is ''SIEM'' (Security Information and Event Management)?','A ways to speed up the logs','A system that collects, correlates, and analyzes logs from many sources to detect security threats in real-time','A tool to delete servers','Naming the pods','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'SIEM tools (like Splunk or ELK with security) help teams find needles in the haystack of log data.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is the purpose of ''Security Champions'' in a DevSecOps model?','To win security competitions','To act as security advocates within development teams, bridging the gap between developers and the security department','To delete old code','Naming the files','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Security champions help scale security expertise by empowering developers to handle everyday security tasks.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What characterizes ''Zero Trust'' architecture?','Trusting everyone in the building','Never trust, always verify: Assuming that the network is already compromised and requiring verification for every request','Deleting the network','Naming the users','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Zero Trust moves security from the perimeter (firewalls) to the individual resource and identity.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is an ''APT'' (Advanced Persistent Threat)?','A very fast virus','A prolonged and targeted cyberattack where intruders gain access to a network and remain undetected for a long time','Deleting the database','Naming the pods','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'APTs are often state-sponsored or highly organized groups looking for long-term data theft.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is ''Secret Rotation''?','Turning the server around','The practice of periodically changing passwords and API keys to limit the amount of time an attacker can use a stolen secret','Deleting the secrets','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Automation is key to frequent secret rotation without breaking applications.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is an ''SBOM'' (Software Bill of Materials)?','A list of developers on a project','A formal, structured record of all components, libraries, and dependencies used in building a piece of software','A ways to name a user','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'SBOMs are essential for tracking which applications are affected when a new vulnerability (like Log4Shell) is discovered in a common library.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What does the ''SLSA'' (Supply-chain Levels for Software Artifacts) framework aim to prevent?','Slow build times','Tampering with software artifacts throughout the build and deployment process by providing a set of incremental security levels','Deleting old code','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'SLSA focuses on provenance and integrity of the build pipeline itself (e.g. preventing unauthenticated code from being injected).','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is ''Rego'' in the context of security policy?','A ways to name a user','A query language used by Open Policy Agent (OPA) to write fine-grained, declarative policies for authorization','A tool to delete old servers','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Rego allows you to express complex rules like ''Users can only delete pods in their own namespace if they have the developer role''.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','How do ''Kubernetes NetworkPolicies'' differ from standard Cloud Security Groups?','NetworkPolicies are only for external traffic','NetworkPolicies allow you to control traffic at the IP address or port level for pod-to-pod communication within the cluster','Security groups are faster','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'NetworkPolicies implement the ''micro-segmentation'' layer inside a Kubernetes cluster to enforce least privilege for networking.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is the purpose of ''Falco'' in a DevSecOps environment?','To speed up deployment','An open-source runtime security tool that detects anomalous activity (like a shell being spawned in a container) by monitoring system calls','A ways to name a server','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Falco provides real-time alerting for malicious behavior that occurs after a container has already been deployed.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What characterizes ''SSRF'' (Server-Side Request Forgery)?','A ways to delete a server','A vulnerability that allows an attacker to induce the server-side application to make HTTP requests to an arbitrary domain of the attacker''s choosing','A tool to name a user','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'SSRF is often used to attack internal services that are not directly exposed to the internet, such as a cloud metadata service (169.254.169.254).','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is a ''Dynamic Secret'' in HashiCorp Vault?','A secret that changes colors','A secret generated on-demand that is unique to a client and has a specific lease duration, being automatically revoked when the lease expires','A ways to name a user','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Dynamic secrets minimize the risk of leaked credentials because they don''t exist until requested and are short-lived.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is ''Homomorphic Encryption''?','Encrypting the same thing twice','An encryption scheme that allows computations to be performed on ciphertext, generating an encrypted result which, when decrypted, matches the result of the operations performed on the plain text','A ways to delete old keys','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'This allows for data processing by third parties without them ever seeing the underlying plain text data.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What characterizes ''Immutable Infrastructure'' from a security perspective?','It cannot be hacked','The practice of replacing old servers with new ones (from a fresh image) for every change, ensuring that unauthorized changes made by attackers are wiped out regularly','Servers that have no storage','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Immutable infrastructure prevents ''configuration drift'' and makes it harder for an attacker to maintain persistence on a machine.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is ''OIDC'' (OpenID Connect)?','A protocol for connecting printers','An identity layer on top of the OAuth 2.0 protocol that allows clients to verify the identity of the end-user based on the authentication performed by an Authorization Server','A ways to delete old users','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'While OAuth is for authorization (access), OIDC is for authentication (identity).','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is an ''Admission Controller'' in Kubernetes?','A ways to name a user','A piece of code that intercepts requests to the Kubernetes API server prior to persistence of the object, potentially validating or mutating the request based on security policy','A tool to delete old nodes','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Admission controllers (like PodSecurityPolicy successor or OPA Gatekeeper) are the ultimate gatekeepers for cluster security.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is the risk of excessive ''Verbosity'' in production error messages?','It makes the logs too big','It can reveal sensitive internal system details (like stack traces or DB structure) that help an attacker craft a more targeted exploit','It''s illegal','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Production apps should return generic error messages to users while logging detailed errors internally.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What characterizes ''CSPM'' (Cloud Security Posture Management)?','A ways to name a cloud','Automated tools that continuously monitor cloud environments for security misconfigurations and compliance violations (e.g. open S3 buckets)','A tool to delete old clusters','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'CSPMs help prevent ''accidental'' exposure caused by complex cloud permission systems.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is a ''Confused Deputy'' attack?','Tricking a manager','A security issue where an entity that doesn''t have permission to perform an action can coerce a more privileged entity (the deputy) to perform the action for it','A ways to delete a user','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'In AWS, the ''ExternalID'' condition is used to prevent the confused deputy problem in cross-account service access.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is ''Dependency Confusion'' (or Namespace Confusion)?','Forgetting the name of a library','An attack where a malicious package with the same name as an internal private package is published to a public repository (e.g. npm), tricking package managers into downloading the malicious version','Deleting the dependencies','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'This attack relies on how build tools prioritize public registries over private ones if not configured correctly.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What characterizes ''Insecure Deserialization''?','Deleting the data','When an application untrusted data and uses it to recreate an object, allowing an attacker to inject malicious code (RCE) or escalate privileges','A ways to name a user','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Deserialization vulnerabilities are extremely dangerous and common in languages like Java, .NET, and Python.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is ''Clickjacking'' (UI Redressing)?','Stealing a mouse','An attack that tricks a user into clicking something different from what the user perceives they are clicking, often using hidden layers or iframes','A ways to delete code','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'The ''X-Frame-Options'' header and ''CSP frame-ancestors'' are used to prevent clickjacking by restricting where a page can be iframed.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is ''Log Injection''?','Writing more logs','An attack where invalid or malicious data is inserted into logs to mislead investigators or corrupt log processing systems','A ways to name a user','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Attackers can use log injection to hide their tracks or exploit vulnerabilities in log analysis software (like Log4Shell).','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is a ''Supply Chain Attack''?','Hacking the trucks','A cyberattack that targets less secure elements in the software development and distribution supply chain (e.g. build systems, updates, dependencies) to infect the final product','Deleting the code','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'The SolarWinds and Kaseya attacks are famous examples where a trusted update was used to distribute malware.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What characterizes ''Polymorphic'' malware?','Malware that can delete itself','Malware that constantly changes its identifiable features (e.g. its own code or encryption keys) to evade detection by signature-based anti-virus','A ways to name a file','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Polymorphism makes malware very difficult to block using traditional static analysis tools.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is ''Forensic Data Capture''?','Writing down what happened','The act of preserving and collecting data (like RAM dumps or disk images) in a way that is admissible in court and ensures it hasn''t been tampered with','A ways to delete logs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Proper forensics is vital for identifying the root cause of an attack and holding attackers accountable.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What characterizes ''KMS'' (Key Management Service) envelope encryption?','Putting the keys in a paper envelope','Using a master key (CMK) to encrypt data-encryption keys (DEKs) which are then used to encrypt the actual data','Deleting old keys','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Envelope encryption allows you to encrypt large amounts of data without sending the actual data to the KMS service.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is ''SSTI'' (Server-Side Template Injection)?','A ways to name a user','When an attacker is able to use native template syntax to inject a malicious payload into a template, which is then executed on the server','A tool to delete old templates','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'SSTI can lead to full remote code execution on the server by leveraging the template engine''s power.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What characterizes ''Insecure Direct Object References'' (IDOR)?','A bug in the object orientation','A type of access control vulnerability where an application uses user-supplied input to access objects directly (e.g. changing the `id` in the URL to see someone else''s profile)','Deleting the objects','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'The fix for IDOR is checking authorization for every requested object, never trusting the ID provided by the user.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is ''DLP'' (Data Loss Prevention)?','A ways to name a user','A set of tools and processes used to ensure that sensitive data is not lost, misused, or accessed by unauthorized users, particularly identifying data that might leave the corporate network','A tool to delete logs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'DLP tools scan outgoing traffic (email, web, USB) for patterns like credit card numbers or internal watermarks.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is an ''Evil Twin'' attack?','Tricking your sibling','A fraudulent Wi-Fi access point that appears to be a legitimate one offered on the premises, but is set up to eavesdrop on wireless communications','Deleting the router','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Evil twin attacks are a form of Man-in-the-Middle attack often found in public places like coffee shops.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is ''Non-repudiation''?','A ways to delete a user','The assurance that someone cannot deny the validity of something (e.g. a signed transaction or log entry)','A ways to name a user','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Digital signatures are the primary mechanism for ensuring non-repudiation in electronic transactions.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is ''Token Binding''?','Tying the computer with a rope','A security property that cryptographically binds a session token to the underlying TLS connection, preventing ''token theft'' from being useful on another machine','A ways to name a user','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'If an attacker steals a bound token, they cannot use it because they don''t have the private key associated with the original client''s connection.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is ''Dynamic Analysis Security Testing'' (DAST) on APIs?','Reading the API code','Interacting with the running API by sending it various payloads (including malicious ones) to observe its response and identify runtime flaws','A tool to delete the API','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'DAST for APIs often requires a ''swaggar'' or ''openapi'' definition to know what endpoints to fuzz.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What characterizes ''Micro-segmentation'' in a cloud network?','Using smaller subnets','A security technique that enables granular security policies to be assigned to individual workloads (pods/instances) to limit lateral movement within a data center','A ways to name a server','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Micro-segmentation is a core part of a zero-trust network strategy.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is ''Runtime Application Self-Protection'' (RASP)?','A ways to speed up the code','Security technology that is built into an application (or its runtime) that can control application execution and detect and block real-time attacks','A ways to name a user','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'RASP can see the ''context'' of an attack from inside the app, allowing for very low false-positive rates compared to a WAF.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is an ''Airdrop'' attack in a secure environment?','Dropping servers from a plane','A wireless attack where a malicious actor sends unauthorized files or data to a device via local wireless sharing protocols (like AirDrop or Nearby Share)','A ways to name a file','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Physical hardware proximity is a common vector for social engineering or malware injection in high-security zones.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What characterizes ''Side-Channel'' attacks?','Attacking the side of the building','An attack based on information gained from the implementation of a computer system, rather than weaknesses in the implemented algorithm itself (e.g. timing, power consumption, or electromagnetic leaks)','A ways to name a user','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Spectre and Meltdown are famous examples of side-channel attacks targeting CPU performance optimizations.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is ''Container Escape''?','When a container finishes its job','A vulnerability that allows an attacker to break out of the container''s isolation and gain access to the underlying host or other containers','A ways to name a pod','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Running containers as non-root and using Seccomp/AppArmor are key ways to prevent container escapes.','pregenerated'),
('01ca660b-3733-4e77-997c-b6e56b2580e9','What is a ''SOC'' (Security Operations Center)?','A ways to name a user','A centralized unit that deals with security issues on an organizational and technical level, containing people, processes, and technology','A tool to delete old servers','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'A SOC provides 24/7 monitoring and response to security threats.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is ''SSRF'' (Server-Side Request Forgery)?','A ways to name a server','A vulnerability where an attacker can trick a server into making unauthorized requests to internal or external systems on its behalf','A ways to delete a server','A ways to name a user','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'SSRF can be used to bypass firewalls and access internal metadata services (like AWS IMDS).','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is ''OPA'' (Open Policy Agent) used for?','A ways to name the pods','A general-purpose policy engine that enables unified, context-aware policy enforcement across the cloud-native stack','Deleting the database','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'OPA uses a language called ''Rego'' to define policies like ''who can access which API'' or ''what container images are allowed''.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What characterizes ''Post-Quantum Cryptography''?','Cryptography that only works on quantum computers','Cryptographic algorithms that are thought to be secure against an attack by a quantum computer','Deleting old keys','Naming the keys','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'With the rise of quantum computing, mathematicians are developing new algorithms (like lattice-based cryptography) that current quantum attacks can''t break.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is the ''Implicit Flow'' in OAuth 2.0 and why is it now discouraged?','It''s too slow','A flow where the access token is returned directly in the URL fragment, making it vulnerable to interception; PKCE is now preferred','It''s for robots only','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Implicit flow (common in old SPAs) lacks security features like single-use authorization codes or client secrets.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What does ''Egress Filtering'' mean in a secure network design?','Filtering traffic coming INTO the network','Controlling and monitoring traffic LEAVING the network to prevent data exfiltration and communication with C2 servers','Deleting the gateway','Naming the routers','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Egress filtering is a vital part of defense-in-depth; many servers should never need to talk to the public internet.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is a ''Rootkit''?','A ways to delete the root directory','A collection of software tools that help an attacker mask their presence on a compromised system, often by modifying the OS kernel','A tool to name the root user','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Rootkits are extremely difficult to detect because they subvert the very tools (like `ls` or `ps`) used to find them.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is ''Differential Privacy''?','Using different passwords','A mathematical framework for sharing information about a dataset by injecting ''noise'' to protect the privacy of individual entries','Deleting private data','Naming the data fields','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Differential privacy allows researchers to get accurate summary statistics without revealing anything about specific individuals in the data.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is ''Formjacking''?','Stealing a physical form','The use of malicious JavaScript code to steal credit card details and other information from payment forms on e-commerce websites','Deleting the form','Naming the fields','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Formjacking is a type of supply chain attack (like the British Airways breach) where third-party scripts are compromised.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is an ''SBOM'' (Software Bill of Materials) and why is it vital for DevSecOps?','A list of developers','A formal, machine-readable inventory of all components and dependencies in a software product, allowing for rapid vulnerability tracking','A ways to delete old versions','Naming the files','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Executive orders and modern security standards now require SBOMs to ensure transparency in the software supply chain.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is ''Runtime Security'' (e.g. Falco)?','Security that runs very fast','Monitoring system calls and behavior in real-time to detect anomalous or malicious activity (like a shell being spawned in a pod)','Deleting the app','Naming the pods','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Runtime security provides the final layer of defense, catching attacks that bypassed all previous gates.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What characterizes ''FIDO2 / WebAuthn'' authentication?','It uses passwords','Standardized passwordless authentication using public-key cryptography (e.g. Yubikey or Biometrics) to prevent phishing','It''s the second version of Fido','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'FIDO2 is considered the pinnacle of authentication security today, as it is immune to most credential theft attacks.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is ''Side-Channel Attack''?','Attacking the side of the server','An attack based on information gained from the physical implementation of a computer system (e.g. power consumption, timing, or electromagnetic leaks) rather than the software','Deleting the app','Naming the users','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Side-channel attacks (like Spectre or Meltdown) can leak high-value secrets like encryption keys.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is ''Purple Teaming''?','A team that wears purple','A collaborative security exercise where Red Teams (attackers) and Blue Teams (defenders) work together to improve detection and response','Deleting the database','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Purple teaming maximizes the learning from security exercises by breaking the ''adversarial'' wall between teams.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is ''Dependency Confusion''?','Being confused about libraries','A type of attack where a hacker publishes a malicious package with the same name as an internal library to a public registry, tricking the build system','Deleting the repo','Naming the packages','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Dependency confusion exploits the priority order of package managers (like npm or pip) to inject malicious code into trusted builds.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is ''Homomorphic Encryption''?','Encryption for identical users','A type of encryption that allows computation to be performed on encrypted data without ever decrypting it first','Deleting the keys','Naming the data','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Homomorphic encryption is the ''holy grail'' of data privacy, allowing cloud services to process sensitive data without seeing it.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is ''SLSA'' (Supply-chain Levels for Software Artifacts)?','A ways to name a user','A security framework, a check-list of standards and controls to prevent tampering, improve integrity, and secure packages and infrastructure','A ways to delete a server','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'SLSA (pronounced ''salsa'') provides a common language for software producers and consumers to discuss artifact security.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is the primary security benefit of using ''Distroless'' images?','They are free','They contain only your application and its runtime dependencies, omitting shells, package managers, and other tools an attacker could use','They are faster to download','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Reducing the attack surface to the bare minimum is a core principle of container hardening.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What characterizes ''Immutable Infrastructure''?','Infrastructure that never crashes','Components that are replaced rather than updated in-place; every change is a fresh deployment from a versioned image','Infrastructure with no internet access','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Immutability prevents ''configuration drift'' and ensures that any malicious unauthorized changes are wiped out on the next deploy.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is the ''Confused Deputy'' problem in cloud IAM?','A manager who forgot their password','A security issue where an entity that does not have permission to perform an action can coerce a more-privileged entity to perform the action for it','A system where all users are admins','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'This often occurs in cross-account service access; AWS uses the ''ExternalID'' parameter to mitigate this specific risk.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is ''IDP'' (Identity Provider) Federation?','A ways to name a user','A system that allows users to use a single set of credentials (SSO) to access applications across different trust domains or organizations','A tool to delete old users','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Federation (using protocols like SAML or OIDC) centralizes identity and reduces the risk of password fatigue.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','How does ''eBPF'' (Extended Berkeley Packet Filter) technology aid in modern security monitoring?','By making the internet faster','By allowing programs to run in the kernel without changing kernel source code, providing deep visibility into system calls, networking, and security events','By deleting the logs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Tools like Falco and Cilium use eBPF for high-performance, low-overhead security observability in Kubernetes.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is a ''Zero-Knowledge Proof'' (ZKP)?','Proving you know nothing','A cryptographic method by which one party can prove to another party that a given statement is true, without conveying any information apart from the fact that the statement is true','A ways to name a user','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'ZKP allows for privacy-preserving authentication, such as proving you are over 18 without revealing your birth date.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What characterizes ''Reachability Analysis'' in SCA (Software Composition Analysis)?','Checking if the server is online','Techniques to determine if a vulnerable function within a library is actually accessible and executable by the application code','A ways to delete code','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Reachability reduces developer ''alert fatigue'' by highlighting vulnerabilities that are truly exploitable in context.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What does ''SOC 2 Type II'' certification verify?','The physical security of the office','The effectiveness of an organization''s security controls over a period of time (usually 6-12 months)','A ways to name a user','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Type I tests design at a point in time; Type II tests operating effectiveness over a duration.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is the ''FedRAMP'' program?','A ways to name a user','A US government-wide program that provides a standardized approach to security assessment, authorization, and continuous monitoring for cloud products and services','A tool to delete old servers','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'FedRAMP is mandatory for any cloud provider selling to US federal agencies.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What characterizes ''SOAR'' in a security operations center?','Flying above the clouds','Security Orchestration, Automation, and Response: technologies that enable organizations to collect inputs and respond to low-level security events automatically','A tool to delete old code','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'SOAR reduces manual labor for SOC analysts by automating repetitive tasks like IP blocking or ticket creation.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What characterizes ''Micro-segmentation'' in a cloud network?','Using smaller subnets','The practice of dividing a network into small, distinct security segments down to the individual workload level, with specific security controls for each','A ways to name a user','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Micro-segmentation prevents lateral movement by attackers within a data center or cloud VPC.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What identifies ''Hardware Security Modules'' (HSM)?','A physical box to hide the computer','Physical computing devices that safeguard and manage digital keys, perform encryption/decryption, and digital signatures','A ways to name a user','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'HSMs are designed to be tamper-evident and tamper-resistant, providing the highest level of key protection.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is ''Insecure Deserialization'' in the OWASP Top 10?','Deleting the data','A vulnerability that occurs when untrusted data is used to abuse the logic of an application, leading to Remote Code Execution (RCE) or privilege escalation','A ways to name a user','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Deserialization bugs often allow attackers to re-instantiate malicious objects that perform unauthorized actions on the server.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is a ''SOC 1'' report primarily concerned with?','Security of the system','Internal controls over financial reporting (ICFR) at a service organization','A tool to delete old servers','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'SOC 1 is for financial audits; SOC 2 is for security, availability, and privacy audits.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What characterizes ''IAST'' (Interactive Application Security Testing)?','Reading the code','A technology that monitors application execution and identifies vulnerabilities in real-time by combining elements of both static and dynamic analysis','A tool to delete code','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'IAST runs inside the application (like an agent) and has access to the code, HTTP traffic, and library info simultaneously.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is ''Attestation'' in the context of trusted computing?','A ways to name a user','The process of providing proof to a third party that a piece of hardware or software is in a specific, trusted state','A tool to delete old servers','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Remote attestation is often used to verify that a cloud server is running a genuine, untampered operating system.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is ''Business Logic'' vulnerability?','A bug that makes the app slow','A flaw in the design and implementation of an application that allows an attacker to elicit unintended behavior by manipulating the app''s workflow','A ways to delete code','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Examples include skipping a payment step or applying a discount code multiple times in ways the developers didn''t intend.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What characterizes ''DPI'' (Deep Packet Inspection)?','Buying a better monitor','A method of network packet filtering that examines the data part (and possibly the header) of a packet as it passes an inspection point','A ways to name a user','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'DPI allows firewalls to block specific application-level protocols or malware patterns hidden within standard traffic.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is ''Token Binding''?','Tying the user with a rope','A security property that cryptographically binds a security token (like a cookie or JWT) to the TLS connection between the client and server','A tool to delete old users','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Token binding prevents ''token theft'' attacks where an attacker steals a cookie to impersonate a user from a different machine.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is ''Defense in Depth''?','Digging a deep hole around the server','An information security strategy that uses multiple layers of security controls throughout an IT system to protect data','A tool to delete old servers','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'If one layer (e.g. firewall) is breached, others (e.g. MFA, encryption) should still prevent a total compromise.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is ''Vulnerability Chaining''?','A ways to name a user','The practice of using multiple low-severity or medium-severity vulnerabilities together to achieve a high-impact exploit','A tool to delete old code','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'A minor info leak combined with a session flaw might lead to full account takeover.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What defines ''Cloud-Native Security'' (4Cs)?','Computer, Cloud, Code, Cookies','Cloud, Cluster, Container, and Code','Cloud, Case, Center, Command','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Security must be applied at all four layers to truly protect a cloud-native application.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is ''Policy-as-Code'' (PaC)?','Writing laws in a document','The practice of managing and enforcing security and compliance policies through code, allowing for automated testing and deployment','A tool to delete old users','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'PaC ensures that infrastructure is automatically checked against standards (like CIS Benchmarks) before ever reaching production.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What characterizes ''Broken Access Control'' in modern applications?','A broken keyboard','Failures that allow users to access functionality or data outside of their intended permissions (e.g. IDOR or horizontal privilege escalation)','A tool to delete code','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'This is currently the #1 vulnerability in the OWASP Top 10 list.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is ''MFA Fatigue'' (MFA Push Spam)?','Being tired of using a password','An attack where the attacker sends numerous MFA push notifications to a user''s device, hoping the user will eventually click ''Approve'' out of annoyance or error','A tool to delete old accounts','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Defense against MFA fatigue includes using ''number matching'' where the user must type a code shown on the screen.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What characterizes ''HSTS'' (HTTP Strict Transport Security)?','A ways to speed up the internet','A server-side header that tells browsers to ONLY interact with that domain using HTTPS, preventing SSL stripping attacks','A tool to delete old images','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'HSTS ensures that even if a user types `http://`, the browser will automatically upgrade the connection to `https://`.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is ''Masking'' vs ''Tokenization''?','They are the same thing','Masking hides part of the data (e.g. ****-1234); Tokenization replaces sensitive data with a non-sensitive ''token'' that has no value if stolen','A tool to delete old files','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Tokenization is superior for PCI compliance as it removes sensitive data from the environment entirely.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is ''Mutation Testing'' for security?','Changing the color of the app','A technique where small ''mutations'' (changes) are introduced into the code to verify if existing security tests are powerful enough to catch the ''bugs''','A ways to delete code','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Mutation testing measures the ''quality'' of your security test suite, not just the code itself.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is the ''Kernel'' of an Operating System from a security perspective?','A ways to name a user','The core program that has complete control over everything in the system; it is the most privileged part of the OS','A tool to delete old servers','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Vulnerabilities in the kernel (like ''Privilege Escalation'') are the most dangerous as they give an attacker total power.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What characterizes ''DRP'' (Disaster Recovery Planning)?','Planning how to hack','A documented process or set of procedures to execute an organization''s response to an unplanned incident that threatens its IT infrastructure','A tool to delete old servers','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'DRP includes ''RTO'' (Recovery Time Objective) and ''RPO'' (Recovery Point Objective) goals.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What defines ''Entropy'' in cryptographic key generation?','The color of the key','The randomness or unpredictability of the source data used to create the absolute strength of a key','A tool to delete old keys','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Low entropy (predictability) allows attackers to guess private keys, even for strong algorithms like RSA or AES.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What characterizes ''GraphQL Introspection'' security risk?','Faster queries','A feature that allows anyone to query the API for its entire schema (queries, mutations, types), which helps attackers map out the internal data structure','A ways to delete old tables','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Introspection should be disabled in production to prevent information disclosure about the internal API design.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is an ''Attestation of Compliance'' (AOC)?','A ways to name a user','A formal document that summarizes the results of an organization''s assessment against a specific standard (like PCI DSS or HIPAA)','A tool to delete old servers','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The AOC is the final proof provided to customers or partners that an audit was successful.','pregenerated'),
('d9fdb125-40ad-4c6c-8ee6-038cc205bf7f','What is ''Steganography''?','Writing code in stone','The practice of concealing a file, message, image, or video within another file, message, image, or video','A tool to delete old files','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Unlike encryption (which is obvious that data is hidden), steganography hides the very fact that communication is occurring.','pregenerated')
