('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','What is the bit-width of the 8085 microprocessor?','4-bit','8-bit','16-bit','32-bit','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'The Intel 8085 is an 8-bit general-purpose microprocessor.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','Which register in the 8085 is also known as the ''Accumulator''?','Register B','Register C','Register A','Register L','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Register A is the accumulator where most arithmetic and logical operations store their results.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','In the 8085 flag register, which flag is set if the result of an operation is zero?','S (Sign)','Z (Zero)','P (Parity)','CY (Carry)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'The Zero flag bit is 1 if the ALU result is zero, and 0 otherwise.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','Which of these are the control signals produced by the 8085?','RD (Read)','WR (Write)','ALE (Address Latch Enable)','CLK OUT','["A","B","C"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',40,'RD, WR, and ALE are key control signals for memory and I/O access.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','The 8085 has how many 16-bit registers?','0','2 (PC and SP)','6 (B, C, D, E, H, L)','1 (Accumulator)','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'While it''s an 8-bit processor, the Program Counter (PC) and Stack Pointer (SP) are 16 bits long to address 64KB of memory.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','What is the total addressable memory space of the 8085?','16 KB','64 KB','1 MB','4 GB','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'With a 16-bit address bus, 2^16 = 65,536 bytes (64 KB) can be addressed.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','What is the function of the ALE pin in 8085?','To clear the accumulator','To de-multiplex the address/data bus (AD0-AD7)','To signal an interrupt','To provide a clock signal','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'ALE (Address Latch Enable) is used to capture the lower 8 bits of the address from the multiplexed AD bus.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','Which of these is the non-maskable interrupt in 8085?','INTR','RST 7.5','TRAP','RST 5.5','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'TRAP is the highest priority non-maskable interrupt in the 8085.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','How many 8-bit general purpose registers are there in the 8085 (excluding A)?','4','6','8','10','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The 6 general-purpose registers are B, C, D, E, H, and L.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','Which pin is used to enter into a Wait state?','READY','HOLD','HLDA','INTR','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The READY pin is used to synchronize the microprocessor with slower peripherals by adding wait states.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','What does the ''MVI'' instruction stand for?','Move Value Indirect','Move Immediate','Move Variable Integer','Multiplication Value','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'MVI A, 32H moves the 8-bit value 32H directly into the Accumulator.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','If IO/M is high and RD is low, what operation is being performed?','Memory Read','I/O Read','Memory Write','I/O Write','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'IO/M'' high selects I/O; RD'' low selects Read.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','Which register is automatically incremented or decremented whenever the stack is used?','Program Counter','Stack Pointer','H-L Register Pair','Accumulator','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'The Stack Pointer (SP) tracks the top of the stack in memory.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','What is the typical supply voltage for an 8085 microprocessor?','3.3 V','+5 V','12 V','1.8 V','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The standard Intel 8085 operates on a single +5V DC power supply.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','What are the multiplexed lines in 8085?','AD0-AD7','A8-A15','D0-D7','ALE and WR','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'AD0-AD7 are used for both the lower 8 bits of the address and the 8 bits of data.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','Which flag is affected by the auxiliary carry from bit 3 to bit 4?','CY','AC','Z','S','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The Auxiliary Carry (AC) flag is used internally for BCD arithmetic instructions like DAA.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','How many bits is the Program Counter (PC) in 8085?','8 bits','16 bits','20 bits','32 bits','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The PC is 16 bits to store the address of the next instruction in memory.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','Which pin is used by a DMA controller to request control of the bus?','INTR','HOLD','READY','RESET IN','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'A master peripheral like a DMA controller places a high signal on the HOLD pin.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','What is the vector address for the TRAP interrupt?','0024H','0034H','003CH','002CH','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'TRAP (RST 4.5) has a vector address of 0024H.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','Which register pair is commonly used as a memory pointer?','BC','DE','HL','AF','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'The HL register pair holds the 16-bit address for ''M'' (Memory) operand operations.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','Instruction ''STA 2000H'' performs which action?','Stores the content of Accumulator at address 2000H','Loads the Accumulator with content of 2000H','Adds 2000H to Accumulator','Jumps to 2000H','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'STA stands for Store Accumulator Direct.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','How many T-states are required for an Opcode Fetch machine cycle in a standard 8085 instruction?','3','4','6','10','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'The opcode fetch cycle typically takes 4 T-states (T1, T2, T3, T4).','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','Which pins are used for serial data transmission in 8085?','RD and WR','SID and SOD','AD0 and AD1','INTR and INTA','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'SID (Serial Input Data) and SOD (Serial Output Data) are dedicated pins for simple serial communication.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','What does a ''Machine Cycle'' represent?','The time required to fetch and execute one instruction','The time required to complete one operation of accessing memory or I/O','The speed of the clock','One clock pulse','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'An instruction is composed of one or more machine cycles.','pregenerated'),
