('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','Which interrupt is level-triggered only in 8085?','RST 7.5','INTR','TRAP','RST 6.5','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'INTR is a maskable, level-triggered interrupt.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','The instruction ''HLT'' in 8085 signifies:','Halt the processor execution','High level trigger','Handle logical truth','Hold lightning fast transfers','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'HLT stops the CPU until an interrupt or reset occurs.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','Which assembly pseudo-code directive is used to define the starting address of a program?','START','ORG (Origin)','EQU','DB','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'ORG 2000H tells the assembler to place the subsequent code starting at memory address 2000H.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','What is the status of IO/M, S1, and S0 for the ''Opcode Fetch'' cycle?','0, 1, 1','1, 1, 1','0, 0, 1','0, 1, 0','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'For Opcode Fetch: IO/M=0 (Memory), S1=1, S0=1.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','Is 8085 Little-Endian or Big-Endian in its multibyte memory storage?','Big-Endian','Little-Endian','Middle-Endian','Doesn''t use bytes','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The 8085 stores the lower byte at the lower address and the higher byte at the higher address.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','Which bus is unidirectional in 8085?','Data Bus','Address Bus','Control Bus','System Bus','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'The address bus only flows from the CPU to external memory/IO.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','Which instruction is used for BCD adjustment of a result after addition?','ANA','DAA','CMA','RAR','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'DAA (Decimal Adjust Accumulator) converts the binary result in the accumulator to BCD format.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','The sequence ''Fetch, Decode, Execute'' is called:','Machine Cycle','Instruction Cycle','T-State','Clock Pulse','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'This is the complete process of processing a single instruction.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','Where is the result of an ''ADD B'' instruction stored?','Register B','Accumulator','Stack','Memory Pointed by HL','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'Register A (Accumulator) is the default destination for arithmetic operations.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','Which instruction complements (inverts) the bits of the Accumulator?','CMA','CMC','ANA','ORI','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'CMA (Complement Accumulator) performs a 1''s complement of the data in A.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','The 8085 can address how many I/O ports?','64','256','1024','65536','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'With an 8-bit port address bus (A0-A7 used for I/O), it can access 2^8 = 256 ports.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','What happens when RESET IN'' is low?','Program starts from 0000H','PC is cleared to 0000H','Interrupts are disabled','All of the above','["D"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Reseting the processor initializes the PC and various internal states.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','What is the status of RD and WR signals during the ''Bus Idle'' state?','Both Low','Both High','RD Low, WR High','RD High, WR Low','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Since these are active-low signals, they stay high when inactive.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','Which instruction is used to move data between two registers?','MOV Rd, Rs','MVI R, data','LXI Rp, d16','LDA addr','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'MOV B, C copies the content of register C to register B.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','The Flag register in 8085 is an 8-bit register, but how many bits are actually used?','4','5','8','3','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'The five flags are S, Z, AC, P, and CY.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','What is the purpose of the ''Clock Generator''?','To keep track of actual time','To provide the master timing signal for all internal operations','To count the number of instructions','To manage interrupts','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'An external crystal oscillator is connected to X1 and X2 pins.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','The ''Wait State'' is added during which T-state?','Between T1 and T2','Between T2 and T3','After T4','Before T1','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'It is introduced between T2 and T3 to allow slow memory/I/O components to catch up.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','Does 8085 support floating point arithmetic natively?','Yes','No','Depends on the version','Only for addition','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'8085 only supports integer operations; floating point must be implemented in software.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','Instruction ''JMP 2500H'' is how many bytes long?','1','2','3','4','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Jump instructions are 3-byte instructions (1 for opcode, 2 for address).','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','Which interrupt has the lowest priority in 8085?','TRAP','INTR','RST 5.5','RST 0','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'TRAP is highest; INTR is the lowest priority interrupt.','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','In ''MOV A, M'', what does ''M'' represent?','Main memory','Contents of the memory location pointed to by HL register pair','Multiple registers','Middle bit','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'M is a virtual register that references memory address [HL].','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','Is the 8085 a RISC or CISC processor?','RISC','CISC','Neither','Both','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'8085 is a Complex Instruction Set Computer (CISC).','pregenerated'),
('bd69ebef-0058-42c2-a655-48f9362a41b2','Instruction ''XRA A'' does what to the accumulator?','XORs A with A, clearing the accumulator','Adds A to A','Swaps high and low nibbles','Shifts A left','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Any value XOR''d with itself is 0, so XRA A is an efficient way to clear Register A and the carry flag.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','What is the addressing mode of the instruction: MVI A, 05H?','Register Addressing','Direct Addressing','Immediate Addressing','Implicit Addressing','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'In immediate addressing, the data (05H) is provided directly within the instruction.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','What does the instruction ''XCHG'' do in 8085?','Exchange the contents of registers A and B','Exchange the contents of HL pair with DE pair','Exchange the contents of PC and SP','XOR the Accumulator','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'XCHG swaps the 16-bit contents of the H-L register pair with the D-E register pair.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','In ''Register Indirect Addressing'', where is the address of the operand stored?','In the instruction itself','In a register pair (like HL)','In the program counter','On the stack','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Example: MOV A, M. Here ''M'' refers to the memory location pointed to by the HL register pair.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','Which of these are valid 8085 instructions?','ADD B','MOV A, C','SUB 25H','MULT D','["A","B"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',40,'8085 has ADD and SUB (SUB requires immediate or register), but it does NOT have a hardware multiplication (MULT) instruction.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','How many T-states are typically required for the ''Opcode Fetch'' machine cycle in 8085?','3','4','6','10','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',35,'Standard opcode fetch takes 4 T-states (T1-T4). Some complex instructions might take 6.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','What does ''SUI 05H'' do?','Subtracts 05H from register B','Subtracts 05H immediately from the Accumulator','Subs the carry to 5','Sets the stack pointer to 05H','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'SUI (Subtract Immediate) subtracts the 8-bit data from the Accumulator.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','Instruction ''LDAX B'' uses which addressing mode?','Register Addressing','Direct Addressing','Register Indirect Addressing','Immediate Addressing','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'LDAX B loads the Accumulator with the content of the memory address found in the BC register pair.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','The ''PUSH B'' instruction decrements the Stack Pointer (SP) by how many?','1','2','4','Depends on B','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'PUSH saves a register pair (16 bits total), so SP is decremented twice.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','Instruction ''CMP C'' updates which flags?','Only Z','Only CY','Z, CY, S, P, AC','None','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Compare (CMP) is essentially a subtraction that doesn''t store the result but sets all arithmetic flags.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','If Accumulator is 05H and ''CMP 05H'' is executed, what happens to the Zero flag?','Set (1)','Reset (0)','Invalidated','Toggled','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'05H - 05H results in 0, so the Zero flag becomes 1.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','Which instruction performs a jump only if the Carry flag is 0?','JC','JNC','JZ','JNZ','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'JNC stands for Jump on No Carry.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','How many machine cycles are in the ''CALL'' instruction?','2','3','5','1','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'CALL involves Opcode Fetch, 2 Memory Reads (target address), and 2 Memory Writes (saving PC to stack).','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','Instruction ''RAL'' shifts the accumulator contents which way?','Right through carry','Left through carry','Circular right','Circular left','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'RAL (Rotate Accumulator Left through carry) moves the MSB to Carry and Carry to LSB.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','What is the result of ''XRA A'' followed by ''INR A''?','00H','01H','FFH','Carry Set','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'XRA A clears A (A=0), and INR A increments it by 1.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','The ''EI'' instruction enables:','Only TRAP','Maskable interrupts','Non-maskable interrupts','DMA transfers','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'EI (Enable Interrupts) sets the internal interrupt flip-flop for maskable interrupts (RST 5.5, 6.5, 7.5, INTR).','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','Instruction ''LXI H, 3000H'' loads which values?','H = 30H, L = 00H','H = 00H, L = 30H','H = 30H, A = 00H','PC = 3000H','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'LXI (Load Register Pair Immediate) loads the 16-bit data into the pair.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','What instruction is used to read the current interrupt mask status?','SIM','RIM','EI','DI','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'RIM (Read Interrupt Mask) loads the Accumulator with interrupt status and SID pin status.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','Which instruction adds the contents of a register pair to the HL register pair?','ADD Rp','DAD Rp','ADC Rp','INR Rp','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'DAD (Double Add) performs 16-bit addition.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','The instruction ''POP PSW'' affects which registers?','Accumulator and Flags','Program Counter','HL pair','Accumulator only','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'PSW (Program Status Word) consists of the Accumulator and the Flag Register.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','What is the length of the ''LXI'' instruction?','1 byte','2 bytes','3 bytes','4 bytes','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'1 byte for opcode, 2 bytes for the 16-bit immediate data.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','In Memory-Mapped I/O, I/O devices are treated as:','Separate ports','Memory locations','Interrupts','Registers','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'I/O devices share the same 64KB address space as memory chips.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','For a ''Memory Write'' operation, IO/M and WR should be:','0 and 0','0 and 1','1 and 0','1 and 1','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'IO/M'' = 0 (Memory), WR'' = 0 (Write).','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','Instruction ''ORI 05H'' performs which logic?','AND Accumulator with 05H','Inclusive OR Accumulator with 05H','Exclusive OR Accumulator with 05H','Move and OR','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'ORI is OR Immediate.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','How many T-states are required for the ''MOV A, B'' instruction?','3','4','6','7','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'It only requires an Opcode Fetch cycle (4 T-states) as it is a register-to-register move.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','Which instruction is used at the end of a subroutine to return to the main program?','JMP','RET','HLT','END','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'RET (Return) pops the address from the stack into the Program Counter.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','Which flag is toggled by the ''STC'' instruction?','Zero','Carry','Sign','Parity','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'STC (Set Carry) explicitly sets the Carry flag to 1.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','What is the priority of ''RST 7.5'' relative to other maskable interrupts?','Highest among maskable','Lowest among maskable','Same as TRAP','Between RST 5.5 and RST 6.5','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Priorities: TRAP > RST 7.5 > RST 6.5 > RST 5.5 > INTR.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','What happens to the parity flag if the result of an operation has an even number of 1s?','Set to 1','Set to 0','Cleared to NULL','It remains unchanged','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'P=1 for even parity, P=0 for odd parity.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','Is the Stack Pointer initialized to a high address or low address usually?','High address','Low address','0000H always','Middle of RAM','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The stack grows downwards in memory from higher addresses to lower addresses.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','Instruction ''SPHL'' moves the contents of which register pair into the Stack Pointer?','BC','DE','HL','PSW','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'SPHL (Stack Pointer toward HL) sets SP = HL.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','How many machine cycles are in the ''INR M'' instruction?','1','2','3','4','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Opcode Fetch, Memory Read (data from [HL]), and Memory Write (updated data back to [HL]).','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','Instruction ''CPI 32H'' performs which operation?','Compares Accumulator with literal 32H','Compares register C with literal 32H','Complements Accumulator 32 times','Clears Parity if it''s 32H','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'CPI is Compare Immediate.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','The signal ALE is internally generated by the:','ALU','Interrupt controller','Control Unit','Bus interface','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'The control unit/timing unit produces ALE at the start of each machine cycle.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','Instruction ''SHLD 2000H'' stores:','Register S at 2000H','Register L at 2000H and H at 2001H','H at 2000H and L at 2001H','HL pair at address in register pair BC','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'SHLD (Store HL Direct) stores the low byte (L) at the given address and the high byte (H) at the next address.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','Which addressing mode uses the operand''s address directly in the instruction?','Register Addressing','Direct Addressing','Immediate Addressing','Register Indirect','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Example: LDA 3000H.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','What happens to the carry flag after ''ANA B''?','It is cleared (0)','It is set (1)','It is toggled','It remains unchanged','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Logical AND/OR/XOR instructions in 8085 clear the Carry flag.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','The hexadecimal value 0FH is equal to which binary?','0000 1111','1111 0000','1010 1010','1111 1111','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'F in hex is 15 dec, which is 1111 in binary.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','Which instruction is used to set the interrupt mask?','RIM','SIM','EI','DI','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'SIM (Set Interrupt Mask) uses the Accumulator content to mask/unmask RST interrupts.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','Which machine cycle is always the first cycle for any 8085 instruction?','Memory Read','Opcode Fetch','I/O Write','Bus Idle','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The CPU must first fetch the opcode to know what to do.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','Wait states are used to allow usage of slow:','CPUs','Memory/I/O devices','Cables','Flags','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The READY line is used to delay the bus cycle.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','Instruction ''RLC'' performs rotate accumulator left. Where does the MSB go?','To LSB only','To Carry only','To both LSB and Carry','It is lost','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'In RLC, the 7th bit shifts into the 0th bit position and also into the Carry flag.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','Instruction ''ADD M'' adds the content of which memory location to A?','The one pointed to by HL pair','The one pointed to by BC pair','The one at address 00H','Stack memory','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'M always refers to memory at [HL].','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','Which interrupt in 8085 is edge-triggered only?','RST 5.5','RST 7.5','INTR','RST 6.5','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'RST 7.5 is positive-edge triggered.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','How many T-states are required for the machine cycle: ''Memory Write''?','3','4','6','2','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Read/Write machine cycles take 3 T-states, while Opcode Fetch takes 4 (minimum).','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','What is the difference between JMP and CALL?','JMP saves no address; CALL saves return address on stack','JMP is faster','CALL is for errors only','They are exactly the same','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'CALL is used for subroutines so that the program can return.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','What is the result of ''A XOR A''?','0','A','1','FFH','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'Bits matched with themselves in XOR result in zero.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','For LXI H, 1234H, memory address HL+1 will contain:','12H','34H','00H','FFH','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'High byte 12H is stored in H, and L gets 34H (Little endian storage in memory if using SHLD, but register-wise H=High, L=Low).','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','Which flag is set if an addition result is larger than 8 bits?','Z','CY','S','P','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'The Carry (CY) flag captures the 9th bit overflow.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','Resetting the 8085 disables which interrupt mask?','TRAP','Only RST 7.5','All maskable interrupts','None','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Reset clears the interrupt enable flip-flops.','pregenerated'),
('0bda299f-4706-406b-90b1-484de1f33666','Instruction ''OUT 01H'' moves data from:','Accumulator to Port 01H','Memory to Port 01H','Port 01H to Accumulator','Register B to Port 01H','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'OUT is the standard way to send data from the Accumulator to an I/O device.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('7c4039ef-34c0-4e63-8d80-70a148e9706e','Which 8085 interrupt has the highest priority?','RST 7.5','TRAP','INTR','RST 5.5','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'TRAP is a non-maskable interrupt and has the highest priority in the 8085 system.','pregenerated'),
('7c4039ef-34c0-4e63-8d80-70a148e9706e','What is the function of the 8255 chip in a microprocessor system?','DMA Controller','Programmable Peripheral Interface (PPI)','Interrupt Controller','RAM expansion','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'The 8255 provides programmable I/O ports for connecting various peripherals to the processor.','pregenerated'),
('7c4039ef-34c0-4e63-8d80-70a148e9706e','In ''Memory Mapped I/O'', how is an I/O device accessed?','Using special IN and OUT instructions','As if it were a memory location, using standard data transfer instructions (like MOV, LDA)','By using a special bus','It cannot be accessed directly','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',40,'Memory-mapped I/O treats device registers as memory addresses, which simplifies the instruction set but consumes address space.','pregenerated'),
('7c4039ef-34c0-4e63-8d80-70a148e9706e','Which of the following are the port names in an 8255 PPI?','Port A','Port B','Port C','Port D','["A","B","C"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',35,'Internal architecture of 8255 contains three 8-bit ports: A, B, and C (Port C can be split into two 4-bit nibbles).','pregenerated'),
('7c4039ef-34c0-4e63-8d80-70a148e9706e','What is a ''Vectored'' interrupt in 8085 terminology?','An interrupt that points to a specific address in memory','An interrupt that can be masked','An interrupt used for graphics','A non-maskable interrupt only','[]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'RST 5.5, 6.5, 7.5 and TRAP are vectored because the CPU automatically jumps to a pre-defined vector address.','pregenerated'),
('7c4039ef-34c0-4e63-8d80-70a148e9706e','What is the function of the 8259 chip?','DMA Controller','Programmable Interrupt Controller (PIC)','Keyboard Controller','Timer/Counter','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The 8259 manages multiple interrupt requests and provides them to the CPU in a prioritized manner.','pregenerated'),
('7c4039ef-34c0-4e63-8d80-70a148e9706e','Which chip is used for Direct Memory Access (DMA)?','8251','8237','8255','8253','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The 8237 DMA controller allows peripherals to transfer data directly to/from memory without CPU intervention.','pregenerated'),
('7c4039ef-34c0-4e63-8d80-70a148e9706e','What is the 8251 chip commonly used for?','Parallel port','USART (Universal Synchronous Asynchronous Receiver Transmitter)','Interrupt management','Video processing','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'8251 facilitates serial communication between the microprocessor and peripherals.','pregenerated'),
('7c4039ef-34c0-4e63-8d80-70a148e9706e','The 8253/8254 chip is a:','Programmable Interrupt Controller','Programmable Interval Timer/Counter','DMA Controller','Display Controller','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'It contains three independent 16-bit counters for generating delays and measuring frequencies.','pregenerated'),
('7c4039ef-34c0-4e63-8d80-70a148e9706e','In 8255, what is the ''BSR'' mode used for?','Binary Status Register','Bit Set/Reset mode for Port C','Byte System Restore','Bus Service Request','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'BSR mode allows individual bits of Port C to be set or reset without affecting other bits.','pregenerated'),
