('03bd0f8d-1078-4007-b8a0-fbc27b48feb6','What is the data bus width and address bus width of the 8086 microprocessor?','8-bit data, 16-bit address','16-bit data, 20-bit address','16-bit data, 16-bit address','32-bit data, 32-bit address','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'8086 is a 16-bit processor (16-bit data) but has a 20-bit address bus to address 1 MB of memory.','pregenerated'),
('03bd0f8d-1078-4007-b8a0-fbc27b48feb6','How is a 20-bit physical address calculated in 8086 using segment and offset registers?','Segment + Offset','(Segment * 10H) + Offset','Segment * Offset','(Segment + Offset) * 16','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'The segment register is shifted left by 4 bits (multiplied by 16 or 10H) and then the offset is added to get the final address.','pregenerated'),
('03bd0f8d-1078-4007-b8a0-fbc27b48feb6','Which register is specifically used as a counter in loop and string operations in 8086?','AX','BX','CX','DX','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'CX stands for ''Count register'' and is the default counter for many complex instructions.','pregenerated'),
('03bd0f8d-1078-4007-b8a0-fbc27b48feb6','Which of these features exist in 8086 but NOT in 8085?','Pipelining (via instruction queue)','Memory Segmentation','Multiplexed address/data bus','Floating point unit on same chip','["A","B"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',40,'8086 introduced a 6-byte instruction queue (pipelining) and segmentation. Both use multiplexing. Early 8086 did NOT have an on-chip FPU.','pregenerated'),
('03bd0f8d-1078-4007-b8a0-fbc27b48feb6','The 8086 is divided into which two functional units?','Arithmetic Unit and Logic Unit','Execution Unit (EU) and Bus Interface Unit (BIU)','Input Unit and Output Unit','Control Unit and Memory Unit','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The BIU fetches instructions and data, while the EU executes them, allowing for a form of parallelism.','pregenerated'),
('03bd0f8d-1078-4007-b8a0-fbc27b48feb6','What are the four segment registers in the 8086?','AX, BX, CX, DX','CS, DS, SS, ES','BP, SP, SI, DI','IP, FLAGS, AL, BL','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'CS (Code Segment), DS (Data Segment), SS (Stack Segment), and ES (Extra Segment) are 16-bit registers that point to the start of memory segments.','pregenerated'),
('03bd0f8d-1078-4007-b8a0-fbc27b48feb6','In 8086, ''MOV AX, [BX + SI]'' is an example of which addressing mode?','Direct Addressing','Based Indexed Addressing','Register Indirect Addressing','Relative Addressing','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'It combines a base register (BX) and an index register (SI) to calculate the effective address.','pregenerated'),
('03bd0f8d-1078-4007-b8a0-fbc27b48feb6','How many flags are there in the 8086 flag register?','5','9','12','16','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'The 8086 has 9 active flags: 6 conditional flags (S, Z, AC, P, CY, O) and 3 control flags (I, D, T).','pregenerated'),
('03bd0f8d-1078-4007-b8a0-fbc27b48feb6','The instruction queue ''Pipelining'' in 8086 is used to:','Store more data','Fetch the next instruction while the current one is being executed','Protect the processor from heat','Increase the memory size','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Pipelining overlaps fetch and execute cycles, significantly increasing performance.','pregenerated'),
('03bd0f8d-1078-4007-b8a0-fbc27b48feb6','What does the ''MN/MX'' pin in 8086 determine?','Minimum or Maximum memory size','Minimum or Maximum operating mode (single vs multi-processor)','Frequency multiplier','Pin count','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'MN (Minimum) mode is for single-processor systems; MX (Maximum) mode is for multi-processor systems using a bus controller (8288).','pregenerated'),
('03bd0f8d-1078-4007-b8a0-fbc27b48feb6','What does the ''REP'' prefix do in 8086 string instructions?','Reports an error','Repeats the instruction CX number of times','Replaces a character','Restarts the program','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'REP (Repeat) is used with string operations like MOVS, STOS, etc., using CX as the counter.','pregenerated'),
('03bd0f8d-1078-4007-b8a0-fbc27b48feb6','How many bytes of space are occupied by the Interrupt Vector Table (IVT) in 8086?','256 bytes','1024 bytes','512 bytes','1 MB','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'The IVT has 256 entries, each 4 bytes long (2 for CS, 2 for IP) = 1024 bytes.','pregenerated'),
