('03bd0f8d-1078-4007-b8a0-fbc27b48feb6','A ''Far'' jump instruction changes which registers?','Only IP','Both CS and IP','Only AX','CS and DS','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'A near jump only changes IP; a far jump changes segments.','pregenerated'),
('03bd0f8d-1078-4007-b8a0-fbc27b48feb6','The BIU in 8086 handles:','Decoding','Fetching instructions and operand data','Arithmetic logic','Resetting flags','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Bus Interface Unit (BIU) communicates with memory and I/O.','pregenerated'),
('03bd0f8d-1078-4007-b8a0-fbc27b48feb6','Which 8086 register is called the ''Base'' register?','AX','BX','CX','DX','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'BX is the base register, often used as a pointer to data in the data segment.','pregenerated'),
('03bd0f8d-1078-4007-b8a0-fbc27b48feb6','What happens if a division operation results in a quotient that is too large for the destination register?','Result is truncated','Divide-by-zero (Type 0) interrupt is generated','Carry flag is set','Processor halts','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Division overflow in 8086 triggers an exception similar to dividing by zero.','pregenerated'),
('03bd0f8d-1078-4007-b8a0-fbc27b48feb6','How much memory does the entire 256-interrupt vector table occupy?','256 Bytes','1 KB','4 KB','64 KB','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Each vector takes 4 bytes (2 for IP, 2 for CS). 256 * 4 = 1024 bytes = 1 KB.','pregenerated'),
('03bd0f8d-1078-4007-b8a0-fbc27b48feb6','What is the function of the 8087 co-processor?','Network management','Mathematical calculations (Floating point)','Video rendering','Disk control','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The 8087 is a Numeric Data Processor (NDP) that handles floating point and trigonometric math.','pregenerated'),
('03bd0f8d-1078-4007-b8a0-fbc27b48feb6','Which pin in 8086 alerts the processor that a co-processor has finished its task?','READY','BUSY''','TEST''','HOLD','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'The WAIT instruction causes the CPU to pause until the TEST'' pin is pulled low by an external device.','pregenerated'),
('03bd0f8d-1078-4007-b8a0-fbc27b48feb6','The 80286 microprocessor can address how much RAM in Protected Mode?','1 MB','16 MB','4 GB','64 KB','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'80286 has a 24-bit address bus in protected mode, allowing 2^24 = 16 MB.','pregenerated'),
('03bd0f8d-1078-4007-b8a0-fbc27b48feb6','What is ''XLAT'' used for in 8086?','Extended Latch','Table translation (using BX as base and AL as index)','Cross-linked addressing','XOR Latch','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'XLAT translates the byte in AL using a look-up table pointed to by BX.','pregenerated'),
('03bd0f8d-1078-4007-b8a0-fbc27b48feb6','In 8086, which segment is used by default for the ''DI'' register when executing string instructions?','CS','DS','ES (Extra Segment)','SS','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'For string operations, SI uses DS and DI uses ES (Destination Index -> Extra Segment).','pregenerated'),
('03bd0f8d-1078-4007-b8a0-fbc27b48feb6','What happens to the 8086 instruction queue when a JMP instruction is executed?','It stays the same','It is cleared (flushed)','It is sorted','It is reversed','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'A jump changes the program flow, making pre-fetched instructions invalid, so the queue must be flushed.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','Which command is used to list all running containers in Docker?','docker list','docker ps','docker show','docker containers','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The ''docker ps'' command lists running containers. Use ''docker ps -a'' to see all containers including stopped ones.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','What is the relationship between a Docker Image and a Docker Container?','Containers are used to create images','A container is a running instance of an image','They are the same thing','Images are used only for cloud deployments','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Images are read-only templates. A container is a runnable instance of an image.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','What is Docker Hub?','A tool to build images','A public registry for sharing Docker images','The Docker engine installed on your PC','A programming language','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Docker Hub is the world''s largest library and community for container images.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','Which command is used to download an image from Docker Hub?','docker get','docker pull','docker fetch','docker download','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'docker pull [image_name] fetches the image from the registry.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','How do you run a container in ''detached'' mode (in the background)?','-b','-d','-bg','--silent','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'The -d flag (detach) runs the container and returns the container ID immediately.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','Which command is used to stop a running container?','docker kill','docker stop','docker halt','docker end','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'docker stop gracefully shuts down a container by sending a SIGTERM signal.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','What is the ''Docker Daemon''?','A virus that infects containers','The background process that manages Docker objects like images and containers','The command line interface','A type of firewall','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'The Docker daemon (dockerd) listens for Docker API requests and manages Docker objects.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','Which instruction specifies the base image to use in a Dockerfile?','START','FROM','BASE','INIT','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'A Dockerfile must begin with a FROM instruction specifying the base image.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','What is the difference between CMD and RUN in a Dockerfile?','CMD runs during build, RUN runs during container startup','RUN runs during build to create the image, CMD provides a default command when the container starts','They are identical','CMD is for script files only','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'RUN executes commands and commits the result to the image layer; CMD sets the entry point behavior.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','In command ''docker run -p 8080:80 nginx'', what does ''8080'' represent?','The port inside the container','The port on the host machine','The process ID','The memory limit','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Port mapping follows the format [host_port]:[container_port].','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','Which command is used to remove a stopped container?','docker delete','docker rm','docker rmi','docker clean','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'docker rm removes containers. docker rmi removes images.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','How can you view the console output (stdout) of a background container?','docker show','docker logs','docker output','docker tail','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'docker logs [container_id] displays the logs for a specific container.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','Which Dockerfile instruction sets the working directory for subsequent instructions?','CD','WORKDIR','DIR','FOLDER','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'WORKDIR creates the directory if it doesn''t exist and switches to it for RUN, CMD, etc.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','Which command allows you to run a new command inside an already running container?','docker start','docker exec','docker run','docker attachment','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'docker exec is commonly used to open a shell inside a running container (e.g., docker exec -it [id] bash).','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','What is a ''Tag'' in the context of Docker images?','A label for the developer','A version identifier for an image (e.g., nginx:latest)','A price tag','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Tags allow you to differentiate versions of the same image.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','What is the primary difference between a Virtual Machine (VM) and a Docker Container?','Containers use their own Guest OS, VMs share the Host kernel','VMs use their own Guest OS, Containers share the Host OS kernel','VMs are faster than containers','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Because they share the host kernel, containers are much more lightweight and start faster than VMs.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','Which command is used to build an image from a Dockerfile in the current directory?','docker create .','docker build -t myimage .','docker image make .','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The dot (.) at the end specifies the build context (current directory).','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','Which flag is used to pass an environment variable to a container during ''docker run''?','-env','-e','-v','-var','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Using -e (or --env) allows you to configure applications inside the container at runtime.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','What happens to the data inside a container when the container is deleted, if no volumes are used?','The data is saved to Docker Hub','The data is permanently lost','The data is moved to a backup folder','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Containers are ephemeral; data must be stored in volumes for persistence.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','Which instruction is used to copy files from the host machine to the image during build?','IMPORT','COPY','CLONE','MOVE','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'COPY [src] [dest] is the preferred way to add local files to an image.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','In a Dockerfile, which instruction informs Docker that the container listens on the specified network ports at runtime?','LISTEN','EXPOSE','OPEN','PORT','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'EXPOSE acts as documentation and an instruction for port mapping, but doesn''t actually ''open'' the port on the host.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','How do you see all Docker images stored locally on your machine?','docker show images','docker images','docker ps -i','docker ls','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The ''docker images'' (or ''docker image ls'') command lists locally available images.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','What is the difference between ''docker start'' and ''docker run''?','There is no difference','docker run creates and starts a NEW container; docker start restarts an EXISTING stopped container','docker start is only for background tasks','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Use ''docker run'' the first time; ''docker start'' for returning to a previously created container.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','Which command is used to remove a local Docker image?','docker rm','docker rmi','docker image clean','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'''rmi'' stands for Remove Image.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','Which flag allows you to keep STDIN open and allocate a pseudo-TTY for interactive tasks?','-i','-it','-y','-ssh','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'-it is standard for interactive terminal sessions (e.g. running a shell).','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','What is ''Docker Compose''?','A tool for making music in containers','A tool for defining and running multi-container Docker applications using a YAML file','The compiler for Docker','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Docker Compose allows you to manage a stack of services (e.g., App + DB) with a single command.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','Which flag is used to give a custom name to a container during ''docker run''?','-n','--name','-id','--label','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'If you don''t provide a name, Docker assigns a random one (like ''nostalgic_hopper'').','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','What does the ''ENTRYPOINT'' instruction do in a Dockerfile?','It lists the entry doors of the container','It configures the container to run as an executable, making the command hard to override','It specifies the user who runs the container','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'ENTRYPOINT is used when you want a container to behave exactly like a specific command.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','Which command is used to upload an image to a registry like Docker Hub?','docker upload','docker push','docker commit','docker sync','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'You must tag the image correctly with your username before executing ''docker push''.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','Which command displays detailed information (in JSON format) about a Docker object?','docker show','docker inspect','docker detail','docker json','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'docker inspect can be used on containers, images, volumes, and networks.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','Which component of Docker is responsible for storing and distributing images?','Docker Engine','Docker Registry','Docker Compose','Docker Desktop','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Docker Hub is the most famous example of a Docker Registry.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','Which command is used to remove all unused Docker data (containers, networks, images)?','docker clear','docker system prune','docker cleanup','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'''docker system prune'' is a powerful way to reclaim disk space.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','Which flag is used to limit the memory usage of a container during ''docker run''?','-ram','-m (or --memory)','-limit','-res','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Restricting resources prevents a single container from crashing the host machine.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','What is the default network type for a Docker container?','host','bridge','none','overlay','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'The ''bridge'' network allows containers to communicate with each other on the same host.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','Which command maps a local directory to a container directory (Volume) during ''docker run''?','-d','-v','-mount','-s','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'-v [host_path]:[container_path] is the shorthand for host-mounted volumes.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','Docker images are built using a series of read-only layers. What happens when a container is started?','A new read-only layer is added','A thin writable layer is added on top','All layers become writable','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'This ''Container Layer'' stores all changes made during the container''s lifetime.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','What is the use of ''.dockerignore'' file?','To tell Docker to ignore errors','To exclude specific files and directories from being sent to the Docker daemon during build','To hide files inside the container','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'This speeds up the build process and keeps sensitive files (like .env) out of the image.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','By default, Docker containers run as which user?','docker','root','admin','guest','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'It is a security best practice to switch to a non-root user in your Dockerfile using the ''USER'' instruction.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','Which command shows the current version of Docker installed?','docker --version','docker -v','docker version','All of the above','["D"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'All these variations work to display version information.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','Which command is used to add a new tag to an existing local image?','docker label','docker tag','docker rename','docker update','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'docker tag [old_name] [new_name] creates a new reference to the same image ID.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','What is the standard filename for the Docker Compose configuration file?','docker.yaml','docker-compose.yml','docker-stack.json','config.docker','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'YAML is the standard format for Docker Compose files.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','Which Docker object is the ''recommended'' way to persist data in Docker?','Bind Mounts','Volumes','TMPFS','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Volumes are managed by Docker and are more flexible and portable than host-specific bind mounts.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','Which command is used to log in to a Docker registry?','docker auth','docker login','docker connect','docker signin','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'You must be logged in to push images to private registries or Docker Hub.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','Which command is used to see real-time resource usage (CPU, RAM, Network) of running containers?','docker top','docker stats','docker monitoring','docker usage','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'docker stats provides a live stream of data similar to ''top'' in Linux.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','What is the difference between ADD and COPY in a Dockerfile?','There is no difference','ADD can download files from URLs and untar archives automatically; COPY only copies local files','COPY is faster than ADD','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'COPY is generally preferred for simplicity unless the extra features of ADD are specifically required.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','How do you view all environment variables inside a running container?','docker variable','docker exec [id] env','docker inspect [id]','Both B and C','["D"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'inspect shows the configured vars, and ''env'' runs the command inside the container to show current values.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','Which flag ensures a container is automatically removed when it stops?','-d','--rm','-auto','-clean','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'--rm is very useful for one-off tasks (like running a compiler) to keep your system clean.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','Docker is based on which Linux feature for resource isolation?','Firewall','Control Groups (cgroups) and Namespaces','Inodes','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'These kernel features provide the separation of processes, networking, and hardware resources.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','What is ''Docker Search'' used for?','Searching for files in a container','Searching Docker Hub for images from the command line','Searching for Docker help online','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'docker search [term] displays popular public images matching the query.','pregenerated'),
('429fbcac-eb4a-4f71-aac9-e3a3bdfd1081','What does the ''Moby'' whale represent?','The Linux kernel','The Docker project logo','A cloud server','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'The whale is the iconic mascot of Docker.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','Which Docker network driver allows a container to share the host''s IP address directly?','bridge','host','overlay','macvlan','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'In ''host'' mode, there is no isolation between host and container networking.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What is the primary use of the ''overlay'' network driver?','To connect two containers on the same host','To enable communication between containers on DIFFERENT Docker hosts (Swarm/K8s)','To hide the container''s IP','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Overlay networks create a distributed network across multiple nodes.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What is the benefit of a ''Multi-stage build'' in a Dockerfile?','It makes the build process slower','It allows you to use one image for building and another for the final runtime, significantly reducing final image size','It allows you to run multiple containers from one file','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Multi-stage builds allow you to leave build tools (like compilers) behind, keeping the final production image small.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What is a ''Bind Mount''?','A volume stored in Docker Hub','Mapping a specific, absolute path on the host machine to a path in the container','A type of network connection','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Bind mounts are useful for development, as changes on the host are instantly reflected in the container.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','In a docker-compose.yml file, what does ''depends_on'' do?','It installs dependencies from npm','It defines the startup order for services (e.g., start DB before App)','It links the container to the internet','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Note: ''depends_on'' doesn''t wait for the app inside the container to be ''ready'', just for the container to ''start''.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What is the difference between ARG and ENV in a Dockerfile?','There is no difference','ARG is for build-time only; ENV is available at both build-time and runtime inside the container','ENV is for numbers only','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Use ARG for things like version numbers during build; use ENV for app configuration like DB_URL.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','How does Docker handle image layer caching?','It rebuilds everything every time','If an instruction and its files Haven''t changed, Docker reuses the cached layer from a previous build to save time','It only caches the first layer','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'This is why you should put instructions that change frequently (like COPY code) at the end of the Dockerfile.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What does ''unless-stopped'' restart policy do?','Restarts the container unless it was manually stopped by the user','Stops the container after 1 hour','Only restarts on severe errors','none of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Unlike ''always'', ''unless-stopped'' won''t restart the container when the Docker daemon reboots if the container was already stopped.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','Why is it a security risk to run Docker containers as ''root''?','Root users use too much memory','If an attacker breaks out of the container, they might gain root access to the host machine''s kernel','Root users cannot connect to the internet','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'The ''Principle of Least Privilege'' dictates running as a non-root user whenever possible.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','Which command is used to start a Docker Compose project in the background?','docker-compose start','docker-compose up -d','docker-compose run background','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'''up'' creates and starts the containers; ''-d'' detaches the session.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','How do you run a local private Docker registry?','By installing a special app on Windows','By running the official ''registry'' image as a container (docker run -p 5000:5000 registry:2)','You cannot run a private registry locally','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Docker provides a simple image to self-host your own registry.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What is the difference between ''--cpus'' and ''--cpu-shares''?','--cpus is for Intel, --cpu-shares is for AMD','--cpus sets a hard limit on total CPU usage; --cpu-shares sets a relative weighting compared to other containers','They are the same','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Shares use 1024 as the default base weight.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','Which command shows the history of an image''s layers?','docker layers [image]','docker history [image]','docker inspect --layers','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'This is useful for debugging image size and seeing how an image was built.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What does ''docker commit'' do?','Saves your code to GitHub','Creates a new image from the current state of a running or stopped container','Updates the Docker engine','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'While useful for debugging, it''s generally better to use a Dockerfile for reproducibility.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','In a bridge network, how can containers communicate with each other by name?','They can''t','By using Docker''s internal DNS (if they are on a custom-created network)','By editing /etc/hosts manually','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Custom bridge networks provide automatic service discovery.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','Which command is used to copy files between a host and a running container?','docker mv','docker cp','docker send','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Usage: docker cp [host_path] [container_id]:[path] or vice versa.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What is the purpose of ''SHELL'' instruction in a Dockerfile?','To name the container','To override the default shell used for the shell form of inline commands (RUN, CMD, ENTRYPOINT)','To enable SSH access','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Commonly used on Windows to switch from cmd to powershell.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What does the ''STOPSIGNAL'' instruction do?','Stops the build if it fails','Sets the system call signal that will be sent to the container to exit (default is SIGTERM)','Tells the coder to stop','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Useful for apps that require a specific signal (like SIGUSR1) to shut down gracefully.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What is the default location for Docker Volumes on Linux?','/etc/docker/volumes','/var/lib/docker/volumes','/home/user/volumes','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'This is where Docker manages data for named volumes.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','Which command allows you to see what has changed in a container''s filesystem compared to its image?','docker status','docker diff','docker inspect --fs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'It shows Added (A), Deleted (D), or Changed (C) files.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','Why should you combine multiple RUN commands using ''&&'' into a single RUN instruction?','To make the Dockerfile shorter','To reduce the number of layers in the image, keeping it smaller and more efficient','To bypass errors','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Every RUN instruction creates a new layer; combining them prevents ''dead'' data from being saved in intermediate layers.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What is an ''Image Scan'' in the context of security?','Taking a picture of the image','Analyzing the software packages inside an image for known security vulnerabilities (CVEs)','Speeding up the image build','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Tools like Snyk or Trivy scan images for outdated and insecure libraries.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','Which command is used to rename an existing container?','docker rename','docker mv','docker update --name','none of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Usage: docker rename [old_name] [new_name].','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','How do you listen for real-time events (like container creation or death) from the Docker daemon?','docker listen','docker events','docker watch','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Useful for auditing or building automation tools that react to container changes.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What is ''Memory Swappiness''?','A high-speed RAM type','A setting that controls how aggressively the kernel swaps container memory to disk','Deleting the RAM','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Setting --memory-swappiness to 0 avoids swapping altogether.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What does a ''HEALTHCHECK'' instruction do in a Dockerfile?','Provides medical advice for devs','Tells Docker how to test if the container application is actually ''healthy'' and functioning correctly','Automatically fixes bugs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'If a health check fails repeatedly, the container is marked as unhealthy.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What are ''Dangling Images''?','Images hanging in the cloud','Unused images with no name/tag (often displayed as <none>:<none>)','Images that have errors','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'These are usually old layers left behind after building an image with the same name/tag.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What is ''Docker Save'' and ''Docker Load'' used for?','Saving the logs','Exporting an image to a tar archive for manual transfer to another machine without a registry','Saving the state of the PC','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Useful for ''air-gapped'' environments with no internet access.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What is an ''init'' process inside a container?','A process that initializes the RAM','A small manager (like ''tini'') that handles zombie processes and signals, often used as the entrypoint','The first user that logs in','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Running with ''--init'' in Docker run helps solve the ''PID 1'' zombie harvesting problem.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','In Docker Compose, what is ''env_file'' used for?','Naming the file','Loading many environment variables from a text file into the container at once','Deleting environment variables','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'This keeps secrets and config separate from your orchestration code.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What does the ''macvlan'' network driver allow you to do?','Assign a MAC address to a container, making it appear as a physical device on your network','Run Docker on a Mac','Translate IP addresses to names','none of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Macvlan is helpful for legacy apps that expect to be on a specific physical subnet.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What is the difference between a ''Volume'' and a ''Bind Mount'' in terms of management?','Bind mounts are managed by Docker; Volumes are managed by the user','Volumes are managed by Docker; Bind mounts rely on the host''s folder structure','There is no difference','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Docker handles the backup, migration, and storage of volumes automatically.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What is ''Docker Content Trust'' (DCT)?','A physical lock for a server','A feature that allows digital signing of images, proving their authenticity and integrity','Trusting everyone on the network','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'By enabling DCT, you ensure that you only pull images that have been signed by a trusted publisher.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What happens if you define the same environment variable in both a Dockerfile and ''docker run''?','The Dockerfile value wins','The ''docker run'' value overrides the Dockerfile value','Both are ignored','It causes a crash','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Runtime configuration always takes precedence over build-time defaults.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What is ''docker top'' used for?','Ranking images by popularity','Displaying the running processes of a specific container','Seeing the top users','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'It helps you see what the entrypoint process is actually doing inside.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What is ''tmpfs'' mount?','A temporary mount in the cloud','Mapping a container path to the host''s system memory (RAM) instead of the disk','A mount for text files only','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'tmpfs is fast and secure as the data is wiped when the container stops.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What does ''ONBUILD'' instruction do?','Starts building immediately','Adds a trigger instruction to an image that will execute later when the image is used as the base for another build','Stops the build','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Useful for creating ''template'' images (like a boilerplate base image).','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','How do you recreate all containers in a Compose project from scratch?','docker-compose start --new','docker-compose up --force-recreate','docker-compose restart all','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'This forces Compose to ignore existing containers even if the config hasn''t changed.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What is a ''User-defined bridge'' better than the ''Default bridge'' network?','It is faster for users','It provides automatic DNS resolution by container name and better isolation','It is exactly the same','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'The default bridge network requires messy ''--link'' commands for discovery.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','Which base image is most famous for being ultra-lightweight (approx 5MB)?','Ubuntu','Alpine Linux','Debian','CentOS','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Alpine is the gold standard for minimal, high-performance container images.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','How can you run a ''docker run'' command as a specific user ID?','--id 1000','--user 1000','-u root:new','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Passing -u (or --user) overrides the value set in the Dockerfile.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What is ''docker wait'' command used for?','Pausing the container','Blocking the terminal session until a container stops, and then printing its exit code','Adding a delay to start','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Often used in CI/CD scripts to wait for a database to finish its migration or a test to finish.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What happens if you use ''COPY .'' in a Dockerfile without a .dockerignore?','It copies nothing','It copies EVERYTHING in the current folder, including node_modules or large local binaries, making the image huge','Docker asks you what to copy','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'This can make builds extremely slow and images bloated.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','How do you view logs of a specific service in Docker Compose?','docker logs [service_name]','docker-compose logs -f [service_name]','docker show logs [id]','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The -f flag follows the log stream live.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What is the ''OOM Killer''?','A virus','An OS feature that kills a container (or process) if it exceeds its allotted memory and impacts system stability','A tool to delete logs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'You can use ''--oom-kill-disable'' but it''s dangerous for host stability.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What does a ''Port Mapping'' of 0.0.0.0:80:80 do?','Nothing','Binds port 80 of the container to port 80 of the host and makes it accessible from any network interface on the host','Hides the port','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Using 127.0.0.1:80:80 would instead only make it accessible from the local host itself.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','Which command displays the system-wide disk usage of Docker (images, containers, volumes)?','docker df','docker system df','docker usage','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'It helps you identify where large amounts of space are being consumed.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What is a ''Base Image''?','The first image you ever made','The image used as the starting point for your Dockerfile (defined in FROM instruction)','A black and white image','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Every Dockerfile build starts on top of a base image.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','What is the use of ''VOLUME'' instruction in a Dockerfile?','To turn up the sound','To inform Docker that a specific directory will be used for persistent data and should have its own mount','To name the container','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Even if the user doesn''t map a volume, Docker creates an anonymous volume for that path.','pregenerated'),
('0e57e833-fc53-405f-b2da-2a2709a6254b','Which command is used to pause all processes in a container?','docker stop','docker pause','docker freeze','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'It sends a SIGSTOP signal, freezing the container''s state in memory.','pregenerated')
