('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is the primary role of a ''Manager Node'' in a Docker Swarm?','To run all container workloads','To maintain the cluster state, schedule services, and manage Swarm APIs','To backup the data','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Manager nodes use Raft consensus to synchronize the state of the swarm.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is a ''Service'' in the context of Docker Swarm?','A background app','The definition of the tasks to execute on the nodes (e.g., image, ports, replicas)','A network connection','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Services allow you to scale applications by defining the number of running replicas.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is the difference between ''Replicated'' and ''Global'' service modes in Swarm?','Replicated runs on all nodes; Global runs on specific number','Replicated runs a specific number of tasks; Global runs exactly one task on every node in the swarm','They are the same','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Global mode is useful for monitoring agents or antivirus software that must run everywhere.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','How does ''Docker Secret'' protect sensitive data in Swarm?','By encrypting the hard drive','By encrypting secrets at rest and in transit, and mounting them into the container''s memory (/run/secrets) only when needed','By hiding them from the logs','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Secrets are safer than environment variables as they are never written to disk or shown in ''docker inspect''.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is a ''Seccomp Profile'' in Docker?','A user profile','A Secure Computing mode profile that restricts the system calls a container can make to the Linux kernel','A way to speed up the container','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Seccomp is a powerful security feature that significantly reduces the kernel''s attack surface for a container.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is the ''Ingress'' network in Docker Swarm?','The internet connection','A special overlay network that facilitates load balancing across all nodes in the swarm for any service port exposed publicly','A private network for admins','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'The ''Routing Mesh'' uses the ingress network to direct traffic to wherever a service task is running.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is a Docker ''Stack''?','A pile of images','A collection of services that share dependencies and can be orchestrated together (usually defined in a Compose file)','A way to backup the server','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'docker stack deploy allows you to manage multiple related services as a single unit.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','Which command initializes a Docker Swarm on a manager node?','docker swarm start','docker swarm init','docker swarm create','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'This generates a join token for other manager and worker nodes.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is a ''BuildKit'' in modern Docker versions?','A tool for kids to build containers','An advanced, high-performance build engine that supports parallelization, secret mounting during build, and better caching','The default logo','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'BuildKit is the modern replacement for the legacy Docker builder, offering massive speed improvements.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What does ''--cap-drop ALL'' do during ''docker run''?','Drops all user connections','Removes all default Linux kernel capabilities from the container, enforcing the most restrictive environment possible','Deletes the container after use','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'For high security, drop all and then selectively ''--cap-add'' only what''s needed (e.g., NET_ADMIN).','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is ''Docker Context'' used for?','To provide context for the code','To easily manage and switch between different Docker endpoints (e.g., local, remote SSH, cloud clusters) from one CLI','To rename containers','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Contexts consolidate your connection info into easy-to-use profiles.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is ''containerd'' in the Docker ecosystem?','The GUI for Docker','An industry-standard core container runtime used by Docker (and K8s) that manages the complete container lifecycle on a node','The Docker installer','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Docker is now built on top of the smaller, CNCF-maintained ''containerd'' runtime.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is a ''Quorum'' in a Docker Swarm manager group?','The maximum number of containers','The majority of manager nodes needed to be online (N/2 + 1) to maintain cluster stability and allow new changes','The number of users','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Without a quorum, managers cannot make decisions (to prevent split-brain scenarios).','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is ''User Namespace Mapping'' in Docker?','Naming users in the container','A feature that maps the container ''root'' user to a non-privileged user on the host, preventing host-level root access if a breakout occurs','Hiding user names','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'This effectively ''sandboxes'' the root user within the container''s own reality.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is the ''Routing Mesh'' in Docker Swarm?','A net for the fans','The ability of any node in the swarm to accept traffic on a published service port and route it to a node running that service','A map of the internet','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'The routing mesh ensures your app stays reachable even as tasks migrate between nodes.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','Which Docker Registry API version is current and most used?','v1','v2','v3','v4','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'The Registry V2 API is the standard for pushing and pulling image layers.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','Which command is used to join a worker node to an existing Swarm?','docker swarm add','docker swarm join --token [token] [manager_ip]','docker node connect','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'The token is obtained from the manager using ''docker swarm join-token worker''.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is ''Block I/O'' (blkio) limit in Docker?','Limiting the number of files','Controlling the read/write speed (weight or IOPS) of a container to prevent disk bandwidth hogging','Stopping a user','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'blkio settings help enforce ''Noisy Neighbor'' isolation for disk performance.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','Which command updates an existing service in a Swarm without stopping it (e.g. changing the image)?','docker service update','docker service refresh','docker stack restart','none of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Docker Swarm performs a ''Rolling Update'' by default, updating one replica at a time.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is the purpose of the ''LABEL'' instruction in a Dockerfile?','To name the file','To add metadata to an image (e.g. author, version, description) for easier filtering and organization','To set an environment variable','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Labels are key-value pairs that can be read by ''docker inspect''.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','How can you view the ''systemd'' logs of the Docker daemon itself on Linux?','docker logs daemon','journalctl -u docker','cat /var/log/docker','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Because Docker runs as a system service, its internal errors are found in the system journal.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is ''Task'' in Docker Swarm?','A background work','The smallest unit of orchestration in Swarm; it represents one container instance belonging to a service','A script for the manager','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'A service might have 5 tasks, which means 5 containers running the same image.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is ''IPAM'' (IP Address Management) in Docker custom networks?','Naming the IP address','The mechanism that decides how IP addresses are assigned to containers (e.g. specifying a subnet and gateway)','A tool to delete IPs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Custom IPAM configurations are essential for complex networking requirements.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is ''Garbage Collection'' in a Docker Registry?','Deleting empty folders','The process of removing blob layers (data) from storage that are no longer referenced by any image tags','Cleaning the registry UI','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Without garbage collection, registries will grow indefinitely as every ''docker push'' of a new version adds data.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','Which command is used to drain all tasks from a specific node in a Swarm (e.g. for maintenance)?','docker node stop','docker node update --availability drain [node_name]','docker node remove','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Draining prevents new tasks from being scheduled on that node and moves existing ones elsewhere.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','How do you enable ''Docker Content Trust'' in your terminal session?','docker feature trust','export DOCKER_CONTENT_TRUST=1','docker config trust --on','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'After setting this env var, every pull/push must be cryptographically signed.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is ''PIDs Limit'' (--pids-limit)?','Limiting the memory weight','Restricting the total number of process IDs a container can create (to prevent Fork Bomb attacks)','Limiting the number of users','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'This prevents a single container from exhausting the host''s process table.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is the benefit of using ''distroless'' base images?','They include more software','They contain only the application and its runtime dependencies, containing no shell or package managers (ultra-secure/minimal)','They are easier to use','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Distroless images are much harder to exploit because they lack common tools like ''sh'' or ''apt''.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','By default, what type of Unix socket does the Docker CLI use to talk to the local daemon?','/tmp/docker.sock','/var/run/docker.sock','/etc/docker.sock','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Protecting this socket file is paramount; giving a container access to it is equivalent to giving it root on the host.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','In Docker Swarm, what is ''Autoscaling''?','Scaling the code automatically','none of the above','The OS fixing itself','A built-in feature of Swarm to scale based on CPU','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Docker Swarm does NOT have built-in autoscaling based on metrics (unlike Kubernetes); it requires external tools or scripts.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is a ''Docker Volume Plugin'' (like Portworx or RexRay)?','A tool to listen to music','A driver that allows Docker to use external storage systems (SAN/NAS/Cloud disks) for persistent volumes','A way to backup the server','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Plugins extend Docker''s capability to integrate with enterprise hardware.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is ''libnetwork''?','A library for the web','The open-source library used by Docker to implement all container networking features (drivers, endpoints, sandboxes)','A network for books','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Libnetwork provides a platform-agnostic way to manage networking.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is ''CA Rotation'' in a Docker Swarm?','Spinning the server','Updating the Certificate Authority and all node certificates to maintain cluster security over time','Changing the admin password','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Periodic CA rotation is a standard security practice to mitigate long-term credential compromise.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','How do you use ''Secrets'' during the Docker Image Build process (BuildKit feature)?','By using ENV','By using the ''--mount=type=secret'' flag in a RUN instruction','By adding them to the Dockerfile text','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'This allows you to pull private dependencies without leaking the token into the image layers.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','In command ''docker network inspect'', what does ''Containers'' section show?','A list of all users','The detailed network config (IP, MAC) for every container currently connected to that specific network','The Docker engine settings','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'This is perfect for troubleshooting connectivity issues between containers.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','Which command removes a service from the Swarm?','docker service stop','docker service rm','docker service delete','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'This instantly stops and removes all tasks associated with that service.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is ''Docker Desktop'' vs ''Docker Engine''?','One is for Mac, one is for Windows','Desktop is the GUI + development tools wrapper (includes VM on Win/Mac); Engine is the core daemon/CLI','There is no difference','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Docker Desktop allows Windows/Mac users to run Linux containers via a lightweight VM.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is ''Docker Config'' object?','A setting in the GUI','A way to store non-sensitive configuration data (like application files) outside of the image and share it with services','The backup for secrets','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Like secrets, configs allow you to decouple application settings from image build.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What does a ''squash'' build do?','Compresses the code','Collapses all new image layers into a single layer at the end of the build to reduce metadata overhead and size','Deletes the logs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Squashing helps keep final production images clean, though it breaks layer sharing between images.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is a ''Logging Driver'' in Docker?','A user that writes logs','A plugin that directs container logs to different destinations (json-file, syslog, journald, splunk, etc.)','A screen for logs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Choosing the right driver is vital for centralized log management in production.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is a ''Placement Constraint'' in Docker Swarm?','A rule about where to sit','A rule that limits which nodes a service can be scheduled on (e.g. only on nodes with ''SSD=true'' label)','A way to delete nodes','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Placement constraints allow you to match application requirements to specific hardware.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','Which command lists all nodes participating in the Swarm?','docker swarm ls','docker node ls','docker show nodes','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'This shows the status and health of every physical/virtual node in the cluster.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is ''AppArmor'' in the context of Docker security?','Armor for the computer','A Linux kernel security module that allows the system administrator to restrict program''s capabilities with per-program profiles','An antivirus program','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Docker loads a default AppArmor profile that provides a strong baseline security for containers.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is ''Docker Events'' filter usage?','Filtering out unwanted users','Using ''--filter'' to watch only specific events (e.g. only ''die'' events for a specific image)','Hiding all events','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Filtering allows you to monitor only what''s important for your automation logic.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is the ''Data Path Port'' used in Swarm Overlay networks?','80','UDP 4789 (VXLAN)','TCP 2377','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'VXLAN encapsulated traffic uses UDP 4789 by default for the data plane.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is ''runC''?','A command to run things','A low-level CLI tool for spawning and running containers according to the OCI (Open Container Initiative) specification','A way to backup the code','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'runC is the actual tool that ''touches'' the Linux kernel to create the container.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is ''Swarm Mode''?','The mode where you have millions of users','The state where a Docker engine participates in a cluster (either as manager or worker)','A virus mode','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Native Swarm orchestration is built directly into the Docker Engine and just needs to be ''initialized''.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What is a ''Shared Volume'' (via NFS/SMB)?','A volume that everyone can see','A volume that can be mounted by multiple containers across different physical hosts simultaneously','A backup tool','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Shared storage is a requirement for horizontally scaled stateful applications.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','Which flag in ''docker ps'' shows the total file sizes of containers?','-v','-s (or --size)','-f','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'This shows the writable layer size vs the virtual (image) size.','pregenerated'),
('e008cf8b-1445-4804-b4d5-980b2dead359','What characterizes ''Self-healing'' in Docker Swarm?','The computer fixing itself with a robot','The manager node automatically restarting or rescheduling tasks if a container or node fails, to maintain the ''Desired State''','The code fixing its own bugs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'The orchestrator constantly monitors ''actual state'' vs ''desired state'' (e.g. 5 replicas).','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','In the Docker architectural stack, what is the ''shim'' process responsible for?','Encrypting the connection','Staying alive after the Docker daemon exits to monitor the container and handle its standard I/O and signals','Deleting the image','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The containerd-shim allows daemon-less containers where the engine can restart without killing the running apps.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','Which Linux Namespace is responsible for isolating the hostname and domain name of a container?','PID namespace','UTS (Unix Timesharing System) namespace','NET namespace','MNT namespace','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'UTS namespace allows a container to have its own hostname, separate from the host and other containers.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','In the ''Overlay2'' storage driver, which directory contains the final combined view of all layers that the container sees?','lowerdir','upperdir','merged','workdir','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The ''merged'' directory is the mount point that combines lower (read-only) and upper (writable) layers via the overlay union filesystem.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','How does Docker Swarm achieve internal load balancing for services internally?','Using Nginx in a hidden container','Using IPVS (IP Virtual Server), a kernel-level load balancer that maps a Service''s Virtual IP to its task IPs','By editing /etc/hosts randomly','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'IPVS provides high-performance, low-latency load balancing directly in the Linux kernel.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What characterizes ''Rootless Docker''?','Docker with no root access on the internet','Running both the Docker daemon and the containers as an unprivileged user to mitigate potential host-takeover exploits','Docker for garden use','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Rootless mode uses user namespaces to fake root privileges for the container without needing real root on the host.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What is ''Docker Buildx'' primarily used for?','Building Docker desktop apps','A CLI plugin that extends the ''build'' command with BuildKit features, most notably for multi-architecture (ARM/x86) builds','Speeding up the internet during build','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Buildx allows you to build and push images for multiple CPU architectures simultaneously using a single command.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','Which algorithm does Docker Swarm use to maintain consensus and elected leaders among manager nodes?','Paxos','Raft','Gossip','Bulletproof','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Raft ensures that all manager nodes have an identical view of the cluster state.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What is ''Cgroups v2'' (Unified Hierarchy) compared to v1?','A faster version of RAM','A redesigned kernel feature that simplifies resource management by using a single hierarchy for all resource types (CPU, Memory, I/O)','A way to hide containers','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Cgroups v2 provides better resource isolation and is easier for orchestrators to manage than the fragmented v1.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What is the ''Gossip'' protocol used for in a Docker cluster?','To share news about the developers','To efficiently propagate node availability and health information across the cluster without a central manager','To encrypt data packets','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Gossip protocol (SWIM-based) ensures every node knows the status of every other node in the overlay network.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What is the role of ''runc'' in the container lifecycle?','To build images','To act as the low-level executor that interfaces with the Linux kernel (namespaces/cgroups) to actually spawn a container','To provide the user interface','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'runc is a lightweight implementation of the OCI Runtime Specification.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What is the purpose of ''Docker Bench for Security''?','A place for Docker fans to sit','An open-source script that checks your Docker deployment against dozens of industry-standard security best practices (CIS benchmarks)','To speed up the Docker daemon','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'It provides a scorecard for how well-hardened your Docker configuration is.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What is ''Copy-on-Write'' (CoW) performance overhead?','It makes copying files slower','The latency penalty incurred the First time a process tries to modify a file from a read-only layer (must be copied to upper layer first)','The CPU cost of hashing','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'For heavy write workloads, using Volumes is better because it avoids the CoW penalty.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','How do you enable ''Read-Only Fileroot'' for a container for extreme security?','--readonly','--read-only','-ro','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'This prevents ANY modifications to the container''s standard filesystem, forcing data to reside only in specific mounts.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What is ''VXLAN'' (Virtual Extensible LAN) encapsulation in Docker?','A type of fiber optic cable','The tunneling protocol used to wrap Layer 2 ethernet frames inside Layer 4 UDP packets to create the Swarm Overlay network','A ways to speed up the internet','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'VXLAN allows Docker to provide consistent networking for containers regardless of the underlying physical network topology.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','How can you debug a container''s network namespace directly using the ''ip netns'' command?','ip netns show','By creating a symlink from /proc/[pid]/ns/net to /var/run/netns/[name]','It is not possible','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Docker hides network namespaces by default, so manual symlinking is required to use standard Linux networking tools.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What is ''Sidecar Container'' pattern?','A container attached to the main container (sharing the same network/storage namespaces) to perform auxiliary tasks like logging or proxying','A container for a secondary user','A backup container','none of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Sidecars are the fundamental building block for ''Service Mesh'' architectures.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What is the ''OCI''?','Open Container Identity','Open Container Initiative: A Linux Foundation project that defines industry standards for container formats and runtimes','Only Cloud Images','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The OCI ensures that images built with Docker can run in K8s, Podman, or any other compliant runtime.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What is the ''No-New-Privileges'' flag (--security-opt=no-new-privileges)?','A flag to prevent user from logging in','A kernel security setting that prevents a process from gaining new privileges (like SUID) even if it executes a privileged binary','A way to delete the logs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'This is a critical hardening step to prevent privilege escalation within a container.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','Which system call is used by ''runc'' to move the container into its new root filesystem?','chroot','pivot_root','mount','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'pivot_root is more secure than chroot as it completely swaps the root device, making breakouts much harder.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What is ''Docker Socket Proxy'' pattern?','Giving every container the socket','A high-security pattern where you run a dedicated container to proxy only SPECIFIC, safe Docker API calls to other containers','Hiding the socket from the users','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'This allows tools to monitor Docker (like Traefik) without having full root-level control via the raw socket.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What is the ''Bridge-nf-call-iptables'' setting?','A way to call the fire department','A Linux kernel setting that controls whether traffic on a bridge is filtered by iptables/nftables rules','A networking cable config','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Docker requires this to be set to ''1'' for its networking and isolation rules to function correctly.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What is ''Zstandard'' (zstd) compression in modern Docker registries?','A way to encrypt data','A high-speed compression algorithm that allows images to be pushed/pulled much faster than the default Gzip','A type of database','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Zstd provides a better balance between compression ratio and speed.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','Which Dockerfile instruction is NOT recommended for production use as it increases image size unnecessarily?','RUN','EXPOSE','CMD','ENTRYPOINT','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'While necessary, every ''RUN'' that cleans up after itself in a DIFFERENT command (not combined) leaves behind a permanent layer of data.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What does ''TTRPRC'' mean in the context of containerd?','Top Tier Record','A high-performance, minimal RPC protocol used by containerd to talk to shims, offering much lower overhead than standard gRPC','The time to run a command','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'ttrpc is used to manage hundreds of shims efficiently without exhausting system resources.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','Which Control Group (cgroup) subsystem handles the isolation of hardware devices (like GPUs)?','cpu','devices','memory','pids','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The ''devices'' cgroup allowlist/denylist controls which /dev entries a container can access.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What is ''Joint Token Rotation''?','Rotating the server','The security procedure of regenerating the Swarm join tokens to prevent unauthorized nodes from joining in the future','Changing the admin password','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Regenerating tokens won''t affect nodes already in the cluster.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','Which legacy Docker storage driver was famous for its block-level (rather than file-level) storage approach?','AUFS','devicemapper','Overlay','vfs','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Devicemapper was complex to configure but offered high performance on older Enterprise Linux versions.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What happens if a process inside a container reaches PID 1 without an init manager?','The computer reboots','It must handle signals (like SIGTERM) itself, otherwise the container may never shut down gracefully','It is automatically given root rights','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Linux Kernel handles PID 1 specially; it doesn''t apply default signal handlers like for other processes.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What is ''Docker Events'' stream format?','Plain text','A stream of JSON objects describing timestamps, actions, and actors','Encoded binary','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The JSON stream makes it easy to parse Docker events in custom monitoring scripts.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What is ''eBPF'' in the context of modern container networking?','A high-speed fiber cable','A revolutionary kernel feature allowing high-performance observability and security filtering without touching the source code','A new version of Docker Compose','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'eBPF (Extended Berkeley Packet Filter) is the future of low-overhead container monitoring and security.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What characterizes a ''SBOM'' (Software Bill of Materials) for a Docker image?','The price of the cloud','A complete inventory of all software components, libraries, and dependencies included in the image layers','A list of developers','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'SBOMs are critical for supply-chain security and compliance.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','How does a Docker Pull work internally regarding layers?','It downloads the whole image as one file','It downloads each layer blob (identified by its SHA256 hash) in parallel and then assembles them locally','It only downloads the last layer','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'This allows Docker to reuse layers already present on the machine, saving bandwidth.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','In Linux, which Namespace isolates Inter-Process Communication (IPCs) like System V structures?','USER namespace','IPC namespace','MNT namespace','NET namespace','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'IPC namespace prevents a container from accessing the message queues or semaphores of another container.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What is ''Namespace Swapping''?','Changing the container name','Using the ''setns'' system call to join an existing namespace (e.g. one container joining the NET namespace of another)','Moving a container to another host','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'This is how ''Sidecar'' containers share the same network stack as the ''Main'' container.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What happens if you run Docker with the ''--privileged'' flag?','Nothing','The container is given almost all host kernel capabilities and access to all devices (effectively removing the sandbox)','The container becomes more secure','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Privileged mode is EXTREMELY dangerous and should only be used for Docker-in-Docker or low-level system tools.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What is ''Distroless'' images build methodology?','Build images without any files','Compiling the application statically and adding it to a ''SCRATCH'' (empty) image base','Using Ubuntu as a base always','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Distroless/Scratch-based builds are the ultimate in size and security optimization.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What is ''Memory reservation'' in Docker orchestration?','Limiting the memory to zero','Providing a ''soft limit'' that guarantees a container gets at least that much RAM, but allowing it to use more if the host is idle','A place for RAM to sit','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Reservations help the orchestrator make better scheduling decisions by knowing minimum requirements.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','How do you configure Docker to pull images from an ''Insecure Registry'' (HTTP instead of HTTPS)?','By using --force','By adding the address to ''insecure-registries'' in the /etc/docker/daemon.json file','You cannot do it','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'This is common in small private labs or during early development phases.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What is ''Task Eviction''?','Deleting the code','When an orchestrator (like Swarm) forces a task to stop on one node (due to failure or maintenance) so it can be recreated elsewhere','Logging out a user','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Eviction ensures that service availability is maintained during hardware issues.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What is ''I/O Throttling'' for containers?','Stopping the internet','Using cgroups to set hard limits on the number of bytes per second a container can read or write to a block device','A way to speed up the disk','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Throttling prevents a single container (like a backup tool) from saturating the disk bandwidth.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What does ''docker info'' show that ''docker version'' does not?','The current time','Detailed statistics about the daemon, like the number of containers (running/stopped), storage driver, and security features enabled','The user''s password','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'''docker info'' provides a comprehensive health summary of the whole Docker subsystem.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What is ''Volume Pruning''?','Cutting the volume','Removing all volumes that are not currently mounted by at least one container','Formatting the volume','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'''docker volume prune'' is essential for clearing out ''ghost data'' left by old test containers.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What is ''Kata Containers'' in the Docker ecosystem?','Containers from Japan','A secure container runtime that runs containers inside lightweight Virtual Machines for better isolation','A tool to delete images','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Kata provides the security of VMs with the management ease of Docker.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','Which technique is used to prevent ''Split-Brain'' in a Swarm leader election?','Ask a human','Odd number of managers and Majority Consensus (e.g. 2 out of 3)','Randomly picking one','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The Raft protocol requires a majority to approve any cluster-wide change.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What is ''Label Schema''?','A way to draw labels','A community-standardized set of LABEL keys (like org.opencontainers.image.source) to ensure metadata consistency across all builders','An encryption key','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Standardized labels allow tools to show consistent information for any image.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What is ''Loopback Interface'' (lo) in a container?','A loop for the fans','The internal network interface (127.0.0.1) that allows a container to talk to its own internal processes','A ways to delete IP','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Every container gets its own isolated loopback interface by the NET namespace.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What is ''Service Availability'' policy in Docker Swarm?','Being online on Tuesdays','Setting ''update_config'' to control how many replicas are updated at once and how long to wait between updates','A law for the internet','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Good update policies prevent total service downtime during a buggy code deployment.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What characterize ''Privilege Escalation'' in Docker?','Getting a job promotion','An exploit where a user inside a container managed to gain root-level permissions on the host operating system','Hiding the password','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Properly configured Namespaces and Seccomp are designed to prevent this.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What is ''Docker Plug-in Architecture'' used for?','Plugging in a mouse','Allowing third-party vendors to extend Docker''s networking, storage, and logging capabilities without modifying the core engine','A ways to speed up the internet','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Plugins allow Docker to adapt to diverse enterprise ecosystems.','pregenerated'),
('78b4b69c-a6c4-4aed-9f10-63e3f731ce1c','What is ''Cache Export'' in BuildKit?','Exporting the code to the cloud','The ability to save build cache data to a remote registry so other team members or CI/CD pipelines can benefit from previous builds','Deleting the cache','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Remote cache sharing makes CI/CD extremely fast even on clean agents.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('80e28c27-a79b-4fd4-b950-10c3e3ff27bb','What is the time complexity of searching for an element in a balanced binary search tree?','O(1)','O(n)','O(log n)','O(n log n)','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Binary search trees halved the search space at each step, leading to logarithmic time.','pregenerated'),
('80e28c27-a79b-4fd4-b950-10c3e3ff27bb','A Stack follows which principle?','FIFO (First-In, First-Out)','LIFO (Last-In, First-Out)','Random Access','Priority Access','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'In a stack, the last element pushed is the first one to be popped (like a stack of plates).','pregenerated'),
('80e28c27-a79b-4fd4-b950-10c3e3ff27bb','What is the Big O time complexity of ''Bubble Sort'' in the worst case?','O(n)','O(n^2)','O(log n)','O(n log n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Bubble sort uses nested loops, resulting in a quadratic time complexity.','pregenerated'),
('80e28c27-a79b-4fd4-b950-10c3e3ff27bb','Which data structure is best for implementing a ''First-In, First-Out'' (FIFO) system?','Stack','Queue','Hash Map','Binary Tree','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Queues process elements in the order they arrived (like a line for tickets).','pregenerated'),
('80e28c27-a79b-4fd4-b950-10c3e3ff27bb','What is the space complexity of a recursive function with depth ''n'' that uses no extra variables?','O(1)','O(n)','O(n^2)','O(log n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'Each recursive call adds a frame to the call stack, leading to O(n) space complexity.','pregenerated'),
('80e28c27-a79b-4fd4-b950-10c3e3ff27bb','What is a ''Linked List''?','A collection of data stored in contiguous memory','A linear data structure where elements are stored in nodes, and each node points to the next node','A list of strings in a file','A way to connect different databases','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'Linked lists are dynamic and can easily grow or shrink, but don''t support constant-time random access.','pregenerated'),
('80e28c27-a79b-4fd4-b950-10c3e3ff27bb','What is the time complexity of accessing an element at a specific index in an Array?','O(1)','O(n)','O(log n)','O(n log n)','["A"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'Arrays support constant-time access via index calculation in memory.','pregenerated'),
