('3ea690aa-f117-4cc7-9a81-0444cce44b34','In a sorted array, what index will ''Binary Search'' check first for array [1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 11]?','0','2','3','5','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'(0 + 5) / 2 = 2 (index 2 contains value 5) - or index 3 depending on implementation. Usually floor(low+high/2) gives 2.','pregenerated'),
('3ea690aa-f117-4cc7-9a81-0444cce44b34','Which sorting algorithm is most efficient for sorting large amounts of data in external storage (Disk)?','Quick Sort','Merge Sort','Bubble Sort','Insertion Sort','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'External Merge Sort uses a divide and conquer strategy that minimizes disk reads/writes.','pregenerated'),
('3ea690aa-f117-4cc7-9a81-0444cce44b34','What is ''String Interning''?','Translating strings to binary','Storing only one copy of each distinct string value','A ways to compress strings','Converting strings to numbers','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Interning is used in Java and Python to save space and speed up comparisons.','pregenerated'),
('3ea690aa-f117-4cc7-9a81-0444cce44b34','What is ''Backtracking''?','A search algorithm that explores all paths','A refined brute force that builds a solution step by step and ''backs up'' if a partial solution cannot be completed','Moving backward in an array','A sorting strategy','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Examples include N-Queens, Sudoku solving, and depth-first search variations.','pregenerated'),
('3ea690aa-f117-4cc7-9a81-0444cce44b34','What is the time complexity of building a heap from an array of n elements?','O(n log n)','O(n)','O(log n)','O(n^2)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Using the ''heapify'' method from the bottom-up, it results in O(n) although it looks like n log n.','pregenerated'),
('3ea690aa-f117-4cc7-9a81-0444cce44b34','What happens if an algorithm has no base case in recursion?','It finishes quickly','Stack Overflow','Out of Memory on Heap','Compilation Error','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Infinite recursion exhausts the call stack space.','pregenerated'),
('3ea690aa-f117-4cc7-9a81-0444cce44b34','In Hashing, what is a ''Perfect Hash Function''?','A function with no hash','A function that generates no collisions for a static set of keys','A function using random numbers','The identity function','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'It maps each key into a unique slot.','pregenerated'),
('3ea690aa-f117-4cc7-9a81-0444cce44b34','What is the time complexity of finding an element in a Hash Map (average case)?','O(1)','O(n)','O(log n)','O(n log n)','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'With a good hash function and distribution, access is constant time on average.','pregenerated'),
('3ea690aa-f117-4cc7-9a81-0444cce44b34','Which of these is a LIFO data structure?','Queue','Stack','List','Graph','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'Last-In First-Out: used by stacks.','pregenerated'),
('3ea690aa-f117-4cc7-9a81-0444cce44b34','What is the ''Height'' of a leaf node?','1','0','n','Depends on the root','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Height is the number of edges to the deepest descendant; for a leaf, that is 0.','pregenerated'),
('3ea690aa-f117-4cc7-9a81-0444cce44b34','In interpolation search, compared to binary search, the probe position:','Is always in the middle','Estimates the position based on the value being searched and the range','Is random','Is always the first index','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Interpolation search works best for uniformly distributed data, similar to how we look for a word in a dictionary.','pregenerated'),
('3ea690aa-f117-4cc7-9a81-0444cce44b34','Which sorting algorithm is known for partition and pivot?','Merge Sort','Quick Sort','Selection Sort','Bubble Sort','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Quick sort is defined by its partitioning step.','pregenerated'),
('3ea690aa-f117-4cc7-9a81-0444cce44b34','An ''Acyclic'' graph is one that contains:','No vertices','No cycles','Only cycles','Infinite paths','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Trees are a classic example of connected acyclic graphs.','pregenerated'),
('3ea690aa-f117-4cc7-9a81-0444cce44b34','Which of these is better than O(n)?','O(n^2)','O(log n)','O(2^n)','O(n log n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Logarithmic growth is significantly slower (more efficient) than linear growth.','pregenerated'),
('3ea690aa-f117-4cc7-9a81-0444cce44b34','How many pointers must be changed to reverse the direction of one link in a singly linked list?','1','2','3','0','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'You typically track ''prev'', ''current'', and ''next'' nodes (shifting links).','pregenerated'),
('3ea690aa-f117-4cc7-9a81-0444cce44b34','An ''Abstract Data Type'' (ADT) defines:','The hardware used','What operations can be performed, but not how they are implemented','String manipulation only','The specific bits in memory','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'ADTs like ''Stack'' or ''List'' define behavior; data structures provide implementation.','pregenerated'),
('3ea690aa-f117-4cc7-9a81-0444cce44b34','What is ''Rehashing''?','Deleting the map','Creating a larger hash table and re-inserting all existing elements when the load factor exceeds a threshold','Encrypting keys twice','Replacing the hash function with a simpler one','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Rehashing keeps the table sparse enough for O(1) performance.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','What is ''Memoization''?','Learning by memory','An optimization technique used primarily to speed up computer programs by storing the results of expensive function calls','A way to delete code','A styling method','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Memoization is a key component of top-down dynamic programming.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','Dijkstra''s algorithm is used to solve which type of problem?','Sorting an array','Finding the shortest path in a weighted graph (with non-negative weights)','Finding the median of a list','Detecting cycles in a graph','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Dijkstra''s uses a greedy approach to find paths from a source to all other vertices.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','What is the difference between BFS and DFS space complexity on a large graph?','BFS uses more memory for its queue; DFS uses memory for its recursion stack','BFS is always more memory efficient','There is no difference','DFS is for trees only','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'BFS can use significant memory if the graph is wide, as it stores nodes at the current depth.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','What is ''Dynamic Programming'' (DP)?','A way to write code fast','A method for solving complex problems by breaking them down into simpler subproblems and storing their results to avoid redundant work','A new programming language','An alternative to SQL','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'DP is effective when subproblems overlap.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','What is a ''Trie'' (Prefix Tree) best for?','Sorting numbers','Storing a set of strings and performing efficient prefix-based lookups (e.g., auto-complete)','Finding the maximum value in a list','Managing database transactions','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'Tries have a time complexity for lookups proportional to the string length, regardless of the number of strings stored.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','What is the ''0/1 Knapsack Problem''?','Filling a bag with the maximum number of items','Choosing items with given weights and values to maximize total value in a knapsack with limited capacity, without picking items partially','Sorting items by weight','A problem in networking','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'This is a classic DP problem that cannot be solved correctly with a simple greedy approach.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','Which of these are Minimum Spanning Tree (MST) algorithms?','Prim''s Algorithm','Kruskal''s Algorithm','Bellman-Ford','Floyd-Warshall','["A","B"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',35,'Bellman-Ford and Floyd-Warshall are shortest path algorithms.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','What is ''Backtracking''?','Undo an operation','A refined brute-force approach that builds candidates for the solution and abandons a candidate (''backtracks'') as soon as it determines the candidate cannot lead to a valid solution','Reversing an array','A tool to track users','["B"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'Backtracking is used for puzzles like Sudoku, N-Queens, and crosswords.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','What is a ''Topological Sort''?','Sorting from top to bottom','A linear ordering of vertices such that for every directed edge ''uv'', vertex ''u'' comes before ''v'' in the ordering','Sorting alphabetically','A way to sort files','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Topological sort is only possible in Directed Acyclic Graphs (DAGs), used for dependency resolution.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','What is ''Amortized Analysis''?','Calculating the total time of a program','A method for analyzing the average performance of an operation over a sequence of operations, even if a single operation might be expensive','A way to optimize database memory','A security auditing technique','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'Example: Resizing a dynamic array (like std::vector) is O(n), but amortized over many pushes, it''s O(1).','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','Which algorithm is most suitable for detecting negative cycles in a directed graph?','Dijkstra''s','Bellman-Ford','Prim''s','Kruskal''s','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Bellman-Ford runs for V-1 iterations; a possible decrease in distance during the V-th iteration signifies a negative cycle.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','What is the time complexity of the standard DP solution for the Longest Common Subsequence (LCS) of two strings of length m and n?','O(m+n)','O(mn)','O(min(m,n))','O(m^n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Filling the 2D table of size (m+1)x(n+1) requires quadratic time.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','What is the purpose of ''Path Compression'' in a Disjoint Set Union (DSU) data structure?','To sort the elements','To make all nodes in a set point directly to the root, speeding up subsequent ''Find'' operations','To delete redundant nodes','To merge sets based on their size','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Path compression ensures that tree height remains very small, leading to near-constant amortized time complexity.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','In a ''Segment Tree'', what is the time complexity to perform a point update and a range query?','O(log n) for both','O(1) update, O(n) query','O(n) update, O(log n) query','O(n log n) for both','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Segment trees represent the array in a tree structure allowing logarithmic access to ranges.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','What is the time complexity of Kruskal''s algorithm, assuming an efficient Union-Find implementation?','O(E^2)','O(E log E) or O(E log V)','O(V^2)','O(V log V)','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'The complexity is dominated by sorting the E edges.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','A problem is in the class ''NP'' if:','It can be solved in non-polynomial time','Its solution can be verified in polynomial time','It is Not Polynomial','It can be solved using nested loops only','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'NP (Nondeterministic Polynomial time) means a certificate (solution) can be checked quickly.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','According to the Master Theorem, what is the complexity of T(n) = 2T(n/2) + n?','O(n)','O(n log n)','O(n^2)','O(log n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'This describes Merge Sort, where a=2, b=2, k=1; Since log_b(a) = k, the result is O(n^k log n).','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','Which algorithm finds all-pairs shortest paths in a weighted graph (even with negative edges, but no negative cycles)?','Dijkstra''s','Floyd-Warshall','Bellman-Ford','Johnsons Algorithm','["B","D"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Floyd-Warshall is O(V^3). Johnson''s is better for sparse graphs.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','What is the time complexity of the KMP (Knuth-Morris-Pratt) pattern matching algorithm for a text of length n and pattern m?','O(n * m)','O(n + m)','O(n^2)','O(m^2)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'KMP avoids redundant comparisons by pre-processing the pattern to find proper prefixes that are also suffixes.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','In DP, what identifies an ''Optimal Substructure''?','The solution to a problem contains within it optimal solutions to its subproblems','The problem has only one subproblem','The problem depends on a pivot','The complexity is O(1)','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Optimal substructure and overlapping subproblems are the two requirements for applying DP.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','What makes a ''Fibonacci Heap'' better than a Binary Heap for certain graph algorithms?','Faster deletion always','O(1) amortized time for ''Decrease Key'' operations','Easier implementation','O(log n) search time','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'This makes algorithms like Dijkstra and Prim faster for dense graphs.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','In A* Search, what does the ''Heuristic'' function h(n) estimate?','The cost from the start node to n','The cost from node n to the goal node','The total path cost','The memory usage','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'A* combines actual cost g(n) and heuristic estimate h(n) to prioritize nodes.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','What is a ''B-Tree'' primarily used for?','In-memory caches','File systems and databases to minimize disk reads for large blocks of data','Simple sorting','Expression trees','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'B-Trees are multi-way trees designed to handle large amounts of data efficiently on disk.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','What does ''x & (x - 1)'' achieve in bit manipulation?','Doubles x','Sets the rightmost set bit to 0','Inverts all bits','Checks if x is negative','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'If x & (x-1) == 0, it means x is a power of 2.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','The ''Graham Scan'' is used to solve which problem?','Fast Fourier Transform','Convex Hull of a set of points','Shortest path in a maze','Sorting large files','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It finds the smallest convex polygon that contains all given points in O(n log n) time.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','How many subproblems are solved in the ''Coin Change'' problem (minimum number of coins) given amount ''n'' and ''k'' denominations?','k^n','n','n * k','log n','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'We solve for each value from 1 to n once.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','What property is unique to an ''AVL Tree'' compared to a red-black tree?','It is a binary search tree','The difference between heights of left and right subtrees of any node is at most 1','Nodes are colored','It can have 3 children','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',40,'AVL trees are more strictly balanced than Red-Black trees, making lookups faster but insertions potentially slower.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','What is the time complexity of ''Hopcroft-Karp'' algorithm for finding max bipartite matching?','O(V + E)','O(E * sqrt(V))','O(V^3)','O(V * E)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'It''s faster than the standard augmenting path approach (O(VE)).','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','Which graph algorithm helps find ''Strongly Connected Components'' (SCC)?','Dijkstra''s','Kosaraju''s Algorithm','Prim''s Algorithm','Bellman-Ford','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Kosaraju''s uses two DFS passes to find components where every vertex is reachable from every other vertex.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','The ''Ford-Fulkerson'' method computes what in a network?','Shortest path','Maximum Flow','Minimum spanning tree','Adjacency matrix','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'It finds paths with available residual capacity until no more augmenting paths exist.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','What is the complexity of computing ''n!'' recursively?','O(1)','O(n)','O(n^2)','O(log n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'n calls are made (n, n-1, ..., 1).','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','What is ''Cuckoo Hashing''?','A hash function that mimics birds','An open-addressing scheme with two hash functions where keys can move between two locations to resolve collisions','A ways to compress hash tables','A hash map that deletes old items automatically','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'It achieves O(1) worst-case lookup time.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','What does a ''P vs NP'' question fundamentally ask?','Can deterministic computers do what non-deterministic ones do?','Are complexity classes equal?','Whether every problem whose solution can be quickly verified can also be quickly solved','Is sorting possible in O(n)?','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'It''s one of the greatest unsolved problems in computer science.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','Which sorting algorithm is ''Adaptive'', meaning it speeds up if the data is already partially sorted?','Quick Sort','Insertion Sort','Selection Sort','Merge Sort','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Insertion sort is O(n) for sorted data and very fast for ''nearly sorted'' data.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','In a DAG, why is the ''Sink'' node important for topological sort?','It has no incoming edges','It has no outgoing edges','It is the root','It has the highest degree','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Every DAG has at least one source (in-degree 0) and at least one sink (out-degree 0).','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','What is the main advantage of a ''Splay Tree''?','Always perfectly balanced','Recent accessed items are moved to the root, making repeated access O(1) in practice','It stores hash values instead of keys','It uses no pointers','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Splay trees use ''Splaying'' to move a node to the root upon every access, and provide O(log n) amortized performance.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','Which traversal of a Binary Search Tree produces a sorted list?','Pre-order','In-order','Post-order','Level-order','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'In-order visits Left -> Root -> Right, which for a BST is strictly increasing values.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','What is the time complexity of inserting a node into a skip list?','O(1)','O(n)','O(log n)','O(sqrt n)','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Skip lists use randomization to achieve O(log n) average case performance similar to balanced trees.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','Which technique avoids recursion by manually managing the stack?','Memoization','Iterative Deepening','Tail Recursion','Static Allocation','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Iterative deepening combines DFS depth limits with BFS level exploration.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','What is the time complexity of Prim''s algorithm using an Adjacency Matrix?','O(V + E)','O(V^2)','O(E log V)','O(V log V)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'With an adjacency matrix, we iterate through all V vertices to find the minimum cut edge.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','In a ''Uniform Cost Search'', nodes are expanded based on:','Depth','Path cost from the root','Path cost to the goal','Heuristic estimate','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'It''s essentially Dijkstra''s algorithm for searching for a goal state.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','What is the space complexity of Merge Sort?','O(1)','O(log n)','O(n)','O(n log n)','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Merge sort requires a temporary array of size n to store merged halves.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','The ''Floyd-Warshall'' algorithm uses which strategy?','Greedy','Divide and Conquer','Dynamic Programming','Recurrence','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'It solves the shortest path subproblems for intermediate vertices.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','In a hash table, what does ''Open Addressing'' mean?','Using linked lists inside buckets','Finding another slot in the array itself if a collision occurs','Allowing keys to be public','Automatically resizing the table','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Open addressing probes the array (linear, quadratic, or double hashing).','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','What is the complexity of building a ''Suffix Tree'' for a string of length n?','O(n^2)','O(n)','O(n log n)','O(2^n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Ukkonen’s algorithm builds it in linear time.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','What is a ''Stable'' sort?','A sort that doesn''t use much memory','A sort that maintains the relative order of records with equal keys','A sort that works for both floats and integers','A sort that always has O(n log n) time','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Merge sort is stable; Quick sort is usually not.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','An ''N-ary'' tree is a tree where each node has at most:','2 children','N children','N - 1 children','Unlimited children','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Binary trees are 2-ary trees.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','What is the time complexity of ''Fibonacci Search''?','O(n)','O(log n)','O(sqrt n)','O(n log n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Like binary search, it repeatedly halves the search space but uses Fibonacci numbers to divide the array.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','Which complexity class represents problems solvable in polynomial time?','P','NP','EXPTIME','NP-HARD','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'P stands for Polynomial.','pregenerated'),
('b38023ca-408d-4165-9f87-5a3466f3291f','What is the time complexity of the Floyd-Warshall algorithm?','O(V^2)','O(V^3)','O(V * E)','O(E log V)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'It iterates through all vertices as intermediate, starting, and ending points (V^3).','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What is ''P vs NP''?','A ranking of cloud providers','A major unsolved problem in computer science asking whether every problem whose solution can be quickly verified can also be quickly solved','A comparison between private and public variables','A database synchronization error','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'P problems are solvable in polynomial time; NP problems have solutions verifiable in polynomial time.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What is the ''KMP'' (Knuth-Morris-Pratt) algorithm for?','Sorting large files','Efficient string matching/searching in O(n + m) time','Compressing text','Database indexing','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'KMP avoids redundant comparisons by pre-calculating pattern shifts.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What is a ''B-Tree'' predominantly used for?','UI layout','Disk-based data storage and databases to maintain sorted data and allow efficient search/insert/delete','Binary encryption','Sorting strings in memory','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'B-trees are optimized for systems that read/write large blocks of data.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What is ''Network Flow'' (e.g., Ford-Fulkerson)?','Managing internet traffic','Modeling the movement of material through a network to find the maximum possible flow from a source to a sink','A way to join tables','A styling method for charts','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'Max-flow problems are vital in logistics, capacity planning, and job assignment.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What is ''Bitmask DP''?','Using a mask for security','A dynamic programming technique where integers are used as bitmasks to represent sets, allowing efficient subproblem representation','A bug in the processor','A way to speed up the internet','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'Bitmask DP is commonly used for problems involving subsets or the Traveling Salesman problem for small ''n''.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What does the ''Master Theorem'' provide?','The best code in the world','A closed-form solution for finding the asymptotic time complexity of many divide-and-conquer recurrence relations','The size of a database','A way to name variables','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'It helps solve recurrences like T(n) = aT(n/b) + f(n).','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','Which of these problems are classified as NP-Hard?','Traveling Salesman Problem (TSP)','Knapsack Problem (non-approximated)','Graph Coloring','Binary Search','["A","B","C"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',35,'TSP, Knapsack, and Graph Coloring are classic NP-hard/complete problems. Binary Search is in P.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What is a ''Red-Black Tree''?','A tree with red and black fruits','A type of self-balancing binary search tree that uses node colors to ensure the tree remains approximately balanced during operations','A list of strings','A database synchronization error','["B"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'Red-Black trees are widely used in libraries (e.g., C++ std::map, Java TreeMap) due to their efficient performance.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What is the ''Traveling Salesman Problem'' (TSP)?','A logistics app','Given a list of cities and the distances between each pair, what is the shortest possible route that visits each city exactly once and returns to the origin?','Searching for a person''s name','A way to speed up shipping','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'TSP is an optimization problem that is computationally expensive for large numbers of cities.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What is the purpose of a ''Skip List''?','To skip certain parts of code','A probabilistic data structure that allows O(log n) search, similar to a balanced tree, but implemented using layers of linked lists','A list of strings in an Excel sheet','A way to optimize memory','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'Skip lists are easier to implement than balanced trees and are used in databases like Redis.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What is the time complexity of the Edmonds-Karp algorithm for maximum flow?','O(VE)','O(VE^2)','O(V^3)','O(E log V)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Edmonds-Karp uses BFS to find augmenting paths, ensuring it runs in polynomial time.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','In DP on Trees, what is the ''Centroid'' of a tree?','The root of the tree','A node whose removal results in no component having more than n/2 nodes','The node with the most children','A leaf node with the maximum depth','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Centroid decomposition is used in tree-based problems to achieve O(n log n) total complexity.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','The ''Aho-Corasick'' algorithm is primarily used for:','Matching a single pattern against a text','Finding occurrences of multiple patterns simultaneously in a text','Sorting strings alphabetically','Compressing text files','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It combines a Trie with failure links to achieve linear time complexity relative to text length.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What is a ''Treap''?','A tree with three children','A randomized data structure that maintains both the BST property and the Heap property simultaneously','A list of strings','A way to join tables','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Treaps use random priorities to stay balanced with high probability.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What does ''NP-Complete'' imply for a problem?','It is in P','It is in both NP and NP-Hard','It cannot be verified','It has no solution','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'A solution to an NP-complete problem can be used to solve any NP problem in polynomial time.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What is the result of the ''Max-Flow Min-Cut'' theorem?','Max flow is equal to the sum of all edge weights','The value of the maximum flow in a network is equal to the capacity of the minimum cut','The minimum flow is equal to 0','The max flow is always even','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'This fundamental duality theorem bridges network flow and combinatorial optimization.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933',' ''Heavy-Light Decomposition'' (HLD) is used to handle:','Graph coloring','Path queries and updates in a tree by decomposing it into linear paths','Searching in a hash map','Minimal spanning forest','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'HLD allows operations like path sums or path max to be computed in O(log^2 n).','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What is the time complexity of the Traveling Salesman Problem using Bitmask DP?','O(n!)','O(n^2 * 2^n)','O(2^n)','O(n^3)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'It reduces the factorial complexity to exponential, making it feasible for n up to ~20.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What is the ''Chinese Remainder Theorem'' useful for in Competitive Programming?','Sorting numbers','Solving systems of simultaneous congruences with different moduli','Finding the shortest path','String hashing','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It''s a staple in number theory based algorithmic problems.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','A ''Kd-tree'' is optimized for which operation?','Sorting numbers','Searching for points in k-dimensional space (Nearest Neighbor search)','Maximum flow','Linear regression','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Kd-trees partition space to quickly narrow down the search in multi-dimensional datasets.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','In A* Search, if the heuristic function h(n) is ''Admissible'', what guarantee does it provide?','It will never find a solution','It will always find the optimal (shortest) path','It will use minimal memory','It will be faster than BFS','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Admissibility means h(n) never overestimates the true cost to reach the goal.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What is ''Persistent Segment Tree''?','A tree that is stored on disk forever','A segment tree that allows access to all its previous versions after updates','A segment tree that cannot be modified','A ways to compress segment trees','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'By creating new nodes only for changed branches, it achieves O(log n) versioning.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What is an ''Articulation Point'' in an undirected graph?','The starting vertex','A vertex whose removal increases the number of connected components','A vertex with the highest degree','A vertex connected to all other vertices','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Articulation points (or cut vertices) are critical for graph connectivity.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','Which algorithm computes the ''Longest Palindromic Substring'' in O(n) time?','KMP','Manacher''s Algorithm','Rabin-Karp','Suffix Array','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Manacher''s exploits symmetry to avoid redundant palindrome checks.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','In Dinic''s Algorithm, what is the ''Level Graph'' used for?','Sorting edges','Finding shortest paths in the residual network toward the sink to find multiple augmenting paths efficiently','Storing vertex degrees','Balancing the tree','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Dinic''s uses level graphs to reach the sink through the shortest available routes in each phase.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','In the context of the game Nim, what does the ''Nim-Sum'' determine?','Total number of stones','Winning strategy (XOR sum of pile sizes)','The number of players','The time limit','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'The Sprague-Grundy theorem generalizes this to many impartial games.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What is ''Cook''s Theorem'' (or Cook-Levin theorem)?','Sorting happens in n log n','Boolean Satisfiability Problem (SAT) is NP-Complete','P != NP','Binary search is the fastest search','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It was the first problem proven to be NP-complete.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','A ''Bloom Filter'' provides what type of answer for membership queries?','Always correct','Probabilistic: No false negatives, but potentially false positives','Probabilistic: No false positives, but potentially false negatives','Random guess','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Bloom filters are space-efficient but allow for some errors in set membership tests.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What is the complexity of ''Strassen''s Algorithm'' for matrix multiplication?','O(n^3)','O(n^2.807)','O(n^2)','O(n log n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'It''s theoretically faster than the standard O(n^3) algorithm by reducing the number of multiplications needed.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','The ''Meeting-in-the-middle'' technique is primarily used to:','Sort an array','Reduce the search space from O(2^n) to O(2^(n/2))','Find the middle of a linked list','Connect two servers','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It''s used in problems like Subset Sum or finding paths in a large state space.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What does a ''Sparse Table'' allow for in O(1) time after O(n log n) preprocessing?','Element updates','Range Minimum/Maximum Queries (RMQ)','Sorting','Deleting any element','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Sparse tables are ideal for static range queries on idempotent functions.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','In a Tree, the ''Diameter'' is:','The number of leaves','The longest path between any two nodes in the tree','The height of the tree','The total number of edges','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It can be found in two DFS/BFS passes.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What is ''Rolling Hash'' commonly used for?','Sorting numbers','Rabin-Karp string matching algorithm','Encryption','Memory management','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It allows computing the hash of a window in O(1) time by sliding it across the text.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','A problem is ''NP-Hard'' if:','It is exactly in NP','Every problem in NP can be reduced to it in polynomial time','It is solvable in polynomial time','It has no solution at all','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'NP-hard problems include all of NP but might not be in NP themselves (e.g., they might take even longer).','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What is the complexity of finding the Lowest Common Ancestor (LCA) after preprocessing?','O(n)','O(1) with O(n log n) preprocessing using sparse tables/Euler tour','O(log n) with no preprocessing','O(n^2)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'LCA can be reduced to the Range Minimum Query problem.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What does ''Hall''s Marriage Theorem'' specify?','Number of edges in a tree','Condition for the existence of a perfect matching in a bipartite graph','Complexity of sorting','How to traverse a graph','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It states that for every subset S of one partition, the size of its neighborhood N(S) must be >= |S|.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','Which technique optimizes certain DP solutions from O(n^3) to O(n^2) (e.g., Matrix Chain Multiplication or Optimal BST)?','Convex Hull Trick','Knuth Optimization','Divide and Conquer Optimization','Memoization','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Knuth optimization applies when the optimal split position satisfies monotonicity.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','The ''Iterative Deepening A*'' (IDA*) algorithm is:','A sorting approach','A variation of A* that uses iterative deepening to save memory','A ways to search strings','Only for trees','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It uses the f-cost (g+h) as the limit for depth-first search in each iteration.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What is ''Burnside''s Lemma'' (or Cauchy-Frobenius Lemma) used for?','Maximum flow','Counting distinct objects under symmetry (Pólya Enumeration Theorem foundation)','Number theory proofs','Finding primes','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'It counts the number of orbits of a group action, useful for problems involving rotations/reflections.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What is the time complexity of the algorithm to find the diameter of a tree using DFS?','O(n)','O(n log n)','O(n^2)','O(log n)','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Two DFS searches are sufficient (start from any node, find farthest node X, then find farthest node from X).','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What is the ''Link-Cut Tree''?','A tree made of link lists','A dynamic data structure for maintaining a forest of trees and performing path operations (link, cut, path sum)','A forest that cannot be changed','A database schema','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It achieves O(log n) amortized time for dynamic tree operations.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','Which algorithm is used for ''Fast Fourier Transform'' (FFT) for polynomial multiplication in O(n log n)?','Euclidean Algorithm','Cooley-Tukey Algorithm','Gauss-Jordan Elimination','Binary Search','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'It''s the most common algorithm for computing the discrete Fourier transform.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','In DP, the ''Convex Hull Trick'' is used to optimize transitions of the form dp[i] = min(m[j]*x[i] + c[j]) to:','O(n^2)','O(n log n) or O(n)','O(n^3)','O(log n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'It maintains the lower/upper hull of lines to quickly find the minimum/maximum value for a given x.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','A ''Perfect Matching'' in a graph is a matching that covers:','The maximum number of edges','Every vertex of the graph exactly once','Only the leaves','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'It means every vertex is endpoints of exactly one edge in the matching.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','The ''Fenwick Tree'' (Binary Indexed Tree) is primarily for:','Sorting strings','Efficient prefix sum updates and queries','Maximum flow','Hash map visualization','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'It is easier to implement and uses less memory than a Segment Tree.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','Which problem is the ''p vs np'' prize worth?','$100','$1,000,000 from Clay Mathematics Institute','A free laptop','$0 (prestige only)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'It is one of the seven Millennium Prize Problems.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What is ''Square Root Decomposition''?','Calculating the square root of a list','Dividing an array into blocks of size approximately sqrt(n) to handle range queries in O(sqrt(n))','A way to sort using squares','Calculating square root in constant time','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It is a simpler alternative to segment trees for certain range query problems.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','Which heap allows for O(1) merging of two heaps in the worst case?','Binary Heap','Binomial Heap','Leftist Heap or Skew Heap (amortized)','B-Tree','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Leftist/Skew heaps are mergeable heaps.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What is the complexity of ''Kruskal''s algorithm'' using a simple list of edges and O(V^2) cycle checks?','O(E log E)','O(E * V)','O(V^3)','O(E^2)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Without Union-Find, cycle checking makes the algorithm much slower.','pregenerated'),
('ac2384de-4a71-4f5e-ac09-4ced9cf9a933','What is ''Ternary Search'' used for?','Searching in three arrays','Finding the maximum or minimum of a unimodal function','Sorting letters','Replacing binary search in all cases','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'It works similarly to binary search but divides the search space into three parts.','pregenerated')
