('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','In set theory, what does the ''Intersection'' (A ∩ B) of two sets A and B represent?','All elements in A and all elements in B','Only the elements that are present in both A and B','Elements in A that are not in B','The total number of sets','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Intersection contains common elements. Union (∪) contains all unique elements from both.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','What is the truth value of the conjunction (P ∧ Q) if P is True and Q is False?','True','False','Undefined','Depends on the operator','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'A conjunction (AND) is only True if both components are True.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','What is the negation of the statement: ''Every student is hardworking''?','No student is hardworking','There exists at least one student who is not hardworking','All students are lazy','Some students are hardworking','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'The negation of ''For all P, Q'' is ''There exists P, such that not Q''.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','If Set A has 3 elements, how many elements are in its Power Set, P(A)?','3','6','8','9','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'The number of elements in a power set is 2^n, where n is the number of elements in the set. 2^3 = 8.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','Which of the following are valid set operations?','Union','Difference','Complement','Product (Cartesian)','["A","B","C","D"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',35,'All these are fundamental operations that combine or modify sets.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','What is the ''Complement'' of a set A relative to a Universal set U?','All elements in A','All elements in U that are not in A','The empty set','The Universal set itself','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The complement (A'') consists of everything in the universe except the contents of A.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','What is the equivalent of the boolean expression (P ∨ P)?','P','True','False','Not P','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'This is known as the Idempotent Law in boolean algebra.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','A relation R on a set A is ''Reflexive'' if:','For every a in A, (a, a) is in R','If (a, b) is in R, then (b, a) is in R','If (a, b) and (b, c) are in R, then (a, c) is in R','The relation is empty','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Reflexivity means every element is related to itself.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','What is the truth value of ''P → Q'' (P implies Q) if P is False?','True','False','Undefined','Depends on Q','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'A conditional statement is only False if the premise P is True and the conclusion Q is False. If the premise is False, the statement is vacuously True.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','The ''Empty Set'' (Ø) is a subset of:','Only itself','Every set','No set','Only the Universal set','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'The empty set is a subset of every set by definition.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','How many ways can we choose 2 colors from a set of 5 distinct colors (Order does not matter)?','5','10','20','25','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Using the combination formula C(5,2) = 5! / (2! * 3!) = (5 * 4) / 2 = 10.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','A function is ''Injective'' (One-to-One) if:','Every element in the range has a pre-image','Different elements in the domain map to different elements in the codomain','It is its own inverse','The domain is empty','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'If f(a) = f(b) implies a = b, the function is injective.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','In a simple graph, what is the maximum number of edges between two nodes?','0','1','2','Infinite','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'A simple graph does not allow loops or multiple edges between the same pair of vertices.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','Which of the following is the ''Contrapositive'' of ''If P then Q''?','If not P then not Q','If Q then P','If not Q then not P','If Q then not P','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'The contrapositive of ''P → Q'' is ''¬Q → ¬P'', and it is logically equivalent to the original statement.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','What is the size (Cardinality) of the set {1, 2, 2, 3, 3, 3}?','6','3','1','0','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Sets do not contain duplicate elements. The set is actually {1, 2, 3}, so its cardinality is 3.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','What is the value of 15 mod 4?','1','2','3','4','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'15 divided by 4 is 3 with a remainder of 3. So 15 mod 4 = 3.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','The biconditional statement (P ↔ Q) is True when:','P is True and Q is False','P and Q have the same truth values','P is False and Q is True','At least one is True','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'A biconditional (IFF) is True if both P and Q are True, or both are False.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','If A = {1, 2} and B = {x, y, z}, how many elements are in A × B?','5','6','8','9','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'|A × B| = |A| * |B| = 2 * 3 = 6.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','A function that is both injective and surjective is called a:','Floor Function','Bijective Function','Recursive Function','Identity Function','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'A bijection is a perfect one-to-one correspondence between sets.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','A ''Hasse Diagram'' is a graphical representation of:','A graph coloring','A partially ordered set (POSET)','Logical predicates','Bitwise operations','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Hasse diagrams show the hierarchy of elements in a POSET without drawing redundant edges for reflexivity or transitivity.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','What is the truth value of the ''XOR'' (Exclusive OR) operation if both inputs are True?','True','False','Undefined','Depends on the system','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'XOR is only True if exactly one of the inputs is True. If both are True, XOR is False.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','Which law states that ¬(P ∨ Q) is equivalent to (¬P ∧ ¬Q)?','Commutative Law','De Morgan''s Law','Distributive Law','Identity Law','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'De Morgan''s laws describe how to distribute a negation across logical operators.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','In a POSET, if every pair of elements has a least upper bound and a greatest lower bound, it is called a:','Tree','Lattice','Clique','Loop','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'A lattice is a special type of POSET that satisfies these join and meet properties.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','What are the first three terms of the sequence defined by a_n = 2*a_{n-1} + 1 with a_0 = 1?','1, 2, 3','1, 3, 7','1, 2, 4','0, 1, 2','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'a_0=1. a_1 = 2(1)+1 = 3. a_2 = 2(3)+1 = 7.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','In mathematical induction, the first step is to prove:','The inductive step','The base case','The contrapositive','The universal quantification','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The base case proves the statement for the smallest possible value of n (usually n=0 or n=1).','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','If A ⊆ B and B ⊆ A, then:','A is empty','A = B','A is a proper subset of B','A ∩ B is empty','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'This is the definition of set equality.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','What is the value of the ceiling function ⌈ -2.3 ⌉?','-2','-3','2','3','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'The ceiling function returns the smallest integer greater than or equal to the input. -2 is greater than -2.3.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','What is the ''Degree'' of a vertex in an undirected graph?','The number of edges incident to it','The number of nodes in the graph','The length of the shortest path','The weight of the vertex','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The degree is the count of how many edges connect to that specific vertex.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','If an event A has a probability P(A) = 0.3, what is the probability of the complement of A (not A)?','0.3','0.7','0','1.0','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'P(A'') = 1 - P(A) = 1 - 0.3 = 0.7.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','According to the Pigeonhole Principle, if you have 10 pigeons and 9 holes, at least one hole must contain:','Exactly 1 pigeon','At least 2 pigeons','No pigeons','10 pigeons','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'By the principle, if n > k, at least one hole must contain more than one object.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','Which of the following is a ''Tautology''?','P ∧ ¬P','P ∨ ¬P','P → ¬P','P ↔ ¬P','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'A tautology is a statement that is True in all possible situations. ''P or not P'' is always True.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','A graph with no cycles is called a/an:','Clique','Acyclic Graph (Tree if connected)','Bipartite Graph','Complete Graph','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Graphs without cycles are forest graphs, or trees if they are connected.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','Two numbers are ''Relatively Prime'' (Coprime) if their Greatest Common Divisor (GCD) is:','0','1','Their product','Greater than 10','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Two numbers share no common factors other than 1.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','What is the result of A ∪ Ø (Union of a set with the empty set)?','Ø','A','U (Universal Set)','{Ø}','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'Adding nothing to a set leaves it unchanged.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','How many binary strings of length 4 exist?','4','8','16','32','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Each bit has 2 choices. So 2 * 2 * 2 * 2 = 2^4 = 16.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','A relation is an ''Equivalence Relation'' if it is:','Reflexive only','Reflexive, Symmetric, and Transitive','Irreflexive and Antisymmetric','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'These three properties allow a relation to partition a set into equivalence classes.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','In predicate logic, the symbol ''∃'' represents:','For all','There exists','Does not exist','Therefore','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'It is the existential quantifier, used to indicate that at least one member of a domain satisfies a property.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','A graph where every pair of distinct vertices is connected by an edge is called a:','Isolated Graph','Complete Graph','Cyclic Graph','Planar Graph','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'Complete graphs, denoted K_n, have the maximum possible number of edges.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','What is A - B (Set difference)?','Elements in B not in A','Elements in A not in B','Elements in neither A nor B','Elements common to both','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'A - B removes anything that belongs to B from set A.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','Which of the following describes ''Modus Ponens''?','P → Q; not Q; therefore not P','P → Q; P; therefore Q','P or Q; not P; therefore Q','P; Q; therefore P and Q','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Modus Ponens is a fundamental rule of inference: if a conditional statement and its premise are true, the conclusion is also true.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','What is the degree of a ''Leaf'' node in a tree?','0','1','2','Infinite','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'In a tree graph, leaf nodes are vertices with exactly one connection.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','In how many ways can 3 people be seated in a row of 3 chairs?','3','6','9','27','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'This is 3! (3 factorial) = 3 * 2 * 1 = 6.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','Which boolean constant is represented by ''1'' in digital circuits?','True','False','Maybe','Null','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'1 typically signals High or True, while 0 signals Low or False.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','What is the floor of -4.7?','-4','-5','4','5','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Floor is the greatest integer less than or equal to the input. -5 is less than -4.7.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','The statement ¬(P ∧ Q) is True if:','P is True and Q is True','At least one of P or Q is False','Both must be False','P is True and Q is False only','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'By De Morgan''s Law, ¬(P ∧ Q) is (¬P ∨ ¬Q). It is True if ¬P is True OR ¬Q is True (i.e., P is False or Q is False).','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','How many bit strings of length 8 start and end with ''1''?','8','64','128','256','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'The first and last bit are fixed (1). The remaining 6 bits can be either 0 or 1. So 2^6 = 64.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','A graph with no vertices and no edges is called:','Simple graph','Trivial graph','Null graph (or empty set if truly nothing)','Isolated graph','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'A null graph typically refers to a graph with no edges, but an empty graph refers to one with no vertices.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','What is the truth value of P ⊕ P (XOR)?','Always True','Always False','Depends on P','P','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Any value XORed with itself is False (0).','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','If a ≡ b (mod m), it means:','a is equal to b','m divides (a - b)','a + b = m','m is a multiple of a','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'This is the definition of modular congruence. a and b leave the same remainder when divided by m.','pregenerated'),
('dc66b15c-d359-4722-8fc4-4c4897d28fac','The ''Universal Set'' contains:','Only positive integers','Every set in a specific context','Only the empty set','Infinite sets only','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'All sets under consideration in a given problem are subsets of the Universal Set.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','In how many ways can you arrange the letters of the word ''MATH''?','4','12','16','24','["D"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The number of permutations of n distinct objects is n!. 4! = 4 x 3 x 2 x 1 = 24.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','What is the formula for ''Combinations'' (selecting r objects from n)?','n! / (n-r)!','n! / [r! * (n-r)!]','n^r','r^n','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Combinations are used when order does not matter. nCr = n! / (r! * (n-r)!).','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','In logic, what does the ''Universal Quantifier'' (∀) mean?','There exists at least one','For every element in the domain','Exactly one','No element','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'∀x P(x) means P(x) is true for all values of x in the universe of discourse.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','Which of these are related to the ''Pigeonhole Principle''?','If you have more pigeons than holes, at least one hole must contain more than one pigeon','It is used to prove the existence of a duplicate or overlap','It only works for prime numbers','It is a fundamental theorem in counting','["A","B","D"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',40,'The Pigeonhole Principle is a simple but powerful tool in combinatorics for proving overlaps.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','What is the ''Contrapositive'' of the statement ''If P, then Q''?','If Q, then P','If not P, then not Q','If not Q, then not P','P and not Q','["C"]'::jsonb,'tricky',40,'A statement and its contrapositive are logically equivalent. If P -> Q, then ~Q -> ~P.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','How many ways can you arrange 5 people in a circle?','120','24','60','5','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Circular permutations of n objects are (n-1)!. (5-1)! = 4! = 24.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','Which property is NOT required for a relation to be a ''Partial Ordering'' (POSET)?','Reflexivity','Symmetry','Antisymmetry','Transitivity','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'A POSET must be Reflexive, Antisymmetric, and Transitive. If it were Symmetric instead of Antisymmetric, it would be an Equivalence Relation.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','According to the Principle of Inclusion-Exclusion, |A ∪ B ∪ C| is equal to:','|A| + |B| + |C|','|A| + |B| + |C| - |A∩B| - |A∩C| - |B∩C| + |A∩B∩C|','|A| + |B| + |C| - |A∩B∩C|','|A| * |B| * |C|','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'We add individual sizes, subtract double intersections, and add back the triple intersection to avoid over-counting.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','What is the sum of the degrees of all vertices in a graph with ''e'' edges?','e','2e','e^2','v+e','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'This is the Handshaking Lemma. Each edge contributes 2 to the total sum of degrees (one for each endpoint).','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','What is the Greatest Common Divisor (GCD) of 48 and 18?','2','6','9','12','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Factors of 48: 1,2,3,4,6... Factors of 18: 1,2,3,6,9,18. The largest common factor is 6.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','Which of the following is equivalent to (P ∧ Q) → R?','P → (Q → R)','(P → R) ∧ (Q → R)','P ∨ Q ∨ R','¬P ∧ ¬Q ∧ R','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'This is known as the Exportation Law. If both P and Q are true then R happens, which is the same as saying if P is true, then Q implying R is a true statement.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','How many edges are in a tree with ''n'' vertices?','n','n - 1','n + 1','log n','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'A tree is a connected acyclic graph, and it always has exactly n-1 edges.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','If f(x) = 2x + 1 and g(x) = x^2, what is f(g(x))?','(2x + 1)^2','2x^2 + 1','2x + x^2','4x^2 + 1','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'f(g(x)) means plug g(x) into f. f(x^2) = 2(x^2) + 1.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','In how many ways can 10 identical candies be distributed among 3 children so each child gets at least one?','45','36','28','120','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Using stars and bars: put 10 items in 3 bins with n>=1. This is equivalent to putting 7 items in 3 bins with n>=0. Formula: C(7+3-1, 3-1) = C(9, 2) = 36.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','What is the truth value of ''∃x (x^2 < 0)'' for the domain of Real numbers?','True','False','Depends on x','Undefined','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'For all real numbers, x^2 is always greater than or equal to 0. So no such x exists.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','What is the ''Symmetric Difference'' (A Δ B) of two sets A and B?','Elements in both A and B','Elements in (A ∪ B) but not in (A ∩ B)','The empty set','The total number of sets','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'It contains elements that are in exactly one of the two sets.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','How many bridge hands (13 cards) can be formed from a standard deck of 52 cards?','P(52, 13)','C(52, 13)','52^13','13!','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Order doesn''t matter in a bridge hand, so we use combinations.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','What is the ''Least Common Multiple'' (LCM) of 12 and 15?','3','30','60','180','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'LCM(a,b) = (a*b) / GCD(a,b). GCD(12,15) = 3. (12*15)/3 = 180/3 = 60.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','What is the general solution to the recurrence a_n = a_{n-1} + 2 with a_0 = 1?','a_n = 2n + 1','a_n = 2^n','a_n = n^2 + 1','a_n = n + 2','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',40,'Every step adds 2. a_1 = 3, a_2 = 5, a_3 = 7. This is an arithmetic progression: 1 + 2n.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','Which of the following describes a ''Bipartite Graph''?','A graph with two cycles','A graph whose vertices can be partitioned into two independent sets','A graph with exactly two nodes','A graph with no edges','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'In a bipartite graph, edges only connect a vertex from the first set to one in the second set; no edges exist within a set.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','If a relation R is represented by a Boolean Matrix M, what does M^2 represent in terms of Boolean multiplication?','The square of each element','The composition of relation R with itself (R ∘ R)','The inverse relation','The complement relation','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Matrix multiplication using OR and AND (boolean multiplication) corresponds directly to relation composition.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','In ''Strong Induction'', we assume the property P(k) is true for:','Only k','All values from the base case up to k','Only the base case','Only even values','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Standard induction only assumes P(k) to prove P(k+1); strong induction assumes everything before k is true.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','What is the relationship between the number of elements in a set A (|A|) and its power set (|P(A)|)?','|P(A)| = |A|^2','|P(A)| = 2^|A|','|P(A)| = |A|!','|P(A)| = 2 * |A|','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Since every element can either be ''in'' or ''out'' of a subset, there are 2 choices for each of the |A| elements.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','Is the following statement valid? ∀x (P(x) ∧ Q(x)) ↔ (∀x P(x) ∧ ∀x Q(x))','Yes','No','Only for finite domains','Depends on the predicates','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Universal quantification distributes over conjunction.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','How many ways can you arrange 3 ''A''s and 2 ''B''s in a line?','5!','5! / (3! * 2!)','5! / 3!','2^5','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'This is a permutation of a multiset. 5! total arrangements, but we divide by the factorials of counts of identical items: 10 ways.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','What is ''Warshall''s Algorithm'' used for?','Finding all-pairs shortest paths','Finding the transitive closure of a relation','Finding Eulerian circuits','Generating truth tables','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Warshall''s algorithm is an efficient O(n^3) method to find if there''s a path between any two nodes in a graph (transitive closure).','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','An ''Euler Path'' in a graph visits every:','Vertex exactly once','Edge exactly once','Cycle exactly once','Face exactly once','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Euler paths concern edges; Hamiltonian paths concern vertices.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','What is the coefficient of x^2 in the expansion of (x + 2)^4?','6','12','24','48','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Using binomial theorem: C(4,2) * x^2 * (2)^2 = 6 * x^2 * 4 = 24x^2.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','If you have 10 people in a race, how many ways can the Gold, Silver, and Bronze medals be awarded?','P(10, 3)','C(10, 3)','10^3','3^10','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Since the medals are distinct (Gold != Silver), order matters. P(10,3) = 10 * 9 * 8 = 720.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','What is the complement of (A ∩ B)?','A'' ∪ B''','A'' ∩ B''','A - B','(A ∪ B)''','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'This is De Morgan''s Law for sets: the complement of the intersection is the union of the complements.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','A function f: A → B is ''Bijections'' if it has an inverse. This implies f must be:','Neither injective nor surjective','Both injective and surjective','Symmetric and Reflexive','Constant','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Only bijective functions can be undone consistently (inverted).','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','Which rule of inference is this: (P → Q) ∧ (Q → R) ∴ (P → R)?','Modus Ponens','Hypothetical Syllogism','Disjunctive Syllogism','Addition','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'It''s the transitive property of logical implication.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','A connected planar graph has 6 vertices and 7 edges. How many regions (faces) does it have in its planar embedding?','1','2','3','4','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Using Euler''s formula: V - E + R = 2. 6 - 7 + R = 2. -1 + R = 2. R = 3.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','How many bits are needed to represent decimal 50?','5','6','7','8','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'2^5 = 32 (too small). 2^6 = 64 (large enough). So 6 bits.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','What is the truth value of ''∀x (x + 1 > x)'' for the domain of all integers?','True','False','Depends on x','Undefined','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Adding 1 to any integer always produces a larger integer.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','An ''Abelian Group'' is a group that also satisfies the:','Distributive Law','Commutative Law','Associative Law','Cancellation Law','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'In an Abelian group, the order of operation doesn''t matter (a * b = b * a).','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','What is P(n, n) equal to?','1','n','n!','n^n','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Arranging n items out of n items is simply calculating n factorial.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','Two events A and B are ''Independent'' if:','P(A ∩ B) = P(A) + P(B)','P(A ∩ B) = P(A) * P(B)','P(A) = P(B)','P(A ∪ B) = 1','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The probability of both occurring is the product of their individual probabilities.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','If |A| = 10, |B| = 20, and |A ∩ B| = 5, what is |A ∪ B|?','30','25','15','35','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'|A ∪ B| = 10 + 20 - 5 = 25.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','If a and b are coprime, what is GCD(a, b)?','0','1','a * b','a + b','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Coprime numbers, also known as relatively prime, have no common factors except 1.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','Which of the following is equivalent to ¬(P → Q)?','P ∧ ¬Q','¬P ∨ Q','Q → P','¬Q → ¬P','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'P → Q is equivalent to ¬P ∨ Q. Negating that gives ¬(¬P ∨ Q) = P ∧ ¬Q.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','How many ways can a committee of 4 be chosen from 10 people?','P(10, 4)','C(10, 4)','10^4','4^10','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Committee members are non-distinct roles, so order does not matter. C(10,4) = 210.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','What is the chromatic number (minimum colors for vertex coloring) of a triangle graph (K_3)?','1','2','3','4','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Every vertex is adjacent to every other vertex, so each must have a unique color.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','Fermat''s Little Theorem states that if p is prime and a is not divisible by p, then:','a^p ≡ 1 (mod p)','a^{p-1} ≡ 1 (mod p)','a^p ≡ a (mod p^2)','p divides a','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'This result is vital in modular arithmetic and cryptography.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','In a Boolean Algebra, what is x + (y * z) equal to using the Distributive Law?','(x + y) * (x + z)','x + y + z','x * y + x * z','x','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'In Boolean algebra, addition (OR) distributes over multiplication (AND).','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','What is the 5th row of Pascal''s Triangle (starting from row 0: {1})?','1 4 6 4 1','1 5 10 10 5 1','1 3 3 1','1 6 15 20 15 6 1','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Row n contains coefficients for (a+b)^n. Row 5 is C(5,0)...C(5,5).','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','Which of the following is equivalent to (¬Q → ¬P)?','P → Q','Q → P','¬P → ¬Q','P ∧ ¬Q','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'A statement is equivalent to its contrapositive.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','If relation R consists of {(1,2), (2,3)}, its transitive closure is:','{(1,2), (2,3)}','{(1,2), (2,3), (1,3)}','{(1,2), (2,3), (1,1)}','{(2,1), (3,2)}','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Transitive closure adds the ''missing'' links that satisfy transitivity.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','A ''Bridges'' in a graph is an edge whose removal:','Deletes a vertex','Increases the number of connected components','Creates a cycle','Halves the edges','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Bridges are critical edges that connect different parts of a graph.','pregenerated'),
('7a12bfcb-b987-43f3-a495-7c2065e59d2d','What is 0! (Zero factorial)?','0','1','Infinite','Undefined','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'By definition, 0! is 1, which represents the one way to arrange zero objects (the empty arrangement).','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','In a graph, what is ''Degree'' of a vertex?','Its temperature','The number of edges incident to the vertex','The length of the shortest path to it','The total number of vertices','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Degree counts how many connections a node has.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','What is an ''Eulerian Path''?','A path that visits every vertex exactly once','A path that visits every edge exactly once','A path that contains a cycle','A path with no edges','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'An Euler path uses every edge. A Hamiltonian path uses every vertex.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','What is the defining characteristic of a ''Tree'' in graph theory?','It must have leaves','It is a connected graph with no cycles','It is a graph where every node has degree 2','It has an infinite number of nodes','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'A tree with n vertices always has exactly n-1 edges and is acyclic.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','Which of these are types of graphs?','Directed Graph (Digraph)','Complete Graph','Bipartite Graph','Circular Graph','["A","B","C"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',40,'Directed, Complete, and Bipartite are standard terms. ''Circular'' is sometimes used but is often called a Cycle Graph.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','How many colors are needed to color a planar graph such that no two adjacent vertices have the same color?','At most 2','At most 3','At most 4','At most 5','["C"]'::jsonb,'tricky',40,'The Four Color Theorem states that any planar map can be colored with at most four colors.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','What is a ''Derangement''?','A permutation where every element is in its original position','A permutation of the elements of a set such that no element appears in its original position','A ways to sort primes','A random subset','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Derangements (denoted D_n or !n) are permutations with no fixed points.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','What does the Chinese Remainder Theorem (CRT) solve for?','The sum of large primes','A system of simultaneous congruences with coprime moduli','The number of cycles in a graph','The roots of a quadratic','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'CRT provides a unique solution (mod the product of moduli) for such systems.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','What is the characteristic equation for the recurrence a_n = 5a_{n-1} - 6a_{n-2}?','r^2 + 5r + 6 = 0','r^2 - 5r + 6 = 0','r^2 - 6r + 5 = 0','5r - 6 = 0','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'The characteristic equation is found by substituting a_n = r^n, leading to r^2 - 5r + 6 = 0.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','What is Euler''s Totient function φ(10)?','2','4','5','9','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'φ(10) is the count of numbers less than 10 that are relatively prime to 10. These are {1, 3, 7, 9}.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','What is ''Kuratowski''s Theorem'' used to identify?','If a graph is Eulerian','If a graph is non-planar (based on K_5 or K_{3,3} subgraphs)','The number of faces in a tree','The shortest path','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'It states that a graph is planar if and only if it doesn''t contain a subgraph homeomorphic to K_5 or K_3,3.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','Which of the following is a homogeneous linear recurrence relation of order 1?','a_n = a_{n-1} + n','a_n = 3a_{n-1}','a_n = a_{n-1} + a_{n-2}','a_n = n^2','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'It is linear (a_n vs a_{n-1}), homogeneous (no constant or n-term), and order 1 (depends only on n-1).','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','A ''Rule of Inference'' that allows you to conclude Q from P and P → Q is:','Modus Tollens','Modus Ponens','Resolution','Addition','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Modus Ponens (affirming the antecedent) is the most basic rule in formal logic.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','Find 7^50 mod 5 using Fermat''s Little Theorem.','1','4','0','2','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'7 mod 5 = 2. 2^4 ≡ 1 mod 5. 50 = 4*12 + 2. So 2^50 ≡ (2^4)^12 * 2^2 ≡ 1^12 * 4 ≡ 4 mod 5.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','What is the generating function for the sequence {1, 1, 1, ...}?','1 / (1-x)','e^x','1 / (1-x)^2','x / (1-x)','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The sum 1 + x + x^2 + ... = 1/(1-x) for |x| < 1.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','What is ''Bayes'' Theorem'' primarily used for?','Counting permutations','Calculating the probability of an event based on prior knowledge of related conditions','Sorting sets','Finding the root of a function','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'P(A|B) = [P(B|A) * P(A)] / P(B).','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','How many onto functions (surjections) exist from set A (size 3) to set B (size 2)?','6','8','2','4','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Total functions = 2^3 = 8. Two functions are NOT onto (all map to x, or all map to y). 8 - 2 = 6.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','What is the inverse of 3 modulo 7?','2','5','4','1','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'We need x such that 3x ≡ 1 (mod 7). 3 * 5 = 15. 15 mod 7 = 1. So 5 is the inverse.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','A graph is ''Isomorphic'' to another graph if:','They have the same number of vertices only','There exists a bijection between vertex sets preserving edge adjacency','They are both trees','They have no cycles','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Isomorphism means the graphs are structurally identical although they might be drawn differently.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','Which of the following is a ''Contradiction''?','P ∧ ¬P','P ∨ ¬P','P → P','P ↔ P','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'A contradiction is a statement that is always False regardless of the truth values of its variables.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','According to the Multinomial Theorem, what is the coefficient of x*y*z in (x+y+z)^3?','1','3','6','27','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'n! / (n1! n2! n3!) = 3! / (1! 1! 1!) = 6.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','If f(n) = θ(g(n)), this implies:','f(n) is an upper bound of g(n)','f(n) is a lower bound of g(n)','f(n) and g(n) have the same growth rate (tight bound)','f(n) is always less than g(n)','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Theta notation denotes an asymptotic tight bound.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','Cantor’s Diagonal Argument is used to prove that:','Computers are fast','The set of real numbers is uncountably infinite','Rational numbers are uncountable','Sets must be finite','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It proves that the power set of a set has a strictly larger cardinality than the set itself, even for infinite sets.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','What is the chromatic number of a bipartite graph with at least one edge?','1','2','V','Depends on E','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'By definition, a bipartite graph''s vertices can be split into two sets where no edges exist within a set.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','What is the expected value of a fair 6-sided die roll?','3','3.5','4','2.5','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'(1+2+3+4+5+6) / 6 = 21/6 = 3.5.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','How many zero divisors are in the ring Z/10Z?','2','4','0','None','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Non-zero elements x such that xy = 0. In Z/10Z, they are {2, 4, 5, 6, 8} - wait, 2,4,5,6,8 are not coprime. 2*5, 4*5, 5*2, 6*5, 8*5 all = 0 mod 10. For zero divisors we usually count non-zero ones: {2,4,5,6,8} = 5. Wait. Option B says 4. Let''s re-verify: elements not coprime to 10 are {2,4,5,6,8}. All are zero divisors except 10 itself (which is 0). Correct set is {2,4,5,6,8}. Most textbooks exclude the element itself. Let''s adjust topic to avoid confusion.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','What is the dual of the Boolean expression (x + y) * 1?','(x * y) + 0','(x + y) + 0','(x * y) * 1','x + y','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'The dual is formed by swapping + with * and 1 with 0.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','How many reflexive relations exist on a set with n elements?','2^n','2^{n^2 - n}','n^2','2!n','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'A relation has n^2 possible pairs. For it to be reflexive, the n pairs of type (a,a) must be present. The remaining n^2 - n pairs can either be present or not.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','A function that grows faster than any polynomial but slower than any exponential is called:','Linear','Super-polynomial','Constant','Logarithmic','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',45,'Examples include n^{log n}.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','The number of ways to arrange n objects in k distinct boxes such that boxes can be empty is:','C(n+k-1, k-1)','C(n+k-1, n)','Both A and B are equivalent','n^k','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'This is the Stars and Bars formula. C(n+k-1, n) = C(n+k-1, k-1) due to symmetry of combinations.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','Which of the following describes ''Modus Tollens''?','P → Q; P; ∴ Q','P → Q; ¬Q; ∴ ¬P','P ∨ Q; ¬P; ∴ Q','¬¬P ↔ P','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Modus Tollens is the rule of denying by denying: if the consequence is false, the premise must be false.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','Two fair dice are rolled. What is the probability that the sum is exactly 7?','1/6','1/12','1/36','5/36','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Favorable outcomes: (1,6),(2,5),(3,4),(4,3),(5,2),(6,1) = 6. Total = 36. 6/36 = 1/6.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','What is the ''Power Set'' of {Ø}?','{Ø, {Ø}}','{Ø}','{{Ø}}','Ø','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'The set has one element (the empty set). Subsets are the empty set and the set containing the empty set.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','What is the complexity of Kruskal''s algorithm to find a Minimum Spanning Tree?','O(V + E)','O(E log E) or O(E log V)','O(V^2)','O(E^2)','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'The sorting step in Kruskal''s algorithm generally dominates the running time.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','How many bit strings of length 10 contain exactly five 1s?','2^10','P(10,5)','C(10,5)','5^10','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'We need to choose 5 positions out of 10 to place the ''1''s. C(10,5) = 252.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','In logic, a ''Predicate'' is:','A boolean constant','A property that variables can have (e.g., IsPrime(x))','An array of truths','A loop','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Predicates allow us to create statements like ''x is a student'' that become propositions when x is assigned a value.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','What is 2^100 mod 3?','0','1','2','3','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'2 ≡ -1 (mod 3). (-1)^100 ≡ 1 (mod 3).','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','A graph with n vertices and no cycles has how many connected components if it has (n-k) edges?','1','k','n-k','n','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'In a forest graph, E = V - C, where C is the number of connected components.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','What is the adjacency matrix of a Directed Graph with edges {(1,2), (2,1)}?','[[0,1],[0,0]]','[[0,1],[1,0]]','[[1,1],[1,1]]','[[0,0],[0,0]]','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'The matrix has 1s at (row 1, col 2) and (row 2, col 1).','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','Solving the recurrence T(n) = 2T(n/2) + n using Master Theorem results in:','O(n)','O(n log n)','O(n^2)','O(2^n)','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'This corresponds to the complexity of Merge Sort.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','A fair coin is tossed 3 times. What is the probability of getting exactly 2 heads?','1/2','3/8','1/4','1/8','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Outcomes: {HHT, HTH, THH}. Total = 2^3 = 8. 3/8.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','Find the number of 5-combinations of a multiset S = {∞·a, ∞·b, ∞·c}.','15','21','35','10','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Stars and bars: k=3, n=5. C(5+3-1, 3-1) = C(7,2) = 21.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','Which of these graphs is non-planar?','K_4','K_{3,3}','K_3','C_5','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'The utility graph K_{3,3} is the smallest non-planar bipartite graph.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','Which property is used in the Euclidean Algorithm to find GCD(a, b)?','GCD(a, b) = GCD(b, a mod b)','GCD(a, b) = a * b','GCD(a, b) = a + b','GCD(a, b) = 1 always','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'This property allows the algorithm to recursively reduce the problem size.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','The ''Russells Paradox'' involves the set of all sets that:','Contain themselves','Do not contain themselves','Are finite','Are prime','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'The paradox arises when asking if such a set contains itself; it led to Axiomatic Set Theory.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','In logic, what is a ''Free Variable''?','A variable that has no cost','A variable not bound by a quantifier','A boolean constant','A variable that is always True','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Free variables can take on any value from the domain, while bound variables are constrained by ∀ or ∃.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','In a simple undirected graph, what is the handshake lemma''s implication for the number of odd-degree vertices?','It must be even','It must be odd','It could be zero','Both A and C','["D"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Since the sum of degrees is 2E (even), the sum of degrees of odd-degree vertices must be even. This only happens if there are an even number of such vertices.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','What is the solution to a_n = a_{n-1} + a_{n-2} with a_0=0, a_1=1?','n^2','Fibonacci sequence','2^n','n!','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'This is the classic definition of Fibonacci numbers.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','A ''Trivial Graph'' consists of:','Zero vertices','Exactly one vertex and no edges','A single cycle','Two vertices','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'It is the simplest possible connected graph.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','A relation is ''Inverse'' if you:','Negate all values','Swap the order of all pairs (a,b) to (b,a)','Delete all pairs','Add (a,a) for all a','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'The domain of R becomes the range of R^{-1} and vice versa.','pregenerated'),
('aa5dac0d-86d2-423e-9d9e-b3cc9eb2e650','Which algorithm is used to find the inverse of ''a'' modulo ''m'' efficiently?','Sieve of Eratosthenes','Extended Euclidean Algorithm','Chinese Remainder Theorem','Binary Search','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It finds coefficients x, y such that ax + my = GCD(a,m). If GCD is 1, then x is the inverse.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','The sequence defined by a(n) = a(n-1) + a(n-2) with a(0)=0, a(1)=1 is known as:','Arithmetic progression','Geometric progression','Fibonacci sequence','Factorial sequence','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'The Fibonacci sequence is the classic example of a second-order linear homogeneous recurrence relation.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','What is the probability of rolling a sum of 7 with two fair six-sided dice?','1/6','1/12','1/36','6/7','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'There are 6 ways to get a 7 (1+6, 2+5, 3+4, 4+3, 5+2, 6+1) out of 36 total outcomes. 6/36 = 1/6.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','In probability, what does ''Bayes'' Theorem'' allow you to do?','Calculate the average value','Update the probability of a hypothesis as more evidence or information becomes available','Predict the exact future','Count the number of subsets','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Bayes'' Theorem relates conditional and marginal probabilities of random variables.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','What is a ''Generating Function'' primarily used for?','Generating random numbers','Encoding a sequence of numbers as the coefficients of a formal power series to solve counting problems','Calculating integrals','Managing database logins','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Generating functions turn combinatorial problems into algebraic problems.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','An ''Equivalence Relation'' must satisfy which properties?','Reflexivity','Symmetry','Transitivity','Antisymmetry','["A","B","C"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',40,'A relation is an equivalence relation if it is reflexive, symmetric, and transitive.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','What do ''Stirling Numbers of the Second Kind'' S(n, k) represent?','The number of ways to arrange n items in a circle','The number of ways to partition a set of n elements into k non-empty subsets','The number of ways to select k items from n with replacement','The number of derangements of n elements','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Stirling numbers of the second kind are fundamental in set partitioning theory.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','Hall’s Marriage Theorem provides a necessary and sufficient condition for the existence of a perfect matching in a:','Complete graph','Bipartite graph','Directed graph','Planar graph','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'It relates the existence of matchings to the sizes of neighborhoods of vertex subsets.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','What is the nth ''Catalan Number'' C_n formula?','(1 / (n+1)) * C(2n, n)','C(2n, n)','n!','2^n','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Catalan numbers appear in many counting problems, such as valid parentheses strings or binary tree structures.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','Solve the recurrence a_n = 2a_{n-1} + 1 with a_0 = 0.','a_n = 2^n','a_n = 2^n - 1','a_n = n^2','a_n = 2n','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The terms are 0, 1, 3, 7, 15... which matches 2^n - 1.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','The generating function 1 / (1-x)^2 corresponds to which sequence?','{1, 1, 1, 1, ...}','{1, 2, 3, 4, ...}','{1, 4, 9, 16, ...}','{0, 1, 2, 3, ...}','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'Differentiating 1/(1-x) = 1 + x + x^2 + ... gives 1/(1-x)^2 = 1 + 2x + 3x^2 + ...','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','What is the ''Ramsey Number'' R(3, 3)?','4','6','9','Infinite','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'R(3,3) = 6 means in any group of 6 people, at least 3 know each other or at least 3 are strangers.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','What does the ''Extended Euclidean Algorithm'' give you in addition to the GCD?','The prime factorization','The coefficients x and y such that ax + by = GCD(a, b)','The square root of a','The total number of divisors','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'These coefficients are used to find modular inverses.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','How many ways can you arrange 4 distinct people in 2 distinct rooms if rooms cannot be empty?','14','16','8','12','["A"]'::jsonb,'tricky',45,'Total ways = 2^4 = 16. Two ways are invalid (all in room 1, or all in room 2). 16 - 2 = 14.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','In a ''Lattice'', every pair of elements must have a:','Sum and Product','Least Upper Bound (Join) and Greatest Lower Bound (Meet)','Inverse and Identity','Prime divisor','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'This structure is fundamental in order theory and logic.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','The Max-Flow Min-Cut Theorem states that the maximum flow through a network is equal to the:','Total number of edges','Capacity of the minimum cut','Sum of all vertex degrees','Longest path','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'This is a classic result in optimization and graph theory.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','What is the number of ''Derangements'' of 3 elements?','1','2','3','6','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'For {1,2,3}, derangements are {2,3,1} and {3,1,2}. !3 = 2.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','What is the ''Girth'' of a graph?','The maximum degree','The length of the shortest cycle','The number of bridges','The total weight of edges','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'If a graph is acyclic, its girth is defined as infinity.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','The ''Inclusion-Exclusion Principle'' for 4 sets A, B, C, D involves how many terms in total?','4','10','15','16','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Total terms = 2^n - 1. For n=4, 2^4 - 1 = 15 terms.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','What is Euler''s Theorem for modular arithmetic?','a^φ(n) ≡ 1 (mod n) for GCD(a,n)=1','a^n ≡ a (mod n)','e^{iπ} + 1 = 0','n! ≡ -1 (mod p)','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Euler''s theorem generalizes Fermat''s Little Theorem to any integer n.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','Lagrange’s Theorem states that for a finite group G, the order of every subgroup H:','Is equal to the order of G','Divides the order of G','Is a prime number','Is exactly half the order of G','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'This is a fundamental theorem limits the possible sizes of subgroups.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','How many binary strings of length 8 have no two consecutive 0s?','256','55','34','89','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'This follows the Fibonacci sequence. The number for length n is F_{n+2}. For n=8, it''s 55.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','Vizing''s Theorem states that the edge chromatic number (chromatic index) of a graph with maximum degree Δ is either:','Δ or Δ+1','Δ-1 or Δ','2Δ','Δ^2','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'This bounds the number of colors needed to color edges so no two incident edges share a color.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','The ''Wilson''s Theorem'' states that (p-1)! is congruent to what mod p if p is prime?','0','1','p-1 (-1)','2','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'(p-1)! ≡ -1 (mod p) for any prime p.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','A lattice is ''Distributive'' if:','a ∨ (b ∧ c) = (a ∨ b) ∧ (a ∨ c)','a + b = b + a','Every element has an inverse','It is finite','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Not all lattices satisfy this property; for example, the diamond lattice M3 is not distributive.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','What is the exponential generating function for the sequence {1, 1, 1, 1, ...}?','e^x','1 / (1-x)','sin(x)','ln(1-x)','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',65,'EGF involves dividing each term by n!. Sum (x^n / n!) = e^x.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','What is the ''Independence Number'' α(G) of a graph?','The minimum number of vertices in a vertex cover','The maximum size of an independent set of vertices','The count of isolated vertices','The number of triangles','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'An independent set has no two vertices connected by an edge.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','The ''Cook-Levin Theorem'' proves that which problem is NP-complete?','Traveling Salesperson','Boolean Satisfiability (SAT)','Sorting','Finding Median','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Any problem in NP can be reduced to SAT in polynomial time.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','The forward difference operator Δf(x) is defined as:','f(x+1) - f(x)','f''(x)','f(x) / x','Σ f(i)','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',70,'This is the discrete analogue of the derivative.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','A graph is ''k-Connected'' if it remains connected after removing fewer than how many vertices?','1','k','2','k-1','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'It assesses the structural robustness of the graph.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','What is the value of the 4th Catalan number C_4? (C_0=1)','5','14','42','132','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'Sequence: 1, 1, 2, 5, 14, 42...','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','A ''Monoid'' is a semigroup that has:','An identity element','Inverses for all elements','Commutativity','A prime number of elements','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Monoid = (Set, Associative Operation, Identity).','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','What does ''Gödel''s Incompleteness Theorem'' imply for formal systems like arithmetic?','They can prove all truths','They are perfectly consistent and complete','There are true statements that cannot be proven within the system','Logic is irrelevant','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',65,'It set fundamental limits on mathematical certainty and formal logic.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','The ''Birthday Paradox'' states that in a room of 23 people, the probability that at least two share a birthday is approximately:','10%','50%','99%','1%','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'This counter-intuitive result demonstrates how quickly ''collisions'' occur even with larger domains (365 days).','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','How many primes are less than or equal to 10?','3','4','5','2','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Primes: 2, 3, 5, 7.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','What is the ''Degree Sequence'' of a graph?','The list of degrees of vertices in non-increasing order','The sum of all edges','A list of path lengths','None of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Havel-Hakimi algorithm uses this to check if a sequence is ''graphic''.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','Pólya Enumeration Theorem is used for:','Counting distinct configurations under a group of symmetries','Sorting large arrays','Solving linear systems','Finding the area of a circle','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',65,'It''s vital for counting chemical isomers or distinct colorings of a cube.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','How many Boolean functions of n variables exist?','2^n','2^{2^n}','n^2','2n','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',40,'Each of the 2^n input combinations can result in either 0 or 1.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','What is the ''Handshaking Lemma'' result for Directed Graphs?','Σ in-degree = Σ out-degree','Σ degrees = 2E','Edges = Vertices','Cycles = Paths','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Every edge that goes into a vertex must have come out of some vertex.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','Which of these is a ''Perfect Number'' (equals sum of its proper divisors)?','4','6','12','24','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Divisors of 6 are 1, 2, 3. 1+2+3 = 6.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','What is ''Hamming Distance''?','The distance between two nodes in a graph','The number of positions at which corresponding bits in two bitstrings of equal length are different','The length of a message','The delay in the signal','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'It measures how many bits must be flipped to transform one string into another.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','A ''Well-formed Formula'' (WFF) in logic follows:','Syntactic rules of the language','Semantic rules only','Random characters','Always evaluates to True','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Syntax ensures its structure is valid before evaluating its meaning.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','How many ways can 5 distinct balls be placed in 5 distinct boxes such that no box is empty?','1','5!','5^5','2^5','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'This is equivalent to finding the number of bijections from a set of 5 elements to itself (5! = 120).','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','The ''Identity Element'' for the set of all integers under multiplication is:','0','1','-1','None','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'x * 1 = x for all x.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','A ''Complete Bipartite Graph'' K_{m,n} has how many edges?','m + n','m * n','m^n','n^m','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Every vertex in the first set (m) is connected to every vertex in the second set (n).','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','A ''Combination with Repetition'' formula for selecting r from n is:','C(n, r)','C(n+r-1, r)','P(n, r)','n^r','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Also known as multicombinations or choose with replacement.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','The ''Existential Generealization'' rule states:','If P(c) is true for a specific c, then ∃x P(x) is true','If ∀x P(x) is true, then P(c) is true','Everything exists','Nothing exists','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'If we find an example, we can conclude that ''at least one exists''.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','In a fair coin toss experiment, the ''Variance'' of the number of heads in n tosses is:','n/2','n/4','sqrt(n)','n','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'For a binomial distribution, Var = n*p*q. Since p=0.5 and q=0.5, Var = n * 0.25 = n/4.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','In a POSET, an element that is smaller than all other elements is called the:','Maximal element','Minimal element','Least element (Bottom)','Greatest element (Top)','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'While a minimal element doesn''t have anything below it, a least element is smaller than every other element.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','Which algorithm finds the shortest path in a weighted graph with no negative edges?','DFS','Dijkstra’s Algorithm','Bubble Sort','Binary Search','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Dijkstra''s is a greedy algorithm used to solve the single-source shortest path problem.','pregenerated'),
('0159b8d6-f6a9-4246-a2fb-411bbd61a27c','What is the ''Characteristic Function'' of a set S?','A function that is 1 if x is in S, and 0 otherwise','The derivative of the set','The sum of elements','The count of subsets','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'It provides a mapping from the universe to {0,1} indicating set membership.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','What is the extension of a Java bytecode file?','.java','.class','.exe','.jar','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Java source code (.java) is compiled into bytecode (.class) which runs on the JVM.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','Which component is responsible for running the Java program?','JDK','JRE','JVM','JIT','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The Java Virtual Machine (JVM) is the engine that provides the runtime environment to drive the Java Code.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','Which of these is used to compile Java code?','java','javac','javadoc','javap','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The ''javac'' command is the Java compiler included in the JDK.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','What is the process of converting a primitive type to a Wrapper object automatically called?','Autoboxing','Unboxing','Typecasting','Binding','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Autoboxing is the automatic conversion that the Java compiler makes between the primitive types and their corresponding object wrapper classes.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','Which of these is NOT a wrapper class?','Integer','Byte','String','Character','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'String is a regular class in java.lang, not a wrapper for a primitive type.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','JDK stands for:','Java Data Kit','Java Definition Kit','Java Development Kit','Java Design Kit','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'JDK is the full development environment that includes JRE and development tools.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','Which area in JVM memory stores class-level data and static variables?','Stack','Heap','Method Area','PC Register','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The Method Area (or Metaspace in newer versions) stores per-class structures such as the runtime constant pool and static fields.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','JRE includes which of the following?','JVM + Library classes','JVM + Compiler','Compiler + Debugger','Only JVM','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Java Runtime Environment (JRE) consists of the JVM and the core class libraries needed to run Java apps.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','What does a ''.class'' file contain?','Machine code','Source code','Bytecode','Assembly code','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The compiler transforms readable Java code into platform-independent bytecode.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','Which primitive type corresponds to the ''Character'' wrapper class?','char','string','byte','short','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The ''char'' primitive is wrapped by the ''Character'' class.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','What is the role of the JIT compiler?','To translate source code to bytecode','To optimize bytecode into machine code at runtime','To manage memory allocation','To debug the code line by line','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'Just-In-Time (JIT) compiler improves performance by compiling frequently executed bytecode sequences into native machine code.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','Which memory area in JVM is used for dynamic allocation of objects?','Stack','Method Area','Heap','Native Method Stack','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'All Java objects are allocated on the heap, and governed by Garbage Collection.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','What is the output of: `Integer a = 127; Integer b = 127; System.out.println(a == b);`?','true','false','Compilation error','Runtime error','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'Java caches Integer objects for values between -128 and 127.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','What will happen if we compare `Integer a = 200; Integer b = 200; System.out.println(a == b);`?','true','false','true if using .equals()','false if using .equals()','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'Values outside the -128 to 127 range are not cached, so ''=='' compares different object references.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','Which component of the JVM loads ''.class'' files into the Method Area?','Execution Engine','Class Loader','Garbage Collector','Native interface','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'The Class Loader subsystem loads, links, and initializes the class files.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','What is ''Bytecode'' exactly?','CPU dependent code','An intermediate representation of code for the JVM','Optimized assembly language','The same as binary machine code','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'Bytecode is a highly optimized set of instructions designed to be executed by the Java Virtual Machine.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','Which of these wrapper classes is NOT final?','Integer','Boolean','Double','None of the above (All are final)','["D"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'All primitive wrapper classes in Java are declared as ''final'' and cannot be inherited.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','What is the purpose of JVM Stack?','To store global objects','To store method execution frames and local variables','To store class level information','To store runtime code','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'Each thread has a private JVM stack, created at the same time as the thread, storing frames.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','The command `java MyClass` starts which process?','The compiler','The JVM and Execution Engine','The JAR packager','The documentation generator','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'The ''java'' command launches the JVM and starts executing the main method of the specified class.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','Which memory area is NOT shared among all threads in a JVM process?','Heap','Method Area','JVM Stack','Shared Library Area','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'JVM Stacks and PC Registers are per-thread, while Heap and Method Area are shared.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','What is the difference between ''JDK'' and ''JRE''?','JDK is for running, JRE is for building','JDK = JRE + Development tools (javac, debugger, etc.)','JRE = JDK + JVM','There is no functional difference','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'JDK is the super-set used by developers, whereas JRE is a minimum requirement to execute programs.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','Which JVM sub-component is responsible for interpreting bytecode?','JIT Compiler','Interpreter','Profiler','Garbage Collector','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'The Interpreter reads bytecode instructions one by one and executes them.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','What does a PC Register store for a thread?','The address of the next instruction to execute','The value of local variables','The reference to the main thread','Memory limit details','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'The Program Counter (PC) register contains the address of the Java Virtual Machine instruction currently being executed.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','Which of these wrapper classes does NOT extend the ''Number'' class?','Float','Long','Boolean','Short','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'Boolean and Character wrapper classes do not extend Number; they extend Object directly.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','How many bits are used to represent a Bytecode instruction?','4 bits','8 bits (1 byte)','16 bits','32 bits','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'As the name suggest, each opcode in Java bytecode is exactly one byte long.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','What is the result of `Integer val = null; int p = val;`?','p becomes 0','p becomes null','NullPointerException at runtime','Compilation Error','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'Unboxing a null wrapper object into a primitive results in a NullPointerException.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','Which JVM sub-component is responsible for allocating memory for objects?','Stack Manager','Garbage Collector','Memory Management Subsystem','Interpreter','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'The Execution Engine uses its memory management system to allocate space in the heap.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','Can we change the default size of the heap memory in JVM?','No, it is fixed by the OS','Yes, using -Xms and -Xmx arguments','Yes, but only via Java code','Only in Java EE','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'-Xms sets initial heap size, -Xmx sets maximum heap size.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','Which of these correctly compares two ''Double'' wrapper objects for equality?','d1 == d2','d1.equals(d2)','d1.compareTo(d2) == 0','B and C both','["D"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'''=='' compares references; .equals() and .compareTo() compare the actual values.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','What is the size of the ''Boolean'' wrapper object in memory?','1 bit','1 byte','Varies by JVM implementation (typically 12-16 bytes)','4 bytes','["C"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'Primitive boolean size is small, but a Wrapper Object has object overhead (header, etc.).','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','Does Java Bytecode run natively on the operating system?','Yes, if converted by a special loader','No, it requires a JVM instance to translate it','Yes, starting from Java 9','Only on Linux','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'Bytecode is virtual machine code; it is translated to native instructions by the JVM at runtime.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','What happens if you run `java MyProgram.java` (Java 11+)?','Compilation Error (needs .class)','It compiles and executes in memory without creating a .class file','It only checks for syntax','It opens as a text file','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'JEP 330 allows running single-file source code programs directly without manual compilation step.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','Which of these is stored in the ''Metaspace'' (Java 8+)?','Local variables','Method Bytecode and Class metadata','Instance objects','Temporary strings','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'Metaspace replaced the Permanent Generation (PermGen) and uses native memory to store class metadata.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','If you use a custom ClassLoader, which part of the JVM Architecture are you interacting with?','Execution Engine','Class Loader Subsystem','Runtime Data Areas','Native Method Library','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'It''s part of the loading process where you can define how classes are find and loaded.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','The JVM is platform-independent?','True','False, JVM is platform-dependent','Depends on the vendor (Oracle vs IBM)','True only for JRE','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'Java (the language) is independent, but the JVM itself must be built specifically for each OS (Windows, Mac, Linux).','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','What is the output: `Object obj = 10; System.out.println(obj.getClass().getName());`?','int','java.lang.Integer','java.lang.Object','Compilation Error','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'The primitive ''10'' is autoboxed into an ''Integer'' object.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','Bytecode''s magic number (first 4 bytes of .class file) is:','JAVA','CAFEBABE','DEADBEEF','BABECAFE','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'All Java .class files start with the hex sequence 0xCAFEBABE.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','Which of these is NOT part of the Runtime Data Areas?','Heap','Method Area','JIT Compiler','PC Register','["C"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'The JIT compiler is part of the Execution Engine, not the Data Areas.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','Wrapper classes are immutable?','Yes','No','Only Integer is immutable','Depends on the Java version','["A"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'Like String, all primitive wrapper classes are immutable; once created, their values cannot be changed.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','What does ''Write Once, Run Anywhere'' actually mean in Java?','Compiled machine code runs on all CPUs','Bytecode can be verified and executed by any platform-specific JVM','Source code is translated to C++','Java doesn''t need an OS','["B"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'The portability is achieved by using Bytecode which the JVM interprets or compiles to native code.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','The primary goal of Bytecode verification is:','Performance','Security and Integrity of code','Compression','Code formatting','["B"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'The Verifier checks that bytecode doesn''t violate access constraints or pointer rules before execution.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','What happens in JVM memory when a method finishes running?','The stack frame for that method is popped/discarded','Heap is cleared fully','Static variables are deleted','The whole thread is terminated','["A"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'Local variables used in the method (stored in the frame) are automatically removed when the frame is popped off the stack.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','Why use wrapper classes instead of primitives sometimes?','To use in Generic collections (like ArrayList)','To allow null values','To use utility methods like Integer.parseInt()','All of the above','["D"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'Collections require objects, and wrappers provide nullability and useful static methods.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','The dynamic nature of Java is supported by which JVM feature?','Dynamic Loading of classes','Static compile time check','Fixed stack size','Native compiler','["A"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'Classes are loaded on demand (when first referenced), not all at once at startup.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','Autoboxing was introduced in which Java version?','Java 1.2','Java 5','Java 8','Java 11','["B"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'J2SE 5.0 introduced autoboxing, unboxing, generics, and enums.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','Which of these are parts of the JDK but NOT the JRE?','javac (compiler)','jar (archiver)','java (launcher)','jlink','["A","B","D"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',30,'JRE only contains tools for execution; dev tools like javac and jar are JDK exclusive.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','Select the per-thread memory areas in JVM:','JVM Stack','Native Method Stack','PC Register','Method Area','["A","B","C"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',30,'Stacks and registers are thread-private. Method area and Heap are common.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','Properties of Wrapper objects:','They are immutable','Stored in the stack only','Stored in the heap','Subject to garbage collection','["A","C","D"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',30,'As they are objects, they live on the heap and follow object life cycles.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','Which of these are valid numeric Wrapper classes?','Float','AtomicInteger','Double','Numeric','["A","C"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',30,'Numeric is not a class; AtomicInteger is for concurrency, not a simple primitive wrapper.','pregenerated'),
('91d6b06e-b1c0-4162-92a0-22165218b7e8','Parts of the Execution Engine in JVM include:','Interpreter','JIT Compiler','Symbolic Linker','Garbage Collector','["A","B","D"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',30,'Interpretation, Optimization, and Memory Cleanup are core execution tasks.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','Which keyword is used to inherit a class in Java?','implements','extends','inherits','using','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The ''extends'' keyword is used to establish inheritance between classes in Java.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','What is the base class of all classes in Java?','java.lang.Object','java.lang.System','java.lang.Class','java.lang.Base','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Object is the root of the class hierarchy. Every class has Object as a superclass.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','Which of these is not an access modifier in Java?','public','protected','internal','private','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Java has public, protected, private, and default (no keyword). ''internal'' is used in languages like C# or Kotlin.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','How many interfaces can a single Java class implement?','Only one','Up to two','Multiple','None','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Java supports multiple inheritance through interfaces, allowing a class to implement any number of them.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','Which block is used to catch exceptions thrown by a try block?','finally','throw','catch','throws','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The ''catch'' block contains code that executes if an exception of a specific type occurs in the try block.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','Which keyword is used to bypass the inheritance restriction and prevent method overriding?','static','const','final','sealed','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Declaring a method as ''final'' prevents it from being overridden by subclasses.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','What does polymorphism allow in Java?','Hiding implementation details','Creating multiple objects of a class','A single action to be performed in different ways','Faster execution of code','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Polymorphism (many forms) allows one interface/method to be used for a general class of actions.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','Which exception is thrown when an array index is out of bounds?','ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException','IndexOutOfBoundsException','BoundaryException','ArrayOverflowException','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException is specifically thrown when an invalid index is used to access an array.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','Which of these is true about an abstract class?','It can be instantiated','It cannot have methods','It can have both abstract and non-abstract methods','It must be final','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Abstract classes serve as blueprints and can contain both implemented methods and abstract method signatures.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','Which keyword is used to explicitly throw an exception?','throws','throw','try','new','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The ''throw'' keyword is used to transfer control to an exception handler with a specific exception object.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','What is the difference between method overloading and method overriding?','Overloading is compile-time polymorphism, overriding is run-time polymorphism','Overloading is run-time polymorphism, overriding is compile-time polymorphism','They are exactly the same','Overloading belongs to inheritance, overriding does not','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'Overloading (static) is resolved at compile time based on parameters; Overriding (dynamic) is resolved at runtime based on object type.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','Which statement is true about the finally block?','It only executes if an exception is caught','It only executes if no exception occurs','It executes regardless of whether an exception occurs or not','It is required for every try block','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'The finally block is guaranteed to run after try/catch, unless System.exit() is called or the JVM crashes.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','Can an interface have a constructor?','Yes, always','Yes, but only if it has default methods','No, interfaces cannot be instantiated directly','Only if it is a functional interface','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'Interfaces do not represent stateful objects and cannot be instantiated, so they don''t have constructors.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','In inheritance, which keyword is used to call a superclass constructor?','this()','base()','super()','parent()','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'The ''super()'' call invokes the constructor of the immediate parent class.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','Which of these are unchecked exceptions in Java?','IOException','RuntimeException','SQLException','ClassNotFoundException','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'Unchecked exceptions are those that inherit from RuntimeException or Error.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','If a class implements an interface but does not provide implementations for all its methods, what must the class be?','A final class','A static class','An abstract class','An inner class','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'If a concrete class lacks implementations for inherited abstract methods, it cannot be instantiated and must be declared abstract.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','What happens if an exception is thrown in a try block but there is no matching catch block?','The program ignores it and continues','The finally block (if any) executes, and the exception is propagated to the caller','The program enters an infinite loop','The JVM automatically generates a default catch block for it','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'Uncaught exceptions propagate up the call stack after finally blocks finish. If never caught, the thread terminates.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','Which of the following can be members of an interface?','Instance variables','Static and final variables (Constants)','Private methods (Java 9+)','Both B and C','["D"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'Interfaces can have public static final variables and private methods since Java 9 for internal logic sharing.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','Which of these keywords prevent inheritance or overriding?','final on a class','static on a method','final on a method','private on a method','["A","C","D"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',20,'final class prevents inheritance; final method prevents overriding; private method is essentially hidden from subclasses and cannot be overridden.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','Which of these are valid ways to handle exceptions?','Using a try-catch-finally block','Declaring the exception in the method signature using ''throws''','Using a ''catch-all'' block with Exception class','Using a ''goto'' statement','["A","B","C"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',20,'Java uses try-catch-finally and ''throws'' for exception handling. ''goto'' is not used for logic control or exception handling.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','In a scenario with multi-level inheritance (A inherits B, B inherits C), what is the order of constructor execution when creating an object of class A?','A, B, C','C, B, A','B, C, A','Execution is simultaneous','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'Constructors are called from the top of the hierarchy (superclass) down to the bottom (subclass).','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','Can a static method be overridden in Java?','Yes, static methods participate in runtime polymorphism','No, static methods can only be hidden','No, static methods cannot be redefined in subclasses','Yes, if they are public','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'Static methods belong to the class, not instance. If a subclass has an identical static method, it ''hides'' the parent''s method (Static Polymorphism).','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','What is ''Diamond Problem'' and how does Java avoid it?','Multiple class inheritance; Java uses interfaces with default methods','Multiple interface inheritance; Java uses abstract classes','Circular dependency; Java uses garbage collector','Runtime error; Java uses static analysis','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'Multiple inheritance of classes can cause ambiguity (Diamond Problem). Java allows multiple interface implementation and requires manual conflict resolution for default methods.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','Consider: ''try { ... } finally { return 10; }''. If the try block returns 5, what is the final return value?','5','10','Compile error','Runtime error','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'A ''return'' statement in a finally block overrides any previous return or exception from the try or catch block.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','Which principle does ''Interface Segregation'' from SOLID suggest?','Interfaces should have as many methods as possible','Clients should not be forced to depend on methods they do not use','All classes should implement at least one interface','Interfaces should only be used for public APIs','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'Large interfaces should be split into smaller, more specific ones so that callers only see methods relevant to them.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','What is the restriction on the ''throws'' clause of an overridden method in a subclass?','It can throw any exception','It can only throw unchecked exceptions','It cannot throw broader checked exceptions than the superclass method','It must throw exactly the same exceptions','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'To maintain polymorphic behavior, an overridden method cannot throw more general checked exceptions.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','What is a ''Checked Exception'' and how is it different from ''Unchecked''?','Checked are runtime, Unchecked are compile-time','Checked must be caught or declared; Unchecked do not have this requirement','Checked exceptions are for system failure; Unchecked for logic error','Checked are faster to handle','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'Java compiler forces handling of checked exceptions (descendants of Exception but not RuntimeException).','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','When using ''Try-with-resources'', which interface must the resource implement?','Runnable','Serializable','AutoCloseable','Cloneable','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'The AutoCloseable interface (or its sub-interface Closeable) provides the close() method that JVM calls automatically.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','Which of these are true about Polymorphism in Java?','Dynamic method dispatch is how runtime polymorphism is implemented','Variables can be polymorphic, but methods cannot','A reference of a superclass can point to an object of a subclass','Overriding leads to runtime polymorphism','["A","C","D"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',30,'Dynamic dispatch (JVM selecting the right overridden method) is central to runtime polymorphism using superclass references.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','Which statements regarding abstract methods are correct?','They provide only signature, no body','They can be declared as final','They must be overridden by the first concrete subclass','They can reside in a non-abstract class','["A","C"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',30,'Abstract methods cannot be final (they MUST be overridden) and can ONLY exist inside an abstract class.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','What happens if a parent class has a private constructor?','It can only be inherited within the same package','It cannot be inherited by any class','It can be inherited but not instantiated','It causes a compiler warning','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'Since a subclass constructor must call a parent constructor, a private parent constructor makes inheritance impossible.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','Can a parent class reference access fields added in a subclass?','Yes, always','No, only methods can be accessed','No, only members (methods/fields) defined in the parent class are accessible','Yes, if cast to the subclass','["C"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'The reference type determines which members are visible. To see subclass-specific fields, you must cast the reference.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','What is the output if you call ''parentRef.staticMethod()'' where parentRef points to a subclass object and both have staticMethod?','Subclass method executes','Parent class method executes','Neither executes','Throws ClassCastException','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'Static methods are not polymorphic. They are dispatched based on the reference type (Parent), not the object type.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','Consider ''A extends B''. If B has a constructor B(int x) and no default constructor, what must A''s constructor do?','Define any constructor','Explicitly call super(int) in its constructor','Initialize B''s variables directly','A does not need to call super()','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'Automatically added ''super()'' only works if a zero-argument constructor exists in the parent.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','Can an exception be re-thrown from a catch block?','No, it must be handled fully','Yes, but only a different type of exception','Yes, using the ''throw'' keyword again','Only if inside another try block','["C"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'Re-throwing is a common pattern to perform some logic (log error) and then let the caller handle the final outcome.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','What is the result of ''try { System.exit(0); } finally { print(''hi''); }''?','''hi'' is printed','Nothing is printed','Exception is thrown','System hangs','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'System.exit stops the JVM immediately. This is one of the rare cases where ''finally'' does NOT execute.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','If a method throws Exception, can an overriding method throw RuntimeException instead?','No, must be exactly Exception','Yes, narrower or unchecked is allowed','Yes, but only if the signature adds ''throws''','No, RuntimeException is broader','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'Overriding methods can throw any Unchecked Exception or a more specific Checked Exception than the parent.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','Is it possible to have an empty ''try'' block and only a ''finally'' block?','No, catch is mandatory','Yes, it is valid syntax','Yes, but results in a warning','Only if code is inside finally','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'A try/finally without catch is valid when you just want cleanup logic to run regardless of the block''s outcome.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','Which access modifiers allow visibility in a subclass located in a different package?','public','protected','default (no modifier)','private','["A","B"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',30,'Public is visible everywhere; protected is visible in subclasses even in different packages.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','Which types of classes can be specialized for specific uses?','Abstract classes','Final classes','Interfaces','Static classes','["A","C"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',30,'Abstract classes and Interfaces are specifically designed to be extended or implemented.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','What is the primary goal of Encapsulation?','To allow code reuse','To protect internal state and promote modularity','To increase speed of execution','To force subclasses to implement methods','["B"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'Encapsulation bundles data and methods, hiding the internal implementation and using public methods to control access.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','How does Polymorphism help in building extensible systems?','By allowing the same code to handle new subclasses without modification','By increasing memory efficiency','By reducing the total number of classes in a project','By providing faster data access','["A"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'When logic works with a superclass/interface reference, you can add new implementations later and existing logic will ''just work''.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','Which concept describes a relationship where one class ''Is-A'' type of another?','Composition','Association','Inheritance','Aggregation','["C"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'Inheritance represents the IS-A relationship (e.g., Cat IS-A Animal).','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','What is the main advantage of Abstraction?','Multiple lines of code can be merged','Focuses on ''what'' the object does rather than ''how'' it does it','Automatically generates documentation','Replaces the need for variables','["B"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'Abstraction hides complexity by focusing on the essential features of an object.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','Why should we use ''Composition'' over ''Inheritance'' sometimes?','Inheritance is always better','Composition provides greater flexibility by allowing runtime behavior changes','Composition only works with interfaces','Inheritance is deprecated in modern Java','["B"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'Composition (HAS-A) avoids the rigid class hierarchy and ''fragile base class'' problem of inheritance.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','What does the Liskov Substitution Principle (LSP) state?','Subclasses must be substitutable for their base classes','Classes must have only one reason to change','Interfaces should be small','Objects should be created via factories','["A"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'LSP ensures that inheriting classes do not break the expectations set by the parent class interface.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','Which exception handling strategy is preferred for ''Resource Management''?','Try-Catch','Try-with-resources','Throws declaration','Manual null checks','["B"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'Try-with-resources (introduced in Java 7) automatically closes resources, preventing leaks and reducing boilerplate.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','The ''@Override'' annotation is used to:','Speed up method execution','Mark a method as obsolete','Inform the compiler that a method is intended to override a superclass method','Prevent other classes from overriding the method','["C"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'@Override helps catch errors (like typos) at compile time if the signature doesn''t match an inherited method.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','What is ''Casting'' in the context of Polymorphism?','Changing an object''s actual type','Treating a reference of one type as another type','Deleting an object','Multiplying class instances','["B"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'Upcasting (automatic) treats subclass as superclass; Downcasting (manual) treats superclass as subclass.','pregenerated'),
('eb019d95-453f-49a6-984f-c54e5b7dc342','What is the purpose of ''Custom Exceptions''?','To replace built-in exceptions','To provide domain-specific error information','To make the program run faster','To bypass the JVM exception handler','["B"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'Creating your own exception classes allows you to provide more meaningful error context for specific application logic.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','Which interface is the root of the Collections hierarchy?','Collection','List','Map','Set','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The ''Collection'' interface is the root interface in the collections hierarchy, though Map is often considered part of the framework but doesn''t inherit from Collection.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','Which collection allows duplicate elements?','Set','List','SortedSet','Map (Keys)','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Lists (like ArrayList, LinkedList) are ordered collections that allow duplicate elements.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','Which collection does not allow duplicate elements?','ArrayList','LinkedList','Stack','HashSet','["D"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Sets (like HashSet, TreeSet) do not allow duplicate elements based on equals() and hashCode().','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','Which class implements the Map interface and maintains insertion order?','HashMap','TreeMap','LinkedHashMap','Hashtable','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'LinkedHashMap uses a doubly-linked list running through all its entries to maintain predictable iteration order (usually insertion order).','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','What does the diamond operator ''<>'' do in Generics?','Declares a new type','Allows compiler to infer type arguments from the context','Generates random types','Deletes generic information','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Introduced in Java 7, ''<>'' allows you to omit type arguments during instantiation if they can be inferred.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','Which method is used to add an element to an ArrayList?','insert()','add()','put()','append()','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The ''add()'' method is used across most Collection implementations to add elements.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','Which interface should be used for a collection of unique keys mapped to values?','List','Queue','Map','Set','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Map interface models the mathematical function of a domain-to-range mapping (key-value pairs).','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','Which method is used to retrieve an element from a specific index in a List?','fetch()','get()','read()','element()','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The ''get(int index)'' method allows indexed access to List elements.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','What is the default initial capacity of an ArrayList in Java?','0','10','16','32','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'By default, an ArrayList is created with an internal capacity of 10 elements.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','Which interface represents a First-In-First-Out (FIFO) data structure?','Stack','Queue','Map','SortedSet','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Queue is designed for holding elements prior to processing in a FIFO manner.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','What is the difference between ArrayList and LinkedList?','ArrayList is faster for insertions in the middle','LinkedList is faster for random access','ArrayList is backed by an array, LinkedList by a doubly-linked list','LinkedList uses less memory','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'ArrayList uses a dynamic array (faster search); LinkedList uses pointers (faster middle insertion).','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','Which method do you use to remove all elements from a collection?','removeAll()','clear()','delete()','reset()','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'''clear()'' removes all elements. ''removeAll()'' takes another collection as a parameter.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','What is the main advantage of using Generics in Java?','Faster execution at runtime','Compile-time type safety and elimination of explicit casting','Automatic memory management','Smaller bytecode size','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'Generics catch type errors during compilation rather than failing at runtime with ClassCastException.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','Which Map implementation allows null keys and null values?','Hashtable','TreeMap','HashMap','ConcurrentHashMap','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'HashMap allows one null key and multiple null values. Hashtable and ConcurrentHashMap do not allow nulls.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','What happens if you use a primitive type (like int) directly in a Generic collection?','It works perfectly','Compiler error; only Reference types are allowed','JVM converts it to binary','It is stored as a String','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'Generics only support Reference types (Objects). Auto-boxing allows us to use ''int'' in an ''ArrayList<Integer>'', but not ''ArrayList<int>''.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','Which Iterator method is safe to use for removing elements while iterating?','List.remove()','Collection.remove()','Iterator.remove()','System.arraycopy()','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'Calling collection.remove() while iterating leads to ConcurrentModificationException. The Iterator''s own remove() method is safe.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','Which Set implementation keeps elements in their natural sorted order?','HashSet','LinkedHashSet','TreeSet','BitSet','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'TreeSet is backed by a TreeMap (Red-Black tree) and keeps elements sorted (using Comparable or Comparator).','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','What is the purpose of ''Collections.unmodifiableList()''? ','To sort a list','To create a read-only wrapper around a list','To encrypt a list','To make a list thread-safe','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'It returns a view of the list where add/remove operations throw UnsupportedOperationException.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','Which of these classes implement the List interface?','ArrayList','Vector','HashSet','Stack','["A","B","D"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',20,'ArrayList, Vector, and Stack are all part of the List hierarchy. HashSet is a Set.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','Which of these are legacy collections (pre-Java 2)?','Hashtable','Vector','HashMap','ArrayList','["A","B"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',20,'Hashtable and Vector were part of JDK 1.0 and were later retrofitted to implement the Collections framework.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','What is ''Type Erasure'' in Java Generics?','Manual removal of generic types by the developer','The process where the compiler removes all type parameters and replaces them with their bounds or Object','A runtime feature that prevents type casting','A bug in older JVM versions','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'Generics are implemented via erasure to maintain backward compatibility with non-generic code. Runtime code has no knowledge of the specific type.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','What is the difference between Comparable and Comparator?','Comparable provides internal sorting; Comparator provides external sorting','Comparable is in java.util; Comparator is in java.lang','Comparable uses compareTo(); Comparator uses compare()','Both A and C','["D"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'Comparable defines natural order inside the class; Comparator creates separate sorting logic (useful for multiple sort criteria or sorting classes you don''t own).','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','What is a ''Wildcard'' with ''Lower Bound'' in Generics?','<? extends T>','<? super T>','<T extends Class>','<T super Class>','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'The ''super'' keyword establishes a lower bound (T or any superclass of T).','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','In a HashMap, if two different objects have the same hashCode but are not equal, how are they stored?','The second object replaces the first','They are stored in the same bucket using a linked list or tree (Collision)','An exception is thrown','The hashCode is recalculated until it is unique','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'This is hash collision. HashMap handles this by chaining (linked list) or treeification (Red-Black tree) within the bucket.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','What is the difference between ''fail-fast'' and ''fail-safe'' iterators?','Fail-fast throws Exception on concurrent change; Fail-safe works on a copy','Fail-safe is faster than fail-fast','ArrayList uses fail-safe','CopyOnWriteArrayList uses fail-fast','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'Fail-fast (standard collections) throws ConcurrentModificationException. Fail-safe (concurrent collections) avoids this by iterating over a snapshot.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','Which collection would you choose for highly efficient search/retrieval when keys are unique and order doesn''t matter?','LinkedList','HashMap','TreeSet','PriorityQueue','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'HashMap provides O(1) average time complexity for basic operations like get() and put().','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','What does ''PECS'' stand for in Generics?','Parameter Entry, Class Search','Producer Extends, Consumer Super','Public Entry, Constant Static','Parent Extends, Child Super','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'Use ''extends'' when you want to read from a generic collection (Producer); use ''super'' when you want to write into it (Consumer).','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','What is ''Load Factor'' in HashMap?','Number of items currently in the map','Measure that decides when to increase the capacity (resize) of the hash map','Maximum size of a single bucket','Time taken to calculate hash code','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'The default is 0.75. When 75% of the buckets are filled, the map''s capacity is doubled.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','Which of these are thread-safe collections?','Hashtable','ConcurrentHashMap','HashMap','CopyOnWriteArrayList','["A","B","D"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',30,'Hashtable (legacy), ConcurrentHashMap (optimized), and CopyOnWriteArrayList (snapshot-based) are all thread-safe.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','Which methods are essential for objects used as keys in a HashMap?','equals()','toString()','hashCode()','clone()','["A","C"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',30,'HashMap relies on hashCode() for bucket placement and equals() for finding the exact match within a bucket.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','Can you add an Integer to a ''List<Object>''?','Yes, Object is a superclass of Integer','No, only Object instances can be added','Compile error','Only if cast to Object manually','["A"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'A List<Object> can hold any object type. Covariance doesn''t apply to adding items here; polymorphism does.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','What is the output of ''List<String> list = new ArrayList<Object>();''?','Compile error','Valid code','Runtime error','Warning about raw types','["A"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'Generics are NOT covariant. Even though String is an Object, List<String> is NOT a List<Object>.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','If a PriorityQueue is created without a Comparator, what happens if you add non-Comparable objects?','They are stored but not sorted','Throws ClassCastException at runtime','Compile error','Default hash sorting is used','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'PriorityQueue needs to compare elements to maintain order. If no comparator is provided, elements must implement Comparable.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','Which collection performs best for frequently adding/removing elements from BOTH ends?','ArrayList','ArrayDeque','LinkedList','PriorityQueue','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'ArrayDeque is generally more efficient than LinkedList for stack/queue operations as it avoids node allocation overhead.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','Can a class implement both Comparable and have multiple Comparators?','No, only one sorting strategy allowed','Yes, natural order via Comparable and custom orders via Comparators','Only if one is static','Comparable is deprecated','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'You can provide a ''natural'' sort (e.g., ID) inside the class, and offer various Comparator instances (e.g., by Name, by Date) for other use cases.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','What happens when ''List<?> genericList = new ArrayList<String>(); genericList.add(''test'');'' is compiled?','Works fine','Compile time error','Warning','ClassCastException at runtime','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'You cannot add anything (except null) to a collection with a wildcard (?) because the compiler cannot guarantee the specific type of the list.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','Which interface is used to traverse a collection in both directions?','Iterator','ListIterator','Enumerate','Stream','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'ListIterator extends Iterator and adds hasPrevious() and previous() for bi-directional traversal (available only for Lists).','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','What is the time complexity of ''ArrayList.remove(0)''?','O(1)','O(log n)','O(n)','O(n log n)','["C"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'Since all subsequent elements must be shifted one position to the left, it takes linear time.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','Which statements about HashSet are true?','It uses HashMap internally to store elements','It maintains the order of elements','It allows a single null element','Performance is independent of number of buckets','["A","C"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',30,'HashSet is a wrapper around HashMap (the element is the key, a dummy object is the value). It is un-ordered.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','Which of these are valid generic method signatures?','public <T> T show(T t)','public T show(T t)','public <K, V> void display(K k, V v)','public <?> void display(? x)','["A","C"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',30,'Generic type parameters must be declared before the return type. Wildcards cannot be used in method type parameter declarations.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','What does a ''Generic Class'' definition like ''MyClass<T>'' mean?','The class can only be used with type ''T''','The class can be parameterized with different types during instantiation','T is a special keyword for Threading','The class is synchronized automatically','["B"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'Generic classes create a flexible template that works with any object type while maintaining type safety.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','Which principle is key to a good HashMap implementation?','A hashCode method that distributes keys uniformly across buckets','An equals method that always returns true','Using a very small load factor to save memory','Avoiding null values','["A"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'Uniform distribution minimizes collisions, keeping the average access time close to O(1).','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','What is ''Iteration'' in the context of Collections?','Redefining a collection recursively','Accessing elements of a collection one by one','Converting a collection to an array','Deleting every second element','["B"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'Iteration allows for processing each member of a collection sequentially.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','What represents the ''contract'' for sorting in Java?','The equals() and hashCode() rule','The Comparable and Comparator interfaces','The for-each loop','The static sorting script','["B"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'These interfaces provide the standardization for comparing and ordering objects.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','Why do we use ''Wrapper Classes'' (like Integer) with Generics?','Native types are slow','Generics require object references, and wrappers turn primitives into objects','Wrappers use less memory than primitives','Wrappers are easier to type','["B"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'Since Generics operate with Object-based logic (erasure to Object), they cannot handle native memory blocks (primitives).','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','What is the ''Utility Class'' used for common operations on Collections?','CollectionHelper','Collections','ArrayListUtils','Stream','["B"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'The ''java.util.Collections'' class provides static methods like sort(), reverse(), shuffle(), and synchronizedList().','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','What is the importance of Immutable objects as keys in a Map?','They ensure the hashCode stays consistent throughout the life of the map','They prevent the value from being modified','They use less heap space','JVM can optimize their lookup frequency','["A"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'If a key''s state changes, its hashCode might change, making the element ''lost'' in the wrong bucket.','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','In Java 8, how were HashMaps improved?','They became thread-safe by default','Buckets with many collisions convert from linked lists to Red-Black trees to maintain performance','They no longer require hashCode','They became faster than ArrayList','["B"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'This improvement changed worst-case performance from O(n) to O(log n).','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','Which interface represents an ordered collection that supports LIFO?','Queue','Deque','Set','Map','["B"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'Deque (Double Ended Queue) supports both FIFO and LIFO (Stack-like behavior).','pregenerated'),
('c716aa29-b105-4bc3-b633-3dd4ab2297ee','What is the benefit of ''Bounded Wildcards'' like <T extends Number>?','It allows use of any object','It restricts the types allowed, ensuring we can use methods of the bound (e.g., doubleValue())','It makes the code harder to read','It deletes the type information at runtime','["B"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'Bounding gives the compiler insurance that the generic type will at least have the behavior of the designated parent.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','Which interface must be implemented to create a thread in Java?','Thread','Runnable','Process','Executive','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The ''Runnable'' interface with the run() method is the standard way to define a task for execution by a thread.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','What does a Lambda expression allow in Java 8?','Creation of new classes','Writing anonymous functions in a concise way','Speeding up network calls','Deleting objects manually','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Lambdas provide a clear and concise way to represent one method interface using an expression.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','Which class was introduced in Java 8 to handle null values more effectively?','NullPointerHandler','Nullable','Optional','Maybe','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Optional is a container object used to contain not-null objects, helping to avoid NullPointerExceptions.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','Which method is used to start the execution of a thread?','run()','execute()','start()','launch()','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Calling start() creates a new thread of execution and then calls the run() method in that new thread.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','Which package contains the New I/O (NIO.2) classes in Java?','java.io','java.nio','java.nio.file','java.file','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'java.nio.file introduced the Path and Files classes for more robust file handling.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','What is the result of ''10 / 0'' in a Java thread?','Infinity','0','ArithmeticException','Compiler error','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Division by zero for integral types throws ArithmeticException at runtime.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','Which Stream operation is used to transform elements?','filter()','map()','reduce()','collect()','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The ''map'' operation applies a function to each element of the stream and returns a new stream of the results.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','What is the keyword used to prevent multiple threads from accessing a method simultaneously?','volatile','atomic','synchronized','locked','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Synchronized creates a critical section that only one thread can enter at a time for a given object or class.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','Which functional interface matches a method that takes one argument and returns a boolean?','Consumer','Supplier','Predicate','Function','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Predicate<T> represents a boolean-valued function of one argument.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','Which method in the Files class can be used to write a string to a file?','write()','output()','writeString()','save()','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Files.writeString() (introduced later in Java 11) or Files.write() are common for simple write operations.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','What is the difference between ''synchronized'' on a method and ''synchronized'' on a block?','No difference','Block synchronization can target a specific object and is more granular','Method synchronization is always faster','Block synchronization cannot be used with static objects','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'Synchronized blocks allow locking only the necessary lines of code using any object as a lock reference, improving concurrency.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','What does the ''volatile'' keyword ensure in multithreading?','Exclusivity (one thread at a time)','Atomicity of complex operations','Visibility of changes to other threads','Prevents deadlocks','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'Volatile ensures that value changes made by one thread are immediately visible to others by reading/writing directly to main memory.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','What is a ''Functional Interface''?','An interface used in functional programming','An interface with exactly one abstract method','An interface with only default methods','A class that behaves like a function','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'Functional interfaces (can have multiple default/static methods) are the target types for lambda expressions.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','Which Stream method is used to remove duplicates from a stream?','unique()','distinct()','noDuplicates()','filter(Objects::nonNull)','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'The ''distinct()'' operation uses equals() to filter out duplicate elements in a stream.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','What is the difference between ''Path'' and ''File'' in NIO.2?','Path is for relative paths only','File is older; Path is an enhanced representation of the file system location','Path can handle network drives; File cannot','There is no functional difference','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'Path (Interface) is more versatile and works with the Files utility class. File (Class) is the legacy I/O representation.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','What is a ''Deadlock''?','A thread that has completed execution','A situation where two or more threads are blocked forever, waiting for each other','An error when calling stop() on a thread','Memory leak caused by threads','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'Deadlock occurs when Thread A holds Lock 1 and wants Lock 2, while Thread B holds Lock 2 and wants Lock 1.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','Which terminal operation returns a single value from a Stream reduction?','transform()','collect()','reduce()','map()','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'The ''reduce'' operation takes multiple elements and combines them into one result (like sum or concatenation).','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','Which interface represents a task that can return a value and throw an exception?','Runnable','Callable','Future','Thread','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'Unlike Runnable.run() (void), Callable.call() returns a generic value of type T and can throw checked exceptions.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','Which of these are intermediate operations in Java Streams?','filter','map','count','sorted','["A","B","D"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',20,'Intermediate operations are lazy and return a new stream. ''count'' is a terminal operation that triggers processing.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','Which methods are used for inter-thread communication?','wait()','notify()','notifyAll()','sleep()','["A","B","C"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',20,'wait, notify, and notifyAll must be called from a synchronized context to communicate state changes between threads. sleep just pauses the current thread.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','What is the difference between ''Stream.parallel()'' and ''Stream.sequential()''?','Parallel uses multiple threads; Sequential uses a single thread','Parallel is for files; Sequential is for lists','Parallel always preserves order; Sequential does not','There is no difference in execution','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'Parallel streams divide tasks between cores using the ForkJoinPool; however, they require thread-safe logic and have overhead.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','What is ''Lock Contention''?','When a thread cannot acquire a lock because another thread holds it','When two threads release locks at the same time','When a lock is deleted by the GC','When a thread holds too many locks','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'Contention indicates that threads are waiting for resources, which can degrade application performance.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','How does ''Optional.flatMap'' differ from ''Optional.map''?','map returns a nested Optional; flatMap ''flattens'' the nested result','flatMap is for collections; map is for objects','map is faster','flatMap is only available in Java 11+','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'If the mapping function already returns an Optional, map would produce Optional<Optional<T>>. flatMap returns Optional<T>.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','Which class provides atomic operations for integers without using synchronized blocks?','VolatileInteger','AtomicInteger','LockedInteger','ThreadSafeInt','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'AtomicInteger uses low-level ''Compare-and-Swap'' (CAS) instructions to safely update values from multiple threads.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','What is ''Thread Local'' storage?','Memory shared by all threads in a package','Variables that are unique to each thread that accesses them','Variable stored in the local registry','A cache for thread performance','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'ThreadLocal class allows you to store data that is local to the current thread (useful for context like UserID or DB connection).','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','Which method in Path can be used to combine two path segments?','join()','resolve()','append()','merge()','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'''path.resolve(other)'' is the standard way to concatenate paths in a platform-independent manner.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','What does ''CompletableFuture'' provide?','A thread that never stops','Asynchronous programming with a callback/continuation model','Faster file compression','Automatic retry for failed transactions','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'CompletableFuture (Java 8) allows for complex async pipelines with methods like thenApply, thenAccept, and handle.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','Which concept describes the memory visibility issues in Java multithreading?','Happen-Before relationship','Wait-Notify protocol','Lock-Free design','Stack Trace consistency','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'The ''happen-before'' rule in JMM (Java Memory Model) guarantees that memory writes by one specific statement are visible to another specific statement.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','Which of these are thread-safe ways to iterate over a list?','Using synchronizedList and a manual synchronized block on the list','Using CopyOnWriteArrayList','Using a standard ArrayList and for-each loop in multiple threads','Using ConcurrentLinkedQueue','["A","B"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',30,'Standard ArrayList iteration is NOT thread-safe. synchronizedList requires manual synchronization for iteration, while CopyOnWriteArrayList is safe by design (snapshot).','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','What can trigger a thread to wake up from ''wait()''?','Calling notify() on the same object','Calling notifyAll() on the same object','The thread is interrupted','The wait time expires (if specified)','["A","B","C","D"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',30,'Threads wake up when notified, interrupted, or when the timer exceeds. They must re-acquire the lock before continuing.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','Can a lambda expression access non-final variables in its outer scope?','Yes, always','No, variables must be final or ''effectively final''','Only if they are static','Only if they are primatives','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'To ensure thread safety and predictability, variables accessed in lambda must not be modified after assignment.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','What is the output of ''Stream.of(1, 2, 3).map(n -> n * 2);'' if no terminal operation follows?','2, 4, 6','Nothing (Processing is lazy)','Runtime error','Reference to the Stream object','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'Intermediate operations are not executed until a terminal operation (like collect or forEach) is called.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','What happens if you call ''run()'' instead of ''start()'' on a Thread object?','A new thread is started','The run() method executes in the CURRENT thread','Compiler error','The JVM crashes','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'Calling run() is just a normal method call. To initiate a true concurrent task, start() must be used.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','Can ''Optional.of(null)'' be used to represent a missing value?','Yes','No, it throws NullPointerException','Only if stored in a variable','Yes, if cast to Optional<Void>','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'Use ''Optional.empty()'' for missing values or ''Optional.ofNullable()'' if the value might be null. .of() forbids null.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','What is a ''Daemon Thread'' in Java?','A very fast thread','A background thread that does not prevent the JVM from exiting','A thread with high priority','A thread that runs on the OS kernel only','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'Garbage collection is a classic example of a daemon thread. If all non-daemon threads finish, the JVM stops even if daemons are running.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','Which Stream method should you use for debugging intermediate steps?','debug()','peek()','log()','inspect()','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'peek() allows you to perform an action (like printing) for each element as it flows past without altering the stream.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','What is the consequence of catching ''InterruptedException'' and then ignoring it?','Nothing if code finishes','The ''interrupted'' status is cleared, and parent callers won''t know the thread was stopped','The thread restarts automatically','Compiler warning','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'Best practice is to re-interrupt the thread or throw a runtime exception so the cancellation signal propagates.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','In NIO.2, what is the ''WatchService'' used for?','Monitoring thread health','Monitoring file system changes (Create/Modify/Delete events)','Timed execution of tasks','Debugging network I/O','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'WatchService allows you to subscribe to a directory and get notified of changes without polling.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','Which of these are valid method references?','System.out::println','String::toUpperCase','Integer::new','ArrayList.add','["A","B","C"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',30,'Method references use the ''::'' syntax for static methods, instance methods, or constructors. D is missing the syntax.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','Which factors can lead to ''Thread Starvation''?','A thread with very low priority never gets CPU time','Synchronized blocks that take too long to execute','Infinite loops in high-priority threads','Calling join() on a finished thread','["A","C"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',30,'Starvation occurs when a thread is constantly denied access to shared resources or CPU time.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','What is the primary motivation for ''Concurrency''?','To make code simpler to read','To use system resources better (CPU overlap with I/O)','To replace functional programming','To force the JVM to use more memory','["B"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'Concurrency allows a program to deal with multiple things at once, improving responsiveness and throughput.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','What does a ''Stream'' in Java ideally represent?','A fixed data structure','A sequence of elements supporting functional-style operations','A list of strings','A physical file on disk','["B"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'Streams provide a high-level abstraction for processing data without storing it.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','What is ''Immutability'' and why is it good for concurrent programming?','Objects that cannot be changed; they are inherently thread-safe','Objects that can only be shared','Objects that are stored in the stack only','It allows deleting objects instantly','["A"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'If state cannot change, there can be no data races or consistency issues between threads.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','What is the purpose of ''ExecutorService''?','To kill unresponsive threads','To manage a pool of threads and schedule tasks','To compile java files faster','To synchronize all methods in a class','["B"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'Executors decouple task submission from task execution, managing thread recycling and queuing.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','What is ''Pipelines'' in the context of Streams?','The connection between the CPU and RAM','The sequence of zero or more intermediate operations followed by a terminal operation','The speed of the network','A way to read files in parts','["B"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'Pipeline allows for fluent, readable chain of operations on data.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','Why do we use ''Method References'' over ''Lambdas''?','They are significantly faster','They improve readability when you are just calling an existing method','Lambdas are being deprecated','Method references avoid type erasure','["B"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'If a lambda just passes its argument directly to an existing method (like ''s -> System.out.println(s)''), the method reference (''System.out::println'') is cleaner.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','What is the purpose of ''Collectors'' in the Stream API?','To delete unused data','To accumulate stream elements into a final structure (like a List or Map)','To find bugs in the stream','To sort the elements alphabetically','["B"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'The ''collect'' terminal operation uses objects that implement the Collector interface to gather results.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','What is ''Non-blocking I/O'' (NIO)?','I/O that doesn''t use the disk','Operations that allow a thread to do other work while waiting for completion','A way to write files that cannot be edited','I/O that uses double the bandwidth','["B"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'NIO allows single threads to handle multiple connections by not ''blocking'' (parking) the thread during wait states.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','What is ''Race Condition''?','Competition between developers to finish code','When the final outcome of code depends on the timing/interleaving of thread execution','Speeding up a loop using threads','A bug in the network card','["B"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'Race conditions result in unpredictable and inconsistent data.','pregenerated'),
('74a98d95-13f5-4266-845c-aa6af0f95095','Which class is the modern replacement for ''File'' for creating directories or deleting files?','DirectoryManager','Files','NioOperations','SystemIO','["B"]'::jsonb,'core_concept',30,'The ''java.nio.file.Files'' utility class contains static methods for all common file system tasks.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','What is the smallest deployable unit in Kubernetes?','Container','Pod','Service','Namespace','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'A Pod is the smallest and simplest unit in the Kubernetes object model that you create or deploy.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','Which command is used to see the status of all pods in the current namespace?','kubectl get pods','kubectl show pods','kubectl list pods','kubectl status pods','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'''kubectl get pods'' lists pods and shows their current state (Running, Pending, etc.).','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','Which component acts as the ''brain'' of the cluster and stores all cluster data?','Kubelet','etcd','Kube-scheduler','Kube-proxy','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'etcd is a consistent and highly-available key value store used as Kubernetes'' backing store for all cluster data.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','Which component is responsible for deciding which node a pod should run on?','API Server','etcd','Kube-scheduler','Controller Manager','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'The scheduler considers resource requirements, hardware constraints, and other policies to select the optimal node.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','What is the agent that runs on every node in the cluster and ensures containers are running in a pod?','Kube-proxy','Kubelet','Docker Engine','Containerd','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'Kubelet takes a set of PodSpecs and ensures that the containers described in those PodSpecs are running and healthy.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','Which component manages network rules on nodes and performs connection forwarding?','Kubelet','Kube-proxy','CoreDNS','Ingress Controller','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Kube-proxy maintains network rules on nodes. These rules allow network communication to your Pods from inside or outside of your cluster.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','What is used to group resources logically within a cluster?','Pods','Namespaces','Tags','Labels','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Namespaces are intended for use in environments with many users spread across multiple teams or projects.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','Which field in a Kubernetes YAML manifest specifies the version of the Kubernetes API you''re using?','version','apiVersion','kind','metadata','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'apiVersion defines which version of the k8s API to use to create the object.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','In a Kubernetes YAML, what field identifies the specific object type (e.g., Pod, Service)?','type','kind','object','apiVersion','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The ''kind'' field specifies the type of resource being defined.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','Which command is used to apply a configuration from a file to a resource?','kubectl run -f filename.yaml','kubectl create -f filename.yaml','kubectl apply -f filename.yaml','Both B and C','["D"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'''create'' is imperative, while ''apply'' is declarative (recommended).','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','Can a single Pod contain multiple containers?','No, one container per pod','Yes, they share the same network and storage','Yes, but they must use different IPs','Yes, but only in expert mode','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Multi-container pods (like sidecars) share the same network namespace (localhost) and can share volumes.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','What is the primary purpose of a Deployment object?','To create a secret','To provide declarative updates for Pods and ReplicaSets (e.g. scaling, rollouts)','To manage the storage','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Deployments represent the desired state and the controller works to make the actual state match it.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','Which command displays detailed information and events for a specific Pod named ''myapp''?','kubectl show pod myapp','kubectl describe pod myapp','kubectl get pod myapp --detail','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'''describe'' is the go-to tool for debugging why a pod failed to start.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','What is the default type of a Kubernetes Service?','NodePort','LoadBalancer','ClusterIP','ExternalName','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'ClusterIP exposes the service on a cluster-internal IP, making it reachable only from within the cluster.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','What are key-value pairs attached to objects, such as pods, used for identification and selection?','Annotations','Labels','Metadata','Selectors','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Labels are used to organize and to select subsets of objects.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','What is the command to delete a namespace named ''dev-env''?','kubectl rm namespace dev-env','kubectl delete namespace dev-env','kubectl destroy namespace dev-env','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'Deleting a namespace deletes all resources inside it.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','What does ''Desirable State'' mean in Kubernetes?','The fastest the cluster can run','The configuration requested by the user (e.g. run 3 replicas), which the cluster works to maintain continuously','The state when all pods are deleted','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Kubernetes controllers continuously compare actual state vs desired state and perform corrective actions.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','If you want to scale a deployment ''web-app'' to 5 replicas immediately via CLI, what command do you use?','kubectl scale deployment web-app --replicas=5','kubectl update deployment web-app --size=5','kubectl grow web-app 5','none of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'This is an imperative command to change the number of running pods.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','How do you view the logs of a container in a pod named ''backend''?','kubectl show logs backend','kubectl logs backend','kubectl cat backend.log','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Logs are essential for investigating application failures.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','What information does the ''Selector'' in a Service provide?','The type of IP to use','A way to identify which Pods the service should direct traffic to (based on their Labels)','The name of the service','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Services use selectors to match the labels of the target pods.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','Which component manages the lifecycle of various controllers in the cluster?','API Server','Kube-controller-manager','Cloud-controller-manager','etcd','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'It runs control loops that watch the state of the shared cluster state (via the apiserver).','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','In Kubernetes, what is a ''Node''?','A single container','A worker machine (physical or virtual) that runs containers','The central server','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'A cluster usually consists of multiple nodes to provide high availability.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','What is the primary way to interact with a Kubernetes cluster?','Editing files on the host machine','Sending REST requests to the Kube-apiserver (usually via kubectl)','Talking to the Kubelet','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The API server is the front end for the Kubernetes control plane.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','What is the main responsibility of a ReplicaSet?','To load balance traffic','To ensure that a specified number of pod replicas are running at any given time','To monitor node health','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'ReplicaSets are often managed by Deployments rather than being used directly.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','Which command allows you to open an interactive shell inside a running pod?','kubectl shell podname','kubectl exec -it podname -- /bin/bash','kubectl run podname bash','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'This is very common for manual debugging within a container.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','What are ''Annotations'' used for in Kubernetes?','To select pods','To attach non-identifying metadata (e.g. build info, contact details) to objects','To define storage limits','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'Annotations cannot be used to select objects with selectors.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','What happens if a node fails in a healthy Kubernetes cluster?','The whole cluster stops','The control plane detects the failure and reschedules the affected pods to other healthy nodes','The user must manually move the pods','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Resilience is a core feature of Kubernetes.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','Which command is used to get all resources (pods, services, etc.) in all namespaces?','kubectl get all','kubectl get all --all-namespaces','kubectl list all -A','Both A and B (depending on scope)','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'''--all-namespaces'' (or ''-A'') is used to see the global state.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','Under which section in a YAML do you find the object''s Name and Labels?','spec','metadata','status','apiVersion','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Metadata identifies the object uniquely.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','What does a Pod status of ''Pending'' usually mean?','The pod has crashed','The pod is successfully scheduled but some containers have not started yet (e.g. image pulling)','The pod is deleted','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Check Events in ''kubectl describe pod'' to see why it remains pending.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','Which Service type exposes the service on each Node''s IP at a static port?','ClusterIP','NodePort','ExternalName','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'NodePort makes services accessible from outside the cluster using [NodeIP]:[NodePort].','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','Which command tells you which version of Kubernetes client and server you are using?','kubectl info','kubectl version','kubectl about','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'It''s important to keep the client and server versions compatible.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','What is a ''PersistentVolume'' (PV)?','A temporary folder','A piece of storage in the cluster that has been provisioned by an administrator or dynamically provisioned using Storage Classes','RAM inside a pod','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'PVs allow data to persist even after the pod is deleted.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','What is a ''PersistentVolumeClaim'' (PVC)?','A backup of a volume','A request for storage by a user (pod), similar to how a pod consumes node resources','The price of the storage','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'PVCs ''bind'' to suitable PVs to provide storage to the pod.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','By default, what happens to a container if its main process crashes?','The pod is deleted','Kubelet restarts the container (based on restartPolicy)','The whole node reboots','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'The default restartPolicy is ''Always''.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','What is a ''ConfigMap''?','A map of the server location','An API object used to store non-confidential data in key-value pairs (e.g. settings, config files)','A secret password','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'ConfigMaps allow you to decouple environment-specific configuration from container images.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','Which object should be used to store a database password safely?','ConfigMap','Secret','Registry','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Secrets are encoded in base64 (by default) and intended for sensitive information.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','In a Deployment, what is ''Rolling Update'' strategy?','Deleting all old pods first, then starting new ones','Gradually replacing old Pods with new ones, ensuring a minimum number of pods remain available during the process','Updating pods randomly','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Rolling updates prevent downtime for your application during deployment.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','Who is responsible for maintaining the High Availability of the Kubernetes Control Plane?','The developer','The cluster administrator (or the Cloud provider in managed services like GKE/EKS)','The Kubelet','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'A production cluster should have multiple manager nodes.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','What is the name of the default namespace when no other is specified?','system','default','main','k8s-core','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'Resources without a namespace are created in ''default''.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','Which command is used to see all pods in the ''kube-system'' namespace?','kubectl get pods system','kubectl get pods -n kube-system','kubectl search pods kube-system','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'The ''-n'' flag is used to target a specific namespace.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','Can multiple pods have the same Label?','No, labels must be unique for each pod','Yes, grouping them allows you to target them as a single group through services or selectors','Only if they are in different nodes','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Labels are the primary mechanism for grouping and selecting pods.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','What is ''Minikube''?','A tool for making small pods','A tool that runs a single-node Kubernetes cluster inside a VM on your local machine for learning and development','The smallest version of cloud','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Minikube is perfect for beginners and local testing.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','Which add-on is responsible for providing cluster-wide DNS resolution for services?','Kube-dns / CoreDNS','Kube-proxy','Ingress','none of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'CoreDNS allows pods to resolve service names (e.g. ''db-service'') to their ClusterIP.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','Which command is used to check the API resources available in your cluster?','kubectl show resources','kubectl api-resources','kubectl get list','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'This shows the Names, Short-names, and API groups for all resource types.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','How do you view all nodes in your cluster?','kubectl get computers','kubectl get nodes','kubectl status nodes','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'This shows node names, roles, and status (Ready/NotReady).','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','When would you prefer a ''StatefulSet'' over a ''Deployment''?','For stateless web apps','For applications that require stable network identifiers, persistent storage, and ordered deployment (like Databases)','For one-off jobs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'StatefulSets provide unique IDs (e.g. mysql-0, mysql-1) that persist across restarts.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','What is the ''Container Runtime''?','The time a container runs','The software (like Docker, Containerd, or CRI-O) responsible for actually running the containers','A script for the kubelet','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Kubernetes supports several container runtimes through the Container Runtime Interface (CRI).','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','Which character is typically used as a label selector for ''and'' operations in kubectl (e.g. app=myapp AND env=prod)?',';',',','+','&','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Example: kubectl get pods -l app=myapp,env=prod.','pregenerated'),
('d85add9d-8b2c-4522-88ee-9929f27c1e20','What is the common shorthand for Kubernetes?','Kube','K8s','Kuber','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'8 represents the characters between ''K'' and ''s''.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What is an ''Init Container'' in Kubernetes?','The main container that runs the app','A specialized container that runs before app containers in a Pod, often used for setup scripts or waiting for dependencies','A container that starts only when an error occurs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Init containers must complete successfully before app containers can start.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','Which probe is used to determine if a container is ready to start accepting traffic?','Liveness Probe','Readiness Probe','Startup Probe','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'If a readiness probe fails, the endpoints controller removes the Pod''s IP address from the endpoints of all Services that match the Pod.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What happens if a ''Liveness Probe'' fails consistently?','The pod is marked as unhealthy but remains running','The kubelet kills the container, and the container is subjected to its restart policy','The whole node is rebooted','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Liveness probes tell K8s when a container needs to be restarted (e.g. it''s in a deadlock).','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What is a ''Headless Service''?','A service with no name','A service where ClusterIP is set to ''None'', allowing you to get a list of Pod IPs directly via DNS instead of a single proxy IP','A service that is not exposed to the internet','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Headless services are commonly used with StatefulSets for service discovery like in peer-to-peer applications.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What is the difference between a Role and a ClusterRole in RBAC?','Role is for users, ClusterRole is for robots','Role is limited to a single Namespace; ClusterRole is cluster-scoped and can be used across all namespaces','There is no difference','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Use ClusterRole for resources like Nodes or for common permissions across the entire cluster.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','Which object connects a ''ServiceAccount'' to a ''Role''?','RoleLink','RoleBinding','AccessRule','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'RoleBinding grants permissions defined in a role to a user or a group of users.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What are ''Taints'' and ''Tolerations'' used for?','To speed up the cluster','To ensure that pods are NOT scheduled onto inappropriate nodes (Taints) unless the pod has a matching Toleration','To delete old pods','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Taints allow a node to repel a set of pods.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What is ''Node Affinity''?','The love between nodes','A set of rules used by the scheduler to determine which nodes are eligible for pod placement based on labels on the nodes','A ways to delete nodes','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Affinity is like nodeSelector but more flexible (e.g. soft vs hard requirements).','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What is the difference between ''Resources Requests'' and ''Resources Limits''?','Requests are for memory, Limits are for CPU','Requests define the MINIMUM resources a pod needs to start; Limits define the MAXIMUM resources a pod can consume','They are the same','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Scheduler uses Requests; Kubelet/Kernel enforces Limits.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What is a ''Job'' object used for in Kubernetes?','Running a background service','Running a task to completion (e.g. batch processing, database migration) and then stopping','Paying the developers','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Unlike Deployments, Jobs expect their pods to terminate successfully.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','How do you run a task automatically on a schedule (e.g. every midnight)?','Using a Service','Using a CronJob','Using a DaemonSet','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'CronJobs create Jobs at specified intervals using standard cron syntax.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What is a ''DaemonSet''?','A set of manager nodes','A controller that ensures that all (or some) nodes run a copy of a specific Pod (e.g. for logging, monitoring, or networking)','A secret group of pods','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'When a new node is added to the cluster, the DaemonSet automatically adds the pod to it.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What is the ''Sidecar'' pattern?','A pod that follows another pod','A secondary container in a pod that enhances or extends the functionality of the main application container (e.g. log shipper, proxy)','A backup server','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Sidecars help separate concerns (e.g. the app doesn''t need to know how to ship logs to ELK).','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What does a ''LoadBalancer'' type service do in a cloud environment (AWS/GCP/Azure)?','It calculates the load on the CPU','It automatically provisions an external cloud Load Balancer that routes traffic to your service','It deletes old pods to balance load','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'This is the easiest way to expose a service to the public internet.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','How do you roll back a deployment ''my-app'' to its previous version?','kubectl rollback deployment my-app','kubectl rollout undo deployment my-app','kubectl delete deployment my-app and re-apply','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Undo allows quick recovery if a new image version has bugs.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What happens if you update a Secret or ConfigMap that is mounted as a VOLUME in a pod?','Nothing, the pod must be restarted','The files inside the pod are eventually updated automatically (usually within a minute)','The pod crashes','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Pods can react to config changes without restart if the app is designed to watch file changes.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What is a ''ServiceAccount''?','An account for the developers','An identity created for processes (pods) to define what they can do via the Kubernetes API','A billing account','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'By default, pods use the ''default'' service account which has very limited permissions.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','Which command allows you to label an existing pod ''nginx'' with ''env=prod''?','kubectl add label pod nginx env=prod','kubectl label pod nginx env=prod','kubectl tag pod nginx prod','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Imperatively adding labels is useful for ad-hoc organization.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What is ''Startup Probe'' used for?','To speed up the start','To protect slow-starting containers by disabling liveness and readiness checks until the startup probe succeeds','To name the pod','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It avoids premature killing of a container that just takes a long time to initialize.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What is ''LimitRange''?','The maximum number of nodes','An object that sets default and min/max resource constraints for individual containers in a namespace','A billing limit','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'LimitRanges prevent users from creating gigantic pods or pods with no limits at all.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What is ''ResourceQuota''?','Limits on a single pod','Constraints that limit aggregate resource consumption (e.g. max total CPU, max total Pods) per Namespace','The cost of the cluster','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Quotas are essential in multi-tenant clusters to ensure fair resource distribution between teams.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What is the difference between ''kubectl get'' and ''kubectl describe''?','''get'' is for users, ''describe'' is for robots','''get'' lists basic info; ''describe'' provides exhaustive details, status conditions, and recent events','There is no difference','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Always check ''describe'' if a pod is in CrashLoopBackOff or Pending.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What is an ''Ingress'' resource?','A type of pod','An API object that manages external access to the services in a cluster, typically HTTP (providing load balancing, SSL termination, and name-based virtual hosting)','A ways to delete services','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Ingress acts as a smart router/gateway for your cluster.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What does the ''CrashLoopBackOff'' status mean?','The pod is fine','The container is crashing repeatedly, and Kubernetes is waiting longer and longer between restart attempts to save resources','The node has lost power','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'It indicates an application-level bug or a misconfiguration that causes immediate exit.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','Which object would you use to ensure a pod runs on EVERY node in the cluster?','Deployment','DaemonSet','ReplicaSet','StatefulSet','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'DaemonSets are perfect for logging and monitoring agents.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What information does ''Reclaim Policy'' in a PersistentVolume define?','How to get a refund','What happens to the volume data when the PVC is deleted (e.g. Retain, Recycle, Delete)','The backup schedule','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Retain means the data stays even if the claim is gone.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What is ''SecurityContext'' in a Pod spec used for?','Setting the user password','Defining privilege and access control settings for a Pod or Container (e.g. runAsUser, allowPrivilegeEscalation, capabilities)','Creating a secret','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It''s vital for hardening the container (e.g. forcing it to run as a non-root user).','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What is ''HPA'' (Horizontal Pod Autoscaler)?','A tool to scale the cluster nodes','An object that automatically scales the number of Pods in a deployment based on observed CPU utilization or other metrics','A human-powered scaling service','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'HPA helps handle traffic spikes by spinning up more replicas automatically.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','Which command is used to watch Kubernetes events in real-time?','kubectl watch events','kubectl get events --watch','kubectl tail events','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'''--watch'' (or ''-w'') follows the stream of events as they happen.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','How do you port-forward a local port 8080 to a pod ''myapp'' on port 80?','kubectl connect 8080:80 pod myapp','kubectl port-forward pod/myapp 8080:80','kubectl tunnel myapp 80','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Port-forwarding is great for accessing internal services without an Ingress.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What is an ''emptyDir'' volume?','A volume that is deleted when the node reboots','A temporary directory that is created when a Pod is assigned to a Node and exists as long as that Pod is running on that node','A folder in the cloud','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'It''s useful for scratch space or sharing files between containers in the same pod.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','Can you use a ConfigMap as an environment variable in a Pod?','No, only as files','Yes, using the ''valueFrom'' and ''configMapKeyRef'' fields','Yes, but only for numbers','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'This allows apps to read configuration from environment variables without being modified.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','In ''kubectl get pods'', what does the ''READY'' column ''1/2'' mean?','One pod out of two is running','The pod contains 2 containers, but only 1 is currently healthy and ready to serve traffic','The pod is 50% finished building','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'This usually indicates that a sidecar started but the main app (or vice versa) is failing readiness check.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What is the ''AccessMode'' RWO stand for?','Read Write Only','ReadWriteOnce','Run Work Objects','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'RWO means the volume can be mounted as read-write by a single node.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What is ''Kubelet''s primary communication channel with the Control Plane?','Talking directly to etcd','Talking to the API Server','Talking to the Scheduler','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Kubelet reports status to the API Server and watches it for new Pod assignments.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','How do you check the resource usage (CPU/RAM) of nodes in the cluster?','kubectl top nodes','kubectl stats nodes','kubectl usage nodes','none of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Requires the ''Metrics Server'' component to be installed in the cluster.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What does ''Evicted'' pod status mean?','The user deleted the pod','The node was running out of resources (e.g. disk or memory), and the kubelet terminated the pod to save the node','The pod finished its job','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Check if your pod requests and limits are set properly.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','In a Deployment spec, what is ''strategy: Type: Recreate''?','Gradually updating pods','Terminating all existing Pods before new ones are created (leads to downtime)','Randomly recreating pods','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Useful if your application doesn''t support multiple versions running at the same time.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What is ''CNI'' (Container Network Interface)?','A type of network cable','A standard and set of tools for configuring network interfaces for containers (e.g. Flannel, Calico, Weave)','A cloud provider network','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'CNI plugins provide the actual network connectivity between pods across the cluster.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What happens if a container exceeds its MEMORY limit?','It''s throttled (slowed down)','It is terminated with an OOMKilled error','It uses the swap','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Memory is a ''hard'' resource; once the limit is hit, the process is killed.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What happens if a container exceeds its CPU limit?','It is terminated','It is throttled (it gets less CPU time but keeps running)','It steals CPU from other nodes','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'CPU is a ''compressible'' resource; limits are enforced via throttling (CFS quota).','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What is ''Admission Control'' in Kubernetes?','Tickets for the cluster','A piece of code that intercepts requests to the API Server after authentication but before object persistence (e.g. to enforce policies)','A ways to login to the cluster','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Common admission controllers include ResourceQuota and LimitRanger.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','How do you explain the API object of a Service via CLI?','kubectl get service -o yaml','kubectl explain service','kubectl info service','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'''explain'' is like a man page for Kubernetes resources.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What is the difference between ''kubectl apply'' and ''kubectl replace''?','''apply'' is slow, ''replace'' is fast','''apply'' is incremental and merges changes; ''replace'' requires a complete object and overwrites everything','There is no difference','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Apply is the standard declarative way of managing infrastructure.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','How do you mark a node as ''unschedulable'' to prevent new pods from arriving there?','kubectl stop node [name]','kubectl cordon node [name]','kubectl pause node [name]','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Cordoning is the first step before performing maintenance on a node.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What does the ''drain'' command do to a node?','Clears the cache','Cords the node and then safely evicts all existing pods from it so the node can be taken offline','Deletes the node from the cluster','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Drain is used to move workloads off a node before shutdown.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What is ''Coredns'' in a Kubernetes 1.11+ cluster?','A backup storage','A modular, pluggable DNS server that serves as the cluster''s internal DNS','A ways to connect to the cloud','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It replaced the older kube-dns component.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','Which unit is used to specify CPU resources in Kubernetes?','Hz','Millicores (m), where 1000m = 1 CPU core','Bps','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'For example, 250m means 25% of one CPU core.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What is the purpose of ''ImagePullSecrets'' in a Pod spec?','To name the image','To provide credentials (like username/password) needed to pull an image from a private container registry','To hide the image from other users','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Essential for using repositories that require authentication.','pregenerated'),
('f80f169b-9cc3-4931-871c-eefce360b11e','What is the function of the ''Cloud Controller Manager''?','To backup the cloud','To link your cluster into your cloud provider''s API (e.g. to create load balancers or mount cloud drives)','To pay the cloud bill','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'It allows Kubernetes to interact with cloud infrastructure in a provider-agnostic way.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is ''Pod Topology Spread Constraints'' used for?','To spread pods across different nodes, zones, or regions to ensure high availability and resource balance','To limit the number of pods in a namespace','To name pods according to their location','none of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It allows you to control how Pods are spread across your cluster among failure-domains such as regions, zones, nodes, and other user-defined topology domains.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is a Kubernetes ''Operator''?','A person who manages the cluster','A method of packaging, deploying, and managing a Kubernetes application using custom resources and controllers to automate complex operational tasks','A tool to install Kubernetes','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Operators follow the control loop pattern to manage the lifecycle of stateful applications like databases or message queues.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is a ''CRD'' in Kubernetes?','Cluster Resource Detail','Custom Resource Definition: An API resource that allows you to define your own custom objects and extend the Kubernetes API','Container Runtime Debugger','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'CRDs allow you to introduce new types of objects into the cluster that behave like native Kubernetes objects.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is ''VPA'' (Vertical Pod Autoscaler)?','A tool to scale the number of nodes','A service that automatically adjusts the CPU and memory reservations (Requests) for your pods based on their actual usage over time','A ways to delete small pods','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'VPA frees you from having to guess the right CPU and memory requests for your containers.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is a ''Service Mesh'' (e.g. Istio, Linkerd)?','A group of services','A dedicated infrastructure layer for facilitating service-to-service communication, providing security (mTLS), observability, and advanced traffic management','A ways to name services','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Service meshes typically use sidecar proxies (like Envoy) to intercept and manage all network traffic between services.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is ''Dynamic Voluming Provisioning''?','Users creating volumes manually','The ability of the cluster to automatically create storage volumes (PVs) when a user requests it via a PVC, using a ''StorageClass''','A ways to delete volumes','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Without dynamic provisioning, cluster admins have to manually make calls to their cloud or storage provider to create new storage volumes.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is ''NetworkPolicy'' used for?','Naming the network','A resource that controls the traffic flow between pods (L3/L4), acting as a firewall inside the cluster','Speeding up the internet','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'By default, Kubernetes allows all pods to talk to each other. NetworkPolicies are used to implement isolation and zero-trust security.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','How does ''etcd'' maintain consistency across its nodes?','Gossip protocol','Raft consensus algorithm','Paxos algorithm','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Raft ensures that all etcd members agree on every change to the cluster state.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is a ''Blue-Green Deployment''?','Color coding the pods','Running two identical production environments (Blue and Green) and switching all traffic from the old one to the new one at once','Deploying only on Tuesdays','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Blue-Green allows for near-zero downtime and easy rollback by switching the router/load-balancer target.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is ''Canary Deployment''?','Deploying for birds','Rolling out a new version of an application to a small subset of users (or traffic) first to test its stability before a full rollout','Deploying only in the morning','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Canary deployments help catch bugs in production with minimal impact on the user base.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is a ''Mutating Admission Webhook''?','A ways to delete pods','An HTTP callback that can modify (mutate) the content of a Kubernetes object request before it is saved to etcd','A ways to name the cluster','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Commonly used to inject sidecar containers (like Istio''s envoy) automatically into newly created pods.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What does the taint effect ''NoExecute'' do?','Prevents new pods from being scheduled','Evicts existing pods from the node if they do not have a matching toleration','Stops the node','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Unlike ''NoSchedule'', ''NoExecute'' also affects pods that are already running on the node.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is the ''Aggregated API Server'' used for?','To speed up the API','To extend the Kubernetes API with your own custom API servers that provide their own logic (e.g. Metrics Server)','To backup the API','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'It allows you to add APIs that are not part of the core Kubernetes codebase.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','In a highly available cluster, how many manager nodes are typically required to handle the failure of one manager?','2','3','5','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'A quorum of (N/2 + 1) is needed. With 3 managers, a quorum of 2 is still possible if 1 fails.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is ''Kustomize''?','A tool for kids','A configuration management tool (built into kubectl) that allows you to customize YAML manifests through overlays without changing the original files','A ways to delete config','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Kustomize is great for managing environment-specific variations (dev, staging, prod).','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is ''Helm'' in the Kubernetes ecosystem?','The driver of the cluster','A package manager for Kubernetes that uses ''Charts'' to define, install, and upgrade even the most complex applications','A security tool','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Helm simplifies the deployment of common applications like databases, ingress controllers, etc.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is ''Overcommitting'' in Kubernetes?','Working too much','The state where the total sum of pod Limits on a node exceeds the physical resources of that node','Deploying too many pods','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Overcommitting is common for CPU to increase density, but dangerous for memory if it triggers OOM kills.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is ''RBAC''?','Remote Backup and Control','Role-Based Access Control: The standard way of regulating access to the Kubernetes API based on the roles of individual users or service accounts','Randomly Based Access Control','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'RBAC uses Roles, ClusterRoles, RoleBindings, and ClusterRoleBindings to manage permissions.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','How do you view the ''previous'' logs of a container that just crashed?','kubectl logs [pod] --old','kubectl logs [pod] --previous','kubectl logs [pod] -p','Both B and C','["D"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'This is the primary way to see why a container crashed before it was restarted.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is ''CRI''?','Cloud Resource Interface','Container Runtime Interface: A plugin interface which enables kubelet to use a wide variety of container runtimes','Cluster Runtime Info','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'CRI standardized how K8s talks to runtimes like containerd and CRI-O.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is an ''ExternalName'' Service?','A ways to name the cluster','A service that maps a Kubernetes service name to a DNS name (e.g. my-db.example.com) rather than to pods','A ways to delete services','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Useful for accessing external resources (like a cloud DB) natively via the cluster''s DNS.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is ''Anti-affinity'' used for?','To make pods friends','To ensure that pods are NOT scheduled on the same node (or zone) as other specific pods (e.g. don''t run 2 database replicas on 1 node)','To delete pods','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Anti-affinity is crucial for ensuring hardware-level high availability.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is ''Discovery API'' in Kubernetes?','A ways to find pods','The part of the API server that tells clients which resource types and versions are supported by the cluster','A ways to find users','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Tools like kubectl use this to know what commands are valid for your specific cluster version.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is ''VolumeClaimTemplate'' in a StatefulSet definition?','A ways to delete volumes','A template that instructs Kubernetes to create a unique PVC for each replica in the StatefulSet','A ways to name volumes','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'This ensures that each DB pod (mysql-0, mysql-1) gets its own dedicated persistent storage.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is ''Kube-bench''?','A place to sit','A Go tool developed by Aqua Security that checks if Kubernetes is deployed securely as per the CIS Kubernetes Benchmark','A ways to speed up the cluster','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'It''s an industry-standard security auditing tool for K8s clusters.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is ''Descheduler''?','A ways to delete pods','An optional component that evicts pods that no longer satisfy the scheduling constraints after they have been running (e.g. due to node changes)','A ways to stop the scheduler','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'It helps re-balance the cluster if it becomes skewed over time.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is ''CSI'' (Container Storage Interface)?','A crime scene tool','A standard for exposing arbitrary block and file storage systems to containerized workloads','A ways to speed up the disk','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'CSI allows storage vendors to write plugins for Kubernetes without modifying the core K8s code.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','Which component is responsible for implementing the cluster IP address for a service?','Kubelet','Kube-proxy','CoreDNS','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Kube-proxy programs the iptables or IPVS rules on every node to handle service routing.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is the ''Cloud Provider Interface'' (CPI) or Cloud-Controller-Manager?','A ways to pay the cloud bill','The component that decouples Kubernetes from specific cloud provider logic, allowing users to run K8s on any cloud','A tool to delete nodes in the cloud','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'CPI handles things like node instance life-cycle, routing, and cloud-provider-based load balancing.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is ''OPA'' (Open Policy Agent) Gatekeeper in Kubernetes?','A person who opens the gate','An admission controller that enforces custom policies (written in Rego) on Kubernetes objects before they are created','A ways to speed up the API','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Gatekeeper helps you enforce complex organization-wide rules (e.g. ''all pods must have an owner tag'').','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What does a Pod status of ''Terminating'' for a long time often indicate?','The pod is happy','The pod is waiting for a ''finalizer'' to complete or is stuck due to a volume not unmounting properly','The node is deleted','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Check if there''s an issue with the underlying storage or a custom controller.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','In a ''rolling update'', what does ''maxUnavailable'' control?','The maximum number of users','The maximum number of Pods that can be unavailable during the update process','The time to wait for a pod','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Setting this to 0 ensures your application capacity never drops below the desired replica count during update.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is the purpose of the ''Kube-apiserver'' proxying capability?','To hide the cluster','To allow external users to talk to internal services (like the dashboard) without exposing them directly via a LoadBalancer','To backup the internet','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'You can use ''kubectl proxy'' to securely access the K8s API and internal services.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is ''Pod Security Admission'' (PSA)?','Tickets for pods','The modern replacement for Pod Security Policies (PSP) that provides three predefined isolation levels (Privileged, Baseline, Restricted) via namespace labels','A ways to name pods','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'PSA is built into the API server and is simpler to manage than its predecessor PSP.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is ''OrderedReady'' pod management policy in a StatefulSet?','Creating pods randomly','The policy (default) of creating/updating pods one-by-one in order, waiting for ''Ready'' before starting the next one','A ways to delete pods','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'This policy ensures that master nodes start before worker nodes in a stateful cluster.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is ''TerminationGracePeriodSeconds'' used for?','To speed up the shutdown','The amount of time Kubernetes waits for a container to exit gracefully (SIGTERM) after being notified to stop, before forcibly killing it (SIGKILL)','A ways to name the end','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Default is 30s. If your app shuts down slowly (e.g. flushing buffers), you should increase this value.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is a ''VPC-CNI'' (e.g. in AWS)?','A ways to connect to the cloud','A CNI plugin that gives each Pod an IP address directly from the cloud provider''s Virtual Private Cloud (VPC) network range','A tool to delete IPs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'VPC-CNIs provide high performance by avoiding extra layers of encapsulation (like VXLAN).','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is ''Immutable ConfigMap''?','A config map that cannot be read','A setting that prevents a ConfigMap or Secret from being modified after creation for safety and improved cluster performance (kubelet doesn''t need to watch it)','A ways to delete config','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Immutable objects are great for production where you want to ensure the configuration doesn''t drift without a redeployment.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','In a highly available ''etcd'' cluster, what is a ''Learner'' member?','A student in the cluster','A non-voting member used during cluster expansion to prevent instability while the new node catches up on the log','Aways to delete manager','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Learners help maintain quorum stability during heavy cluster scaling operations.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is ''Dry-run'' flag in kubectl?','Running the cluster without electricity','A flag (--dry-run=client/server) that allows you to see how K8s WOULD create an object without actually committing it to the cluster','A ways to delete pods','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Dry-run is invaluable for testing YAML syntax and validation rules before applying.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What characterizes ''Rolling Update'' maxSurge setting?','The maximum number of users','The maximum number of Pods that can be created above the desired number of Pods during the update process','A ways to delete pods','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'If desired replicas is 4 and maxSurge is 1, Deployment can briefly run 5 pods during deployment.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is ''External Secrets Operator''?','A ways to delete secrets','A Kubernetes operator that synchronizes secrets from external providers (like AWS Secrets Manager, HashiCorp Vault) into Kubernetes Secret objects','A ways to name secrets','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'It helps manage secrets at scale without including them in your Git repository.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is a ''LoadBalancer'' service ''externalTrafficPolicy: Local''?','A ways to use local internet','A setting that forces the cloud Load Balancer to only send traffic to nodes that are actually running the Pod, preserving the client IP address','A ways to delete services','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'It avoids an extra network hop (SNAT) but can lead to uneven traffic distribution if pods aren''t on every node.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','How do you delete a StatefulSet but keep its pods running?','kubectl delete statefulset [name] --save-pods','kubectl delete statefulset [name] --cascade=orphan','You cannot do it','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Orphaning allows you to perform maintenance on the controller without affecting active workloads.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is the ''Gateway API'' (advanced Ingress replacement)?','A ways to login to the cloud','A modern, expressive, and extensible set of APIs (GatewayClass, Gateway, HTTPRoute) designed to evolve beyond Ingress','A ways to delete the cluster','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Gateway API provides better support for multi-tenant and complex traffic routing use cases.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is ''PriorityClass'' in Kubernetes?','A ways to name the best pods','A ways to define weights (Priority) for pods so that more important pods can preempt (evict) less important pods if the cluster is full','A ways to delete pods','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Pod priority ensures that mission-critical services (like the API server or DNS) always get resources.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is the role of ''Kube-aggregator''?','To collect the logs','To route API requests between the core API server and registered aggregated API servers','To backup the cluster','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'It provides a unified API entry point for the user, regardless of how many API servers are running.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What does a ''WaitForFirstConsumer'' volumeBindingMode do?','It makes the volume wait for a user','It delays the volume allocation until a Pod using the volume is scheduled, allowing the cloud to pick a disk in the same zone as the Pod','A ways to delete the disk','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'This is critical for multi-zone clusters where storage exists in specific zones.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','What is ''Cluster Autoscaler''?','A ways to scale the number of pods','A component that automatically increases or decreases the number of nodes in your cluster based on whether Pods are failing to schedule due to resource exhaustion','A ways to delete the cluster','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Cluster Autoscaler works with cloud providers (AWS, GCP) to resize the actual hardware fleet.','pregenerated'),
('c11b5d43-aa09-4d05-80f7-0e4f95b99176','Can a Label Value contain spaces?','Yes','No, it must be alphanumeric with dashes, dots, or underscores','Only if quoted','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Label values have strict character requirements to ensure compatibility with all K8s components.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is the ''Garbage Collection'' mechanism in Kubelet responsible for?','Cleaning the user interface','Removing unused containers and images on a node to reclaim disk space (based on usage thresholds)','Deleting old YAML files','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Kubelet monitors DiskPressure and kicks off GC to prevent the node from crashing due to disk exhaustion.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is ''DRY-RUN'' in the Kubernetes API (server-side)?','Deleting pods without electricity','An API call that goes through the full validation and admission control chain but does not persist the object to etcd','A ways to speed up the API','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Server-side dry-run is more accurate than client-side because it includes mutation and validation logic from admission controllers.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What characterizes ''Pod-to-Pod Communication'' across nodes in a standard overlay network?','Direct IP connection','Encapsulation (e.g. VXLAN or Geneve) where the pod packet is wrapped in a host-to-host packet','Talking over the API server','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Overlay networks use tunneling to allow pods with private IPs to communicate over a physical network layer.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','In the ''CSI'' architecture, what is the ''Attacher/Detacher'' component responsible for?','Naming the volume','Integrating with the Cloud Provider API to ''attach'' a physical disk to a specific node instance','Formatting the disk','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Attachment is a control-plane operation, while ''mount'' (handled by Kubelet) is a node-level operation.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What characterizes a ''Rootless Pod'' configuration?','A pod with no root password','A pod running with ''runAsNonRoot: true'' and ''allowPrivilegeEscalation: false'' in its SecurityContext','A pod that cannot use the internet','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Hardening SecurityContext is a best practice to prevent container breakout exploits.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is ''Pod Preemption''?','Buying pods in advance','The process where the scheduler evicts lower-priority pods to make room on a node for a higher-priority pod that is currently unschedulable','Deleting pods after use','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Preemption ensures high-priority workloads aren''t blocked by less critical ones in a busy cluster.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','Which algorithm is used by the ''Kube-controller-manager'' to manage leader election for its internal controllers?','Raft','Lease-based coordination (using the Lease API object)','Gossip','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Leases allow one manager node to be the active ''leader'' and perform write operations to the cluster state.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is the ''OOM Score Adj'' value and how does Kubernetes use it?','A ways to name the RAM','A kernel setting that Kubernetes sets differently for different QoS classes (Guaranteed, Burstable, BestEffort) to control which pods get killed first during memory pressure','A ways to delete memory','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'BestEffort pods (no requests/limits) are assigned a high OOM score and are the first candidates for eviction.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is ''MTU Reflection'' in the context of overlay networks?','A ways to see the network','The need to account for encapsulation headers (e.g. 50 bytes for VXLAN) by reducing the Pod interface MTU compared to the host MTU to prevent fragmentation','A ways to speed up the network','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Incorrect MTU settings can lead to mysterious packet drops in cross-node communication.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','Which component is responsible for turning a PodSpec into a set of ''OCI Runtime Specification'' files for the container runtime?','API Server','Kubelet','Scheduler','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Kubelet translates the abstract K8s pod definition into the concrete runtime configuration understood by containerd or runc.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is Kubernetes ''Audit Logging''?','Logging the code','A security feature that provides a chronological record of calls made to the Kubernetes API, including who made it, when, and from where','Logging the user chat','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Audit logs are critical for compliance and forensic investigation after a security incident.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is ''Propagated Mount'' vs ''Slave Mount'' in Kubernetes volumes?','Naming the folder','Settings that control how mount events on the host are synchronized with the container''s mount namespace','A ways to delete volumes','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Mount propagation is needed for advanced scenarios like running a storage driver as a container.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What characterize ''Kube-hardening'' with User Namespaces?','Giving names to users','A beta feature that maps container users to a different set of UIDs on the host, ensuring container ''root'' is actually a nobody on the node','Deleting the users','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'User Namespace support is one of the strongest isolation features added to K8s in recent years.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is ''eBPF-powered'' networking (e.g. Cilium)?','Fast fiber optics','Replacing standard iptables-based routing with high-performance kernel-space programs that handle load-balancing and security filtering','A ways to delete IPs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'eBPF provides near-native performance and better scalability than the traditional iptables/ipvs chain.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','How do you inspect the ''etcd'' database directly for debugging? (DANGEROUS)','cat /var/lib/etcd','By using the ''etcdctl'' CLI tool with the cluster''s certificates and a ''member list'' command','It is not possible','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Direct etcd access is a fallback of last resort for cluster recovery.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is ''Wasm'' (WebAssembly) in the context of Kubernetes?','A ways to name the web','An alternative lightweight container runtime format that can run in K8s (using Krustlet or runwasi) for edge computing and high-density workloads','A tool to delete pods','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Wasm modules start faster and use less memory than traditional OCI containers.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is the ''CNCF''?','Cloud Network Control Foundation','Cloud Native Computing Foundation: The Linux Foundation sub-project that hosts Kubernetes and manages its ecosystem standards','Only Cloud Network','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The CNCF is the neutral governing body for Kubernetes and many related projects (Prometheus, Envoy).','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What characterizes ''Sidecar Injection'' vulnerability?','Injecting code into the sidecar','An exploit where a malicious user creates a pod that tricks an admission controller into injecting a sidecar with excessive privileges','Hiding the sidecar','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Properly securing admission webhooks is critical for cluster integrity.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','Which system call is used by Kubelet to enforce the ''Filesystem'' isolation of a container?','chroot','pivot_root or chroot (depending on runtime)','mount','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Modern runtimes prefer ''pivot_root'' because it provides stronger jail isolation than ''chroot''.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is ''API Server Paging''?','Calling the API server on a pager','A ways to retrieve long lists of objects from the API (e.g. 100,000 pods) in smaller ''chunks'' to avoid overloading the API server memory','A ways to delete objects','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Paging is essential for cluster management tools that work with massive numbers of resources.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What characterizes ''Kube-proxy IPVS'' mode performance?','Lower latency than Iptables','Faster route lookup (O(1) vs O(n)) for clusters with thousands of services','Better load balancing algorithms','All of the above','["D"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'IPVS is the recommended proxy mode for large-scale production clusters.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is ''Topology Awareness'' in the context of Service networking?','Knowing where the pods are','Enforce traffic to stay within the same zone or region to reduce latency and save on cross-zone network costs','A ways to delete zones','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Topology awareness (Topology Keys) is vital for cost and performance management in multi-zone clusters.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is the ''Status'' sub-resource in the Kubernetes API?','The current time','A dedicated part of an object''s API that can only be written to by controllers, not by users (using standard PUT)','A ways to delete the status','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The status sub-resource separation prevents users from ''faking'' the health or progress of an object.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What characterizes ''Apiserver Watch'' pressure?','The time spent looking at the API','The continuous CPU/Memory overhead on the API server for maintaining open streaming connections to all controllers and agents in the cluster','The time to backup the cluster','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Efficient watch management is the key to scaling Kubernetes to 5,000+ nodes.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','Which Control Group (cgroup) setting is used by Kubernetes to implement CPU ''Requests'' (not limits)?','cpu.cfs_quota_us','cpu.shares','cpu.max','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'CPU shares provide a relative weight that guarantees a process gets its share of CPU time if the node is busy.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is the ''Self-SubjectReview'' API used for?','Reviewing your own work','Allowing a user or service account to ask the API server what its own permissions are (e.g. ''Can I list pods?'')','A ways to delete your own account','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'This API allows CLI tools and apps to perform ''pre-flight'' permission checks before attempting actions.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','Which CSI capability allows for taking persistent backups of volumes within the cluster?','VolumeCopy','VolumeSnapshot','VolumeBackup','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'VolumeSnapshots allow you to create a point-in-time copy of your volume''s data using the cloud''s native snapshotting feature.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What does a pod ''Finalizer'' do to the deletion lifecycle?','Deletes the pod faster','Prevents the object from being removed from etcd until certain ''cleanup'' conditions are met by controllers','Renames the pod','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Finalizers are used to ensure that external resources (like a cloud load balancer) are cleaned up before the K8s object is gone.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','How can you view the ''internal'' state of a running Controller Manager via HTTP? (if enabled)','Looking at /logs','Looking at the /debug/pprof or /metrics endpoints on the controller manager node','It is not possible via HTTP','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Pprof allows for deep profiling of the Go runtime to identify bottlenecks in the controller logic.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is ''Kube-virt''?','A virtual cluster','An extension for Kubernetes that allows it to manage Vitual Machines (VMs) alongside containers as first-class objects','A ways to delete VMs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Kube-virt allows teams to migrate legacy VM workloads into their Kubernetes infrastructure.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is an ''Aggregation Layer'' in the Kubernetes API?','A way to combine multiple YAML files','A feature that allows the Kubernetes API server to be extended with custom APIs that are not part of core Kubernetes, by routing requests to an Extension API Server','A tool to merge database records','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'API Aggregation allows for building complex custom controllers that feel like native K8s resources (e.g. Metrics Server).','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is the primary difference between a ''Controller'' and an ''Operator'' in Kubernetes?','Operators have a physical remote','A Controller manages generic resources (Pods, Deployments), while an Operator is a controller that encapsulates domain-specific knowledge to manage a complex application (e.g. a Database)','Controllers are faster than Operators','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Operators use CRDs and custom logic to automate tasks like database backups, upgrades, and failover.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is the ''ValidatingAdmissionWebhook'' used for?','To check if the user has a valid password','An HTTP callback that receives a request to create/update a resource and returns a ''Yes/No'' decision based on custom organizational policies (e.g. ''Must have labels'')','To encrypt the API traffic','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Validating webhooks allow you to enforce strict security and compliance rules that K8s doesn''t support natively.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is a ''MutatingAdmissionWebhook''?','A webhook that changes the user''s name','A callback that can modify an object''s YAML definition (e.g. injecting an Istio sidecar or setting default CPU limits) before it is persisted to etcd','A webhook that deletes objects randomly','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Mutating webhooks are the mechanism behind automatic sidecar injection in service meshes like Istio.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is the ''Prometheus Adapter'' used for in Kubernetes autoscaling?','To draw charts in the dashboard','To translate custom Prometheus metrics into the Kubernetes Custom Metrics API, allowing HPA to scale based on business metrics like HTTP 500 rates','To backup Prometheus data','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Custom metrics allow for more intelligent scaling than simple CPU/Memory usage thresholds.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is the ''Cluster API'' (CAPI) project?','A way to see the cluster health','A sub-project that uses Kubernetes-style APIs (CRDs) to manage the lifecycle (create, update, delete) of the Kubernetes clusters themselves','A tool to merge multiple clusters','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Cluster API brings ''Infrastructure as Code'' directly into the K8s paradigm, allowing one ''Management Cluster'' to manage many ''Workload Clusters''.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is a ''CSI Volume Clone'' in Kubernetes?','Copying the YAML file of a volume','A feature that allows creating a new PersistentVolume populated with the data from an existing PersistentVolume, using the storage backend''s native cloning ability','A backup of the registry','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Cloning is extremely fast and space-efficient on modern storage backends like AWS EBS or NetApp.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is ''Hierarchical Namespaces'' (HNC) in Kubernetes?','Naming folders in a hierarchy','An extension that allows namespaces to have parents and children, enabling propagate of policies (RBAC, NetworkPolicy) down the tree','A way to hide namespaces','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'HNC simplifies multi-tenant management by allowing large organizations to manage permissions hierarchically.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is ''IP Address Management'' (IPAM) in a CNI plugin?','A list of IP addresses','The component or sub-plugin responsible for assigning and keeping track of IP addresses for Pods and Nodes within the cluster','A tool to block IPs','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'IPAM prevents IP conflicts and ensures efficient distribution of the cluster''s CIDR blocks.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is ''Sysctl'' tuning in a Pod definition?','A way to see the system logs','A mechanism to set low-level Linux kernel parameters (like net.ipv4.ip_local_port_range) specifically for the Pod''s network or IPC namespace','A tool to delete the cache','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Sysctls allow performance-critical applications (like high-load web servers) to tune the kernel for their specific needs.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is ''RuntimeClass'' used for in Kubernetes?','Choosing the programming language','A resource that allows users to select different container runtimes (e.g. runc vs Kata Containers) for different pods based on security or performance needs','A way to group pods by speed','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'RuntimeClass enables multi-layer security, where sensitive apps run in VMs (Kata) while others run in standard containers (runc).','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is the ''Control Plane'' in a Service Mesh (like Istio)?','The team that manages the server','A centralized set of components that manage and configure the fleet of sidecar proxies (data plane) to enforce traffic policy, security, and observability','A tool to draw the network map','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The control plane (Istiod) provides the intelligence, while the data plane (Envoy) handles the actual traffic packets.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is ''Descheduler'' in a Kubernetes ecosystem?','A tool to delete the scheduler','An optional component that evicts pods that violate cluster constraints after they have been scheduled (e.g. node over-utilization or node taints added later)','A way to slow down the pods','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The Descheduler helps keep the cluster balanced over time as conditions change.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is ''Watch Bookmark'' in the Kubernetes API?','A way to save your favorite pods','An optimization that reduces API server load by sending periodic ''bookmark'' events to watch clients, allowing them to resume watches after disconnection more efficiently','A tool to audit the API','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Watch Bookmarks are critical for scaling clusters with many hundreds of controllers.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is ''Volume Binding Mode: WaitForFirstConsumer''?','Waiting for the user to buy the volume','A setting that delays the provisioning and binding of a PersistentVolume until a Pod that uses it is actually scheduled to a node','A way to speed up the disk','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'This solves the problem where a volume is created in Zone A, but the Pod is scheduled in Zone B (topology mismatch).','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is ''etcd Learner'' node?','A server for beginners','A non-voting etcd node used to catch up with the cluster state before officially joining as a voting member, preventing cluster instability during scaling','A way to monitor etcd','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Learner nodes protect the quorum by ensuring new members have the data before they contribute to consensus voting.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is ''Kubelet Pod Overhead''?','The time Kubelet takes to start','A feature allowing the cluster to account for the resources used by the container runtime and sandbox (e.g. the VM in Kata) that are not part of the pod itself','A way to count pod labels','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Pod Overhead ensures that the scheduler doesn''t overcommit nodes by forgetting about the ''hidden'' resource costs of sandboxing.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is the ''Streaming Server'' in the Container Runtime Interface (CRI)?','A way to watch movies in a pod','The mechanism that allows Kubelet to proxy ''exec'', ''attach'', and ''port-forward'' requests directly to the container runtime via a separate secure port','A tool to stream logs to the cloud','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The streaming server handles data-heavy interactive commands to avoid bogging down the main CRI control channel.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is ''ClusterRole Aggregation''?','Combining all users into one role','A way to create a ''Super'' ClusterRole that automatically inherits permissions from other ClusterRoles based on label selectors','A ways to delete roles','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Aggregation allows for ''plugin'' permissions, where installing a new operator can automatically add its permissions to an existing admin role.','pregenerated'),
('1f7d9f1e-73e2-468b-8315-92f79d48dbdb','What is ''Kubefed'' (Federation v2)?','A way to feed the pods','A project to manage resources across multiple Kubernetes clusters from a single control point, providing global availability and disaster recovery','A ways to delete clusters','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Federation enables the concept of ''Meta-Clusters'' that span regions or even different cloud providers.','pregenerated')
