('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','Which command is used to list the contents of a directory in Linux?','dir','ls','list','show','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The ''ls'' command lists all files and directories in the current folder.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','In the permission string ''-rwxr-xr-x'', what does the first ''rwx'' represent?','Permissions for the User (Owner)','Permissions for the Group','Permissions for Others','System permissions','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Linux permissions are grouped into three sets: Owner, Group, and Others.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','What does the command ''chmod 755 filename'' do?','Sets permissions to read-only for everyone','Sets full permissions for owner, and Read+Execute for group and others','Deletes the file','Changes the file owner to user 755','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'7 (4+2+1 = rwx), 5 (4+1 = r-x). So Owner has rwx, others have r-x.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','Which command is used to display the current working directory path?','path','cwd','pwd','whereami','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'''pwd'' stands for ''Print Working Directory''.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','Which of the following are common Linux distributors (Distros)?','Ubuntu','CentOS','FreeBSD','Debian','["A","B","D"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',35,'Ubuntu, CentOS, and Debian are famous Linux distributions. FreeBSD is a Unix-like OS but based on Berkeley Software Distribution, not the Linux kernel.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','Which command is used to change your current directory?','go','cd','move','ch','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'''cd'' stands for Change Directory.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','To create a new, empty file, you can use the command:','new','create','touch','make','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The ''touch'' command creates an empty file if it doesn''t exist or updates the timestamp if it does.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','How do you create a new directory named ''my_folder''?','newdir my_folder','mkdir my_folder','cd my_folder','touch my_folder','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'''mkdir'' stands for Make Directory.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','Which command is used to copy a file?','mv','cp','rm','cat','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'''cp'' stands for Copy.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','Which command is used to move or rename a file?','cp','mv','rn','rm','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'''mv'' stands for Move; it is also used for renaming.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','To delete a file in Linux, the command is:','del','erase','rm','trash','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'''rm'' stands for Remove.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','Which command displays the contents of a file on the screen?','show','read','cat','print','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'''cat'' (concatenate) prints the entire file to stdout.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','To view the manual or help page for a command, use:','help','info','man','guide','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'''man'' command displays the reference manual for most Linux commands.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','The most common default shell in Linux distributions is:','cmd','zsh','bash','ksh','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Bash (Bourne Again SHell) is the standard interactive shell for most distros.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','What is the username of the Linux ''Superuser'' with full system access?','admin','master','root','system','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'The ''root'' user has unrestricted access to all files and commands.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','How do you clear the current terminal screen?','clean','clear','wipe','reset','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The ''clear'' command wipes the text from the terminal window.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','Which command tells you the name of the user you are currently logged in as?','me','id','whoami','user','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The ''whoami'' command prints the effective username.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','What does ''~'' (tilde) represent in Linux directory paths?','The root directory','The parent directory','The user''s home directory','A hidden folder','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'~ is shorthand for /home/username.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','Which command allows you to view a file page by page (scrolling down)?','cat','more','page','view','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'''more'' (and ''less'') are pagers used to view long text files.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','How can you view just the first 10 lines of a file?','first 10 file','tail file','head file','top file','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'''head'' shows the beginning of a file.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','How can you view just the last 10 lines of a file?','last 10 file','tail file','head file','bottom file','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'''tail'' shows the end of a file.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','To remove an empty directory, use:','del','rm','rmdir','removedir','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'''rmdir'' only works on empty directories.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','What command moves you up one level in the directory tree?','cd .','cd ..','cd /','cd ~','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'''..'' represents the parent directory.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','Linux was created by:','Bill Gates','Steve Jobs','Linus Torvalds','Dennis Ritchie','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'Linus Torvalds released the first Linux kernel in 1991.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','Which command is commonly used to safely shut down the system?','stop','off','shutdown','kill','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'''shutdown'' allows you to notify users and bring the system down cleanly.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','Which command is used to search for a pattern inside files?','find','search','grep','lookup','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'grep (global regular expression print) is the standard text-searching tool.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','What character is used to pipe the output of one command into another?','>','<','|','&','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'The pipe character | connects the stdout of command A to the stdin of command B.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','What does the ''>'' operator do?','Appends output to a file','Redirects output to a new file (overwriting existing content)','Compares two numbers','Deletes a file','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'ls > files.txt saves the output of ls into files.txt.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','How do you view the list of commands you previously typed?','log','past','history','prev','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The ''history'' command displays the shell''s command history buffer.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','Which command is used to check connectivity to another host?','check','ping','net','test','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'ping sends ICMP ECHO_REQUEST packets to network hosts.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','In the ''vi'' editor, which key do you press to enter ''Insert Mode''?','s','i','x','ESC','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'''i'' enters insert mode at the current cursor position.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','How do you quit the ''vi'' editor without saving changes?',':q!',':wq',':x','EXIT','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,':q! forces the editor to quit even if changes were made.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','Which command is used to change file permissions?','chown','chmod','chgrp','permit','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'chmod (change mode) is used to set rwx permissions.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','Which command is used to change the owner of a file?','chmod','chown','usermod','owner','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'chown (change owner) modifies file ownership settings.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','Files that start with a ''.'' in Linux are:','System errors','Hidden files','Temporary files','Executables','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'A leading dot hides files from a standard ''ls'' command.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','Which tool is commonly used to install software on Debian-based systems like Ubuntu?','yum','apt','rpm','brew','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'APT (Advanced Package Tool) handles software installation and updates.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','Which command shows a live, updating view of system processes?','ps','top','list','cpu','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'''top'' provides a real-time summary of CPU/Memory usage and active tasks.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','Which command lists files and includes detailed info like size and permissions?','ls -a','ls -l','ls -h','ls -R','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'-l stands for ''long format'' listing.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','What does ''>>'' mean in shell redirection?','Overwrite a file','Append output to the end of a file','Filter out errors','Read from a file','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'>> adds data to an existing file without deleting previous content.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','Which command is used to display network interface information?','ip config','ifconfig (or ip addr)','netstat','network','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'ifconfig is the traditional tool, while ''ip addr'' is the modern replacement.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','To determine what type of data a file contains, use:','cat','file','type','whatis','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The ''file'' command uses magic numbers to identify file types.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','Which command is standard for creating or extracting compressed archive files (.tar.gz)?','zip','tar','rar','gzip','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'''tar'' (tape archive) is used to bundle files together.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','What command takes you directly to your home directory?','cd','cd ~','cd /home','Both A and B','["D"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'Typing ''cd'' alone defaults to your home directory.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','What is the absolute root of the Linux file system represented by?','~','/','..','/root','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'The forward slash / is the highest level directory.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','Which command lists currently running processes for the current user?','list','ps','top','proc','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'ps (process status) gives a snapshot of current tasks.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','The ''*'' wildcard character in the shell matches:','A single character','Any number of characters (including zero)','Only numbers','Only hidden files','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'rm *.txt deletes all files ending in .txt.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','Which command shows the amount of free disk space on the system?','du','df','free','disk','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'df stands for ''disk free''.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','Which command shows disk usage of a specific file or directory?','df','du','usage','size','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'du stands for ''disk usage''.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','To find where a command''s executable file is stored, use:','where','which','locate','find','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'''which ls'' would show /usr/bin/ls.','pregenerated'),
('b60604b3-a474-46ca-aeb7-a0883a0146fe','Which command is used to display the value of an environment variable?','show','echo','print','val','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'echo $PATH displays the system search path.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','What is the difference between ''>'' and ''>>'' in Linux redirection?','> overwrites the file, while >> appends to the file','>> overwrites the file, while > appends','> is for errors, >> is for data','There is no difference','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Single bracket wipes existing content; double bracket adds to the end of the file.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','What does the pipe operator `|` do?','It deletes two files at once','It takes the output of the first command and passes it as input to the second command','It creates a backup','It hides the output from the screen','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Piping is a core Unix philosophy: building complex tools by chaining simple ones together.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','Which command is used to search for a specific text pattern inside files?','search','find','grep','awk','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'grep (Global Regular Expression Print) searches through files for lines that match a given pattern.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','Which of these are valid ways to search for a file named ''config.json'' in the current directory?','find . -name ''config.json''','locate config.json','grep config.json','ls -R | grep config.json','["A","B","D"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',35,'find and locate search for filenames. Grep searches inside file content. Chaining ls and grep is a manual way to find files.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','How do you redirect only the error messages (stderr) of a command to a file?','command > error.log','command 2> error.log','command E> error.log','command | error.log','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',40,'In Linux, fd 1 is stdout and fd 2 is stderr. Using 2> targets the error stream specifically.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','Which command is used to terminate a process by its PID?','stop','kill','exit','end','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The ''kill'' command sends a signal (defaults to SIGTERM) to a process.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','What is the signal number for ''SIGKILL'', which forced-stops a process?','1','15','9','0','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'kill -9 sends SIGKILL, which cannot be ignored or handled by the process.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','What does the command ''chown root:admins file.txt'' do?','Changes the file owner to admins and group to root','Changes the file owner to root and group to admins','Changes permissions for root','Deletes the file','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The colon separates the user and the group in the chown command.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','Which command creates a symbolic link to a file?','link file linkname','ln file linkname','ln -s file linkname','cp -l file linkname','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'The -s flag specifies a symbolic (soft) link.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','Which command is used to securely log into a remote Linux server?','telnet','ftp','ssh','login','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'SSH (Secure Shell) provides encrypted communication for remote access.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','In a shell, which character matches exactly one character?','*','?','.','!','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'''?'' is the single-character wildcard; ''*'' matches any number of characters.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','Which file contains the list of local users and their basic info?','/etc/users','/home/passwd','/etc/passwd','/root/users','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'/etc/passwd contains UID, GID, home directory, and default shell.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','Which system service is responsible for running scheduled tasks?','syslog','cron','init','bash','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'The ''cron'' daemon executes commands at specified intervals defined in ''crontabs''.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','Which command shows information about CPU architecture and kernel version?','sysinfo','uname -a','kernel','osinfo','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'uname -a provides a full system summary.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','How do you set an environment variable named ''MY_VAR'' that is accessible to sub-processes?','MY_VAR=value','set MY_VAR value','export MY_VAR=value','env MY_VAR=value','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'''export'' turns a shell variable into an environment variable.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','Which command allows you to see the process hierarchy in a tree format?','ps -tree','pstree','top','tree','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'pstree shows parents and children processes visually.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','Which command shows active network connections and listening ports?','ifconfig','netstat','ping','traceroute','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'netstat (or its replacement ''ss'') is used for network troubleshooting.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','In Linux, everything is a:','Process','File','Directory','Shell','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The ''everything is a file'' philosophy includes hardware devices, sockets, and pipes.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','How do you create a shortcut ''ll'' that runs ''ls -l''?','alias ll=''ls -l''','shortcut ll=''ls -l''','map ll=''ls -l''','ll := ''ls -l''','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'''alias'' creates temporary command shortcuts in the current shell session.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','Which command is used to format a partition with the ext4 filesystem?','fdisk','mkfs.ext4','format','mount','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'mkfs (make filesystem) creates common Linux partition formats.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','Which command find files larger than 100MB in the home directory?','find ~ -size +100M','ls -lh ~','grep 100MB ~','locate 100M','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'The find command allows filtering by various metadata like size or type.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','Which file is executed when a bash shell starts for an interactive user?','.bash_config','.profile','.bashrc','.bash_history','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'.bashrc contains shell configurations, aliases, and functions.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','To hide the output of a command completely, you can redirect it to:','/dev/zero','/dev/null','/tmp/null','/etc/shadow','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',35,'/dev/null is the ''black hole'' of the file system; output sent there is discarded.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','Which command is used to extract specific columns from a text file?','grep','sed','cut','tr','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'The ''cut'' command extracts sections from each line of a file.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','Which stream editor is commonly used for basic text substitution (find and replace) via the CLI?','grep','vim','sed','awk','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'sed (stream editor) is used to perform basic transformations on an input stream.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','What does a ''+'' at the end of a permission string (e.g. -rwxrwxr--) indicate?','An error','An Access Control List (ACL) is attached to the file','The file is a directory','The file is extra large','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'ACLs allow more granular permissions than the standard owner-group-other model.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','Which command displays the message buffer of the kernel (boot messages, hardware issues)?','log','dmesg','syslog','bootlog','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'dmesg helps in diagnosing drivers and hardware detection issues.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','Which command shows the path taken by packets to a network host?','ping','route','traceroute','path','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'traceroute lists all the intermediate routers between your computer and the destination.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','Which command is used to add a user to a group?','useradd','usermod','groupadd','groupmod','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'usermod -aG groupname username is the standard way to modify user group memberships.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','What is the ''setuid'' (SUID) bit used for?','Setting a password','Allowing a user to execute a file with the permissions of the file owner','Hiding a file','Running a file in the background','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'SUID is often used on commands like ''passwd'' so users can update root-protected files.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','Which package manager is used on Red Hat based systems like Fedora or RHEL?','apt','yum (or dnf)','brew','pacman','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'dnf is the modern successor to the yum package manager.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','Which command updates the database used by the ''locate'' command?','update','dbupdate','updatedb','findupdate','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'locate is fast because it uses a database, which needs periodically updated via updatedb.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','In which directory are most system log files stored?','/etc/logs','/home/logs','/var/log','/root/log','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'/var/log contains logs for the kernel, auth, web servers, and more.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','Which variable contains the directories that the shell searches for executable commands?','$HOME','$USER','$PATH','$SHELL','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'PATH is a colon-separated list of directories.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','What is the first process launched by the Linux kernel with PID 1?','bash','init (or systemd)','kthreadd','login','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',40,'PID 1 is the parent of all other non-kernel processes.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','Which command is used to attach a storage device to a specific directory?','attach','mount','link','map','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Mounting makes the contents of a drive accessible at a point in the file tree.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','Which command provides a brief description of what a command does in one line?','describe','whatis','intro','help','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'whatis searches the manual page descriptions for keywords.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','To repeat the very last command typed, you can use:','!!','!last','..','rep','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',20,'!! is an ''event designator'' that translates to the previous command line.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','How do you run a command in the background?','&& at the end','& at the end','run-bg','detach','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'sleep 10 & runs the sleep process without blocking the terminal.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','What is the numeric equivalent of ''r--r--r--''?','777','444','Read All','666','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'r=4, w=2, x=1. 4+0+0 = 4.','pregenerated'),
('46755c87-5420-49de-859e-f39787974b7f','What is the numeric equivalent of ''rwx------''?','777','700','Full owner','100','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'4+2+1=7 for owner, 0 for group/others.','pregenerated'),
