INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','What is the ''Shebang'' line at the top of a bash script?','#!/bin/bash','// start bash','<-- bash -->','@use bash','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The shebang tells the OS which interpreter to use to execute the script.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','In a bash script, which variable holds the exit status of the most recently executed command?','$0','$#','$?','$$','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'$? returns 0 if the previous command was successful, and a non-zero value otherwise.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','What is a ''Cron Job''?','A high-priority process','A scheduled task that runs automatically at specified intervals','A way to compile code','A virus that slows down the clock','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Crontab is the utility used to schedule periodic tasks in Linux.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','Which of the following are valid conditional operators in a bash `if` statement?','-eq (equal)','-ne (not equal)','-f (file exists)','=== (strict equal)','["A","B","C"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',40,'Bash uses flags like -eq for numbers and -f for file checks. === is a JavaScript operator.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','What does the code `NAME=''User''; echo "Hello $NAME"` output?','Hello $NAME','Hello User','Hello NAME','Nothing','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Double quotes allow variable expansion in bash.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','In a bash script, how do you capture the output of a command into a variable?','VAR = command','VAR=$(command)','VAR={command}','VAR:command','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The $() syntax is called command substitution.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','Which loop structure is used to iterate over a list of items in bash?','while','for','until','loop','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'A ''for'' loop is standard for iterating over arrays or command outputs.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','What does the ''Sticky Bit'' on a directory do?','Prevents anyone from deleting the directory','Only the file owner, directory owner, or root can delete or rename files in that directory','Makes all files inside read-only','Fast-tracks file access','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'The sticky bit is commonly set on /tmp to prevent users from deleting each other''s files.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','What does LVM stand for in Linux storage?','Linux Volume Manager','Logical Volume Manager','Linked Volume Map','Low Volume Mode','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'LVM allows for flexible resizing of partitions and spanning across multiple disks.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','Which bootloader is most commonly used in modern Linux distributions?','LILO','GRUB','SYSLINUX','BIOS','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'GRUB (Grand Unified Bootloader) allows selecting OS and kernel versions at boot.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','Which file map hostnames to IP addresses locally before checking DNS?','/etc/dns','/etc/hosts','/var/net/hosts','/root/network','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'/etc/hosts provides local override for name resolution.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','Which command is used to insert a module into the Linux kernel?','modload','insmod','kernload','addmod','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'insmod inserts a .ko file into the running kernel.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','Which command is preferred for loading kernel modules as it handles dependencies automatically?','lsmod','modprobe','insmod','rmmod','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'modprobe looks at module dependency files to load everything required.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','Which command is used to start a process with a specific ''niceness'' value?','nice','renice','priority','setprio','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Niceness values range from -20 (highest priority) to 19 (lowest priority).','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','Which command is used to change the priority of an already running process?','nice','renice','chprio','top','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'renice allows you to adjust the priority via PID.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','Which tool is the modern systemd replacement for viewing system logs?','logview','journalctl','syslog-cat','system-logs','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'journalctl queries the systemd journal database.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','Which flag is used with ''tar'' to compress the archive using gzip?','-c','-z','-j','-v','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'-z invokes gzip; -j invokes bzip2; -J invokes xz.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','What does an ''Inode'' store in a Linux filesystem?','The filename and path','Metadata about a file like size, owner, and timestamps','The actual text data inside the file','The user''s password','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'An Inode stores everything about a file EXCEPT its name and the data itself.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','What is a ''Zombi'' process?','A process that steals CPU','A process that has completed execution but still has an entry in the process table','A virus that infects other processes','A process that runs forever','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Zombies occur when a parent hasn''t yet ''reaped'' the exit status of its child.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','Which signal is sent when you press Ctrl+C in the terminal?','SIGQUIT','SIGINT','SIGSTOP','SIGKILL','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'SIGINT (Signal Interrupt) cleanly tells a process to stop.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','Which signal is sent when you press Ctrl+Z in the terminal?','SIGINT','SIGTSTP','SIGQUIT','SIGKILL','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'SIGTSTP (Terminal Stop) pauses the process and sends it to the background.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','Which directory contains device files like /dev/sda?','/etc','/dev','/sys','/proc','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'/dev is the ''devices'' directory representing hardware as files.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','Which virtual filesystem provides information about running processes?','/bin','/proc','/tmp','/var','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'/proc is a pseudo-filesystem that allows viewing kernel and process data.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','Which framework provides Mandatory Access Control (MAC) in Linux?','FirewallD','SELinux','AppArmor','Both B and C','["D"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'SELinux and AppArmor reinforce security by restricting what programs can do.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','What does the ''export'' command do?','Saves a file to a USB drive','Makes a shell variable available to child processes','Installs a new package','Sends an email','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Without export, a variable is only available in the current shell session.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','What does the ''$0'' variable represent in a script?','The first argument','The name of the script itself','The number of arguments','The process ID','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'$1, $2, etc., are positional parameters; $0 is the script path/name.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','What does ''$#'' represent in a bash script?','The value of the first argument','The total number of arguments passed to the script','A comment','The root password','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'$# allows scripts to check if the user provided enough input.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','Which command is used to copy files securely between hosts using SSH?','cp','scp','ftp','ssh-copy','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'scp (secure copy) uses the SSH protocol for encryption.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','Which file specifies the DNS nameservers for a Linux system?','/etc/dns.conf','/etc/resolv.conf','/etc/network/dns','/root/dns','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'resolv.conf typically contains ''nameserver'' lines with IP addresses.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','Which command displays the Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) of disk partitions?','uuid','blkid','diskid','fdisk -l','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',35,'blkid (block ID) helps in identifying disks for /etc/fstab.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','Which file is responsible for mounting filesystems automatically during boot?','/etc/mount.conf','/etc/fstab','/etc/boot/mounts','/proc/mounts','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'fstab stands for ''File System Table''.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','What is the function of the ''nohup'' command?','Clears all processes','Allows a command to continue running even after the user logs out','Hides the process from ''top''','Speeds up the command','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'nohup ignores the SIGHUP (Hangup) signal sent when a terminal closes.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','What is the ''Kernel'' in Linux?','The desktop environment','The core part of the OS that manages hardware and system resources','A type of shell','A collection of apps','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The kernel is the bridge between software and hardware.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','Which file contains the encrypted passwords for Linux users?','/etc/passwd','/etc/shadow','/etc/secure','/root/pass','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'/etc/shadow is only readable by root for security.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','Which command lists all currently defined shell and environment variables?','list','env','printenv (or set)','vars','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'printenv shows environment variables, while ''set'' shows all variables.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','In ''grep'', which flag is used for a case-insensitive search?','-v','-i','-c','-l','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'-i ignores case; -v inverts matching; -c counts matches.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','What does the ''awk'' command primarily focus on?','Compressing files','Pattern scanning and processing language for structured text files (like CSVs)','Setting user passwords','Building the kernel','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'AWK is a powerful scripting language for field-based text manipulation.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','How do you delete a non-empty directory including all its contents?','delete dir','rm -f dir','rm -rf dir','rmdir -force dir','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'r (recursive) and f (force) are needed to remove nested directories.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','Which command is used to download files from the internet via CLI?','get','wget','download','fetch','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'wget (or ''curl'') are standard command-line download tools.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','How do you search for files modified in the last 24 hours?','find . -mtime -1','ls -t','grep recent','locate -recent','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'-mtime (modification time) accepts days; -mmin accepts minutes.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','Which file stores the group information for the local system?','/etc/passwd','/etc/group','/home/groups','/root/group','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'It lists group name, GID, and members.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','What is the PID of the kernel itself?','1','0','99','No PID','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'The ''swapper'' or ''idle'' process is PID 0.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','What is the main advantage of ''less'' over ''more''?','It uses less memory','It allows backward scrolling in a file','It is colorful','It can edit files','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'''less'' doesn''t have to read the entire file before starting, making it faster for large files.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','How do you remove an alias?','alias -r','unalias','rmalias','clear alias','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'unalias alias_name removes it from the current session.','pregenerated'),
('1fe98809-57bd-426b-9a02-98ca6dd99fc6','Which command is used to get information about the PCI devices in a system?','pcilist','lspci','showpci','cardinfo','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'lspci lists all PCI controllers and attached devices (GPU, NIC, etc.).','pregenerated'),
