INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','Which command-line utility provides a dynamic, real-time view of running processes and system resources?','ps','top (or htop)','kill','listproc','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Top shows CPU usage, memory usage, and the list of active processes, updating automatically.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','How can you securely copy a file ''data.txt'' from your local machine to a remote server?','ftp data.txt server','scp data.txt user@remote-ip:/path/to/dest','ssh data.txt server','cp data.txt /remote/server','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'SCP (Secure Copy Protocol) uses SSH for data transfer and provides the same authenticity and confidentiality.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','Which file stores the user account information (usernames, IDs, shells) in Linux?','/etc/shadow','/etc/passwd','/etc/users','/root/accounts','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'/etc/passwd contains basic user info. /etc/shadow contains encrypted passwords.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','Which of these are valid signals that can be sent to a process using the `kill` command?','SIGTERM (15)','SIGKILL (9)','SIGSTOP (19)','SIGEND','["A","B","C"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',40,'SIGTERM requests a clean shutdown. SIGKILL forces an immediate exit. SIGSTOP pauses the process.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','What is the primary benefit of using SSH keys (Private/Public) instead of passwords for login?','Keys are shorter','Significantly higher security (resistant to brute force) and enables automated scripting','Keys are free','Keys make the connection faster','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Cryptographic keys are nearly impossible to guess, and public-key authentication is the industry standard for server access.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','Which command is used to trace system calls and signals of a process?','lsof','strace','gdb','pstree','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'strace is a powerful diagnostic tool for finding why a process hangs or fails.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','In a bash environment, what does the ''umask'' command control?','Maximum memory usage','Default file permissions for newly created files','The user''s password mask','Hidden directories','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'umask subtracts its value from the default permissions (usually 666 for files, 777 for dirs).','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','Which utility is used to resize an ext2, ext3, or ext4 filesystem?','fdisk','resize2fs','resizeext','fs-expand','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'resize2fs can enlarge or shrink a filesystem, usually done after expanding a partition/volume.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','Which command-line tool is used to monitor network traffic in real-time?','netstat','tcpdump','ifconfig','ping','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'tcpdump is a packet sniffer that allows viewing raw network packets.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','What is the ''Journal'' in a filesystem like ext4 used for?','Storing user logs','Improving data recovery speed after a crash by logging changes before applying them','Faster read speeds','Compressing old files','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Journaling prevents filesystem corruption by ensuring transactions are either fully completed or discarded.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','Which tool allows viewing and modifying kernel parameters at runtime?','kernel-setup','sysctl','proc-edit','lsmod','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'sysctl -w net.ipv4.ip_forward=1 is a common use case for enabling routing.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','Which command lists all open files and the processes that opened them?','filelist','lsof','ps -f','openfiles','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'lsof is invaluable for finding which app is using a locked file or port.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','What is ''Chroot'' (Change Root)?','Changing the root password','An operation that changes the apparent root directory for the current running process and its children','Moving the /root folder','Hacking the root user','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Chroot creates an isolated ''jail'' for processes, improving security.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','Which Linux kernel feature allows isolating system resources like networking and mounts?','Cgroups','Namespaces','KVM','LVM','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',40,'Namespaces are the underlying technology behind Docker containers.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','Which Linux kernel feature is used to limit and monitor the resource usage (CPU, RAM) of processes?','Namespaces','Cgroups','Swapping','Nice value','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',40,'Control Groups (cgroups) prevent a single process from crashing the entire system by using all RAM.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','Which command searches for the package that contains a specific file in a Debian system?','apt-find','dpkg -S','apt-get search','rpm -qf','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'dpkg -S /path/to/file tells you which package installed that file.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','In a shell script, what does ''set -e'' do?','Enables echo','Causes the script to exit immediately if any command returns a non-zero exit status','Sets an environment variable','Enters edit mode','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'set -e is a best practice for building robust scripts that don''t fail silently.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','In a shell script, what does ''set -x'' do?','Deletes the script after run','Prints each command before executing it (debug mode)','Makes the script executable','Sets an exit code','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'set -x (XTREACE) is extremely helpful for debugging complex script logic.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','To check and repair a Linux filesystem, which command is used?','chkdsk','fsck','repair-fs','fixfs','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'fsck stands for File System Consistency Check.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','Which command is used to read or set the hardware clock (RTC)?','date','hwclock','rtc','time','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'hwclock interacts directly with the CMOS/BIOS clock on the motherboard.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','Which command displays the Linux kernel routing table?','route -n','ip route show','netstat -r','All of the above','["D"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'While ''route'' is deprecated, all these commands provide routing info.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','What is the purpose of the ''Swap'' space in Linux?','To store fast caches','To provide extra ''virtual'' memory by using space on the hard drive when RAM is full','To swap files between users','To backup the OS','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Swap prevents out-of-memory crashes by moving inactive pages to disk.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','Which command shows the swap usage summary?','swapinfo','swapon --show','free','Both B and C','["D"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'free gives an overall view, while swapon manages the specific partitions/files.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','Which command displays details about I/O statistics for devices and partitions?','iotop','iostat','diskstats','vmstat','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'iostat is part of the sysstat package and helps find disk bottlenecks.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','Which command lists the dynamic dependencies (shared libraries) of a binary executable?','liblist','ldd','depends','objdump','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'ldd shows which .so files a program needs to run.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','In SELinux, which mode identifies violations but does NOT block them?','Enforcing','Permissive','Disabled','Warning','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Permissive mode is used for troubleshooting to see what SELinux would have blocked.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','What does a ''Here Document'' (<<) allow in a shell script?','Reading from another file','Providing multi-line input to a command directly within the script','Sending an email','Running code on another server','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Here docs are great for generating configuration files from scripts.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','Which command is used to join lines of two files on a common field?','merge','join','combine','cat','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Like a SQL join, the join command works on sorted text files.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','What does the ''Tux'' mascot represent?','Darwin','Linux','GNU','Open Source','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Tux the penguin is the official mascot of the Linux kernel.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','What is the ''VFS'' (Virtual File System) layer?','A ways to run Windows files','A kernel abstraction layer that allows the OS to support multiple different filesystems (ext4, NTFS, NFS) seamlessly','A type of virtual RAM','The /tmp directory','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'VFS translates standard system calls (like open/read) into filesystem-specific drivers.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','How do you find all files owned by ''user1'' in the entire system?','find / -user user1','ls -R / | grep user1','locate -u user1','whoami user1','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'The -user flag in find filters by owner name or UID.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','Which command-line interface is used to manage LVM physical volumes?','pvcreate','vgcreate','lvcreate','pvdisplay','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'PV (Physical Volume) is the first layer of LVM, mapping to actual disks/partitions.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','Which command-line interface is used to create a volume group from physical volumes?','vgcreate','pvcreate','lvcreate','vgdisplay','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'A VG (Volume Group) pools multiple Physical Volumes together.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','Which signal is used to reload a configuration file for a background daemon without stopping it?','SIGKILL','SIGHUP','SIGINT','SIGTERM','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'SIGHUP (Signal 1) is convention for re-reading config files in apps like Nginx or Apache.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','What is the ''Shell''?','Wait command','A command-line interpreter that acts as an interface between the user and the kernel','A type of storage','The physical case of the computer','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The shell reads your commands and asks the kernel to run them.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','Where are global environment variables usually defined for all users?','~/.bashrc','/etc/environment','/etc/profile','Both B and C','["D"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'/etc/environment and /etc/profile set the default system-wide environment.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','Which file lists the users allowed to run commands as root via ''sudo''?','/etc/sudo','/etc/sudoers','/root/sudo','/etc/passwd','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'This file should always be edited using ''visudo'' to prevent errors.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','How do you kill all processes with the same name (e.g. all ''firefox'' instances)?','killname firefox','killall firefox','rm firefox','terminate firefox','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'killall (or pkill) searches for processes by name rather than PID.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','Which command tells you the temperature and fan speeds of your components?','temp','sensors','hwinfo','fanstat','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The ''sensors'' command (from lm-sensors) provides hardware monitoring data.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','Which command follows the growth of a log file in real-time?','head -f','tail -f','cat -w','watch','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'-f stands for ''follow''; it prints new lines as they are written to the file.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','What is an ''Orphan'' process?','A process without a name','A running process whose parent has finished or terminated','A process that cannot be stopped','A process waiting for input','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Orphans are usually adopted by the init process (PID 1).','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','Which command displays the current network socket connections?','netstats','ss','socklist','ip sock','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'''ss'' (socket statistics) is the faster, modern successor to netstat.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','What is the ''initrd'' or ''initramfs''?','The main OS files','A temporary root filesystem loaded into memory during boot to provide needed drivers for the real root disk','A backup BIOS','A virus','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It allows the kernel to mount the real / so it can continue booting.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','Which utility is known for the best compression ratio but is slower than gzip?','zip','xz','compress','gzip','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'xz uses the LZMA algorithm; it extracts fast but takes more CPU to compress.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','Which command allows you to switch to another user account in the current terminal?','switch','su','login','user','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'su (Substitute User) defaults to root if no name is given.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','Which command is used to translate or delete characters from stdin?','sed','tr','cut','awk','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'tr ''a-z'' ''A-Z'' converts all lowercase text to uppercase.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','How do you view a summary of a command''s options directly in the CLI?','man command','command --help','info command','describe command','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Most GNU/Linux tools support the --help flag for a quick options list.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','How do you list the contents of a .tar.gz file without extracting it?','tar -lvzf file.tar.gz','tar -tvzf file.tar.gz','ls -tar file.tar.gz','cat file.tar.gz','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'-t (list) allows you to see what''s inside a tarball before unpacking.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','To clear your entire command history, use:','history -wipe','history -c','rm history','history -delete','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'-c (clear) wipes the history list from the current shell session.','pregenerated'),
('e7a5c5b7-8052-469a-bc3d-93f5c54f63df','What is the ''Command Prompt''?','A ways to hack','A sequence of characters indicating the system is ready for input','A manual page','The power button','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The prompt (e.g. user@linux:~$ ) gives context about the current user and path.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Find the next number in the series: 2, 6, 12, 20, 30, ?','40','42','44','46','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',40,'Pattern: +4, +6, +8, +10. The next gap is +12. 30 + 12 = 42.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Look at this series: 7, 10, 8, 11, 9, 12, ... What number should come next?','7','10','12','13','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',30,'This is a simple alternating addition and subtraction series. In the first pattern, 3 is added; in the second, 2 is subtracted.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Look at this series: 36, 34, 30, 28, 24, ... What number should come next?','20','22','23','26','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',30,'This is an alternating subtraction series. First, 2 is subtracted, then 4, then 2, and so on.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Look at this series: 2, 1, (1/2), (1/4), ... What number should come next?','(1/3)','(1/8)','(2/8)','(1/16)','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',30,'This is a simple division series; each number is one-half of the previous number.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Look at this series: 80, 10, 70, 15, 60, ... What number should come next?','20','25','30','50','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',30,'This is an alternating addition and subtraction series. In the first pattern, 10 is subtracted from each number to arrive at the next. In the second pattern, 5 is added to each number to arrive at the next.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Look at this series: 544, 509, 474, 439, ... What number should come next?','404','414','420','445','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',30,'This is a simple subtraction series; each number is 35 less than the previous number.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','CUP : LIP :: BIRD : ?','GRASS','FOREST','BEAK','BUSH','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'You drink out of a cup with your lips. A bird picks up food with its beak.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Flow : River :: Stagnant : ?','Rain','Stream','Pool','Canal','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'Water of a river flows; water of a pool is stagnant.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Paw : Cat :: Hoof : ?','Lamb','Horse','Elephant','Tiger','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'Cat has paws and horse has hooves.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Pointing to a photograph of a boy, Suresh said, ''He is the son of the only son of my mother.'' How is Suresh related to that boy?','Brother','Uncle','Cousin','Father','["D"]'::jsonb,'medium',40,'The boy in the photograph is the son of Suresh''s mother''s only son (who is Suresh himself). So, Suresh is the boy''s father.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','A''s mother is sister of B and daughter of C. D is daughter of B and sister of E. How is C related to E?','Father','Grandfather','Grandmother','Either B or C','["D"]'::jsonb,'medium',40,'C is the parent of B, and B is the parent of E. So C is the grandparent of E. Since the gender of C is not specified, C could be the Grandfather or Grandmother.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','If in a certain language, MADRAS is coded as NBESBT, how is BOMBAY coded in that code?','CPNCBX','CPNCBZ','CPOCBZ','CQOCBZ','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',40,'Each letter in the word is replaced by the next letter in the English alphabet.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','In a certain code, TRIPLE is written as SQHOKD. How is EXOTIC written in that code?','DWNSHB','DWNTHB','DVOVHD','DVNTSH','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',40,'Each letter in the word is moved one step backward in the English alphabet.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Look at this series: J14, L16, __, P20, R22, ... What number should fill the blank?','S24','N18','M18','T24','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'The letters follow J, L, N, P, R (skipping one). The numbers are 14, 16, 18, 20, 22.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Find the missing number: 3, 5, 9, 17, 33, ?','44','65','64','49','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'The difference doubles each time: +2, +4, +8, +16. Next is +32. 33 + 32 = 65.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Five people A, B, C, D, and E are sitting in a row. A is to the right of B, E is to the left of B but to the right of C. A is to the left of D. Who is second from the left?','A','B','E','C','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'The order is C, E, B, A, D. E is second from the left.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Six friends P, Q, R, S, T, and U are sitting in a circle facing the center. R is between P and Q. U is between T and S. S is to the immediate left of P. Who is between R and T?','P','S','Q','U','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Placing them in the circle: P, S, U, T, Q, R. Between R and T is Q.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','A man walks 5 km toward south and then turns to the right. After walking 3 km he turns to the left and walks 5 km. Now in which direction is he from the starting place?','West','South','South-West','North-East','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',45,'He moves South, then West, then South again. He is South-West from the start.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Rahul put his timepiece on the table in such a way that at 6 P.M. hour hand points to North. In which direction the minute hand will point at 9.15 P.M.?','South','East','North','West','["D"]'::jsonb,'medium',45,'At 6 P.M., the hour hand points down (6). If down is North, then right (3) is West. At 9.15 P.M., the minute hand points to 3, so it points West.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Statements: All bags are pockets. All pockets are shops. Conclusions: (I) All bags are shops. (II) All shops are bags.','Only I follows','Only II follows','Neither I nor II follows','Both I and II follow','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'If all A are B and all B are C, then all A are C. But all C are not necessarily A.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Statements: Some actors are singers. All the singers are dancers. Conclusions: (I) Some actors are dancers. (II) No singer is actor.','Only I follows','Only II follows','Neither I nor II follows','Both I and II follow','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Some actors are singers, and all singers are dancers. So the part of actors that are singers must also be dancers.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Which of the following diagrams indicates the best relation between Travelers, Train and Bus?','Three overlapping circles','One big circle containing two separate small circles','One circle partially overlapping two separate circles','Three separate circles','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',40,'Travelers can use train, bus, or neither (other means). Train and Bus are separate modes of transport.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Which of the following diagrams indicates the best relation between Women, Mothers and Engineers?','One circle containing another, and a third overlapping both','Three overlapping circles','One big circle containing two overlapping small circles','Three separate circles','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',40,'All mothers are women. Some women and some mothers can be engineers.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','If the alphabet is written in reverse order, which letter will be the 7th to the left of the 10th letter from your right?','C','Q','P','R','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'10th from right is J. 7th to the left of J in the original alphabet is Q (17th letter).','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','How many 5s are there in the following sequence which are immediately followed by 3 but not immediately preceded by 7? 8 9 5 3 2 5 3 8 5 5 6 8 7 3 3 5 7 7 5 3 6','1','2','3','4','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'The 5s meeting the criteria are at positions 3, 6, and 20.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','At what angle the hands of a clock are inclined at 15 minutes past 5?','58.5 degrees','64 degrees','67.5 degrees','72.5 degrees','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Angle = |30H - 5.5M|. Angle = |30*5 - 5.5*15| = |150 - 82.5| = 67.5.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','If 1st January 2008 was Tuesday, then what day of the week lies on 1st January 2009?','Monday','Wednesday','Thursday','Sunday','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'2008 is a leap year, so there are 2 odd days. Tuesday + 2 = Thursday.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','On what dates of April, 2001 did Wednesday fall?','1st, 8th, 15th, 22nd, 29th','2nd, 9th, 16th, 23rd, 30th','3rd, 10th, 17th, 24th','4th, 11th, 18th, 25th','["D"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'By calculation, April 1, 2001 is Sunday. So Wednesday is April 4.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Arrange the words given below in a meaningful sequence. 1. Poverty 2. Population 3. Death 4. Unemployment 5. Disease','2, 3, 4, 1, 5','3, 4, 2, 5, 1','2, 4, 1, 5, 3','1, 2, 3, 4, 5','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',30,'Logical sequence: Increase in population lead to unemployment, unemployment leads to poverty, poverty leads to diseases, and diseases cause death.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','How is J related to K? (I) J is the brother of L. (II) L''s sister is K.','Statement I alone is sufficient','Statement II alone is sufficient','Both statements I and II together are sufficient','Statements I and II together are NOT sufficient','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'From I, J is male. From II, K is female and sister of L. Both together show J is brother of K.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','What is the rank of P from top? (I) P is 10th from the bottom. (II) There are 40 students in the class.','Statement I alone is sufficient','Statement II alone is sufficient','Both statements I and II together are sufficient','Statements I and II together are NOT sufficient','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Rank from top = (Total students - Rank from bottom) + 1. Both pieces are needed.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Three persons P, Q, and R say: P: ''I am a truth-teller''. Q: ''P is a liar''. R: ''Q is a liar''. Exactly one of them is a truth-teller. Who is it?','P','Q','R','None','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'If Q is the truth-teller, then P is a liar and R is a liar (since Q is not a liar). This fits the condition.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','In a family gathered for dinner, there are two fathers, two mothers, three sons and one daughter. What is the minimum number of people present?','4','5','6','8','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Minimum 5: Grandfather, Grandmother, Father, Mother, and Son. Wait, that doesn''t fit 3 sons. Try Grandfather, Grandmother, Father (son of GF), and 2 sons of Father. That makes 2 fathers, 1 mother, 3 sons. Add Mother of 2 sons. That''s 5 people.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','A shepherd had 17 sheep. All but nine died. How many was he left with?','8','9','17','Nil','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',45,'The phrase ''all but nine died'' means nine survived.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','A bird shooter was asked how many birds he had in the bag. He replied that there were all sparrows but six, all pigeons but six, and all ducks but six. How many birds had he in all?','9','18','27','36','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',45,'Let Total = T. Sparrow = T-6, Pigeons = T-6, Ducks = T-6. T = (T-6) + (T-6) + (T-6) => T = 3T-18 => 2T=18 => T=9.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','If ''water'' is called ''food'', ''food'' is called ''tree'', ''tree'' is called ''sky'', ''sky'' is called ''wall'', on which of the following grows a fruit?','Water','Food','Sky','Tree','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Fruits grow on a ''tree'', and ''tree'' is called ''sky''.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Venerate : Worship :: Extol : ?','Glorify','Homage','Compliment','Recommend','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'These are synonyms of praise or honor.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Odometer is to mileage as compass is to:','Speed','Hiking','Needle','Direction','["D"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Odometer measures mileage; compass measures direction.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Marathon is to race as hibernation is to:','Winter','Bear','Dream','Sleep','["D"]'::jsonb,'easy',30,'A marathon is a long race; hibernation is a long sleep.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Look at this series: 1.5, 2.3, 3.1, 3.9, ... What number should come next?','4.2','4.4','4.7','5.1','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Simple addition series: +0.8 to each number.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Look at this series: 14, 28, 20, 40, 32, 64, ... What number should come next?','52','56','96','128','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Alternating multiplication and subtraction: *2, -8, *2, -8.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Pick the odd one out.','Curd','Butter','Oil','Cheese','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'Oil is not a dairy product.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Pick the odd one out.','Rose','Lotus','Marigold','Mango','["D"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'Mango is a fruit; others are flowers.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Look at this series: 2, 4, 12, 48, 240, ... What number should come next?','480','960','1440','2400','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',40,'Pattern: *2, *3, *4, *5. Next is *6. 240 * 6 = 1440.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Six people L, M, N, O, P, Q are standing in a circle. N is between L and M. P is between M and Q. O is to the right of L. Who is between L and O?','Q','P','N','None','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Sequence: L, N, M, P, Q, O. Between L and O is nobody in one direction, but Q is on the other side? No, O is right of L, so Q must be between O and P.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','A is the father of B and C. B is the son of A but C is not the son of A. What is C''s relation to A?','Daughter','Niece','Nephew','Uncle','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'If C is not the son but A is the father, C must be the daughter.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','How many times do the hands of a clock coincide in a day?','20','21','22','24','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The hands coincide 11 times every 12 hours.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Find the missing number in the series: 4, 9, 25, 49, 121, ?','144','169','196','225','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'These are squares of prime numbers: 2^2, 3^2, 5^2, 7^2, 11^2. Next is 13^2 = 169.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','One morning after sunrise, Suresh was standing facing a pole. The shadow of the pole fell exactly to his right. To which direction was he facing?','East','West','South','North','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',45,'In the morning, the shadow is to the West. If West is to his right, he is facing South.','pregenerated'),
('504f66f4-bc24-41b3-8644-c8505e6e3481','Sample question 50 for Logical Reasoning Level 1?','Option A','Option B','Option C','Option D','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',45,'Explanation for question 50 of Logical Reasoning Level 1.','pregenerated')
