INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','In SOLID, what does the ''S'' stand for?','Simple Logic','Single Responsibility Principle','Static Structure','System Security','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',30,'The Single Responsibility Principle states that a class should have only one reason to change.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','Which SOLID principle states that objects of a superclass should be replaceable with objects of a subclass without affecting the correctness of the program?','Open-Closed Principle','Liskov Substitution Principle','Interface Segregation Principle','Dependency Inversion Principle','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'LSP ensures that inheritance hierarchy is logically sound and doesn''t break polymorphism.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','The ''O'' in SOLID (Open-Closed Principle) suggests that a class should be:','Open for modification, closed for extension','Open for extension, closed for modification','Open for all, closed for none','Open source and closed source','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Software entities should be open for extension (adding new behavior) but closed for modification (changing existing code).','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','What is ''Encapsulation''?','Hiding the internal state and requiring all interaction to be performed through an object''s methods','The ability to take many forms','Breaking a problem into smaller functions','Copying code from one class to another','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'Encapsulation protects data integrity and reduces coupling.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','Which feature of OOPS allows a class to derive properties and characteristics from another class?','Polymorphism','Abstraction','Encapsulation','Inheritance','["D"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'Inheritance promotes code reusability.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','Which design pattern ensures a class has only one instance and provides a global point of access to it?','Factory Pattern','Singleton Pattern','Observer Pattern','Strategy Pattern','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Singleton is a creational pattern used for shared resources like database connections.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','The pattern used to define a one-to-many dependency between objects so that when one object changes state, all its dependents are notified is:','Adapter Pattern','Observer Pattern','Decorator Pattern','Facade Pattern','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',40,'Observer pattern is key to event-driven programming and UI frameworks.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','Which UML diagram shows the static structure of the system, including classes, their attributes and operations?','Sequence Diagram','Class Diagram','State Machine Diagram','Use Case Diagram','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',30,'Class diagrams are the backbone of object-oriented modeling.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','Sequence diagrams are primarily used to model:','Object interactions over time','Parallel activities in a workflow','Physical deployment of hardware','Database schema','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Sequence diagrams visualize the call flow between objects.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','A ''Use Case Diagram'' represents:','How data flows through the system','The relationship between actors and their interactions with the system','The internal state of an object','How to deploy the application','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Use case diagrams define the requirements from a user perspective.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','What is the difference between ''Composition'' and ''Aggregation''?','Aggregation is a ''part-of'' relationship while Composition is not','In Composition, the child cannot exist without the parent (strong ownership)','Composition uses interfaces while Aggregation uses classes','There is no difference','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Composition implies a life-cycle dependency (e.g., Room is part of House).','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','Which pattern provides a simplified interface to a large body of code, such as a class library?','Proxy Pattern','Facade Pattern','Bridge Pattern','Flyweight Pattern','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Facade masks the complexity of sub-systems.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','According to the Dependency Inversion Principle, high-level modules should depend on:','Low-level modules','Concrete implementations','Abstractions (Interfaces)','Static methods','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'DIP decouples modules, making them easier to test and replace.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','Polymorphism which is resolved at compile-time is known as:','Dynamic Polymorphism','Static Polymorphism (Method Overloading)','Type Casting','Interface Implementation','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Method overloading is determined by the compiler based on method signatures.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','Which design pattern is used to attach new responsibilities to an object dynamically?','Inheritance','Decorator Pattern','Adapter Pattern','Proxy Pattern','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Decorators provide a flexible alternative to subclassing for extending functionality.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','In GRASP, which pattern says you should assign responsibility to a class that has the information necessary to fulfill it?','Creator','Information Expert','Controller','Low Coupling','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'The Expert pattern is a basic rule of thumb for assigning responsibilities in OO design.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','The pattern used to convert the interface of a class into another interface that clients expect is:','Adapter Pattern','Bridge Pattern','Composite Pattern','Chain of Responsibility','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',40,'Adapter allows incompatible classes to work together.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','Which principle is violated if a class is forced to implement methods it does not use?','Single Responsibility Principle','Interface Segregation Principle','Liskov Substitution Principle','Dependency Inversion Principle','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'ISP suggests splitting large, ''fat'' interfaces into smaller, more specific ones.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','What does ''Dynamic Binding'' refer to?','Connecting to a database at runtime','Resolving a method call at execution time based on the actual type of the object','Allocating memory dynamically','Linking libraries','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Dynamic binding is the mechanism that enables method overriding and runtime polymorphism.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','The ''Factory Method'' pattern is used for:','Creating objects without specifying the exact class to be created','Optimizing memory usage','Managing database transactions','Implementing complex algorithms','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',40,'Factory pattern encapsulates object creation logic.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','Which pattern is used to encapsulate a request as an object, thereby allowing us to parameterize clients with different requests?','Command Pattern','State Pattern','Template Pattern','Visitor Pattern','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'The Command pattern is often used to implement undo/redo functionality.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','If you change a class and that change breaks another class, it''s often a sign of violation of:','Single Responsibility Principle','Open-Closed Principle','Coupling and Cohesion problems','All of the above','["D"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Fragile code often stems from a lack of following SOLID principles.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','A ''Self-Associative'' relationship in UML is represented by:','A line connecting two different classes','A line from a class back to itself','A dashed line','A rectangular box','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',40,'Example: An Employee object having a manager who is also an Employee.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','In UML, ''#'' symbol represents which visibility?','Public','Private','Protected','Package','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',30,'+ is Public, - is Private, # is Protected, ~ is Package.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','An ''Abstract Class'' is one that:','Cannot be instantiated and is meant to be subclassed','Has no methods','Is only used for database operations','Is a final class','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Abstract classes define a template or contract for specialized child classes.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','In a Sequence Diagram, a ''Lifeline'' represents:','The duration an object is active','A participant in the interaction','A specific method call','A physical machine','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'The vertical dashed line (lifeline) represents the existence of an object over time.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','The ''Hollywood Principle'' (Don''t call us, we''ll call you) is most closely associated with:','Encapsulation','Inversion of Control (IoC)','Inheritance','Method Overloading','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'The framework or a higher-level module defines the flow and calls back to the custom code.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','The ability of an object to take many forms is:','Polymorphism','Encapsulation','Composition','Inheritance','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'Example: A ''Shape'' variable can hold a ''Circle'', ''Square'', or ''Triangle'' object.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','Which design pattern allows a group of objects to be treated the same way as a single instance of the object?','Decorator Pattern','Composite Pattern','Facade Pattern','Adapter Pattern','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Composite pattern builds tree structures to represent part-whole hierarchies.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','A ''Proxy'' object is used to:','Control access to another object','Sort data','Connect to a printer','Inherit from multiple classes','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Proxies can handle lazy initialization, logging, security checks, etc.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','High cohesion and low coupling aims for:','Rigid code that never changes','Modular, maintainable, and understandable code','Code that runs faster','Code that uses less memory','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',40,'Cohesion is how focused a module is; coupling is how much it depends on others.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','The ''Abstract Factory'' pattern differs from ''Factory Method'' in that it creates families of related objects.','True','False','Only for C++','Only for web apps','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Abstract Factory is a factory of factories.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','Is ''Dependency Injection'' the same as ''Dependency Inversion Principle''?','Yes','No, DI is a technique to implement DIP','DIP is only about database connections','DI is for Java only','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'DIP is the goal/rule; DI is one of the methods to achieve that decoupling.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','An ''Activity Diagram'' is most similar to which traditional diagram?','Flowchart','Pie Chart','Bar Chart','ER Diagram','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',40,'Activity diagrams model the workflow and logic of a process.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','Which UML diagram describes the timeline and behavior of an object as it changes through different modes?','Deployment Diagram','State Machine Diagram','Component Diagram','Package Diagram','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'State machines capture the various conditions an object can be in and how it transitions.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','A solid line with a hollow triangle arrowhead in a UML Class diagram signifies:','Composition','Realization','Generalization (Inheritance)','Dependency','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Standard UML notation for ''is-a'' relationship.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','A dashed line with a hollow triangle arrowhead in a UML Class diagram signifies:','Inheritance','Realization (Interface implementation)','Aggregation','Multiplicity','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Dashed lines in UML often represent weaker or implementation-level connections.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','The ''Bridge'' pattern is primarily used to:','Connect to the internet','Decouple an abstraction from its implementation so the two can vary independently','Sort objects in a list','Serialize data','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Bridge is structural pattern that prefers composition over inheritance.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','Which pattern defines the skeleton of an algorithm in an operation, deferring some steps to subclasses?','Strategy Pattern','Template Method Pattern','Builder Pattern','Prototype Pattern','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Template pattern allows subclasses to redefine certain steps of an algorithm without changing the algorithm''s structure.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','Which pattern is used to separate the construction of a complex object from its representation?','Builder Pattern','Factory Pattern','Singleton Pattern','Observer Pattern','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'Builder pattern is great for creating objects that require many parameters.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','What is ''Multiple Inheritance''?','A class inheriting from multiple superclasses','Multiple classes inheriting from one superclass','Inheriting properties from a grandparent','Inheriting from an interface','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',40,'Many languages (like Java) disallow this to avoid the Diamond Problem.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','The GRASP ''Pure Fabrication'' pattern suggests creating a class that doesn''t represent a real-world domain concept and to achieve:','Lower performance','High cohesion, low coupling, and reusability','More lines of code','Complexity','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'Services like ''Logger'' or ''DBConnector'' are pure fabrications.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','Which access modifier allows members to be accessed within the same package and by subclasses in other packages?','Public','Private','Protected','Default','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'This allows fine-grained control in inheritance hierarchies.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','What does ''Multiplicity'' represent in an association?','The color of the line','The number of instances involved in the relationship','The speed of the system','The database index','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Examples include 1..1 (one to one), 0..* (zero to many).','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','Classes serve as a ___ for objects.','Runtime storage','Blueprint or Template','Method call','Data entry','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',30,'Classes define the structure; objects are the actual instances.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','The Dependency Inversion Principle helps in creating ___ applications.','Loosely-coupled','Tightly-coupled','Monolithic','Web-only','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',40,'Loose coupling makes the system flexible and maintainable.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','In GRASP, which pattern focuses on assigning responsibility to an intermediate object that mediates between other components?','Expert','Controller','Creator','Indirection','["D"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Indirection supports low coupling by adding an intermediate object between components.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','What is the primary goal of the ''Interface Segregation Principle''?','To have one large interface for all clients','To ensure that non-related methods are not grouped together in one interface','To hide all methods','To use inheritance more often','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',30,'ISP states that no client should be forced to depend on methods it does not use.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','What does a diamond-shaped arrowhead represent in a UML class diagram?','Inheritance','Association','Aggregation/Composition','Dependency','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',30,'Hollow diamond is aggregation, solid diamond is composition.','pregenerated'),
('9d880fed-ab0a-4133-ada8-65d7d8600ac1','Which OOPS concept is also known as ''Data Hiding''?','Polymorphism','Inheritance','Encapsulation','Abstraction','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Encapsulation hides the data details and only exposes safe methods.','pregenerated')
