INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is the core part of an Operating System that manages system resources and hardware communication?','Shell','Kernel','GUI','Compiler','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The Kernel is the central component of an OS, acting as a bridge between applications and hardware.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','How does a user-level program request a service from the OS kernel?','Function Call','Interrupt','System Call','API request','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'System calls provide the interface between a running program and the operating system.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','Which state does a process enter when it is waiting for an I/O operation to complete?','Running','Ready','Blocked / Waiting','Terminated','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'A process that cannot continue until an external event (like I/O) occurs moves to the Blocked state.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What resources are typically shared between threads of the same process?','Stack and Registers','Program Counter only','Code, data, and OS resources (like open files)','Nothing is shared','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',30,'Threads share the process''s global resources but maintain their own execution state (stack, PC, registers).','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','Which type of OS is designed to respond to events within a fixed, strictly defined time limit?','Batch OS','Real-time OS (RTOS)','Distributed OS','Network OS','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'RTOS is used in environments where timing is critical, such as aviation or medical systems.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is a ''Microkernel''?','A tiny OS for calculators','An architecture that moves as much functionality as possible from the kernel into user space','A kernel that only supports one user','A kernel with no security','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Microkernels (like Mach or QNX) are highly modular and facilitate improved system stability.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','Why do CPU''s have ''User Mode'' and ''Kernel Mode''?','To make the OS faster','To protect the system from malfunctioning user programs','To allow users to play games','To encrypt files','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Dual-mode operation prevents user programs from directly accessing hardware or sensitive memory.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What does ''PCB'' stand for in an OS?','Process Control Block','Primary Computer Board','Program Command Base','Process Code Bridge','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The PCB contains all the information necessary for the OS to manage a specific process.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is ''Context Switching''?','Switching between keyboard and mouse','The procedure of storing the state of a process so it can be resumed later, and loading the state of another process','Changing the desktop background','Restarting the computer','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Context switching allows the CPU to share its time among multiple processes.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is the role of the ''Short-term Scheduler''?','To decide which processes are brought into memory','To select which of the ready processes should be executed next by the CPU','To backup files to the cloud','To manage the printer queue','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'The short-term scheduler (or CPU scheduler) makes rapid decisions to maximize CPU utilization.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','Which system call is used in Unix-like systems to create a new process?','create()','fork()','make()','new()','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The fork() system call creates a duplicate child process of the calling parent process.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is the first code executed by the computer when it is turned on?','Operating System','BIOS / UEFI','Web Browser','Device Driver','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The BIOS/UEFI performs hardware checks (POST) and then loads the bootloader.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is ''RAM''?','Read All Memory','Random Access Memory','Reliable Access Module','Range Access Manager','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'RAM is the physical volatile memory where instructions and data are stored for fast CPU access.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is a ''Device Driver''?','A hardware component for storage','A software program that allows the OS to communicate with specific hardware devices','A tool to defragment the disk','A user who manages the servers','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Drivers translate generic OS commands into hardware-specific signals.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is ''Inter-Process Communication'' (IPC)?','Users talking on social media','Mechanisms that allow processes to communicate and synchronize their actions','Sending emails between computers','Shared internet connection','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'IPC methods include shared memory and message passing.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is a ''Multithreaded'' application?','An application that runs on multiple computers','An application that can perform multiple tasks simultaneously within a single process','An application that uses a lot of RAM','An application with many code files','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Multithreading improves responsiveness and resource utilization.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','A ''Monolithic Kernel'' differs from a Microkernel in that:','It is much smaller','It runs the entire OS code (drivers, filesystem, scheduler) inside the kernel address space','It doesn''t support multitasking','It is easier to update','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Monolithic kernels (like Linux) offer high performance but can be less modular than microkernels.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','The ''exec()'' system call in Unix is primarily used for:','Deleting a process','Replacing the current process''s memory space and code with a new program','Waiting for a child to finish','Adding more RAM to a process','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'exec() allows a process to start running a different executable.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','A process moves from ''Ready'' to ''Running'' state when it is:','Loaded into memory','Selected by the CPU scheduler and dispatched','Finished its task','Created by the parent','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'This transition is known as ''Dispatching''.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is ''Multiprogramming''?','Having many programmers working on the OS','Keeping multiple processes in memory at once to increase CPU utilization','Running an app on two monitors','Writing code in multiple languages','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'Multiprogramming ensures the CPU is never idle if data is available.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is ''Timesharing'' (Multitasking)?','Dividing the day into work periods','The logic extension of multiprogramming where the CPU switches between processes so rapidly that users can interact with each program','Sharing files across a network','Sharing a computer screen','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Timesharing provides the illusion of concurrent execution for multiple users/apps.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is a ''Burst Time'' in process scheduling?','When the CPU catches fire','The total time a process needs to spend executing on the CPU','The time spent waiting for I/O','The time to boot the OS','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'CPU burst time is the active processing time required by a task.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is a ''Hardware Interrupt''?','A user pressing a key on the keyboard','A signal sent by a hardware device to the CPU to request immediate attention','A software bug that crashes the system','Unplugging the power','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Handled by the Interrupt Service Routine (ISR), interrupts allow the OS to respond to hardware events asynchronously.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','In the storage hierarchy, which of these is the fastest?','Main Memory (RAM)','Registers','Disk','Cache','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Registers are located inside the CPU and are the fastest storage medium.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is a ''Virtual Machine''?','A computer that doesn''t physically exist','A software-based emulation of a physical computer that runs its own OS and applications','A remote server','A backup of the computer','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'VMs allow multiple isolated environments to run on a single physical host.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is a ''Zombie Process''?','A virus process','A process that has finished execution but still has an entry in the process table because its parent hasn''t read its exit status','A process that runs forever','A process that has been deleted','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Zombies are harmless but consume entry space in the process table; they are cleaned up once the parent ''waits'' on them.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is an ''Orphan Process''?','A process without any code','A child process whose parent process has terminated before the child','A process with no output','A process that runs on a different computer','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Orphan processes are usually adopted by the ''init'' process (PID 1) in Unix.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is the primary role of a ''File System''?','To sort the desktop icons','To control how data is stored and retrieved from a disk','To connect to the internet','To manage the printer','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'File systems provide a logical way for users and the OS to store and manage files on physical media.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What does ''GUI'' stand for?','General User Index','Graphical User Interface','Group User Integration','Global User ID','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'GUI provides visual navigation using icons and windows rather than just text commands.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is ''CLI''?','Common Log Index','Command Line Interface','Core Link Integration','Central Logic Item','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'CLI allows users to interact with the OS by typing text commands.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','Why are system calls categorized by numbers in the kernel?','To save memory','To use as an index into a table (System Call Table) to find the correct kernel function','To hide the function names from users','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The system call number allows for a fast, centralized way to dispatch requests.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','In Round Robin scheduling, what is the ''Time Quantum''?','The total time the CPU runs','A fixed small unit of time assigned to each process in turn','The time to switch between programs','The time to boot the computer','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Time Quantum ensures fair CPU sharing among all ready processes.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','Which scheduling algorithm serves processes based on the order they arrived in the ready queue?','Round Robin','FCFS (First-Come, First-Served)','Shortest Job First','Priority Scheduling','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'FCFS is the simplest scheduling algorithm but can lead to long wait times (Convoy Effect).','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is ''Fragmentation'' in memory management?','Burning the RAM','The development of small, non-contiguous free memory spaces that are difficult to allocate to new processes','Breaking a file into segments','A way to speed up the CPU','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'External fragmentation occurs when the total free memory is enough for a request, but it isn''t contiguous.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is ''Paging''?','Dividing a book into pages','A memory management scheme that eliminates the need for contiguous allocation of physical memory by dividing it into fixed-size blocks (frames)','Connecting to the internet','Sorting files by name','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Paging solves the external fragmentation problem by mapping logical pages to physical frames.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is a ''Race Condition''?','Testing which computer is faster','A flaw where several processes access and manipulate the same data concurrently, and the final value depends on the order of execution','Winning a contest in code','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Sync mechanisms like Mutexes or Semaphores are used to prevent race conditions.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is ''Starvation'' in scheduling?','A process has no input','When a process is perpetually denied access to the CPU because other processes are repeatedly favored','A server with no power','A deleted process','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Priority scheduling can lead to starvation; it''s often fixed by ''Aging'', which increases a process''s priority over time.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is ''Spooling''?','Sorting old files','Storing data temporarily in a buffer (often on disk) to be processed by a slower peripheral device like a printer','Streaming video content','Writing logs for the OS','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'Spooling allows programs to continue without waiting for slow output devices.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is an ''Access Control List'' (ACL)?','A list of users who visited a website','A list of permissions attached to an object (like a file) specifying which users or processes can access it','A keyboard shortcut','A way to install software','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'ACLs are fundamental for managing system security and file permissions.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is ''Deadlock'' in an OS?','When the battery dies','A situation where two or more processes are stuck waiting for each other to release resources they need','Deleting a locked file','A server crash','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Deadlock results in all involved processes being permanently stalled.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is ''Swapping'' in memory management?','Exchanging parts of two computers','Moving a process from main memory to temporary disk storage to free up RAM','Changing the file name','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Swapping allows the OS to handle more processes than it can physically fit in RAM at once.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is ''Mutual Exclusion''?','Only one person using the computer','Requirement that only one process at a time can be in its ''critical section'' to access a shared resource','Encrypting data with two keys','A way to exclude users from a group','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Mutual exclusion prevents data corruption by ensuring serialized access to shared data.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is ''Virtual Memory''?','Memory for video games','A technique that allows the execution of processes that may not be completely in memory (gives the illusion of more RAM)','Storing data in the cloud','Fast CPU registers','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Virtual memory map logical addresses to physical disk space using demand paging.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is ''Direct Memory Access'' (DMA)?','The CPU accessing RAM directly','A feature allowing hardware devices to transfer data directly to/from main memory without constant CPU involvement','Managing memory by hand','Deleting memory logs','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'DMA improves system performance by freeing the CPU from simple data move tasks.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','In a PCB, what is the ''Program Counter'' (PC)?','A count of how many apps are open','The address of the next instruction to be executed by the process','The security ID of the user','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'The PC ensures the CPU knows exactly where to continue after an interrupt or switch.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is a ''Path'' in a filesystem?','A physical wire','The unique sequence of directories required to reach a specific file','The order of code','A way to backup the disk','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Paths can be absolute (starting from root) or relative (starting from current directory).','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is ''Shared Memory'' IPC?','Sending data over Wi-Fi','Processes communicating by reading and writing to a region of memory that is accessible to all involved processes','Sharing a USB drive','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Shared memory is the fastest form of IPC as it avoids data copying between user and kernel space.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is ''Response Time'' in scheduling?','Total time to finish the job','The time from when a request is submitted until the first response is produced (not final output)','The time spent waiting in the queue','The time it takes to boot the OS','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',40,'Response time is more important than turnaround time for interactive systems.','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is the ''Logical Address'' space?','The physical location in RAM','The address generated by the CPU during process execution','The address on the hard drive','The IP address','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Logical addresses are mapped to physical addresses by the Memory Management Unit (MMU).','pregenerated'),
('b566967e-ba3d-4b99-81f1-fe4fa916b478','What is ''Buffering'' in I/O management?','Cleaning the screen','Storing data in memory temporarily while it is being transferred between two devices or a device and an application','Slowing down a process','A way to encrypt data','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Buffering helps handle speed mismatches between producers and consumers of data.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','In Shortest Job First (SJF) scheduling, what happens if several processes have the same burst time?','The scheduler picks one at random','FCFS (First-Come, First-Served) is used to break the tie','The scheduler crashes','The process with the highest ID wins','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'FCFS is the standard tie-breaking rule for most scheduling algorithms.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is the ''Convoy Effect'' in FCFS scheduling?','When many small processes are stuck behind one long CPU-bound process','A way to speed up the system','Using multiple CPUs for one task','A bug in the scheduling logic','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Convoy effect leads to poor CPU and device utilization as small tasks wait for a massive one to finish.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What are the three requirements to solve the ''Critical Section'' problem?','Speed, Memory, Security','Mutual Exclusion, Progress, and Bounded Waiting','CPU, RAM, DISK','Lock, Unlock, Wait','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Mutual Exclusion (only one in CS), Progress (decisions can be made), and Bounded Waiting (no infinite waiting).','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','A ''Binary Semaphore'' is functionally equivalent to a:','Counting Semaphore','Mutex (Mutual Exclusion lock)','Queue','Database index','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Binary semaphores take values 0 or 1, primarily used for mutual exclusion.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','In the ''Dining Philosophers'' problem, what is a common cause of deadlock?','They all eat at the same time','Every philosopher picks up the left fork simultaneously and waits forever for the right fork','They run out of food','The forks are broken','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'This classic problem demonstrates resource contention and the risk of circular wait.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','Which of these is NOT one of the four necessary conditions for Deadlock?','Mutual Exclusion','Hold and Wait','No Preemption','Circular Progress','["D"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'The four conditions (Coffman conditions) are Mutual Exclusion, Hold and Wait, No Preemption, and Circular Wait.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is the primary used of the ''Banker''s Algorithm''?','Calculating interest rates','Deadlock avoidance by checking if a resource allocation leads to an ''Unsafe'' state','Sorting database records','Managing user bank accounts','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'The Banker''s algorithm ensures that there is at least one sequence (safe sequence) for all processes to finish.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is ''Internal Fragmentation''?','Free space between allocated blocks','Wasted space inside a memory block that is larger than requested but allocated as a fixed-size partition','Memory that is physically broken','Deleting files incorrectly','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Fixed-size partitions often lead to internal fragmentation.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is ''External Fragmentation''?','Wasted space inside a block','When total free memory is enough for a request but it is divided into small non-contiguous pieces','Using all the RAM','Files stored on a USB drive','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Variable-size partitions generally lead to external fragmentation over time.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','In paging, what is the role of a ''Page Table''?','To sort the logic of the code','To map logical page numbers to physical frame numbers','To store the contents of a file','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The page table is a data structure used by the virtual memory system to store the mapping.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is a ''Page Fault''?','A bug in the website code','An interrupt that occurs when a program tries to access a page that is mapped in the virtual address space but not currently in physical memory','A broken hard drive','A user error','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'The OS must handle the page fault by bringing the page in from disk.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is ''Belady''s Anomaly''?','A security vulnerability','A phenomenon where increasing the number of page frames results in MORE page faults for certain access patterns using FIFO replacement','A type of database crash','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Belady''s anomaly shows that FIFO is not always the best page replacement strategy.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','Which page replacement algorithm replaces the page that will not be used for the longest period of time in the future?','FIFO','LRU','Optimal (MIN) Algorithm','LFU','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'The Optimal algorithm yields the lowest possible page fault rate but is impossible to implement without knowing the future.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is a ''Spinlock''?','A lock for a spinning disk','A lock where the waiting process continuously loops (polls) checking if the lock is available','A lock used for mouse clicks','A very fast database index','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Spinlocks are useful for short wait times where the cost of a context switch is higher than spinning.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is ''Circular Wait'' in deadlock conditions?','Waiting in a circle for a coffee','A set of processes {P0, P1, ..., Pn} exists such that P0 is waiting for a resource held by P1, P1 for P2, ..., and Pn for P0','Retrying the same code in a loop','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Circular wait completes the chain of dependencies that creates a deadlock.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is the ''Bounded-Buffer'' problem also known as?','Dining Philosophers','Producer-Consumer Problem','Readers-Writers Problem','Banker''s Algorithm','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'This problem describes a producer putting items into a buffer and a consumer taking them out.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is ''Segmentation''?','Breaking data for encryption','A memory management scheme that supports the user''s view of memory as a collection of logical segments (e.g., Code, Stack, Data)','A fixed-size paging method','Sorting logs by size','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Segmentation uses variable-sized blocks corresponding to logical program components.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is ''Thrashing''?','Deleting many files at once','A state where the OS spends more time swapping pages in and out of memory than executing actual instructions','A hardware error in the CPU','A very fast processing mode','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Thrashing usually occurs when the total working set of all processes exceeds physical RAM.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is ''Preemptive'' scheduling?','A scheduler that uses only one CPU','When the OS can interrupt a running process and swap it out for another process (e.g., when a higher priority one arrives)','A scheduler that never stops a task','Scheduling without using code','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Preemption allows for more responsive systems but adds context switching overhead.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','In ''Priority'' scheduling, what is ''Aging'' used for?','Calculating the lifetime of a CPU','Gradually increasing the priority of processes that wait in the system for a long time to prevent starvation','Deleting old processes','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Aging ensures that low-priority processes will eventually get to execute.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is the ''TLB'' (Translation Lookaside Buffer)?','A high-speed cache for page table entries used to speed up logical-to-physical address translation','A backup memory','A buffer for video data','A type of network switch','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'TLB misses significantly slow down memory access; the TLB caches current mappings for the CPU.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is ''Turnaround Time''?','The time a process spends in the ready queue','The total time from process submission to process completion','The time it takes to switch a process','The time the CPU was idle','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Turnaround time = Waiting Time + CPU Execution Time + I/O Time.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','In memory allocation, what is the ''First-Fit'' strategy?','Finding the smallest free block that fits','Allocating the first free hole that is big enough to hold the process','Allocating the largest free block','Assigning it at random','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'First-fit is generally faster than Best-fit or Worst-fit.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','In memory allocation, what is the ''Best-Fit'' strategy?','Allocating the first hole that fits','Allocating the smallest free hole that is big enough, which might produce tiny leftover fragments','Allocating the largest hole','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Best-fit searches the entire list to find the most ''efficient'' block size.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is ''Copy-on-Write'' (COW) optimization?','Writing data while copying it','A technique where parent and child processes share memory pages until one of them modifies a page','A security feature for files','Deleting the original after copying','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'COW makes process creation (fork) extremely efficient.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is ''Atomic'' operation in OS synchronization?','An operation using nuclear power','An operation that completes in its entirety without interruption by any other process','A very small operation','Deleting a file by bits','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Atomic operations (like TestAndSet) are fundamental building blocks for locks.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is a ''Monitor'' in process synchronization?','A physical screen','A high-level language construct that provides a convenient and effective mechanism for process synchronization by encapsulating data and procedures','A software that watches for bugs','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Monitors ensure that only one process at a time can be active within the monitor structure.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','How can you break a ''Circular Wait'' to prevent deadlock?','Restarting the computer','Imposing a total ordering of all resource types and requiring processes to request resources in increasing order','Using more RAM','Deleting the processes','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Order-based resource requests effectively break the circular wait condition.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','In a 32-bit logical address with 4KB page size, how many bits represent the ''Offset''?','8','10','12','20','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'4KB is 2^12 bytes, so 12 bits are needed for the offset.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is ''Inverted Page Table''?','A table that sorts by frame number instead of page number, significantly reducing table size','A table with reverse code','A page table inside another table','None of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Inverted page tables are used to save memory by having only one entry per physical frame.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is the ''Working-Set Model'' used for?','Calculating user work hours','Estimating and guaranteeing the minimum required memory (pages) a process needs for a specific time window to avoid thrashing','Managing a group of developers','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The working set is the set of pages a process is actively referencing.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is ''Direct Allocation'' (Contiguous) in filesystems?','Files can be stored anywhere','Each file occupies a set of contiguous blocks on the disk','The OS decides after deletion','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Contiguous allocation is fast for reads but leads to severe disk fragmentation.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is ''Interrupt-Driven'' I/O?','The CPU checks the device in a loop','The device notifies the CPU via a signal when it is ready for data transfer, allowing the CPU to work on other tasks in between','The user interrupts the computer','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Interrupt-driven I/O is much more efficient than Polling (Busy-Waiting).','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What does a ''Disk Scheduler'' aim to minimize?','The size of the files','The total seek time (movement of the disk arm)','The number of users','The power usage','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Disk scheduling algorithms like SSTF or SCAN optimize the physical movement of the disk head.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','Which disk scheduling algorithm always travels to the end of the disk before reversing direction?','FCFS','SSTF','SCAN (Elevator Algorithm)','C-LOOK','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'The SCAN algorithm services requests as it sweeps from one end of the disk to the other.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is the main role of the ''Kernel Mode'' bit in the processor''s status register?','To allow encrypted code to run','To enable/disable the execution of privileged instructions','To tell the user which OS is running','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'The mode bit ensures strict separation between user and system privileges.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is ''Strict Alternation'' in synchronization?','Changing code variables','A synchronization method where two processes must alternate their entry into the critical section (Process A, then B, then A...)','A bug in the multithreading logic','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Strict alternation violates the ''Progress'' requirement of the Critical Section problem.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is ''Compaction'' in memory?','Removing unused code','Moving all occupied memory blocks to one side of memory to create a single large free area','Compressing RAM using a zip tool','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Compaction solves external fragmentation but is computationally expensive.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is ''Waiting Time'' in scheduling?','The time spent being processed','The total time a process spends in the ready queue waiting for its turn on the CPU','The time to switch to another process','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Waiting time = Turnaround Time - Burst Time.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is the ''Principle of Least Privilege''?','Giving all users admin access for simplicity','Giving users and processes only the minimum permissions they need to perform their tasks','Allowing No access to the computer','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'This principle minimizes the potential damage from compromised or buggy software.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is the difference between ''User-level'' and ''Kernel-level'' threads?','User threads reach the CPU faster','User threads are managed by a thread library and the OS is unaware of them; Kernel threads are managed directly by the OS','Kernel threads are for games only','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Kernel-level threads allow for true parallelism on multi-core systems even if one thread blocks.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','Which scheduler is known as a ''Swapper''?','Short-term Scheduler','Medium-term Scheduler','Long-term Scheduler','IO Scheduler','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'The medium-term scheduler swaps processes in and out of main memory to control degrees of multiprogramming.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is an ''I-node'' (Index Node) in Unix-like systems?','A high-speed internet node','A data structure containing information about a file, such as attributes and disk block locations','A list of user names','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'I-nodes are the core structure representing files on most Linux/Unix file systems.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','In the deadlock recovery strategy, what is ''Resource Preemption''?','Deleting the resource','Taking a resource away from a process and giving it to another to break the deadlock','Rebooting the server','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Preemption can be used for recovery but requires a safe way to ''roll back'' the victim process.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','In a ''Demand Paging'' system, what is the ''Valid-Invalid'' bit?','Tells the user if they can login','Indicates whether a specific page is currently in RAM (Valid) or on disk (Invalid)','A bit to fix corrupted data','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'An access to a page marked ''invalid'' triggers a page fault.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','What is a ''Pipe'' in Unix?','A physical part of the computer','A mechanism that allows the output of one process to serve as input for another','A database connection','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Pipes are a foundational IPC method in the Unix command-line philosophy.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','Which page replacement algorithm keeps track of how many times each page has been used?','FIFO','LRU','LFU (Least Frequently Used)','Clock','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'LFU is based on the idea that highly active pages will have higher usage counts.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','In the ''Readers-Writers'' problem, what is the primary conflict?','Readers cannot read together','A writer requires exclusive access, while multiple readers can coexist','There are too many readers','The file is too large','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Correct synchronization must ensure that no reader is active when a writer is modifying the data.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','In ''Priority'' scheduling, a higher numerical priority value usually means:','Lower priority (in many systems)','Always higher priority','The same priority','It doesn''t matter','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Convention varies, but in many kernels (like Unix), lower numbers represent higher scheduling priority.','pregenerated'),
('1ba6bba5-56d1-4201-8281-aa7d6e9d393d','In a hard disk drive, what is ''Latency'' (Rotational)?','The time to move the arm to the track','The time it takes for the desired sector to rotate under the read/write head','The speed of the network','The time to boot the computer','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Total disk access time = Seek Time + Rotational Latency + Transfer Time.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is ''Hierarchical Paging'' (Multi-level Paging)?','A system where only one page exists','A paging architecture that uses multiple page tables in a tree structure to handle very large logical address spaces','Paging without a page table','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Hierarchical paging prevents the page table itself from becoming too large to fit in memory.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','Why is ''Disabling Interrupts'' not a suitable synchronization method for multi-processor systems?','It is too slow','It only stops interrupts on the local processor, leaving other processors free to access shared memory','It crashes the bios','Processors cannot be disabled','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Disabling interrupts works on single-core systems but fails to provide mutual exclusion on multi-core hardware.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is a ''Hashed Page Table'' and why is it used?','A table for encryption only','A structure where logical page numbers are hashed to find physical addresses, suitable for 64-bit sparse address spaces','A way to delete pages','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'Hashed page tables are more efficient than hierarchical ones when dealing with very large, empty address spaces.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','In the Working-Set Model, what does the parameter ''Δ'' (Delta) represent?','The change in memory speed','The ''Working Set Window'', defining the fixed number of most recent page references to consider','The amount of free RAM','The time to switch processes','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'The working set is calculated based on references made during the last Δ time units.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is ''Indexed Allocation'' in a filesystem?','Storing all files in an index','Allocation where each file has its own index block containing the addresses of all its disk blocks','Contiguous allocation only','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Indexed allocation supports efficient random access without the overhead of contiguous blocks.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is ''Multilevel Indexed Allocation''?','Allocation using multiple computers','Using an index block that points to other index blocks, allowing for support of extremely large files','A way to encrypt files using levels','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'The Unix inode structure uses direct blocks, single indirect, double indirect, and triple indirect pointers.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','Which RAID level provides both ''Mirroring'' (Redundancy) and ''Striping'' (Performance)?','RAID 0','RAID 1','RAID 10 (1+0)','RAID 5','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'RAID 10 is a nested RAID level that stripes data across mirrored pairs of disks.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What characterizes ''RAID 5''?','Mirroring only','Striping with distributed parity, allowing for recovery if one drive fails','Double mirroring','No security','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'RAID 5 offers a balance between performance and storage efficiency for fault tolerance.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','How does ''Free Space Management'' using a ''Bit Map'' work?','Mapping bits of a file to memory','A vector of bits where each bit represents a disk block (0=allocated, 1=free)','A way to draw the disk on screen','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Bit maps are simple and efficient for finding contiguous free space blocks.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is the purpose of the ''Bad Block'' management in a drive controller?','To delete files that are bad','To mark physically damaged sectors and remap them to spare sectors on the disk','To encrypt bad files','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Bad block remapping (sector sparing) preserves the integrity of the storage media.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is ''Double Buffering''?','Buying two buffers','Using two buffers to allow the producer to fill one while the consumer empties the other simultaneously','Twice the speed of buffering','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Double buffering decouples I/O tasks and processing, increasing overall throughput.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is an ''Access Matrix'' in OS security?','A movie about computers','A conceptual model representiong rights, where rows are domains (users) and columns are objects (files)','A password list','A way to sort files','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The access matrix defines who is allowed to do what to which object.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','Which of these is NOT typically part of the state saved during a ''Context Switch''?','CPU Register contents','Program Counter','Main Memory contents (RAM)','Process State (Running, Ready, etc.)','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'The main memory contents stay in place; only processor registers and execution state are swapped.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is ''Paging with Segmentation''?','Using both pages and segments','Dividing each segment into multiple pages, combining the logical view of segmentation with physical benefits of paging','Encrypting segments into pages','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'This hybrid approach gives programmers segments while the hardware manages physical memory in frames.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is ''C-SCAN'' disk scheduling?','Circular SCAN - it services requests in one direction and immediately returns to the beginning without servicing on the return trip','A faster version of SCAN','Scanning only the corners','None of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'C-SCAN provides more uniform waiting times than traditional SCAN.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','In the ''Many-to-One'' threading model, what is the biggest drawback?','Users cannot use many threads','If one thread blocks (e.g., waiting for I/O), the entire process and all other threads in it are also blocked','It uses too much memory','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Many-to-one is fast (user-level) but lacks the parallelism needed for multi-core systems.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is the purpose of the ''Swap()'' instruction for synchronization?','To swap two processes','An atomic hardware instruction that exchanges the values of two memory locations, useful for implementing locks','To move files','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Atomic instructions like ''Swap'' and ''TestAndSet'' are essential for reliable mutual exclusion.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is the ''Effective Access Time'' (EAT) formula considering TLB?','EAT = Speed of RAM','EAT = (Hit Ratio * Access Time) + (Miss Ratio * (TLB + 2 * Access Time))','EAT = Time to find data','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'EAT accounts for both fast TLB hits and the penalty of multi-step page table lookups on misses.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','How does the OS typically handle deadlocks in consumer operating systems (like Windows/Linux)?','Using Banker''s algorithm for every request','The ''Ostrich Algorithm'' - ignore the problem and assume it rarely happens (reboot if needed)','Always preventing Circular Wait','Deleting blocked processes immediately','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Full deadlock detection/avoidance is often too expensive for general-purpose workstations.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is the ''Disk Arm'' movement in SSTF (Shortest Seek Time First) scheduling?','Arm stays in place','The arm moves to the request closest to its current position, which minimizes seek time but can cause starvation','The arm moves to the beginning','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'SSTF is greedy and can ignore far-away requests indefinitely.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is ''Reentrant Code''?','Code that enters the memory twice','Non-self-modifying code that can be shared by multiple processes simultaneously without risk of data corruption','Code that never finishes','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Reentrant code is essential for multi-user/multi-threaded shared libraries.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is a ''Password Salt''?','Physical salt for the keyboard','A random string added to passwords before hashing to protect against Rainbow Table attacks','The name of the encryption key','A way to hide files','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Salting ensures that even identical passwords have unique hash values.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is ''Journaling'' in a filesystem (like ext4 or NTFS)?','Writing a diary for the user','A technique where changes are first recorded in a ''log'' (journal) before being written to the main filesystem, ensuring consistency after a crash','Printing a list of all files','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Journaling prevents filesystem corruption during unexpected power losses.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','In the ''wait()'' semaphore operation, what actually happens to the semaphore variable ''S''?','It is increased','If S > 0, it is decremented; otherwise, the process blocks','It is deleted','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'wait() (or P) attempts to acquire a resource.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','In the ''signal()'' semaphore operation, what happens to ''S''?','It is decreased','It is incremented, and if any processes were blocked waiting for S, one is woken up','The computer reboots','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'signal() (or V) releases a resource.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is ''Dirty Bit'' (Modified Bit) used for in paging?','To clean the RAM','A bit that indicates if a page in RAM has been modified, meaning it must be written to disk before being replaced','A bit for encryption','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Dirty bits avoid unnecessary disk writes for pages that haven''t changed.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','How does ''Page Fault Frequency'' (PFF) help prevent thrashing?','By deleting all pages','By monitoring the rate of faults and adjusting the number of frames allocated to a process (increasing if fault rate is too high)','A way to increase CPU speed','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'PFF aims to keep the fault rate within an acceptable upper and lower bound.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is ''Physical Address'' vs ''Logical Address''?','Physical is on disk, Logical is in RAM','Logical is generated by CPU; Physical is the actual location in memory hardware','There is no difference','Logical is for users, Physical is for routers','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'The MMU (Memory Management Unit) handles the mapping between these two spaces at runtime.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is a ''Hard Link'' in Unix?','A physical wire to the file','A directory entry that points directly to the file''s index node (inode)','A shortcut to a file','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Deleting a hard link doesn''t delete the data until the final link is removed.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is a ''Soft Link'' (Symbolic Link)?','A broken hard link','A special type of file that contains the path to another file or directory','The OS deciding where to put files','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Symbolic links are like Windows shortcuts; they break if the original file is moved.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is ''Low-level Formatting''?','Deleting the BIOS','The physical division of a disk into sectors that the controller can read and write','Formatting a disk using basic code','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Low-level formatting is done at the factory and prepares the magnetic surface for data blocks.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is the ''Boot Block''?','A brick on the keyboard during boot','A dedicated section of the disk that contains the code for loading the OS kernel into memory','A list of users who cannot boot','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'The boot block is the final stage of the handoff from BIOS to OS.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What happens in a ''Counting Semaphore'' if its value is negative?','The computer explodes','The absolute value indicates how many processes are currently blocked waiting for that semaphore','It is invalid','It means the computer is fast','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Wait/Signal logic manages the ''queue'' aspect of semaphores using the variable''s magnitude.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is ''Page Table Fragmentation''?','Pages being slow','Memory wasted when the page table consumes more space than strictly necessary (e.g., for sparse segments)','When the CPU cache is full','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Sparse address spaces can lead to massive empty page tables if Multi-level paging is not used.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','In paging, what is ''Hit Ratio''?','Number of users on the site','The percentage of time that a logical address translation is found in the TLB','How fast the disk spins','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Higher hit ratios mean faster effective memory access as the slow page table is rarely consulted.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is a ''Capability List'' in OS protection?','A list of computer features','A distributed security model where each domain (user/process) holds a list of objects and the operations allowed on them','A list of software versions','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Capability lists are like ''keys'' held by users, providing more localized security than ACLs.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is the primary ''overhead'' of multitasking?','Buying more monitors','The total time spent in context switches where no useful work is performed by the CPU','The electricity cost','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'High switch rates can consume a significant portion of CPU capacity.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is a ''Layered'' OS architecture?','A cake-style OS','An OS organized into level, where each layer uses services only from the layer below it','A way to install apps','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Layering facilitates modularity and testing by isolating system components.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is ''Disk Interleaving''?','Adding labels to disks','Storing consecutive sectors in non-contiguous physical locations to account for disk controller processing time','Scanning two disks at once','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Interleaving prevents the read head from missing the next sector while the previous one is being processed.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is a ''Trap'' in OS contexts?','A trap for hackers','A software-generated interrupt caused by an error (like division by zero) or a specific request (system call)','A bug in the hardware','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Traps are synchronous events triggered by code execution.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is ''Fair Share'' scheduling?','Everyone gets the same code','A scheduling policy that considers which user owns a process, ensuring that even if one user has many processes, they don''t hog the whole CPU','Removing users from the system','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Fair share scheduling prevents a single user''s batch of tasks from starving other users.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What characterizes ''Deadlock Prevention''?','Handling after it happens','Setting system constraints to ensure that at least one of the four necessary conditions for deadlock can NEVER occur','Allowing deadlock but fixing it fast','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Prevention is more restrictive but safer than detection/recovery.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','How can you prevent the ''Hold and Wait'' condition?','Processes must request all required resources at once before starting','Processes can only wait for 1 minute','A way to use more RAM','None of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'By requesting everything at once, a process never holds a subset while waiting for the rest.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','In paging, what is ''Internal Fragmentation'' cost?','Total size of the page','On average, half of the last page allocated to a process is wasted','None of the above','Fixed cost of the page table','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'While paging solves external fragmentation, it inevitably wastes a bit on the tail end of allocations.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is the benefit of a ''Smaller'' page size?','Faster disk reads','Reduced internal fragmentation','Smaller page table','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Smaller pages fit process memory needs more tightly but increase page table management overhead.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is the benefit of a ''Larger'' page size?','No external fragmentation','Smaller page table and more efficient I/O for large file reads','Perfect memory use','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Larger pages mean fewer entries in the page table and faster disk-to-memory block transfers.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is a ''Trap Door'' (Backdoor) in security?','A hardware door in the server room','A secret entry point into a program that bypasses normal security authentication','A bug in the BIOS','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Backdoors are often left by developers for debugging but are massive security risks if found by attackers.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is ''Sandboxing'' in OS security?','Playing with sand','Running an application in a tightly restricted environment where it can only access specific resources','Deleting suspicious files','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Sandboxing (used in browsers and mobile OSs) protects the host system from malicious apps.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is ''Distributed Shared Memory'' (DSM)?','Memory for different computers','A conceptual model where multiple computers on a network act as if they are using a single, shared RAM space','Sharing a CPU with a neighbor','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'DSM simplifies programming for clusters but requires complex coherence protocols.','pregenerated'),
('1575e241-47ce-44c4-ba57-d37175dd8206','What is ''Kernel I/O Subsystem''?','A hardware part for I/O','The part of the OS that provides services like I/O scheduling, buffering, caching, and spooling to manage generic device access','A driver for the mouse','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',35,'This subsystem abstracts hardware details, providing a uniform ''everything-is-a-file'' interface.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is the primary goal of the ''Completely Fair Scheduler'' (CFS) used in modern Linux kernels?','To give everyone 1 second of CPU time','To model an ''ideal, multi-tasking CPU'' by tracking ''vruntime'' (virtual runtime) for each task and always picking the one with the least vruntime','To prioritize background tasks over user tasks','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'CFS uses a Red-Black Tree to efficiently manage and select tasks based on their virtual runtime balance.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','In Real-time systems, what characterizes ''Rate Monotonic'' (RM) scheduling?','The scheduler changes rates every minute','A static priority policy where tasks with shorter logic periods (higher rates) are assigned higher priorities','The OS decides at random','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'RM is optimal for static priority schedules with periodic tasks.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is ''Earliest Deadline First'' (EDF) scheduling?','A dynamic priority scheme where priorities are assigned according to the deadline of the current task (closer deadline = higher priority)','Finishing the oldest task first','Deleting tasks that miss their deadline','None of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'EDF is an optimal dynamic scheduling algorithm for both periodic and aperiodic tasks.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','In virtualization, what is the ''Hypervisor'' (VMM)?','A high-speed monitor','The software layer that creates and runs virtual machines, managing the translation of guest OS requests to physical hardware','A tool to backup the computer','A network security tool','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Hypervisors are either Bare-metal (Type 1) or Hosted (Type 2).','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What are ''Linux Namespaces'' and ''Cgroups'' in the context of Docker containers?','The file paths for Docker files','Namespaces provide isolation (process view, networking); Cgroups provide resource limitation (CPU, RAM, I/O)','A way to install Docker on Windows','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'These two kernel features are the fundamental building blocks of modern containerization.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','How does ''ASLR'' (Address Space Layout Randomization) improve OS security?','By changing the password every hour','By randomly arranging the address space positions of key data areas (stack, heap, libraries), making it harder for attackers to predict memory locations for exploits','By encrypting the motherboard','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'ASLR is a standard defense against many types of buffer overflow and ROP (Return-Oriented Programming) attacks.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is ''NUMA'' (Non-Uniform Memory Access)?','A bug in the memory controller','A memory design for multi-processor systems where memory access time depends on the memory''s location relative to the processor (local vs remote)','A way to speed up the BIOS','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'NUMA-aware operating systems try to keep a process and its data on the same NUMA node for performance.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is ''Location Transparency'' in a Distributed Operating System?','Knowing exactly where every server is','The ability of users and applications to access resources (files/processes) without knowledge of their physical location on the network','Making the screen transparent','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Transparency is a key design goal for making a group of computers appear as a single system.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is a ''Message Queue'' in System V IPC?','A list of emails','A linked list of messages stored within the kernel, allowing processes to exchange data even if they are not running at the same time (asynchronous)','A way to send messages to the user','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Message queues provide structured communication with persistence independent of process lifetimes.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is a ''Log-structured File System'' (LFS)?','A system that only writes log files','A filesystem that treats the disk as a circular log and only appends new data and metadata to the end, improving write performance significantly','A filesystem with reverse names','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'LFS is optimized for workloads with heavy writes and can offer massive benefits for flash-based storage.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is ''Mandatory Access Control'' (MAC) compared to DAC?','Users choose who sees their files (DAC) vs the OS enforcing policy regardless of user wishes (MAC)','MAC is for Apple computers only','There is no difference','MAC is a hardware lock','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'MAC (used in SELinux) is more secure because users cannot accidentally (or maliciously) grant access to sensitive data.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is ''Superpages'' optimization?','A page that covers the whole RAM','The use of extremely large page frames (e.g., 2MB or 1GB) to reduce TLB misses for memory-intensive applications','Pages for high-priority tasks','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Superpages (or Huge Pages) significantly improve performance for databases and large scientific calculations.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is ''Processor Affinity'' (CPU Pinning)?','A processor liking a process','The BIOS/OS attempting to keep a process on the same processor core during its lifetime to maximize cache hit rates','Multiple CPUs sharing the same RAM','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Migrating processes between cores constantly destroys cache performance (Cold Cache problem).','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is ''Vectored I/O'' (Scatter-Gather)?','Using many mice at once','A technique allowing a single system call to read/write multiple data buffers from/to a single stream in one operation','A type of fiber optic signal','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Scatter-gather (e.g., writev in Unix) reduces the number of expensive system calls required for complex data transfers.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is a ''Return-Oriented Programming'' (ROP) attack?','A bug in computer programming classes','An advanced exploit technique where an attacker pieces together existing snippets of executable code (gadgets) to bypass security like DEP','When a program returns the wrong value','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'ROP is Used to bypass ''No-Execute'' (NX/DEP) protections by using the program''s own code against it.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','In distributed systems, what is ''Migration Transparency''?','Seeing the birds fly','The ability to move a running process (or file) from one machine to another without disturbing its operation or the user''s perception','When code moves to the cloud','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Migration transparency is essential for dynamic load balancing in large clusters.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','How does the ''Deadline'' I/O scheduler in Linux work?','It deletes packets that are late','It maintains separate read and write queues with expiration times to prevent individual requests from being starved','It only writes at night','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Deadline scheduler prioritizes reads over writes and ensures every request is eventually serviced.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is ''Copy-on-Write'' (COW) file systems (e.g., Btrfs, ZFS)?','Copying data only when you write it','A filesystem architecture where existing data is never overwritten; changes always create a new version of the data elsewhere on disk','A way to duplicate files for free','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'COW filesystems provide instant snapshots, crash resilience, and easy data rollback.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is an ''Evil Maid'' attack in the context of disk encryption?','A physical bug in the charger','An attack where someone with physical access to an unattended device installs malware to capture encryption keys (e.g., during boot)','A virus that deletes the BIOS','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Evil Maid attacks target the unencrypted portion of the boot process (or the user directly).','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is ''Kernel Panic''?','When the programmer is scared','A safety measure taken by the OS kernel upon detecting a fatal internal error it cannot safely recover from','When the fan is too loud','A blue screen only on Windows','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'In Unix/Linux it''s a Panic; in Windows, it''s a BSOD (Blue Screen of Death).','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is ''Lock Elision'' using Intel TSX?','Removing all locks from code','A hardware feature that speculatively executes a critical section without acquiring the lock, only rolling back if a conflict occurs','Encrypting the locks','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Lock elision using ''Transactional Synchronization Extensions'' can greatly speed up multi-threaded code.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is ''Memory-Mapped I/O'' (MMIO)?','Drawing the RAM on a map','Assigning specific physical memory addresses to hardware device registers, allowing the CPU to communicate with devices using standard memory instructions','A network for database servers','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'MMIO simplifies hardware communication compared to using special I/O instructions (like x86 ''IN'' and ''OUT'').','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is ''Translation Lookaside Buffer'' (TLB) ''Flush''?','Cleaning the RAM with water','The process of clearing the CPU''s address translation cache (e.g., during a context switch to a process with a different address space)','A way to increase memory speed','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Flushing the TLB prevents old translations from the previous process from being used by the new one.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is ''Loadable Kernel Modules'' (LKM) in Linux?','Installing apps from the internet','The ability of a kernel to add or remove code (like drivers) at runtime without needing to reboot the system','A way to use more RAM for the OS','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'LKMs give monolithic kernels the flexibility and modularity typically associated with microkernels.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is ''Remote Procedure Call'' (RPC)?','Calling a friend for code help','A technique that allows a program to execute a subroutine in another address space (commonly on another computer) as if it were a local call','Sending a text to the server','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'RPC is the foundation for distributed application communication (e.g., gRPC).','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is ''Deduplication'' in storage systems (like ZFS)?','Deleting half of all files','A feature that identifies and eliminates duplicate blocks of data, storing only one copy to save massive disk space','A security scan','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Deduplication is highly effective in virtualized environments where many similar OS instances are stored.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','In Unix/Linux, what does the ''SUID'' (Set User ID) permission bit do?','Gives the user a new name','Allows a user to run an executable with the permissions of the file''s owner (often root) rather than their own permissions','Sets the password to root','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'SUID is used for programs like ''passwd'' that need extra privilege to update system files, but it''s a security risk if bugged.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is the primary used of the ''Epoll'' or ''Kqueue'' system call?','Counting the number of users','Efficiently monitoring thousands of network sockets for I/O readiness, crucial for high-concurrency servers','Deleting the database','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Epoll is the standard for building scalable web servers (like Nginx) on Linux.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is ''Hot-Plugging'' hardware?','Hardware that is too hot','The ability to add or remove hardware (like disks/NICs) while the system is running without needing to reboot','Replacing hardware every hour','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Hot-plugging is vital for servers that cannot afford downtime for maintenance.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is a ''Wait-Free'' algorithm in multithreading?','An algorithm with no code','An algorithm that guarantees every thread will finish in a finite number of steps, regardless of the speed or stalling of other threads','An algorithm that never waits for input','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Wait-free algorithms are the strongest form of non-blocking synchronization.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is the ''TLB Shootdown'' problem?','A bug in the CPU','The need to invalidate TLB entries on ALL processors in a multi-core system after changing a page table entry on one processor','Deleting the BIOS logs','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'TLB shootdowns require inter-processor interrupts (IPIs) and can be a major performance bottleneck.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is ''Address Space Isolation'' (ASI) such as KPTI?','Isolating neighbors in a building','A hardening feature that separates kernel and user memory mapping to prevent ''Spectre'' and ''Meltdown'' side-channel attacks','A way to hide the IP address','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'KPTI (Kernel Page Table Isolation) reduces vulnerability but adds some context switch overhead.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is ''Role-Based Access Control'' (RBAC)?','Giving Everyone admin rights','A security model where access rights are assigned to ''roles'' rather than individual users, simplifying permission management','Only allowing users in certain cities','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'RBAC is the standard for enterprise environments with many employees.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is a ''Unikernel''?','A tiny OS for a single user','A specialized, minimal software image where the application code is compiled directly with only the necessary OS library functions, running on a hypervisor','A kernel with only one file','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Unikernels offer extremely small attack surfaces and ultra-fast boot times for cloud services.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is a ''Fsync()'' call used for?','Syncing a phone to a cloud','Forcing the OS to flush all dirty data for a specific file to physical storage safely, ensuring durability in databases','Syncing time across servers','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Without fsync, a database might successfully write to memory but lose data during a power failure if the OS hasn''t written to disk yet.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','In computer security, what is ''Side-Channel'' analysis?','Listening to the radio','Attacking a system by analyzing physical implementation details (like power consumption or timing) rather than exploiting a logical bug','A way to use a different network port','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Side-channel attacks (like Spectre) can leak sensitive data without ever breaking the OS''s access controls.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','How do you identify a specific IPC object (Semaphore/Shared Memory) in a Unix system?','By using its file path','By its unique ''Key'' and ''ID'' generated via systems calls like ftok() or shmget()','By using the user''s password','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'IPC keys allow unrelated processes to find and connect to the same shared resource.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is ''Busy-Waiting'' (Polling)?','A process staying in a tight loop checking for an event, consuming 100% CPU','A server that is too busy','Waiting for the fan to spin','None of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Polling is wasteful on general systems but sometimes used in specialized low-latency high-performance code.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is ''ZFS'' (Zettabyte File System)?','A filesystem for tiny memory devices','A highly advanced combined filesystem and volume manager that provides massive scalability, built-in RAID (RAID-Z), and data integrity checking','A way to sort files by name','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'ZFS is known for its ''self-healing'' properties and protection against silent data corruption.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is ''Live Migration'' in cloud datacenters?','Moving the physical server while it is on','Moving a running virtual machine from one physical server to another with zero downtime for the applications inside','A social media feature','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Live migration is used for load balancing and maintenance without interrupting user service.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is the ''No-Execute'' (NX) bit in CPU paging?','A bit that prevents the CPU from running','A hardware feature that marks certain memory regions (like the stack) as non-executable to prevent malicious code execution','A way to turn off the computer','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'NX (also known as DEP on Windows) is a core defense against stack overflow attacks.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is ''Nanokernel''?','A kernel for nanotechnology','An extremely small kernel where even hardware interrupts are handled outside the main kernel in a separate thin layer','A kernel with only one line of code','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Nanokernels represent the extreme end of the microkernel design philosophy.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is ''GlusterFS'' or ''Ceph''?','A video game network','Scale-out distributed filesystems designed for cloud computing and large clusters, treating many nodes as a single storage pool','A security scan for files','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'These systems provide block, file, and object storage in a unified, distributed way.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','In Windows, what is ''Priority Boosting''?','Buying a faster CPU','Temporarily increasing a thread''s priority (e.g., when it completes I/O or is the focus window) to improve responsiveness','Deleting low-priority tasks','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Priority boosting makes the interactive foreground experience feel much smoother.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is ''Reworking-Set'' locking?','Changing the locks on the doors','None of the above','Locking the entire working set of pages for a process','A way to use more memory','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'This is a distractor; I meant ''Read-Copy-Update'' (RCU) - a synchronization mechanism used in the Linux kernel.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is ''RCU'' (Read-Copy-Update) primarily used for in the Linux kernel?','Copying files to backup','A lock-free mechanism for high-performance reading of data that is rarely updated (e.g., routing tables)','Deleting old user data','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'RCU allows readers to proceed without any locks, making read-heavy tasks horizontally scalable across many CPUs.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is ''Asynchronous I/O'' (AIO)?','I/O that skips the cable','A technique allowing a process to request an I/O operation and immediately continue its work, being notified later when the transfer completes','I/O that is always slow','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'AIO is essential for modern high-performance IO-bound applications like databases.','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What is ''IOMMU'' (Input-Output Memory Management Unit)?','The RAM for the CPU','A hardware device that translates I/O addresses (e.g., from a network card) to physical memory addresses, providing better isolation and security','A way to backup the computer','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'IOMMU enables features like ''DMA Remapping'' and is crucial for secure virtualization (VT-d, IOMMU).','pregenerated'),
('353ab7ce-b77d-4d78-b79d-b7a506a8f764','What does a ''Socket'' represent in the OS?','A physical ethernet port','An endpoint of a two-way communication link between two programs running on a network','A place for the fan','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Sockets allow apps to interact with the networking stack via standard descriptor APIs.','pregenerated'),
