('85db1a10-9c7d-41ed-9ca1-50fbd8ae33f5','Which keyword is used to handle exceptions in Python?','catch','except','error','throws','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Python uses ''try...except'' blocks for exception handling.','pregenerated'),
('85db1a10-9c7d-41ed-9ca1-50fbd8ae33f5','What does `*args` represent in a function definition?','A dictionary of keyword arguments','A tuple of variable positional arguments','A list of required arguments','A pointer to an array','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'*args allows a function to accept any number of positional arguments which are gathered into a tuple.','pregenerated'),
