('3e0f121d-929b-4098-ba7e-dc512819029c','What is ''Constant Folding'' in Python''s compiler?','Folding paper','Evaluating constant expressions (e.g. 2 + 2) at compile time','A ways to name users','A training session','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'The peer optimizer (peephole) performs this optimization.','pregenerated'),
('3e0f121d-929b-4098-ba7e-dc512819029c','What is ''Hash Randomization'' in Python?','Random users','A security feature that adds a random seed to string hashing to prevent Denial of Service (DoS) attacks','A ways to delete registers','A backup tool','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'It helps prevent attackers from creating many strings with the same hash value.','pregenerated'),
('3e0f121d-929b-4098-ba7e-dc512819029c','What is a ''Coroutines-based generator''?','A generator that uses yield from','An object that can be suspended and resumed, often used in async frameworks','A ways to delete files','A training session','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'Prior to native async/await, generators were heavily used for coroutines.','pregenerated'),
('3e0f121d-929b-4098-ba7e-dc512819029c','What is the purpose of `sys.setrecursionlimit()`?','To speed up code','To change the maximum depth of the Python interpreter stack','To delete old code','A backup tool','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'It is useful for very deep recursive algorithms, but can cause crashes if set too high.','pregenerated'),
('3e0f121d-929b-4098-ba7e-dc512819029c','What characterizes ''Weak references'' to objects?','None of these; Weak references are used to create caches of heavy objects without keeping them alive.','A ways to delete info','A backup tool','none of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'Python''s weakref module allows for this behavior.','pregenerated'),
('3e0f121d-929b-4098-ba7e-dc512819029c','What is ''Taint Analysis'' in Python security?','Cleaning air','A security technique that tracks user input (taint) across the program to prevent vulnerabilities like SQL injection','A ways to delete info','A training session','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'Some tools provide automated taint analysis for Python web frameworks.','pregenerated'),
('3e0f121d-929b-4098-ba7e-dc512819029c','What is the ''Borg'' pattern in Python?','A pattern for robots','A way of creating objects that share the same state but are different instances (Monostate pattern)','A ways to delete code','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'It''s an alternative to Singleton where state shared via the __dict__ attribute.','pregenerated'),
('3e0f121d-929b-4098-ba7e-dc512819029c','What is the ''Buffer'' in io module?','A ways to manage internet speed','An intermediate storage area for I/O operations (RawIOBase, BufferedIOBase, TextIOBase)','A ways to delete files','A backup tool','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'Python''s io module provides a class hierarchy for handling stream data.','pregenerated'),
('3e0f121d-929b-4098-ba7e-dc512819029c','How do you detect memory leaks in a Python program?','Using a timer','Using tools like objgraph, tracemalloc, or memory_profiler','Deleting files','A training session','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'tracemalloc is a built-in module for tracking memory allocations.','pregenerated'),
('3e0f121d-929b-4098-ba7e-dc512819029c','What characterizes ''Zero-copy'' operations in Python?','Copying zero files','Operations that do not require copying data into another memory buffer (e.g. using sendfile or memoryview)','A ways to delete registers','A backup tool','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'Zero-copy is essential for high-performance network programming.','pregenerated'),
('3e0f121d-929b-4098-ba7e-dc512819029c','What is ''Frame'' in a Python traceback?','A picture frame','A data structure containing information about a function call (local vars, PC, etc.)','A ways to delete code','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Tracebacks navigate these frame objects to show the call history.','pregenerated'),
('3e0f121d-929b-4098-ba7e-dc512819029c','What is ''Code Object''?','A block of code','A compiled representation of a piece of Python source code (bytecode + metadata)','A ways to name a user','A backup tool','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Code objects are immutable and used by the virtual machine.','pregenerated'),
('3e0f121d-929b-4098-ba7e-dc512819029c','What does `__mro_entries__` do?','Entries in a list','An protocol used by some classes (like generics) to influence how they appear in the MRO of subclasses','A ways to delete info','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'It is part of PEP 560, allowing for more flexible generic types.','pregenerated'),
('3e0f121d-929b-4098-ba7e-dc512819029c','What is ''PEP 8''?','A type of soda','The style guide for Python code','A ways to delete code','A training module','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'Following PEP 8 ensures consistency and readability across Python projects.','pregenerated'),
('3e0f121d-929b-4098-ba7e-dc512819029c','What is ''CPython-specific'' behavior?','Behavior found only in the CPython implementation, not guaranteed by the Python language spec','Fast behavior','A ways to delete info','none of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'Wait time during GC or exact ref count timing can be implementation-defined.','pregenerated'),
('3e0f121d-929b-4098-ba7e-dc512819029c','Which module allows you to manipulate the CPython garbage collector directly?','garbage','gc','collect','system_gc','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'The ''gc'' module allows for manual control and monitoring of memory collection.','pregenerated'),
('3e0f121d-929b-4098-ba7e-dc512819029c','What does `types.SimpleNamespace` do?','A simple name','A class that provides a simple object to which you can add attributes; similar to an empty class instance','A ways to delete info','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'It is often more convenient than creating a custom class just for storage.','pregenerated'),
('3e0f121d-929b-4098-ba7e-dc512819029c','What is ''Duck Typing'' security risk?','Typing errors','Accepting any object that ''looks'' right might lead to unexpected behavior if methods are subverted','A ways to delete register','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'Security-sensitive code should verify types or use protocols (ABCs) to ensure interface compliance.','pregenerated'),
('3e0f121d-929b-4098-ba7e-dc512819029c','How do you achieve parallelism (true multi-core) in Python?','Using threading','Using the multiprocessing module to create separate processes (each with its own GIL)','A ways to delete info','A training system','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'Multiprocessing bypasses the GIL by using separate memories and processes.','pregenerated'),
('3e0f121d-929b-4098-ba7e-dc512819029c','What is ''Abstract Base Class'' (ABC)?','A class with no methods','A class that cannot be instantiated and is used to define a common interface for it''s subclasses','A basic class','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'The ''abc'' module provides infrastructure for defining abstract base classes.','pregenerated'),
('3e0f121d-929b-4098-ba7e-dc512819029c','What is ''Circular Reference''?','A reference in a circle','When two or more objects refer to each other, creating a cycle that reference counting cannot clear','A software bug in RAM','none of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'The garbage collector''s cycle-detector handles these types of memory leaks.','pregenerated'),
('3e0f121d-929b-4098-ba7e-dc512819029c','What is the purpose of `__slots__`?','To save memory','To speed up code','To delete info','none of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'Slots prevent the creation of a per-instance dictionary, which saves significant memory.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','What is the cube root of 729?','7','8','9','11','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',45,'9 * 9 * 9 = 729.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','If 20% of a number is 120, then 120% of that number will be:','20','120','480','720','["D"]'::jsonb,'easy',45,'20% of X = 120 => X = 600. 120% of 600 = 720.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','A person fetches a book for $500 and sells it for $600. What is the profit percentage?','10%','20%','25%','50%','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',45,'Profit = 600 - 500 = 100. Profit% = (100/500)*100 = 20%.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','Find the average of first five multiples of 3.','3','9','12','15','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',40,'Multiples: 3, 6, 9, 12, 15. Sum = 45. Average = 45/5 = 9.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','Two numbers are in the ratio 3:5. If 9 is subtracted from each, the new ratio is 12:23. The smaller number is:','27','33','49','55','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',45,'Let numbers be 3x, 5x. (3x-9)/(5x-9) = 12/23. 69x - 207 = 60x - 108. 9x = 99. x = 11. Smaller number = 3*11 = 33.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','A can do a piece of work in 10 days and B can do it in 15 days. How many days will they take if they work together?','6','8','9','12','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',50,'Resultant = (10*15)/(10+15) = 150/25 = 6 days.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','A train 240 m long passes a pole in 24 seconds. How long will it take to pass a platform 650 m long?','65 seconds','89 seconds','100 seconds','150 seconds','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',50,'Speed = Distance / Time = 240 / 24 = 10 m/s. Time to cross platform = (240 + 650) / 10 = 890 / 10 = 89 seconds.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','The simple interest on $5000 at 10% per annum for 3 years is:','500','1000','1500','2000','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',45,'SI = (P * R * T) / 100 = (5000 * 10 * 3) / 100 = 1500.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','Find compound interest on $10000 at 10% per annum for 2 years compounded annually.','2000','2100','2200','2500','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Amount = 10000 * (1 + 10/100)^2 = 10000 * 1.21 = 12100. CI = 12100 - 10000 = 2100.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','Which of the following is a prime number?','33','81','93','97','["D"]'::jsonb,'easy',40,'97 is a prime number as it has only two factors, 1 and itself.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','The sum of all even numbers between 1 and 31 is:','16','240','480','512','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',50,'Even numbers: 2, 4, ..., 30. This is an AP with n=15. Sum = (n/2)(first + last) = (15/2)(2+30) = 15*16 = 240.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','The HCF of two numbers is 11 and their LCM is 693. If one of the numbers is 77, find the other company.','7','9','63','99','["D"]'::jsonb,'medium',45,'Product of numbers = HCF * LCM. 77 * X = 11 * 693 => X = (11 * 693)/77 = 693/7 = 99.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','Which is the greatest among 3/4, 5/6, 7/8, 9/10?','3/4','5/6','7/8','9/10','["D"]'::jsonb,'easy',40,'If the difference between numerator and denominator is same, the fraction with larger numbers is greater.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','Two dice are thrown simultaneously. What is the probability of getting two numbers whose product is even?','1/2','3/4','3/8','5/16','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',45,'Total 36. Product is odd only if both are odd (3*3 = 9 outcomes). Remaining 27 have even product. Prob = 27/36 = 3/4.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','Father is four times as old as his son. In 20 years, he will be only twice as old as his son. The father''s present age is:','40','60','80','90','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',50,'F = 4S. F+20 = 2(S+20). 4S+20 = 2S+40 => 2S = 20 => S=10. F = 40.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','In what ratio must tea at $62/kg be mixed with tea at $72/kg so that the mixture is worth $64.50/kg?','3:1','3:2','4:3','5:3','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'Ratio = (72 - 64.5) / (64.5 - 62) = 7.5 / 2.5 = 3/1.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','A pipe can fill a tank in 8 hours and another can empty it in 16 hours. If both are opened, in how many hours will the tank be full?','8','10','15','16','["D"]'::jsonb,'medium',50,'Net rate = 1/8 - 1/16 = 1/16. So it takes 16 hours.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','A shopkeeper sells an article at a loss of 10%. Had he sold it for $75 more, he would have gained 5%. The cost price of the article is:','500','750','1000','1250','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Difference in % = 5 - (-10) = 15%. 15% of CP = 75. CP = 75/0.15 = 500.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','How many 3-digit numbers can be formed from digits 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 if repetition is allowed?','60','120','125','150','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'For each place, we have 5 choices. 5 * 5 * 5 = 125.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','The length of a rectangle is increased by 20% and its breadth is decreased by 20%. What is the area change?','0%','4% increase','4% decrease','2% decrease','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',50,'Net change = 20 - 20 - (20*20)/100 = -4%.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','Calculation of the area of a circle with a radius of 7 cm is (use π = 22/7):','44 sq cm','154 sq cm','308 sq cm','616 sq cm','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',50,'Area = πr^2 = (22/7) * 7 * 7 = 154.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','Find the annual income from $2500, 8% stock at 125.','200','160','150','250','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Income = (Face Value * Income%) = (2500 * 8) / 100 = 200.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','A boat travels upstream at 6km/h and downstream at 14km/h. Speed of boat in still water is:','8 km/h','10 km/h','12 km/h','20 km/h','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Speed in still water = (Downstream + Upstream) / 2 = (14+6)/2 = 10.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','The difference between a number and its three-fifths is 50. What is the number?','75','100','125','150','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',45,'X - 3X/5 = 50 => 2X/5 = 50 => X = 125.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','A student has to obtain 33% of the total marks to pass. He got 125 marks and failed by 40 marks. The maximum marks are:','300','500','800','1000','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',45,'Pass marks = 125 + 40 = 165. 33% of X = 165 => X = 165/0.33 = 500.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','The value of (256)^0.16 * (256)^0.09 is:','4','16','64','256.25','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',40,'Sum of indices = 0.16 + 0.09 = 0.25. (256)^0.25 = (256)^(1/4) = 4.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','If log (x/y) + log (y/x) = log (x+y), then:','x + y = 1','x + y = 0','xy = 1','x = y','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'log( (x/y)*(y/x) ) = log(1) = log(x+y). So x+y=1.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','By selling an article for $100, a person gains $15. What is his gain percentage?','15%','12.5%','17.6%','20%','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',40,'CP = 100 - 15 = 85. Gain% = (15/85)*100 ≈ 17.64%.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','If A:B = 2:3 and B:C = 4:5, then A:B:C is:','8:12:15','2:4:5','2:3:5','8:10:15','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',35,'Multiply first ratio by 4 and second by 3. A:B=8:12, B:C=12:15.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','A mixture contains milk and water in ratio 5:1. On adding 5 liters of water, ratio becomes 5:2. The quantity of milk is:','15 liters','25 liters','30 liters','5 liters','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',50,'Milk=5x, Water=x. (x+5) part of water is now 2 parts. Since milk remains 5x. x+5 = 2x => x=5. Milk = 5*5=25.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','A can do a work in 15 days and B in 20 days. They work together for 4 days, then A leaves. In how many days B will finish the remaining work?','10','10(2/3)','8','12','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'1 day''s work together = 7/60. 4 days'' work = 28/60 = 7/15. Remaining = 8/15. B takes (8/15) / (1/20) = 32/3 = 10(2/3) days.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','The average weight of 8 men is increased by 1.5 kg when one of them who weighs 65 kg is replaced by a new man. The weight of the new man is:','70 kg','74 kg','76 kg','77 kg','["D"]'::jsonb,'easy',35,'Total increase = 8 * 1.5 = 12 kg. New weight = 65 + 12 = 77 kg.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','Two trains of length 110m and 90m are running in opposite directions with speeds 36km/h and 54km/h respectively. In what time will they pass each other?','8 seconds','10 seconds','12 seconds','15 seconds','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',45,'Relative Speed = 90 km/h = 25 m/s. Total Distance = 200 m. Time = 200 / 25 = 8.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','In what time will $64000 yield $4921 interest at 5% per annum compounded half-yearly?','1.5 years','2 years','3 years','4 years','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',50,'64000 * (1 + 2.5/100)^n = 64000 + 4921 = 68921. (41/40)^n = 68921/64000 = (41/40)^3. n=3 half-years = 1.5 yrs.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','What is the least number which when divided by 8, 12, 16 leaves remainder 3 in each case?','45','48','51','54','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',30,'LCM of 8, 12, 16 is 48. Number = 48 + 3 = 51.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','The last day of a century cannot be:','Monday','Wednesday','Tuesday','Friday','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'Last day of 100th, 200th, 300th, 400th century are Friday, Wednesday, Monday, Sunday. (5, 3, 1, 0). Tuesday is never a last day.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','A man rows downstream 32 km and upstream 14 km, taking 6 hours each time. The velocity of current is:','1.5 km/h','2.5 km/h','3 km/h','1 km/h','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Down speed = 32/6, Up speed = 14/6. Current speed = (32/6 - 14/6)/2 = (18/6)/2 = 3/2 = 1.5.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','A tank is 25 m long, 12 m wide and 6 m deep. The cost of plastering its walls and bottom at 75 paise per sq m is:','450','558','600','744','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',50,'Area = (25*12) + 2*(25*6 + 12*6) = 300 + 2*(150 + 72) = 300 + 444 = 744 sq m. Cost = 744 * 0.75 = 558.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','In order to have an income of $600 from 3% stock at 90, one must invest:','15000','18000','20000','25000','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',50,'Income 3 -> investment 90. Income 600 -> investment (90/3)*600 = 18000.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','3.5 can be expressed in terms of percentage as:','0.35%','3.5%','35%','350%','["D"]'::jsonb,'medium',45,'3.5 * 100 = 350%.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','The fourth proportional to 5, 8, 15 is:','18','21','24','28','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',35,'5/8 = 15/x => 5x = 120 => x = 24.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','A man buys a cycle for $1400 and sells it at a loss of 15%. What is the selling price of the cycle?','$1090','$1160','$1190','$1202','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',45,'SP = 85% of 1400 = 0.85 * 1400 = 1190.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','If A''s height is 40% less than that of B, how much percent B''s height is more than that of A?','33.33%','40%','60%','66.66%','["D"]'::jsonb,'medium',45,'A = 0.6B. B = A/0.6 = 1.666...A. So B is 66.66% more than A.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','What is the smallest three-digit prime number?','101','103','107','109','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',35,'100 is even, 101 is prime.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','The average of 7 consecutive numbers is 20. The largest of these numbers is:','20','22','23','24','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',45,'If average of 7 consecutive is 20, the middle (4th) number is 20. The sequence is 17, 18, 19, 20, 21, 22, 23.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','If 15 men can reap a field in 35 days, in how many days will 21 men reap the same field?','25','20','30','22','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',50,'M1D1 = M2D2 => 15 * 35 = 21 * D2 => D2 = (15 * 35) / 21 = 5 * 5 = 25.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','The area of a square is 225 sq cm. What is its perimeter?','15 cm','30 cm','60 cm','45 cm','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',45,'Side = sqrt(225) = 15. Perimeter = 4 * 15 = 60.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','A sum of money at simple interest amounts to $815 in 3 years and to $854 in 4 years. The sum is:','$650','$690','$698','$700','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'Interest for 1 year = 854 - 815 = 39. Interest for 3 years = 39 * 3 = 117. Principal = 815 - 117 = 698.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','The LCM of two numbers is 48. The numbers are in the ratio 2:3. The sum of the numbers is:','28','32','40','64','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',45,'Let numbers be 2x, 3x. LCM(2x, 3x) = 6x = 48 => x = 8. Numbers are 16, 24. Sum = 40.','pregenerated'),
('5aff7190-680e-4c87-8a1b-b8fd7bfcae2d','If 0.75 : x :: 5 : 8, then x is equal to:','1.12','1.2','1.25','1.30','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',35,'0.75/x = 5/8 => 5x = 6.00 => x = 1.2.','pregenerated')
