INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','Which SDLC model is characterized by a linear, sequential flow of phases?','Agile','Waterfall','Spiral','Scrum','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'In Waterfall, each phase must be completed before the next one begins (Reqs -> Design -> Implementation -> Test).','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','In Scrum, what is the ''Sprint''?','A meeting to discuss bugs','A fixed-time period (typically 2-4 weeks) in which a specific set of work is completed','A person who writes code very fast','A document describing all features','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'The Sprint is the heart of Scrum, focusing the team on delivering a ''done'' increment of the product.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What is the primary focus of the Spiral Model in each cycle?','Speed of delivery','Risk Analysis','Documentation size','Marketing','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The Spiral model is a risk-driven process model that combines elements of design and prototyping-in-stages.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What is the difference between Functional and Non-functional requirements?','Functional requirements are for users, non-functional are for machines','Functional defines ''what'' the system does; Non-functional defines ''how'' the system performs (quality attributes)','Functional requirements are code; non-functional are tests','There is no difference','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Functional: ''User can login''. Non-functional: ''Response time must be < 1s''.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','Which of these are typical phases in a software development lifecycle?','Requirement Gathering','Deployment','Hardware Manufacturing','Maintenance','["A","B","D"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',35,'Requirements, Analysis, Design, Implementation, Testing, Deployment, and Maintenance are standard SDLC phases.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What is the primary goal of software testing?','To fix all bugs','To find bugs and ensure quality','To write documentation','To sell the software','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Testing aims to uncover defects and verify that requirements are met.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','Which type of testing focuses on individual components or modules of the software?','Integration Testing','System Testing','Unit Testing','Acceptance Testing','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Unit testing is performed by developers to verify the logic of a single function or class.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What does the ''A'' stand for in the SMART criteria for requirements?','Actionable','Achievable','Accurate','Automated','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'SMART stands for Specific, Measurable, Achievable, Relevant, and Time-bound.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','Which document lists all the desired features of a product in Scrum?','Project Plan','Product Backlog','Requirement Spec','Design Document','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The Product Backlog is a dynamic list of everything that might be needed in the product.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','Which type of maintenance is performed to fix bugs discovered after release?','Adaptive Maintenance','Corrective Maintenance','Perfective Maintenance','Preventive Maintenance','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Corrective maintenance addresses actual faults in the system.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','Which type of maintenance is performed to update software to work in a new environment (e.g., new OS)?','Corrective','Adaptive','Perfective','Preventive','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Adaptive maintenance is about staying compatible with external changes.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What is ''Software Portability''?','The speed of the software','The ease with which software can be moved from one environment to another','The size of the installer','The number of users supported','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Portability is a key non-functional requirement for cross-platform apps.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What is the primary purpose of a software prototype?','To be the final product','To help users understand and clarify requirements','To test the hardware','To train the developers','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Prototypes are mock-ups used to gather feedback early in the design phase.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','In modular design, what is ''Cohesion''?','The degree of dependency between two modules','The degree to which elements within a module belong together','The speed of module execution','The number of lines in a module','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'High cohesion is desirable as it indicates a module has a single, well-defined purpose.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','In modular design, what is ''Coupling''?','The measure of internal strength inside a module','The measure of interdependence between software modules','The process of joining two programmers','The length of the module','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Low coupling is desirable as it makes modules easier to change independently.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What does a bubble (circle) represent in a Data Flow Diagram (DFD)?','Data store','Process or Transformation','External Entity','Data Flow','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Circles represent functions or processes that transform input data into output.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What does SRS stand for?','Software Review System','Software Requirements Specification','System Requirement Spreadsheet','Standardized Review Set','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The SRS is the foundational document that describes what the software should do.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What is the purpose of the Daily Stand-up meeting?','To report progress to management','To synchronize activities and identify blockers','To perform code reviews','To plan the next sprint','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'It''s a short synchronization meeting for the development team.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What is the difference between Verification and Validation?','There is no difference','Verification is ''Are we building the product right?''; Validation is ''Are we building the right product?''','Verification is automated; Validation is manual','Verification happens at the end; Validation happens at the start','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Verification ensures the product matches designs/specs. Validation ensures it meets user needs.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','Which chart is commonly used to show project schedules and task durations?','Pie Chart','Gantt Chart','Scatter Plot','Flowchart','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Gantt charts visualize the start and finish dates of the terminal elements and summary elements of a project.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What is the main benefit of modularity in software?','Increases execution speed','Makes the system easier to understand, develop, and maintain','Reduces the number of lines of code','Removes the need for testing','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Dividing a system into modules reduces complexity by creating smaller, more manageable units.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','In the V-Model, what is mapped against the ''Requirement Analysis'' phase?','Unit Testing','User Acceptance Testing (UAT)','Integration Testing','Code Review','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'The V-model links development phases to their corresponding testing phases.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What is a ''User Story''?','A bug report','An informal, natural language description of one or more features from an end-user perspective','A biography of the founder','A training manual','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'User stories are a primary way requirements are captured in Agile.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What does COCOMO stand for in project estimation?','Common Cost Model','Constructive Cost Model','Computerized Cost Model','Complex Coding Model','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'COCOMO is an algorithmic software cost estimation model.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','Which model is best suited for large, expensive, and complicated projects with high risk?','Waterfall','Spiral','Prototyping','Build and Fix','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The Spiral model''s heavy focus on risk analysis makes it ideal for complex projects.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What is the difference between QA (Quality Assurance) and QC (Quality Control)?','There is no difference','QA is process-oriented (preventing defects); QC is product-oriented (identifying defects)','QA is done by clients; QC is done by developers','QA is automated; QC is manual','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'QA focuses on the process of building the product, while QC focuses on the final product.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What is ''Regression Testing''?','Testing a new feature','Re-running functional and non-functional tests to ensure that previously developed and tested software still performs after a change','Testing the software with random inputs','Testing the hardware compatibility','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'It ensures that ''bug fixes'' or ''updates'' don''t break existing functionality.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','Which of these is a top-down design strategy?','Starting with fine details and building up','Starting with the overall system view and breaking it into sub-systems','Focusing only on the UI','Focusing only on the database','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Top-down decomposition handles complexity by refining a high-level view into detailed parts.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What is ''Black Box Testing''?','Testing without knowledge of the internal code structure','Testing with full access to the source code','Testing the physical hardware','Testing in the dark','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Black box testing focuses on functional requirements (input vs output).','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What is ''White Box Testing''?','Testing the UI colors','Testing with knowledge of the internal logic and code structure','Testing done by users','Testing with empty files','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'White box testing (or clear box) involves checking the code paths and internal logic.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What is ''Scope Creep''?','When the project finishes early','The uncontrolled growth or continuous change in a project''s scope','A type of software bug','Moving the project to a new server','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Scope creep typically happens when requirements are not clearly defined or managed.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What is the primary purpose of version control software (e.g., Git)?','To write code automatically','To manage changes to source code over time and allow collaboration','To encrypt the final product','To host the marketing website','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Version control allows tracking history, branching, and merging collaborative work.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What does ''Cyclomatic Complexity'' measure?','The number of lines of code','The number of independent paths through a program''s source code','The amount of memory used','The number of users','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'It helps in determining the number of test cases needed to cover every logic path.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What is ''Refactoring'' in software development?','Adding new features','Restructuring existing code without changing its external behavior','Deleting the entire project','Writing the documentation','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Refactoring improves code readability, maintainability, and complexity.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','Who is responsible for representing the interests of the customer in Scrum?','Scrum Master','Product Owner','Developer','Project Manager','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The Product Owner prioritizes the backlog based on business value.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What does UML stand for?','Universal Model Language','Unified Modeling Language','Unit Management Level','User Map Logic','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'UML is a standardized way to visualize system architecture and design.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What is a ''Peer Review'' in software engineering?','Users testing the app','A process where developers check each others'' work for errors or quality issues','Managers checking the progress','Comparing with competitors','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Code reviews are a critical part of maintaining a high-quality codebase.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What is ''Software''?','The physical parts of a computer','A collection of programs, documentation, and configuration data','The internet','A type of hardware','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Software is more than just code; it includes everything that makes the code usable.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','Which characteristic refers to the degree to which a software system can be easily modified?','Efficiency','Maintainability','Reliability','Usability','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Maintainability covers testability, modifiability, and reusability.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What is the ''Full form'' of SDD?','Software Deployment Document','Software Design Description','System Data Diagram','Software Development Details','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'The SDD describes how the software system will be structured to satisfy requirements.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','Which SDLC model involves building a simplified version of the system first?','Waterfall','Prototyping Model','Iterative Model','Big Bang Model','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Prototyping helps in early validation with users.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What is the ''Critical Path'' in a project schedule?','The easiest way to finish','The sequence of tasks that determines the shortest time possible to complete the project','A list of dangerous bugs','The path to the server','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',40,'Any delay in the critical path tasks results in a delay of the entire project.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','Acceptance testing is typically performed by:','Developers','End-users or Clients','Project Managers','Hardware Engineers','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'It''s the final stage before ''Go Live'' to ensure the product satisfies business requirements.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What is ''Alpha Testing''?','Testing in a real environment','Testing by the internal development team inside the organization','Testing on mobile devices','The first test ever done','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Alpha testing is ''internal'' acceptance testing.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What is ''Beta Testing''?','Testing done by internal employees','Testing done by a select group of actual users in a ''real-world'' environment','Testing for performance only','A second round of unit testing','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Beta testing gather feedback from real users before official release.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What does MTBF stand for?','Mean Time Between Failures','Maximum Time Before Fix','Maintainability Testing Base Frequency','Measured Total Bug Factor','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'MTBF is a statistical measure of how reliable a system is.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','In top-down integration testing, what are ''Stubs''?','Real modules','Temporary dummy modules that simulate the behavior of lower-level components','Broken pieces of code','Test reports','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Stubs allow testing the high-level logic before low-level parts are ready.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','In bottom-up integration testing, what are ''Drivers''?','The actual hardware drivers','Special modules that trigger or ''drive'' the test on lower-level components','Testers who drive to the office','Documentation tools','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Drivers substitute for high-level logic to test utility modules.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','What is the ''Waterfall'' model''s main weakness?','It''s too fast','Difficult to accommodate changes late in the project','Requires no documentation','Only for small teams','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Because it''s linear, returning to a previous stage is very costly.','pregenerated'),
('993bced7-5bf1-4412-af1d-34e21cb3e7bf','Software Engineering is often described as:','Art and Magic','The application of engineering principles to software development','Hackathon culture','A way to avoid hardware books','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'It emphasizes discipline, professional processes, and measurable quality.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','Which testing level focuses on testing individual components or pieces of code in isolation?','System Testing','Unit Testing','Acceptance Testing','Integration Testing','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Unit testing verifies that each small part of the application works correctly on its own.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','What is ''Top-Down Integration''?','Testing from the database up to the UI','Testing from the main control module downwards using stubs to simulate lower modules','Testing the hardest parts first','Letting managers test the software','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Top-down starts with high-level logic and uses ''stubs'' (placeholders) for components not yet implemented.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','In the V-Model, which phase is directly linked with the ''User Acceptance Testing'' (UAT) phase?','Unit Design','High Level Design','Requirements Analysis','System Analysis','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'The V-model maps each development phase to a corresponding test phase. Requirements are verified by UAT.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','Which of the following are characteristics of ''White-Box'' testing?','Knowledge of internal code/logic','Focus on data flow and control flow','Testing based ONLY on functional requirements','Code coverage measurement','["A","B","D"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',40,'White-box testing looks inside the ''box'' (at the code). Black-box testing ignores internal structure.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','What is the primary goal of Regression Testing?','Searching for new features','Verifying that recent changes have not broken existing functionality','Finding the root cause of a crash','Testing for performance regressions','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Regression testing ensures that software fixes or additions didn''t introduce new bugs in old code.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','Which testing technique involves diving the input domain into classes of data from which test cases can be derived?','Equivalence Partitioning','Boundary Value Analysis','Cause-Effect Graphing','Orthogonal Array Testing','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Equivalence Partitioning reduces the number of test cases by grouping inputs that should behave similarly.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','Which testing technique focuses on the edges of input ranges, such as 0, 1, 99, and 100 for a range of 1-100?','Equivalence Partitioning','Boundary Value Analysis','Error Guessing','Path Testing','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'BVA is highly effective since errors most frequently occur at the boundaries of input domains.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','What does LOC stand for when measuring software size?','Levels of Code','Lines of Code','Logic of Components','Library of Classes','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'LOC is a traditional but controversial metric for measuring the size of a software project.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','In UML, what does an ''Aggregation'' relationship represent between two classes?','A ''is-a'' relationship','A ''part-of'' relationship where the child can exist independently of the parent','A ''part-of'' relationship where the child CANNOT exist without the parent','A data dependency','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Aggregation is a ''weak'' whole-part relationship, unlike Composition (which is strong).','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','In UML, what does ''Composition'' represent?','A ''is-a'' relationship','A whole-part relationship where the child is destroyed when the parent is destroyed','Independent modules','A list of strings','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'In composition, the lifetime of the ''part'' is strictly managed by the ''whole''.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','Explicitly in Scrum, who is responsible for removing impediments to the team''s progress?','Product Owner','Scrum Master','Development Team','CEO','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The Scrum Master is a servant-leader who helps the team stay focused by clearing ''roadblocks''.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','What is ''Function Point'' analysis used for?','Debugging functions','Measuring the functional size of software by looking at inputs, outputs, queries, and files','Testing math libraries','Measuring CPU usage','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Function points are language-independent and focus on the external user view.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','What is a ''Baseline'' in Software Configuration Management?','The bottom border of a window','A formally reviewed and agreed-upon version of a software artifact','Minimum requirements','The first line of code','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Baselines serve as the starting point for further development and change control.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','What is a ''Walkthrough'' in the context of software quality?','A guided site visit','An informal meeting where a designer leads team members through a software product to find defects','A tutorial for users','A type of unit test','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Walkthroughs are more informal than ''Inspections'' but still help in finding logical errors.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','Which formal review process involves a moderator, a scribe, and checklists to find defects?','Walkthrough','Inspection (Fagan inspection)','Peer Desk Check','Ad-hoc Review','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Inspection is the most structured form of technical review.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','Which metric provides an indication of the complexity of a program by counting decision points?','Size metric','Cyclomatic Complexity (McCabe metric)','Performance metric','Usage metric','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'It''s calculated as V(G) = E - N + 2P where E is edges and N is nodes.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','In the Capability Maturity Model (CMM), what is Level 1?','Initial (Ad-hoc and chaotic processes)','Repeatable','Defined','Managed','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Level 1 indicates that success depends solely on individual effort and heroics.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','What is the highest level of maturity in the Capability Maturity Model Integration (CMMI)?','Optimized','Optimizing','Continuous Improvement','Managed','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'At Level 5 (Optimizing), focus is continually on improving process performance.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','Who is the primary audience for the SRS (Software Requirements Specification)?','Developers and Clients','Only End users','Only QA','Only Sales','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'It serves as the contract between the customer and the developers.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','Which design pattern ensures a class only has one instance and provides a global point of access to it?','Factory','Observer','Singleton','Strategy','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Singleton is useful for managing global state like a logging service or DB connection.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','What is ''Requirement Elicitation''?','Deleting requirements','The practice of gathering/discovering requirements from stakeholders','Writing requirements into code','Testing requirements','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Techniques include interviews, surveys, workshops, and observation.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','In requirements management, what does ''Traceability'' mean?','Drawing requirements','The ability to track a requirement from its origin to its implementation and testing','Measuring the size of a requirement','Hiding requirements from developers','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'A traceability matrix ensures that every requirement is covered by at least one test case.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','Maintenance that involves enhancing or adding new features requested by users is called:','Adaptive Maintenance','Perfective Maintenance','Corrective Maintenance','Preventive Maintenance','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Perfective maintenance aims to improve the software based on user feedback.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','What does MTTF stand for?','Mean Time To Failure','Maximum Time To Finish','Median Time To Fix','Main Task Tracking Factor','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'MTTF is used for non-repairable systems, indicating average lifespan.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','Which type of cohesion is considered the best (strongest)?','Logical Cohesion','Functional Cohesion','Sequential Cohesion','Temporal Cohesion','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Functional cohesion means every part of the module contributes to a single, well-defined task.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','Which type of coupling is considered the worst (tightest)?','Data Coupling','Content Coupling','Control Coupling','Stamp Coupling','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Content coupling occurs when one module modifies the internal data of another.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','According to McCall''s quality model, ''Usability'', ''Integrity'', and ''Reliability'' are part of:','Product Revision','Product Operation','Product Transition','Quality Control','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Product Operation refers to qualities expected when the software is actually running.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','What is ''Stress Testing''?','Testing under normal conditions','Testing the software beyond its operational limits to see how it fails (break point)','Testing the team''s mental health','Testing only the UI','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Stress testing identifies the upper bound of the system''s capacity.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','What is the primary objective of a ''Feasibility Study''?','To hire developers','To determine if the project is technically and financially viable to pursue','To write code','To market the product','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The study should result in a GO/NO-GO decision relative to the project.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','What is a ''Spike'' in Agile development?','A sudden increase in user traffic','A time-boxed task focused on research or prototyping to reduce uncertainty','A person who is late','A bug in the database','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Spikes are used to clarify requirements or explore technical solutions.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','What is ''Throwaway Prototyping''?','A prototype that is meant to be recycled','A prototype developed quickly to explore requirements and then discarded','A prototype that becomes the final product','A bug in the SDLC','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'This contrasts with ''Evolutionary Prototyping'', where the code is progressively refined into the product.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','What is a ''Legacy System''?','A brand new system','An old system that is still in use and critical but hard to maintain/upgrade','A system left in a will','A computer for gaming','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Legacy systems often use outdated technology but hold vital business data.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','What is a ''Burndown Chart''?','A list of developers to fire','A graphical representation of work left to do versus time','A thermal map of the server room','A chart of bugs found','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'It helps the team visualize if they will complete the sprint backlog on time.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','In Scrum, which role is not part of the ''Scrum Team'' trio?','Product Owner','Project Manager','Scrum Master','Developers','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Scrum intentionally avoids a traditional hierarchical Project Manager role.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','What is ''Halstead complexity'' based on?','Decision points','The number of operators and operands in the source code','The size of comments','Execution time','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Halstead metrics attempt to measure software''s volume, difficulty, and effort.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','What is ''Fan-in''?','The number of modules that call a specific module','The number of modules called by a specific module','The size of a module','Fans in the computer','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'High fan-in is generally good as it indicates high reuse.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','What is ''Fan-out''?','The number of modules calling this module','The number of modules that a specific module calls','The amount of data moving out','A type of design pattern','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Very high fan-out might indicate that a module is too complex and should be split.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','What is ''Estimation by Analogy''?','Randomly guessing','Estimating a new project''s cost/effort based on data from a similar previous project','Counting lines of code','Asking the client to estimate','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'It relies on historical data and expert judgment.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','What is the primary role of the ''Scribe'' in a formal inspection?','To moderate the meeting','To document all defects and issues raised during the meeting','To write the code','To test the software','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'The scribe ensures that all discovered flaws are tracked and addressed later.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','Which ISO standard specifically defines software quality attributes (like portability, reliability)?','ISO 9001','ISO 9126','ISO 27001','ISO 14001','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'ISO 9126 (and its successor ISO/IEC 25010) categorizes software qualities.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','In Software Engineering, what is the ''Silver Bullet'' problem coined by Fred Brooks?','A bug that cannot be killed','The idea that there is no single tool or technique that can provide an order-of-magnitude improvement in productivity','A fast developer','The need for expensive hardware','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Brooks argued that the essential complexity of software is inherently difficult to solve.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','Testing that evaluates the system from the perspective of its intended users in a realistic environment is called:','Operational Testing','Scenario Testing','Alpha testing','Stress testing','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Scenario testing uses world-real stories to uncover defects with business processes.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','What is ''Earned Value Management'' (EVM)?','Paying developers based on value','A technique that combines schedule, costs, and scope to measure project performance and progress','A way to calculate bonuses','A type of database indexing','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'EVM provides early warnings of project performance issues.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','What does a ''Stub'' substitute for in integration testing?','A user','A module being called (lower-level)','A module that calls (higher-level)','A database server','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Stubs are ''below'' the module being tested.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','Software is: Programs + Documentation + ______?','Marketing','Data/Configuration','The box','Hardware','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'The ''Data'' or configuration part is essential for the system to function correctly.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','What is ''Reverse Engineering''?','Building software from top to bottom','Analyzing a system to create representations of it at a higher level of abstraction','Writing code backwards','Deleting the compiled file','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Often implies recovering design info or source code from binaries.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','What is ''Re-engineering''?','Fixing code bugs','Modification of a software product after it has been reverse engineered','Hiring new engineers','Restarting the project','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'It''s essentially ''Reverse Engineering'' followed by ''Forward Engineering''.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','Which of these is the most significant cost in the total lifecycle of most software systems?','Development','Maintenance','Requirements Gathering','Packaging','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Approximately 60-80% of total software costs go towards maintaining it after release.','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','What is the primary goal of the ''Design phase'' in SDLC?','To write code','To transform requirements into a complete technical representation of the system','To find bugs','To train users','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Design bridges the ''what'' (SRD) to the ''how'' (Code).','pregenerated'),
('092e1829-e92e-48b8-9148-734c586e4e8a','A ''Black box'' represents a system where:','The logic is secret','Internal workings are hidden and only inputs/outputs are visible','It is broken','The code is written in Python','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Encapsulation and abstraction are key software engineering concepts that use black box reasoning.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','Which design pattern ensures that a class has only one instance and provides a global access point to it?','Factory','Observer','Singleton','Strategy','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Singleton is a creational pattern that limits object instantiation to a single object.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is the primary objective of the ''Observer'' pattern?','To hide data from users','To define a one-to-many dependency so that when one object changes state, all its dependents are notified automatically','To convert one interface to another','To optimize database queries','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Observer is used for implementing distributed event-handling systems.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','In the MVC (Model-View-Controller) architecture, what is the ''Model'' responsible for?','Rendering the user interface','Handling user input and business logic','Managing data and business rules','Connecting to the internet','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The Model represents the data and logic. The View is the UI. The Controller handles the input and interaction.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is one major drawback of a Microservices architecture compared to a Monolith?','It''s impossible to scale','Increased operational complexity (deployment, monitoring, inter-service communication overhead)','Single point of failure for the whole system','Code is harder to read','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',40,'While microservices offer scalability and independence, they introduce significant networking and infrastructure overhead.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','Which of these are ''Creational'' design patterns?','Builder','Adapter','Prototype','Singleton','["A","C","D"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',40,'Builder, Prototype, and Singleton are creational. Adapter is structural.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is the primary role of a ''Controller'' in MVC architecture?','Displaying data','Managing data and business logic','Handling user input and updating the Model/View accordingly','Storing information in a database','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The Controller acts as an interface between the View and the Model.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','In MVC, which component is responsible for rendering the User Interface?','Model','View','Controller','Router','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'The View is where the output is presented to the user.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What does the ''S'' in SOLID principles stand for?','Systematic Design','Single Responsibility Principle','Secure Coding','Scalable Infrastructure','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'SRP states that a class should have one, and only one, reason to change.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What does the ''O'' in SOLID principles stand for?','Object Oriented','Open-Closed Principle','Operational Efficiency','Optimal Performance','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Objects should be open for extension but closed for modification.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What does the ''L'' in SOLID principles stand for?','Layered Architecture','Liskov Substitution Principle','Logical Consistency','Low Coupling','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Objects in a program should be replaceable with instances of their subtypes without altering correctness.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What does the ''I'' in SOLID principles stand for?','Infrastructure Integration','Interface Segregation Principle','Internal Consistency','Implicit Logic','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Many client-specific interfaces are better than one general-purpose interface.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What does the ''D'' in SOLID principles stand for?','Data Driven Design','Dependency Inversion Principle','Deployment Automation','Detailed Analysis','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Depend upon abstractions, not concretions.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is the primary difference between Continuous Delivery and Continuous Deployment?','There is no difference','Continuous Delivery requires manual approval to go to production; Continuous Deployment is fully automated','Delivery is for software; Deployment is for hardware','Deployment happens before Testing','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',40,'Continuous Delivery ensures code is always *releasable*, while Deployment automatically pushes it.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is ''Domain Driven Design'' (DDD)?','A way to design domain names for websites','An approach to software development for complex needs by connecting the implementation to an evolving model of core business concepts','A testing strategy for databases','A way to automate code comments','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'DDD focuses on the ''Ubiquitous Language'' and ''Bounded Contexts'' within a business domain.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is ''CQRS'' in architecture?','Code Quality Review System','Command Query Responsibility Segregation (separating read and write operations)','Centralized Query Reporting Service','Complex Queue Routing Strategy','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'CQRS uses different data models for reading and writing data.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is the purpose of an ''API Gateway'' in a microservices architecture?','To connect the office to the internet','To act as a single entry point for client requests, handling routing, composition, and policy enforcement','To store the database','To write front-end code','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'API Gateways centralize cross-cutting concerns like authentication and rate limiting.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','Which design pattern is used to add new functionality to an existing object without altering its structure?','Adapter','Decorator','Bridge','Composite','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Decorator provides a flexible alternative to sub-classing for extending functionality.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','Which pattern is used to ''flatten'' a complex interface of a subsystem into a simpler one for the client?','Proxy','Facade','Flyweight','Chain of Responsibility','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Facade provides a simplified high-level interface to a set of interfaces in a subsystem.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','Which pattern defines a family of algorithms, encapsulates each one, and makes them interchangeable at runtime?','State','Strategy','Template Method','Visitor','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Strategy allows the algorithm to vary independently from clients that use it.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is the ''Circuit Breaker'' pattern used for in distributed systems?','To turn off the power in the server room','To prevent a failure in one service from cascading to others by failing fast when a service is known to be down','To speed up database connections','To encrypt inter-service traffic','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It helps systems remain resilient by avoiding calls to failing downstream services.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is ''Mutation Testing''?','Testing on viruses','Modifying the program''s source code in small ways and checking if existing tests fail (to measure test suite quality)','Testing software on different operating systems','A type of performance testing','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',45,'If a mutation doesn''t cause a test to fail, it indicates a gap in the test suite.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is ''TDD'' (Test-Driven Development)?','Testing after deployment','A process where you write a failing test first, then write the code to make it pass, and finally refactor','Testing only the UI','Developing tests for third-party libraries','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'TDD leads to better design and high test coverage by forcing developers to think about requirements first.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is ''Inversion of Control'' (IoC)?','Giving users control of the server','A design principle where a custom-written portion of a computer program receives the flow of control from a generic framework','Turning the monitor upside down','Removing the main function','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Dependency Injection is a common implementation of IoC.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is ''Formal Specification'' in software engineering?','Writing requirements in a Word document','The use of mathematical notation to describe software requirements and behavior with high precision','A meeting with the CEO','A list of bug reports','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Formal methods (like Z notation) are used in safety-critical systems to mathematically prove properties.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is ''Technical Debt''?','Money owed to cloud providers','The implied cost of additional rework caused by choosing an easy (but limited) solution now instead of a better approach that would take longer','The cost of buying new laptops for developers','A type of bank loan','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'If not ''repaid'' via refactoring, technical debt makes future changes progressively harder.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','Which of these is a key principle of ''The Twelve-Factor App'' methodology?','Storing config in code','Treating logs as event streams','Manual deployment','Sharing state in memory','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Twelve-factor apps are designed for portability and resilience on modern cloud platforms.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is the ''Law of Demeter''?','Every developer must have a degree','A design heuristic where a given object should have limited knowledge about other objects: ''only talk to your immediate friends''','Complexity doubles every two years','Tests must be done before coding','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',40,'This principle helps in maintaining low coupling in object-oriented systems.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','In clean architecture (by Robert C. Martin), what sits at the center ''Circle''?','Database','Entities (Enterprise Business Rules)','Web Framework','External UI','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'The core should be independent of frameworks, UI, and external agencies.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is ''Serverless'' computing primarily focused on for the developer?','Managing physical servers','Writing business logic without worrying about the underlying server infrastructure','Removing all databases','Using peer-to-peer networks','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Cloud providers automatically manage the allocation of machine resources.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is ''Property-based testing''?','Testing for memory leaks','Defining properties that should hold true for any valid input and letting a tool generate many random inputs to verify them','Testing private properties of a class','Testing CSS properties','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Example tools include Hypothesis for Python or QuickCheck for Haskell.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What does ''Canary Deployment'' refer to?','Testing on birds','Rolling out a new version to a small subset of users before rolling it out to everyone','Deploying code at high altitudes','Using yellow icons','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Canary releases provide a safety net by testing the new code on real traffic at a small scale.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is ''Hexagonal Architecture'' (also known as Ports and Adapters)?','Building software for 6-sided screens','An architecture pattern that aims at creating loosely coupled application components that can be easily connected to their software environment by means of ports and adapters','A system with 6 core modules','A way to draw flowcharts','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It emphasizes independence from the UI and Database, similar to Clean Architecture.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','Which of these describes ''Logical Cohesion''?','Parts are grouped because they are technically related but do different things based on a switch/parameter','Parts are grouped to perform one single function','Parts are grouped because they run at the same time','Parts are grouped alphabetically','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Logical cohesion is generally frowned upon as it makes the module harder to understand and test.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is ''Code Coverage'' really measuring?','What percentage of requirements are met','What percentage of the source code is executed when a particular test suite runs','The amount of comments in code','The speed of testing','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',45,'While useful, 100% coverage doesn''t guarantee a bug-free system.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','In the Basic COCOMO model, what determines the effort estimation?','The number of users','Size of the software in KLOC (Kilo Lines of Code)','The budget of the client','The level of experience of developers','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Basic COCOMO uses a simple formula based primarily on code size.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is the ''Six Sigma'' goal in software quality?','6 bugs per version','3.4 defects per million opportunities','6 developers per team','Completing projects in 6 weeks','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Six Sigma is a disciplined, data-driven approach for eliminating defects.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is ''Chaos Engineering''?','Programming without a plan','The discipline of experimenting on a system in order to build confidence in the system''s capability to withstand turbulent conditions in production','Deleting the database to see what happens','Hiring inexperienced developers on purpose','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Netflix''s ''Chaos Monkey'' is a famous tool that kills server instances to test resilience.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is ''Integration Testing'' in a microservices environment?','Testing that a single function works','Testing that multiple services work together correctly, often focusing on network calls and data contracts','Compiling the code','Testing the UI layout','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'It''s more complex than monolithic integration due to networking and service dependencies.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is a ''Hotfix''?','A coffee break','An urgent software patch to fix a critical bug in a production environment','A fast computer','A training session','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Hotfixes are usually pushed outside the regular release cycle.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','Which design pattern is most appropriate for creating an undo mechanism?','Singleton','Memento','Factory','Proxy','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Memento captures and externalizes an object''s internal state so the object can be restored to this state later.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','Which pattern involves providing a placeholder for another object to control access to it?','Decorator','Proxy','Flyweight','Composite','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Proxies can handle lazy loading, security, or remote object interaction.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What does GIGO stand for in Software Engineering?','Global Incident Group Organizer','Garbage In, Garbage Out','Generic Integration Graphical Object','Git Input Group Output','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'If the input to a system is flawed, the output will also be flawed regardless of process quality.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is ''Self-documenting code''?','Code that writes its own README','Code written with clear naming conventions and structure that is easy to understand without external docs','Code with many comments','Code that generates a PDF','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'While useful, it rarely replaces the need for high-level architectural documentation.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is ''Extreme Programming'' (XP)?','Coding while skydiving','An Agile framework that focuses on high technical quality through practices like pair programming and CI','A framework for supercomputers','Programming for gamers','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'XP values include Communication, Simplicity, Feedback, and Courage.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','Which testing is done without executing the code?','Dynamic Testing','Static Testing','Stress Testing','Load Testing','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Static testing includes code reviews, walkthroughs, and static analysis tools.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is ''Big Bang Integration''?','Testing only the center of the universe','A method where all modules are integrated simultaneously to create the entire system','A fast compiler','A very loud bug','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',40,'It is generally discouraged because it makes it extremely hard to isolate faults when everything fails at once.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is the ''Principle of Least Astonishment''?','Always surprise the user','Software should act in a way that is consistent with the expectations of its users','Code should be written as fast as possible','Never use advanced features','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'This principle applies to both UI/UX and API design.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is the ''Unified Process'' (UP)?','A process of joining two companies','An iterative and incremental software development process framework, often associated with UML','A type of database indexing','A way to compile code for multiple OS','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'The Rational Unified Process (RUP) is the most popular refinement of UP.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is ''Observability'' in modern software engineering?','Watching the developer code','The ability to understand a system''s internal state purely from its external outputs (trance, logs, metrics)','Using a webcam','Writing documentation for users','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Observability is critical for managing complex, distributed cloud systems.','pregenerated'),
('73b886e5-3cf3-4291-b948-b8953a05ffc5','What is ''Threat Modeling'' in the design phase?','Fighting with developers','A process of identifying, enumerating, and prioritizing potential vulnerabilities and mitigations','Using AI to generate bugs','A type of performance test','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Techniques like STRIDE help in building secure software from the ground up.','pregenerated')
