('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What does ''Cyclomatic Complexity'' measure in a program?','The number of lines of code','The number of independent paths through the source code (logical complexity)','The number of cycles in the hardware clock','The total file size in kilobytes','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'High cyclomatic complexity indicates the code is hard to test and maintain due to many branches and decision points.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','In the SOLID acronym, what does the ''L'' stand for, and what does it prescribe?','Logical Consistency; Programs should be logical','Liskov Substitution Principle; Objects of a superclass should be replaceable with objects of its subclasses without breaking the application','Layered Architecture; Apps should have at least 3 layers','Loop Invariants; Loops must be well-defined','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Liskov Substitution ensures that inheritance is used correctly such that subclasses are truly ''is-a'' types of their parents.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','Which type of maintenance is performed to keep a system up-to-date with a changing environment (e.g., a new OS update)?','Corrective Maintenance','Adaptive Maintenance','Perfective Maintenance','Preventive Maintenance','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Adaptive maintenance is about modifying the software to work in a new or changed environment.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','Which of these are SOLID design principles?','Single Responsibility Principle','Open-Closed Principle','Interface Segregation Principle','Least Privilege Principle','["A","B","C"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',45,'SOLID stands for Single Responsibility, Open-Closed, Liskov Substitution, Interface Segregation, and Dependency Inversion.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is ''Cohesion'' in software design?','The degree to which different modules depend on each other','The degree to which the elements inside a module belong together','The speed of the network','A physical property of magnets','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'High cohesion means a module does one thing and does it well. Low coupling is usually paired with high cohesion for good design.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is ''Coupling'' in software design, and what is the ideal state?','The internal strength of a module; Ideal is high coupling','The measure of interdependence between modules; Ideal is low coupling','The number of users; Ideal is many users','The file size; Ideal is small files','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Low coupling makes modules independent, making the system easier to maintain and change.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is the ''Service Mesh'' pattern primarily used for in microservices?','Storing data as a mesh','Managing service-to-service communication, often using a sidecar proxy to handle reliability, security, and observability','A type of firewall','Increasing CPU speed','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Istio and Linkerd are common implementations of the service mesh pattern.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is ''Halstead complexity'' based on?','Decision points','The number of operators and operands in the source code','The amount of comments','Execution time','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Halstead metrics attempt to measure software''s volume, difficulty, and effort.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','In Function Point analysis, which of these is NOT a parameter considered?','External Inputs','Internal Logical Files','Lines of Code (LOC)','External Interface Files','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Function Points focus on the functional size, independent of the programming language or LOC.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','At which CMM level does an organization focus on continuous process improvement through both incremental and innovative technological changes?','Level 3: Defined','Level 4: Managed','Level 5: Optimizing','Level 2: Repeatable','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Level 5 organizations collect and analyze data to drive continuous improvement.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is ''Hexagonal Architecture'' (Ports and Adapters)?','A building with 6 sides','An architecture that separates the core business logic from external dependencies (DB, UI, APIs) using interfaces (ports) and implementations (adapters)','A system with exactly 6 layers','A way to draw flowcharts','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It allows the application to be tested in isolation and swap out technologies easily.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What does MTTR stand for in reliability engineering?','Maximum Time To Repair','Mean Time To Recover (or Repair)','Median Task Time Record','Minutes To Total Resolution','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'MTTR is a key metric for how quickly a system can be restored after a failure.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','How is Availability (A) mathematically calculated?','MTBF / (MTBF + MTTR)','MTTR / MTBF','MTBF - MTTR','MTBF + MTTR','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Availability represents the proportion of time a system is functional.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is ''Change Control'' in SCM?','Changing the color of the UI','The process of formally submitting, evaluating, approving, and coordinating changes to a baseline configuration','Deleting the project history','Forcing users to update','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Change control prevents ''scope creep'' and ensures that changes don''t introduce regressions.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What does a ''Clean Room'' software engineering approach emphasize?','Developing code in a sterile laboratory','Mathematical verification and statistical quality control to achieve zero-defect software','Deleting the database','Writing code without using libraries','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It relies on formal methods and discourages unit testing by the developer, focusing instead on correctness proofs.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is the ''Fan-In'' of a module?','The number of lines of code','The number of modules that call (control flows into) the given module','The number of internal variables','The speed of the cooling system','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'High fan-in suggests high reuse but also that the module might be a central point of failure.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is the ''Fan-Out'' of a module?','The number of users who like the module','The number of modules called by (control flows out from) the given module','The number of lines in a print function','A type of design pattern','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'High fan-out can indicate that a module is too complex and depends on too many other components.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is ''Model Checking''?','Checking a fashion model''s portfolio','An automated technique for verifying that a finite-state model of a system satisfies a formal specification (often using temporal logic)','Testing a database schema','Drawing UML diagrams','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'Model checking is used extensively in hardware and safety-critical software verification.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is ''Event Sourcing''?','A way to find events to attend','Storing the state of a system as a sequence of immutable events rather than just the current state','Using JavaScript event listeners for everything','Deleting log files','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'This allows for complete audit trails and replaying history to restore state.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is ''Mutation Testing'' designed to evaluate?','Potential virus spread','The effectiveness of the test suite (by injecting small faults into the code and seeing if tests catch them)','The hardware durability','The speed of the compiler','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'If a code change (mutation) survives, it means the tests didn''t cover that specific logic/path.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','In Site Reliability Engineering (SRE), what is an ''Error Budget''?','Money to pay for bugs','The maximum amount of time a technical system is allowed to be down, used to balance innovation speed with stability','The number of bugs a developer can make','The cost of testing','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'If the budget is exhausted, releases must stop until stability is restored.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is the COCOMO model primarily used for?','Measuring network speed','Software cost and effort estimation based on the size of the project (KLOC)','Testing security','Drawing DFDs','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'COCOMO stands for COnstructive COst MOdel.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is ''CQRS'' (Command Query Responsibility Segregation)?','A way to write SQL','A pattern that separates the data model for updates (commands) from the model for reads (queries)','A type of firewall','A bug tracking tool','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'CQRS is often used in high-performance systems and paired with Event Sourcing.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What does ''Z notation'' use as its primary mathematical foundation?','Boolean algebra only','Zermelo-Fraenkel set theory and first-order predicate logic','Calculus','Geometry','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Z is a formal specification language used to describe and model computing systems.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is the ''Six Sigma'' goal in terms of defects per million opportunities (DPMO)?','100','3.4','0','1000','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Six Sigma aim for near-perfect quality by reducing process variation.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is the ''Law of Demeter'' (Principle of Least Knowledge)?','All users are the same','A design heuristic where an object should only talk to its ''friends'' (immediate neighbors) and never reaching through them (''talk to strangers'')','Code must be open source','Complexity doubles every two years','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It helps in achieving loose coupling and encapsulation.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is ''Software Rejuvenation'' in the context of long-running systems?','Hiring young developers','Proactively restarting a system or its components to clean up resource leaks (memory, sockets) before failure occurs','Rewriting the system in Java','Deleting the old database','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'It''s a preventive measure to improve availability in systems known to have ''software aging''.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is the ''Sidecar'' pattern in microservices?','A motorcycle feature','Deploying a helper container (the sidecar) alongside the main application container to handle cross-cutting concerns like logging or networking','Running a backup server in another city','A UI theme','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'The sidecar extends the main container''s capabilities without modifying it.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is ''Agile Unified Process'' (AUP)?','Agile but slow','A simplified version of IBM''s Rational Unified Process (RUP) that incorporates Agile values (Focus on modeling, implementation, and test)','A type of database join','Coding without documentation','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'AUP keeps the RUP structure but simplifies the complexity and overhead.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is ''Shared Nothing'' architecture?','Removing the internet','A distributed computing architecture where each node is independent, self-sufficient, and shares no central disk or memory','A system where users don''t share data','Deleting the database','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'It is highly scalable as there are no single points of contention.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is ''Software Aging''?','The hardware getting old','The progressive accumulation of errors (like memory leaks or fragmentation) in a system that eventually leads to performance degradation or failure','Developers getting old','Obsolete documentation','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Software rejuvenation is used to combat software aging.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is ''Preventive Maintenance''?','Fixing bugs after they crash the server','Activity aimed at detecting and correcting latent faults in the software before they become effective faults','Updating colors','Buying a firewall','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It''s about anticipating future problems and fixing them now (e.g., refactoring or updating libraries).','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','In the context of ''AI Engineering'', what is ''Data Drift''?','Moving data to a new server','The phenomenon where the distribution of input data changes over time, potentially impacting a model''s prediction accuracy','Losing data','Slow database queries','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Monitoring for drift is a critical part of the MLOps lifecycle.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is ''Model Inversion Attack'' in ML Security?','Flipping the weight of neural nets','An attack where an adversary uses model outputs to infer information about the sensitive training data','Deleting the model','Making the model slow','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Providing privacy guarantees (like Differential Privacy) can help mitigate this.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is ''Fluent Interface'' in API design?','An interface that speaks many languages','An API designed to be highly readable through method chaining (e.g., obj.doThis().thenThat())','A fast UI','A type of network port','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It aims to make the code read like a sentence.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is ''Fuzz Testing'' (Fuzzing)?','Testing for extra white space','An automated testing technique that involves providing invalid, unexpected, or random data as inputs to a computer program','Testing the team''s loyalty','A round of unit testing','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Fuzzing is often used to find security vulnerabilities and memory leaks.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is ''Win-Win'' Requirements Negotiation?','Winning against the client','A collaborative approach (like Boehm''s Spiral) where stakeholders identify their ''win conditions'' and negotiate towards a mutually beneficial set of requirements','Ignoring the budget','Getting double the work for double the price','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It focuses on reconciling conflicting stakeholder goals early.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is ''Semantic Versioning'' (SemVer)?','Dictionary ordering of code','A versioning scheme (MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH) where version numbers convey meaning about the underlying changes','Adding comments to versions','Giving versions names like ''Apple'' or ''Banana''','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'MAJOR changes indicate breaking changes; MINOR for new features; PATCH for backwards-compatible bug fixes.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','Which design pattern is used to separate an abstraction from its implementation so that the two can vary independently?','Adapter','Bridge','Composite','Decorator','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Bridge is structural, focusing on composition over inheritance.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','Which design pattern allows you to compose objects into tree structures to represent part-whole hierarchies?','Flyweight','Composite','Proxy','Facade','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'The Composite pattern lets clients treat individual objects and compositions of objects uniformly.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is ''Bang Metric''?','A measure of how loud the code is','A function-oriented size metric developed by DeMarco to measure the deliverable ''bang'' of a system based on its specification','The speed of the CPU','A way to count bugs','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'It counts data primitives, state transitions, etc., from a system specification.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is the ''Basis Set'' in path testing?','A set of elementary school books','The set of linearly independent paths through a program (determined by cyclomatic complexity)','A list of users','The database connection string','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Achieving 100% basis path coverage ensures that every statement and branch has been executed at least once.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is ''All-Pairs Testing''?','Testing two developers at once','A combinatorial testing method that ensures all possible discrete pairs of input parameters are tested at least once','Testing the front and back end simultaneously','Testing even-numbered bugs only','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It significantly reduces the number of test cases while still catching most interaction bugs.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is the ''Brooks'' Law'' regarding project management?','Always hire more people','Adding manpower to a late software project makes it later','Documentation must be 100 pages long','The fastest coder wins','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Due to communication overhead and ramp-up time for new members.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What does a ''Death March'' project refer to in software engineering management?','A project for a cemetery','A project whose schedule or scope is significantly beyond what is achievable, leading to burnout and guaranteed failure','A project that was canceled early','A training session on security','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Coined by Edward Yourdon, it describes high-pressure environments with unrealistic expectations.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is ''ADR'' in software documentation?','Automatic Data Recovery','Architecture Decision Record','Advanced Deployment Report','Authorized Developer Registry','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'ADRs capture the ''why'' behind an architectural choice, providing context for future maintainers.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is ''Least Privilege'' in secure coding design?','Paying developers a low salary','Granting an entity only the minimum levels of access necessary to perform its functions','Using free open source software','Hiding the code from users','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It minimizes the potential damage from a compromised component.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is the ''YAGNI'' principle?','You Always Get New Items','You Ain''t Gonna Need It (don''t add functionality until it''s actually required)','Your App Gets No Interest','Yet Another Great Network interface','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'It discourages over-engineering and premature optimization.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is ''Scrum of Scrums'' designated for?','A very large meeting room','Scaling Agile development by coordinating multiple Scrum teams working on the same product','Deleting the Scrum Master role','Testing the Scrum process itself','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'It helps in managing dependencies across disparate but related teams.','pregenerated'),
('25523245-184e-442b-ad20-de000c19ede4','What is ''Statistical Software Quality Assurance''?','Calculating the average number of bugs','Using statistical methods to analyze defects and identify the ''Vital Few'' causes (Pareto analysis)','Counting users every day','Measuring CPU cycles','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'The 80/20 rule states that 80% of defects can be traced to 20% of causes.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is ''Vertical Scaling''?','Adding more machines to the network','Increasing the capacity (CPU, RAM) of a single existing machine','Moving the server to a higher building','A styling method for charts','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Vertical scaling (scaling up) involves upgrading the hardware of an existing server.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is the primary role of a ''Load Balancer''?','To speed up the internet','To distribute incoming network or application traffic across multiple servers','To store backup data','To encrypt passwords','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Load balancers prevent any single server from becoming a bottleneck and increase system availability.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is ''Horizontal Scaling''?','Adding more machines to your resource pool','Making the machines smaller','Rotating the server 90 degrees','Sharing code horizontally','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Horizontal scaling (scaling out) involves adding more nodes (servers) to the system.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is a ''CDN'' (Content Delivery Network)?','A high-speed internet plan','A distributed network of servers that delivers content based on geography','A database for images','A data encryption algorithm','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'CDNs reduce latency by caching content closer to the end-user''s physical location.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is the main purpose of ''Caching''?','To store archival data for 10 years','To store data in a fast-access layer (like RAM) for rapid retrieval','To delete temporary files','To manage server hardware','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Caching improves performance by keeping frequently accessed data in fast memory.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What does ''DNS'' stand for?','Domain Name System','Data Network Service','Digital Name Server','Distributed Node Storage','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'DNS translates human-friendly domain names (like google.com) into IP addresses.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What does ''High Availability'' mean in system design?','The system is always cheap','The system remains operational and accessible for a high percentage of time','The system can store infinite data','The system has many developers','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'High availability aims for minimal downtime, often targeted as ''99.99%'' (four nines).','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is a major advantage of a Relational Database (SQL)?','No schema needed','Strong data consistency and support for complex ACID transactions','Unlimited speed for all operations','Built-in image processing','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'SQL databases are excellent for structured data where relationships and consistency are critical.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is a ''Reverse Proxy''?','A server that retrieves resources on behalf of a client from one or more servers','A server that blocks the internet','A type of database','A way to backup code','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'A reverse proxy (like Nginx) sits in front of web servers and handles requests from clients.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is ''Latency'' in a network?','The amount of data transferred per second','The time it takes for a request to travel from source to destination','The number of users online','The weight of the silver cables','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Latency is the delay in communication between systems.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','Which type of scaling usually requires a Load Balancer?','Vertical Scaling','Horizontal Scaling','Manual Scaling','Internal Scaling','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Horizontal scaling adds more servers, so a Load Balancer is needed to distribute traffic among them.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','In a stateless architecture, where is the session data typically stored?','On the local hard drive of the web server','In a centralized store like Redis or a Database','In the RAM of the CPU','Session data is not allowed','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Stateless servers don''t store client data locally, allowing any server to handle any request by fetching state from a central store.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is ''Redundancy'' in system design?','Deleting extra code','The duplication of critical components to increase reliability','Making the system slower on purpose','Increasing the price of the server','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Redundancy ensures that if one component fails, a backup is ready to take its place.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','When you type a URL in a browser, which server gives you the IP address first?','Database Server','DNS Server','Mail Server','File Server','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'The DNS server resolves the domain name into an IP address so the browser can connect.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is a ''Single Point of Failure'' (SPOF)?','A bug in the code','A part of a system that, if it fails, will stop the entire system from working','A slow database query','An expensive server','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'SPOFs are avoided by introducing redundancy and high availability.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is ''Sharding''?','Encrypting a table','Horizontal partitioning of data across multiple database instances','Merging two databases together','Deleting old logs','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Sharding splits a large database into smaller, faster, more manageable pieces called data shards.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is ''Throughput''?','The time it takes to process a single request','The number of requests a system can handle in a given time period','The total size of the database','The speed of the CPU','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Throughput measures the total volume of work processed.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','Which protocol is most commonly used for communication between a browser and a web server?','FTP','HTTP/HTTPS','SSH','SMTP','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'HTTP (Hypertext Transfer Protocol) is the foundation of data communication for the World Wide Web.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is an ''IP Address''?','A person''s home address','A unique numerical label assigned to each device connected to a computer network','A type of password','A way to count users','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'IP addresses identify devices on a network, allowing them to communicate.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is ''Round Robin'' load balancing?','Giving all requests to the fastest server','Distributing requests to each server in a fixed, sequential order','Distributing requests randomly','Storing requests in a circle','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Round Robin is one of the simplest load balancing algorithms.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is ''Write-Through'' caching?','Data is written to the cache and then immediately to the database','Data is only written to the cache','Data is written to the database first, then the cache is updated later','Data is written to disk twice','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Write-through ensures consistency between the cache and the database but adds latency to write operations.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','If a system has ''Five Nines'' of availability, what is its target uptime?','99.9%','99.999%','95.555%','90.00000%','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Five nines (99.999%) corresponds to less than 6 minutes of downtime per year.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','Which of these is a popular NoSQL database?','MySQL','PostgreSQL','MongoDB','Oracle DB','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'MongoDB is a document-oriented NoSQL database.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','Where does Redis typically store its data for high speed?','Hard Disk Drive (HDD)','Solid State Drive (SSD)','Random Access Memory (RAM)','External USB','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Redis is an in-memory data structure store, making it extremely fast.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is a ''Monolith''?','A system where all components are tightly coupled in a single program','A system with many small servers','A type of database index','A stone monument','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Monolithic architecture is the traditional unified model for software development.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','Which port does HTTPS typically use?','80','443','21','22','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',15,'HTTP uses port 80; HTTPS (secure) uses port 443.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is ''Eventual Consistency''?','Data is consistent immediately','A guarantee that if no new updates are made, eventually all accesses will return the last updated value','Data will never be consistent','Data is consistent once a month','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',35,'Eventual consistency is common in distributed NoSQL databases to allow high availability.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What are ''Sticky Sessions''?','Websites that load slowly','A feature where all requests from a specific client are routed to the same server for a session','Sessions that never log out','A database backup method','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Sticky sessions (session affinity) help maintain locally stored session data on a specific server.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is ''DNS Caching''?','Storing DNS records in the database','Temporarily storing IP addresses locally to avoid frequent DNS lookups','Deleting DNS records','An internet security protocol','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'DNS caching at the browser or OS level speeds up web browsing.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','Which of these is most likely to cause high latency?','A high-bandwidth fiber optic cable','Data traveling across long physical distances (e.g., across oceans)','Using a small font on the website','Having too many monitors','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Physical distance and the number of hops between systems increase latency.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is ''Asynchronous'' communication?','The sender and receiver must be active at the same time','The sender sends a message and doesn''t wait for an immediate response to continue','Communication that only happens on weekends','Using two phones at once','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Asynchronous communication (often using queues) improves system decoupling and responsiveness.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is ''Master-Slave'' (or Primary-Replica) replication?','All servers can read and write data equally','One server handles all writes, and data is copied to other servers (slaves) for reading','Servers take turns being the master','A way to delete data automatically','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'This pattern scales read requests but the Master can be a bottleneck for writes.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','Why do Load Balancers perform ''Health Checks''?','To see if the servers have viruses','To ensure traffic is only sent to servers that are active and responding correctly','To count how many files are on the server','To update the operating system','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Health checks allow the load balancer to remove unhealthy servers from the pool automatically.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is an ''API Gateway''?','A physical door in a data center','A server that acts as an entry point for all API requests, handling tasks like routing and security','A list of IP addresses','A type of database table','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'API Gateways simplify client interactions and centralize security and monitoring.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is ''Object Storage'' commonly used for?','Executing complex SQL queries','Storing massive amounts of unstructured data like images, videos, and backups','Running a web server','Storing temporary variables','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Services like AWS S3 are examples of object storage designed for scalability and durability.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is ''Failover''?','When a system fails and stays down','The automatic switching to a redundant or standby computer server or network upon failure','A way to reset a password','Sending the wrong data','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Failover is key to maintaining high availability during hardware or software crashes.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','Which of these is a disadvantage of Vertical Scaling?','It adds network overhead','It has an upper hardware limit and usually causes downtime during upgrades','It requires complex load balancing','It makes the code harder to write','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'You can only add so much RAM or CPU to a single machine before hitting a limit.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','In the CAP Theorem, what do C, A, and P stand for?','Consistency','Availability','Partition Tolerance','Performance','["A","B","C"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',40,'CAP Theorem states a distributed system can only guarantee two out of these three.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is ''Strong Consistency''?','Data is consistent eventually','A guarantee that any read request will return the most recent write or an error','Consistency of code style','No data is ever lost','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Strong consistency is hard to achieve in highly distributed systems without sacrificing availability.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','Database ''Indexing'' is primarily used to:','Speed up data retrieval','Encrypt sensitive columns','Delete duplicate rows','Compressed the database size','["A"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'Indexing allows the database engine to find data without searching every row.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is the primary benefit of Microservices over Monoliths?','Lower hardware cost','Independent deployment and scaling of different parts of the system','Simpler debugging','Zero network latency','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Microservices allow teams to work on and scale different features independently.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is ''Replication''?','Adding more lines of code','Keeping copies of data on multiple servers to increase durability and availability','Moving the database to a new cloud provider','Creating mock data for testing','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Replication protects against data loss and helps with read scalability.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is ''Bandwidth''?','The delay in the network','The maximum rate of data transfer across a network path','The width of the server rack','The number of servers in a cluster','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',25,'Bandwidth identifies how much data can move through a network connection in a given time.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is ''Weighted Round Robin''?','Servers are selected by their weight in kilograms','Servers are assigned a weight based on capacity, and more power servers receive more requests','A random selection method','Selecting the server that was added last','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'This ensures that more powerful servers handle a larger share of the traffic.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is ''Cache Invalidation'' usually considered?','The easiest part of system design','One of the most difficult challenges in computer science (maintaining data freshness)','A way to add more data to the cache','A database maintenance tool','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'As the quote goes: ''There are only two hard things in Computer Science: cache invalidation and naming things.''','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is a ''Static IP''?','An address that changes every day','An IP address that is permanently assigned to a computer or device','An address for a website that is down','A secret password','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Static IPs are used for servers that need to be reachable at the same address consistently.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What layer of the OSI model does a ''Layer 7'' Load Balancer operate at?','Network Layer (IP)','Transport Layer (TCP)','Application Layer (HTTP/HTTPS)','Physical Layer','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Layer 7 load balancers can make routing decisions based on URL, cookies, or HTTP headers.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','Which of these is a fully managed storage service by AWS?','Nginx','Redis','S3 (Simple Storage Service)','PostgreSQL','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'S3 is highly durable object storage widely used in modern architectures.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','In a distributed system, a ''Heartbeat'' is used to:','Play music in the background','Signal to other nodes that a specific node is still alive and operational','Sync timestamps','Count the number of users','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Heartbeats are essential for failure detection in distributed clusters.','pregenerated'),
('4f74975b-959b-4844-9722-5ff95e4da506','What is the primary benefit of Database Sharding?','It makes SQL queries easier to write','It allows a database to scale horizontally by distributing data across many servers','It reduces the amount of data stored','It replaces the need for indexes','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'Sharding is used when a single database server can no longer handle the load or store the data.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','According to the CAP Theorem, which two properties do most distributed NoSQL databases like Cassandra prioritize during a network partition?','Consistency and Availability','Availability and Partition Tolerance','Consistency and Partition Tolerance','Performance and Scalability','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'In the event of a partition (P), a system must choose between Availability (A) or strict Consistency (C).','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is the primary problem solved by ''Consistent Hashing'' in a distributed system?','Encrypting data across multiple servers','Minimizing data movement when nodes are added or removed from a cluster','Speeding up the CPU speed','Cleaning up the hard drive','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Consistent hashing ensures that only a small fraction of keys need to be remapped when the number of slots changes.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is the role of a ''Message Queue'' like RabbitMQ or Kafka?','To store only the final output of the code','To enable asynchronous communication between services by decoupling the producer and consumer','To manage the server''s user login','To increase the system''s internet speed','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Queues allow systems to handle spikes in traffic and process tasks in the background.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What does the ''LRU'' cache eviction policy stand for?','Longest Running Unit','Least Recently Used','Low Resource Unit','Last Reliable Update','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'LRU removes the item that hasn''t been accessed for the longest time when the cache is full.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','Which database type is generally preferred for data with many-to-many relationships and a rigid schema?','KeyValue Store','Document Database','Relational Database (SQL)','Graph Database','["C"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'SQL databases excel at managing relationships and maintaining data integrity via joins.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is an ''Edge Server'' in a Content Delivery Network (CDN)?','A server located at the center of the world','A server located at the ''edge'' of a network, physically close to users to serve cached content','A server that backups data once a month','A physical wall in the data center','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Edge servers minimize request travel distance (latency) for users.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is ''Multi-Master'' replication?','One master server and many slave servers','Multiple servers that can handle both read and write requests and sync with each other','A server that doesn''t share data','Using a secondary database as a backup only','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Multi-master replication increases write scalability but introduces complex conflict resolution issues.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','In a distributed system, what is ''Read-Your-Writes'' consistency?','A user can read their own updates immediately after writing them','Users can only read what others have written','The system reads random data','None of the above','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'This ensures a user sees their own changes even if the total system is eventually consistent.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','Which algorithm is commonly used for ''Rate Limiting''?','Bubble Sort','Token Bucket','Binary Search','Round Robin','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'The Token Bucket algorithm allows for bursts of traffic while maintaining a steady average rate.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is the purpose of ''Service Discovery'' in a microservices environment?','To find a job','To automatically detect the network location (IP/Port) of services in a dynamic cluster','To delete unused code','To encrypt network traffic','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Tools like Consul, Etcd, or Zookeeper help services find each other in a cloud environment.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','Apache Zookeeper is often used as a:','Web Server','Distributed Configuration and Coordination Service','Database for storing gigabytes of text','Streaming video platform','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Zookeeper manages centralized config, leader election, and group membership for distributed systems.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is a ''Hot Standby''?','A server that is turned off but ready to be used','A secondary server that is running and kept fully synchronized with the primary, ready for immediate failover','A backup on a USB drive','A very hot server room','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Hot standby minimizes failover time with nearly zero interruption.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is a ''Forward Proxy'' used for?','Protecting a group of servers from the internet','Protecting a group of clients (users) as they access the internet','Scaling a database','Storing images','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Forward proxies act on behalf of the client, often for security, privacy, or content filtering.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is the trade-off for adding many indexes to a database table?','Reads become slower','Writes become slower and more storage is consumed','The database becomes smaller','The system uses less CPU','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Every index must be updated whenever a row is inserted, updated, or deleted.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What does ''JWT'' stand for in web security and API design?','Java Web Token','JSON Web Token','Joint Web Task','Just Web Tool','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'JWT is an open standard for securely transmitting information between parties as a JSON object.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is ''Quorum'' in a distributed database system?','The maximum number of users','The minimum number of nodes that must agree to a read or write operation to be considered successful','The speed of the database','A type of SQL query','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Quorum ensures data consistency by requiring a majority of nodes to respond.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is a ''Cache Miss''?','When the cache is too small','When the requested data is not found in the cache and must be fetched from the slower primary store','When the cache is deleted','When the wrong data is stored','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Cache misses increase latency because they require a backend data fetch.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is ''IP Hashing'' in load balancing?','Changing the user''s IP','Determining which server handles a request by taking the hash of the client''s IP address','A way to encrypt IPs','A database partitioning technique','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'IP hashing helps in achieving session persistence by routing the same client IP to the same server.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','Can a single system guarantee all three: Consistency, Availability, and Partition Tolerance simultaneously?','Yes, with enough Geld (money)','No, it is technically impossible in a distributed system','Yes, if the servers are all in the same building','No, unless you use SQL','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',35,'The CAP theorem states that you can only provide two of the three guarantees at once.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What does ''ELK stack'' stand for?','Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana','Easy Log Keeper','Encryption Layer Kernel','Elastic Link Kernel','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'The ELK stack is a popular log aggregation and visualization toolset.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is ''Fan-out'' in messaging systems?','Decreasing the number of servers','Delivering a single message to multiple consumers at the same time','The cooling system of a server','A way to sort data','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Fan-out is common in pub/sub architectures.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is the ''Circuit Breaker'' pattern?','A physical switch in the server room','A pattern used to detect failures and prevent cascading failures by stopping calls to a failing service','A way to speed up network traffic','A database optimization tool','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Circuit breakers protect the system from getting overwhelmed by failing downstream dependencies.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','In a ''Pub/Sub'' model, what do the components represent?','Public and Sub-public','Publisher and Subscriber','Processor and Server','Printer and Scanner','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'The publisher sends messages without knowing who will receive them; subscribers sign up to receive specific topics.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is ''Write-Ahead Logging'' (WAL)?','Writing logs after the data is committed','A technique where data changes are first recorded in a persistent log before being applied to the actual database','Logging only successful queries','Deleting logs every hour','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'WAL is used to ensure atomic commits and data durability in case of a crash.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is ''RAID''?','A bug in the system','Redundant Array of Independent Disks, used for data redundancy and/or performance','A type of network router','An internet security protocol','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'RAID combines multiple disks to prevent data loss if one disk fails.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is ''Least Connections'' load balancing?','Avoiding servers with high latency','Sending a request to the server that currently has the fewest active sessions','Sending a request to the oldest server','Using a random server','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'This method is useful when servers have different capacities or processing requirements.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is ''Back-pressure'' in a distributed system?','The wind speed in the server room','The resistance or force exerted against the flow of data when a consumer cannot keep up with a producer','A type of database indexing','A way to push updates to users','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Back-pressure prevents the consumer from being overwhelmed and potentially crashing.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is ''Write-Back'' (or Write-Behind) caching?','Data is written to the cache and then immediately to the DB','Data is written solely to the cache, and the database is updated asynchronously after some delay','Deleting the cache before a write','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'This provides high write performance but carries the risk of data loss if the cache fails before the DB is updated.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What does ''ACID'' stand for in relational databases?','Atomicity, Consistency, Isolation, Durability','Accuracy, Core, Internal, Data','Access, Control, Internal, Database','All-in-one Consistency, Integrity, Durability','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'ACID properties ensure reliable processing of database transactions.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is ''Vertical Partitioning'' of a database?','Splitting rows across multiple servers','Splitting tables by dividing columns into separate tables to reduce I/O','Deleting columns that aren''t used','Sorting data by size','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'This is often used to move infrequently accessed columns to separate storage.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is a ''Cold Standby''?','A running server that acts as a backup','A server that is available but turned off, needing time to start up and sync during a failover','A server in a very cold room','A backup on paper','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Cold standby is cheaper but significantly increases recovery time (RTO).','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is ''Throughput'' vs ''Latency'' tradeoff?','There is no tradeoff','Optimizing for handling many requests (Throughput) may increase the time per request (Latency)','Decreasing latency always increases throughput','Throughput and latency are the same thing','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Designing a system often involves balancing these two depending on user needs.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is a ''Wide-column Store'' database?','A database that only stores strings','A NoSQL type that uses a column-oriented data structure (e.g., Cassandra, HBase)','A SQL table with many columns','A physical storage method','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Wide-column stores offer high performance and a highly scalable architecture.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is ''SLA'' (Service Level Agreement)?','A type of code comment','A contract between a service provider and client that defines the level of service and uptime expected','A software library','A type of hardware','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'SLAs provide a baseline for availability guarantees.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','Which of these is a binary communication protocol often used for efficiency in microservices?','JSON','XML','gRPC (using Protocol Buffers)','HTML','["C"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'gRPC is more efficient than REST/JSON for inter-service communication because it uses a binary format.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','In distributed systems, what is the ''Gossip Protocol''?','Servers sharing rumors about the users','A peer-to-peer communication protocol where nodes share information about neighbors to reach cluster-wide consensus','A way to delete database logs','A high-speed internet protocol','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Gossip protocols are used for failure detection and state dissemination in large clusters like Cassandra.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is ''Stateless'' scaling?','Scaling by adding more hard drives','Scaling application servers that do not store client context locally, making them easily replaceable','Scaling without using code','Using only one server','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Stateless servers are key to efficient horizontal scaling.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is a ''Hot Spot'' in database sharding?','A high-speed internet area','A specific shard that receives a disproportionately large amount of traffic or data, causing a performance bottleneck','A server that is too hot','A popular database feature','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Hot spots usually occur due to poor choice of a shard key (e.g., sharding by date for a trending event).','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is ''Distributed File System'' (DFS)?','A way to store files on one computer','A file system that allows many machines to access and share files as if they were local','A file that is shared on social media','A database tool','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Examples include HDFS (Hadoop) and S3, which provide scalable and durable storage.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is a ''Sidecar'' pattern in microservices?','A passenger on a motorcycle','Attaching a helper component to a service to handle infrastructure concerns like logging, monitoring, or networking','A second server that does the same thing as the first','A way to scale databases','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Sidecars are commonly used in service meshes like Istio.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is ''Heartbeat'' monitoring primarily used for?','To check the developer''s pulse','To detect if a node or service in a cluster has failed','To count the number of visitors','To optimize database queries','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'If the heartbeat stops, the system can initiate failover.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is ''N+1'' redundancy?','Having one more component than theoretically required to handle the load','Having double the servers','Adding one user at a time','A type of math problem','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'N+1 ensures that if one server fails, the remaining N can still handle the entire traffic.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is a ''VIP'' (Virtual IP) in load balancing?','A Very Important Person''s IP','An IP address that is not tied to a specific physical server, allowing it to move to a backup server during failover','An encrypted IP address','A private local IP','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'VIPs are crucial for floating load balancers or highly available database clusters.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','Which of these provides real-time, bi-directional communication between client and server?','HTTP GET','WebSockets','REST API','FTP','["B"]'::jsonb,'tricky',30,'WebSockets maintain a persistent connection for low-latency full-duplex communication.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is a ''Layer 4'' load balancer?','A load balancer that understands cookies','A load balancer that operates based on TCP/UDP ports and IP addresses','A load balancer for image processing only','A random routing tool','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Layer 4 load balancers are faster but less intelligent than Layer 7 ones.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is ''Throttling'' in system design?','Stopping the server completely','Intentional slowing down of a service or user request to prevent system overload','A way to speed up the database','Deleting old files','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Throttling protects system resources during traffic spikes or DDoS attacks.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is the ''Purge'' strategy in CDN caching?','Removing all servers','Manually forcing the removal of cached content before its TTL expires','Automatically deleting logs','Encrypting the cache','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Purging is necessary when content changes upstream and users must see the update immediately.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is ''Denormalization'' in database design?','Creating more table relationships','Introducing redundant data into a database to improve read performance by avoiding joins','Cleaning up the data schema','Converting NoSQL to SQL','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Denormalization trades storage space and write complexity for significantly faster read queries.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is ''Saga'' pattern in microservices?','A long story about the server','A pattern for managing distributed transactions by breaking them into a series of local transactions with compensations','A way to merge all code into one file','A database backup tool','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Sagas provide a way to maintain data consistency across multiple independent services.','pregenerated'),
('a3ab8e2e-ef32-4faa-87d8-d5d7716b3407','What is ''Dead Letter Queue'' (DLQ)?','A queue for letters that weren''t mailed','A secondary queue where messages that cannot be processed successfully are sent for debugging','A deleted database','A type of server crash','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'DLQs prevent messages from cycling indefinitely and allow developers to investigate failures.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is the primary purpose of ''Paxos'' or ''Raft'' algorithms?','To compress data for storage','To achieve consensus among a group of unreliable servers in a distributed system','To encrypt user passwords','To optimize CSS rendering','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'These algorithms ensure that a cluster of nodes agrees on a single value even if some nodes fail.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What are ''Vector Clocks'' used for in distributed databases?','To measure the speed of the hardware','To detect and resolve causality and version conflicts between data updates in an eventually consistent system','To sync the time on the servers'' BIOS','To schedule cron jobs','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Vector clocks help systems like DynamoDB identify when two updates happened concurrently (conflicts).','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is ''Active-Active'' Geo-replication?','All users go to a single central data center','Data is served and accepted for writes in multiple geographic regions simultaneously','Servers taking turns to process data weekly','A way to delete data in two countries at once','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Active-active setups provide lowest latency and highest availability but are extremely complex to sync.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is a ''LSM Tree'' (Log-Structured Merge-tree)?','A tree in the data center garden','A data structure optimized for write-heavy workloads by buffering writes in memory and flushing them to disk sequentially','A way to sort SQL tables','A physical storage rack','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'LSM trees are used by Cassandra, LevelDB, and RocksDB to handle massive write volumes.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','In the Circuit Breaker pattern, what does the ''Half-Open'' state represent?','The service is completely down','The system allows a limited number of requests to pass through to test if the failing service has recovered','The system is working perfectly','The database is being backed up','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Half-open allows the system to gracefully transition back to a normal state if the downstream service is healthy.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','Why is ''Consistent Hashing'' preferred over ''Modulo Hashing'' (key % n) for distributed caching?','Consistent hashing is easier to write','Consistent hashing minimizes data reshuffle (rehashing) when nodes are added or removed','Modulo hashing only works for integers','Consistent hashing uses less memory','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'With modulo hashing, adding one node moves almost all keys; with consistent hashing, only 1/n keys move.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is the ''Split-Brain'' problem in a cluster?','When the CPU cache fails','When two or more sets of nodes lose connectivity but continue to operate as if they are the sole master, leading to data corruption','When a developer forgets to save code','When the system has too many users','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Consensus protocols like Raft prevent split-brain by requiring a majority quorum for any updates.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is ''Quorum Read'' (R) and ''Quorum Write'' (W) configuration?','R + W = N where N is the number of replicas','R + W > N ensures strong consistency in a distributed system','R and W must always be 1','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'By ensuring R+W > N, you guarantee that the read set and write set always overlap by at least one node.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is a ''Service Mesh'' (e.g., Istio, Linkerd)?','An upgraded internet cable','A dedicated infrastructure layer for handling service-to-service communication, including security, traffic control, and observability','A database for microservices','A type of UI component','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Service meshes use sidecar proxies to manage network complexity transparently from the application code.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is ''Idempotency'' in API design?','Getting a different result every time you call an API','The property where making the same request multiple times has the same effect as making it once','The speed of the API','Reducing the API payload size','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Idempotency is crucial for safe retries in case of network failures.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is a ''Bloom Filter'' primarily used for?','Cleaning air in a server room','Highly efficient probabilistic check if an element is in a set (it can have false positives, but never false negatives)','Sorting massive datasets on disk','Encryption of database keys','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'Bloom filters save expensive disk lookups by proving an element is NOT present.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is the ''Write Amplification'' problem in SSDs and databases?','The increase in font size of logs','The phenomenon where the amount of data physically written to the storage media is a multiple of the data logical written by the application','Higher volumes during writes','Database crashes during writes','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Write amplification reduces drive lifespan and decreases performance.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is ''Chaos Engineering'' (e.g., Netflix Chaos Monkey)?','When the code is very messy','The practice of intentionally injecting failures into a production system to test and improve its resilience','A random hacking attack','Deleting files randomly by mistake','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Chaos engineering helps find hidden weaknesses in complex distributed systems.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is ''BGP'' (Border Gateway Protocol) hijacking?','Stealing a server physically','Maliciously changing the routing table of the internet to redirect traffic to the wrong destination','A way to speed up DNS','Bypassing a firewall','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'BGP is the protocol that manages how packets are routed across the global internet.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is the ''Cache Stampede'' (Thundering Herd) problem?','When the cache server catches fire','When a popular cache key expires and massive numbers of concurrent requests hit the backend DB at once','Adding too many keys to the cache','Using two caches together','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'This can crash the database; it''s solved by locking or probabilistic early re-computation.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is a ''B-Tree'' versus ''B+ Tree'' in database indexing?','B+ trees store data in all nodes, B-trees only in leaves','B+ trees store actual data/pointers only in leaf nodes, which are linked together for faster range scans','B-trees are for NoSQL, B+ are for SQL','They are identical structures','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'B+ trees are standard for database indexes because they optimize disk I/O and range queries.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is ''Database Denormalization'' common for in high-scale systems?','Reducing the disk space used','Improving read performance by eliminating complex JOINS through data duplication','Making the database schema harder to read','Ensuring data is only in one place','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'At scale, joins (especially across distributed nodes) are prohibitively expensive.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is ''Server-Sent Events'' (SSE)?','Servers sending emails to users','A standard allowing servers to push real-time data updates to web pages over HTTP','A type of database trigger','A crash report','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'SSE is simpler than WebSockets for one-way (Server to Client) real-time updates.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is an ''Elastic IP''?','An address that stretches across the network','A static IP address designed for dynamic cloud computing that can be quickly remapped to another instance during failure','An IP for a VPN only','A temporary IP that lasts 5 minutes','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Elastic IPs allow you to maintain a consistent DNS endpoint while hardware underneath changes.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is ''Erasure Coding'' in storage systems?','Encrypting data with a key','A method of data protection in which data is broken into fragments, expanded and encoded with redundant data pieces for high durability','Deleting data after 30 days','A way to hide files','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Erasure coding (used in S3) provides higher durability than simple RAID replication with less storage overhead.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is the ''Saga'' pattern for distributed transactions?','A long story about the server','Managing a transaction across multiple services by using a sequence of local transactions and compensation actions if one fails','Using a single massive SQL transaction for all services','A way to merge all databases into one','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Sagas avoid long-lived distributed locks and improve system scalability.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is a ''Zero Trust'' architecture?','Assuming no user is active','An IT security model that requires strict identity verification for every person and device trying to access resources, regardless of location','Don''t trust the code you wrote','Trusting only users in the physical office','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Zero Trust ensures that being ''inside the network'' does not automatically grant access to assets.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is the ''PACELC'' theorem an extension of?','CAP theorem','ACID properties','Moore''s law','BASE properties','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',55,'PACELC clarifies the tradeoff between Latency (L) and Consistency (C) when the system is running normally (E - else).','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is ''Global Cache'' in system design?','The browser cache on every user device','A centralized cache used by all application nodes (e.g., Redis cluster) to ensure data consistency','A cache that stores the entire internet','Caching only global variables','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Global cache avoids duplicate cache entries in local node caches.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is ''Infrastructure as Code'' (IaC)?','Writing code inside the data center','Managing and provisioning infrastructure through machine-readable definition files (e.g., Terraform) rather than manual processes','Drawing server diagrams in code','Using Python to restart a server','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'IaC ensures consistent, repeatable, and version-controlled infrastructure deployment.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is ''Anycast'' routing?','Sending a message to everyone','A network addressing and routing method where a single IP address is shared by multiple geographic locations, routing traffic to the nearest one','Sending packets in a random direction','A way to broadcast TV on the internet','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Anycast is commonly used by CDNs and DNS providers to minimize global latency.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is a ''Merkle Tree'' used for in systems like Git or Blockchain?','Storing names of tree species','Efficiently verifying that data has not been tampered with and syncing differences across nodes','Sorting code files','A way to draw the system diagram','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Merkle trees use hashes to efficiently detect changes in large datasets.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is ''Log Aggregation''?','Merging multiple math logs','The process of collecting, centralizing, and indexing logs from various servers in a distributed system (e.g., Fluentd, Splunk)','Deleting logs every 5 minutes','Sharing logs on social media','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Log aggregation is vital for debugging and monitoring distributed microservices.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is ''Polyglot Persistence''?','Using only one database for everything','Using different data storage technologies for different parts of an application (e.g., SQL for profiles, Redis for cache, Neo4j for social)','A database written in many languages','Storing files in multiple languages','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Not all data is fit for a single model; polyglot persistence uses the best tool for each specific job.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is ''Database Federation''?','Merging all databases in a country','Splitting a database into multiple physical servers by functional area (e.g., users table on one DB, products on another)','Encrypting the database name','A way to count database rows','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Federation is an early step in database scaling before moving to more complex sharding.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is an ''Availability Zone'' (AZ)?','The area where internet is free','A distinct location within a cloud region designed to be isolated from failures in other AZs (separate power, cooling, network)','One server room','A time zone for the database','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Deploying across multiple AZs protects your system from data center-level disasters.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is ''QUIC'' protocol (HTTP/3)?','A faster way to write code','A new transport layer protocol built on top of UDP to reduce latency and improve connection migration over traditional TCP','A way to compress images','A database query language','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'QUIC reduces the number of round trips needed for establishing secure connections.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','In Raft consensus, how often are ''Heartbeats'' sent by the Leader?','Every minute','Continuously to prevent followers from starting a new election','Only when data changes','Every hour','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Heartbeats maintain the Leader''s authority; if they stop, the followers assume the Leader died and elect a new one.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is a ''Single Sign-On'' (SSO) architecture?','Allowing only one user to login at a time','An authentication scheme that allows a user to log in with a single ID to any of several related, independent software systems','A password that expires after one use','A very long password','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'SSO improves user experience and security by centralizing session management.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is ''Canary Deployment''?','Deploying code in a birdcage','A rollout strategy where a new version of software is first released to a small, specific subset of users before rolling it out to everyone','Deleting old code before new code arrives','Testing code on a fake server','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Canary deployments act as an early warning system for bugs in new releases.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is a ''Negative Cache''?','A cache that doesn''t work','Caching the ''absence'' of an item (e.g., 404 Not Found) to prevent repeated expensive lookups for data that doesn''t exist','Deleting items from the cache','A cache for large files only','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Negative caching prevents ''Cache Holes'' that could allow a user to flood the backend with invalid requests.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is ''Tiered Storage''?','Storing data in different levels of the building','Assigning data to different storage media (e.g., RAM vs SSD vs HDD) based on cost, performance, and access frequency','Backup on paper','Using only one type of drive','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Tiered storage helps balance cost and performance by moving ''cold'' data to cheaper, slower media.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is ''Thundering Herd'' in general computing?','Too many servers in one room','When a large number of processes/threads are awakened by an event but only one can handle it, wasting CPU resources','A stampede of users on a website','Deleting many files at once','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Thundering herd can lead to severe system slowdowns and contention.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is ''Head-of-Line'' (HOL) blocking in TCP?','When the lead developer stops working','A performance limitation where a single lost or delayed packet stops all subsequent packets from being processed by the application','Blocking the first person in line','A security firewall feature','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'HOL blocking is a major reason why HTTP/3 moved to a UDP-based transport (QUIC).','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is ''Blue-Green'' deployment?','Mixing two versions of code in the same server','Running two identical production environments (Blue and Green). Traffic is switched to the new version (Green) after it passes tests.','Using a blue background for the website','A way to categorize bugs','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Blue-Green deployment allows near-zero downtime and instant rollback capabilities.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is ''Sharding Key'' selection criteria?','Picking a random string','Picking a key that ensures even distribution of data (avoiding hot spots) and minimizes cross-shard queries','Using the auto-incrementing ID for everything','The shortest column name','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Shard key selection is the most critical decision when implementing database sharding.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is ''Protocol Buffers'' (Protobuf)?','A way to buffer YouTube videos','A language-neutral, platform-neutral, extensible mechanism for serializing structured data (developed by Google)','An internet speed booster','A type of firewall','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'Protobuf is smaller, faster, and simpler than XML or JSON for service communication.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is the ''Two-Phase Commit'' (2PC) protocol?','Comming twice during the day','A distributed algorithm that coordinates all processes in a distributed transaction on whether to commit or rollback','A way to update Two databases at once without a coordinator','A type of code update','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'2PC provides strong consistency but can become a bottleneck because it requires locking.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','In stream processing, what is ''At-least-once'' delivery?','Messages might never be delivered','A guarantee that messages will be delivered one or more times, ensuring no data loss but allowing duplicates','Messages are delivered exactly one time','Messages are delivered to everyone','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'At-least-once is a common tradeoff for performance and reliability in systems like Kafka.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is ''Failover Cluster''?','A group of servers that fail together','A set of independent computers that work together to increase the availability of services and applications','A very large data center','A type of load balancer','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Clusters provide a safety net; if one node fails, the service is picked up by another node in the cluster.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is ''Cold Start'' in Serverless (FaaS)?','A server room in winter','The latency experienced when a function is triggered after being idle, as the cloud provider must spin up a new container','A computer that won''t turn on','Buying a new computer','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Cold starts are a significant performance consideration for serverless architectures.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is ''WAF'' (Web Application Firewall)?','A physical wall around the data center','A firewall that monitors, filters, and blocks HTTP traffic to and from a web application, protecting against attacks like SQL injection and XSS','A tool to compress web pages','A way to speed up user logins','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'WAFs operate at Layer 7 and provide deep packet inspection for web requests.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','Which method is commonly used for ''Message Acknowledgment'' in queues?','Sending a thank you email','The consumer notifying the queue that a message has been successfully handled, so the queue can safely delete it','Writing a log entry','Deleting the message immediately after sending','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Acknowledgments (ACKs) ensure reliable delivery in message-oriented middleware.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is ''Tombstone'' in NoSQL databases like Cassandra?','The end of a database','A marker used to signal that a piece of data has been deleted, ensuring the deletion propagates to all replicas','A physical server name','An old version of the software','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Tombstones prevent deleted data from ''reappearing'' if a node goes down and comes back up with an old copy.','pregenerated'),
('4acd2e1b-dbe1-454e-aac4-6504fce6f668','What is ''Database Read Replicas'' lag?','When the database is too fast','The time delay between a write to the primary (Master) and when it becomes available on the replicas (Slaves)','A connection error to the database','The time it takes to delete data','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Replication lag is a critical metric for systems that rely on read replicas for scaling.','pregenerated')
INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','When designing a system like ''WhatsApp'', which primary challenge does the service face regarding connection management?','High CPU utilization per user','Maintaining millions of concurrent long-lived socket connections (WebSockets) on a single server','Slow database queries for messages','Encryption overhead','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'High-scale chat apps must optimize OS kernel parameters to handle millions of persistent connections.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is the ''Lambda Architecture'' specifically designed for?','Running serverless functions','Processing massive amounts of data by using both batch-processing and stream-processing methods','Scaling Python applications','Designing UI components','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Lambda architecture provides low-latency views of real-time data while ensuring consistency with archival batch data.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','How does ''HyperLogLog'' (HLL) help in system design for large-scale analytics?','It encrypts massive datasets using logs','It provides a probabilistic way to estimate the number of unique elements (cardinality) in a huge set with minimal memory','It sorts data in logarithmic time','It records all user logins for history','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'HLL can estimate millions of unique values using just a few kilobytes of RAM.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','In Consistent Hashing, what is a ''Virtual Node'' used for?','A server that doesn''t exist','To ensure even distribution of data across physical nodes by mapping multiple hash points to a single actual server','To back up the master node','To simulate network traffic','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Virtual nodes prevent data skew when a cluster has servers of different capacities or irregular hash distribution.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is ''Database Write Skew'' in the context of snapshot isolation?','Writing data diagonally in the table','A situation where two transactions read the same data, but update different parts of it, violating a global constraint that wasn''t visible to either','Writing too fast for the server','A physical disk failure during a write','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Write skew is an anomaly where isolation levels fail to maintain application-level invariants.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is an ''Inverted Index'' in the context of search engines like Elasticsearch?','An index sorted in reverse alphabetical order','A map of words to their document locations, allowing for ultra-fast full-text search','A list of documents without content','Deleting the original data and keeping the index','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Inverted indexes are the core data structure enabling efficient searching across millions of documents.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is ''Jitter'' in a retry policy?','A bug causing UI flickering','Adding a random delay to retry attempts to prevent many clients from retrying at the exact same moment (Thundering Herd)','The speed of the network cable','A way to speed up the CPU','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Jitter smoothly distributes load on a recovered service by staggering synchronized retry attempts.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','In Google Bigtable, what is a ''Tablet''?','A mobile device for data entry','A contiguous range of rows in a table, which is the unit of distribution and load balancing','A small database','A hardware storage module','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Tablets are dynamically split and moved between servers to handle massive scale.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','Why do some high-performance systems use ''UDP'' instead of ''TCP'' for data transfer?','UDP is more reliable','TCP''s handshake and congestion control add too much latency for use cases like gaming or real-time streaming','UDP encrypts data automatically','UDP is newer than TCP','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'UDP trades delivery guarantees for speed and low overhead.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is ''CQRS'' (Command Query Responsibility Segregation)?','A way to sort SQL tables','Pattern that uses different models for updating data (commands) and reading data (queries)','Combining all queries into one command','A database backup tool','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'CQRS allows scaling and optimizing reads independently from writes.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is ''TF-IDF'' primarily used for in search algorithms?','Total Factorial Identification','Term Frequency-Inverse Document Frequency: a weighting factor to evaluate how important a word is to a document','A data encryption standard','A protocol for fast file transfer','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'TF-IDF is used by search engines to rank the relevance of documents to a user query.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is ''Log Aggregation'' vs ''Log Streaming''?','They are the same thing','Aggregation collects logs periodically; Streaming processes and transmits log events in near-real-time as they occur','Aggregation is only for text files','Streaming is slower than Aggregation','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Log streaming (e.g., using Kafka) is essential for modern real-time alerting and observability.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is ''Leasing'' in the context of distributed cache consistent updates?','Renting a server','Granting a node exclusive rights to update a cache key for a specific period to prevent race conditions','Deleting old cache data','A way to buy hardware','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Leases provide a mechanism to coordinate updates without heavy global locking.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is ''N-1'' redundancy in a data center context?','Subtracting one server','Designing infrastructure so that it can continue operating even if its largest component fails','Having one extra backup on a USB','A way to delete data','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'N-1 ensures that the failure of any single component won''t cause system downtime.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is a ''Quadtree'' used for in systems like Uber or Yelp?','Managing four databases together','A tree data structure where each node has exactly four children, used for efficient spatial indexing and location-based searches','A way to count users in four regions','An encryption method for maps','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Quadtrees allow for fast retrieval of ''nearby'' points (e.g., finding the nearest driver or restaurant).','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','In Apache Kafka, what is a ''Partition''?','A wall in the server room','The unit of parallelism; an ordered set of messages within a topic that can be processed by a single consumer in a group','A type of database index','A small part of a message','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Partitions allow Kafka topics to scale horizontally across many brokers.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is ''Column-oriented'' storage (e.g., Apache Parquet, Redshift) best for?','Fast single-row lookups (OLTP)','Analytical queries across large datasets with complex aggregations (OLAP)','Storing user profile pictures','Writing data very fast','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Columnar storage only reads the columns needed for a query, significantly reducing disk I/O for analytics.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What does a ''MapReduce'' algorithm actually do?','Draws a map of the database','Processes huge datasets in parallel by splitting work (Map) and then consolidating results (Reduce)','Reduces the size of a map image','Finds a path between two map coordinates','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'MapReduce is the foundational paradigm for processing Big Data across large clusters.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is the ''Ambassador'' pattern?','A person representing a country','A helper service that acts as a proxy for a primary service, handling external connectivity and logging','A special load balancer','A database synchronization tool','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The Ambassador pattern simplifies network communication by offloading common tasks to a separate helper process.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is ''Rate Limiting'' vs ''Egress Filtering''?','They are the same thing','Rate Limiting limits incoming requests; Egress Filtering restricts what traffic can ''leave'' your network','Egress is only for email','Rate Limiting is for hardware only','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Egress filtering is critical for preventing data exfiltration and limiting the impact of compromised servers.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is ''BFT'' (Byzantine Fault Tolerance)?','A database that never crashes','The ability of a system to reach consensus even if some members give conflicting or false information (malicious behavior)','A very old sorting algorithm','A hardware failure in a cable','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'BFT is the core requirement for making decentralized systems like Blockchain reliable.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','When building a ''Real-time Bidding'' system (AdTech), what is the most critical design constraint?','Data durability','Absolute minimum latency (usually <100ms end-to-end)','Total storage size','Encryption depth','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'In AdTech, the auction must happen while a webpage is loading, making latency the #1 priority.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is ''Negative Caching'' helpful for?','Deleting the cache','Reducing load on the database by remembering that a certain key DOES NOT exist','Storing errors in the cache','A cache that runs in reverse','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Negative caching prevents ''Cache Holes'' where missing data lookups hit the DB repeatedly.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is ''NoSQL Polyglot Persistence''?','Using many databases for the same user','Using different storage technologies for different data models in the same application based on their specific needs','A database that supports multiple languages','None of the above','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'This maximizes efficiency by using Graph DBs for social links, Document DBs for profiles, etc.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','In a distributed DB, what is a ''Hot Shard''?','A shard that is on a very hot server','A specific shard that handles significantly more traffic than others, leading to performance bottlenecks','A shard that is recently updated','A very fast shard','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Hot shards are often caused by poor shard key design, like sharding by a non-uniformly distributed field.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is the role of a ''Transit Gateway'' in cloud architecture?','A tunnel for high-speed trains','A hub that connects multiple VPCs and on-premises networks, simplifying connectivity management','A way to send data to users faster','A security firewall','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Transit gateways avoid ''full-mesh'' VPC peering, making complex cloud networks manageable.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is ''Dead Letter Queue'' (DLQ) used for?','Deleted messages','Storing messages that couldn''t be processed after multiple attempts, for manual inspection and debugging','A queue for old servers','A type of system crash report','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'DLQs prevent failing messages from clogging the main processing pipeline.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is ''Event Sourcing''?','Finding the source of an event','Persisting the state of an entity as a sequence of immutable state-changing events, rather than just the current state','A log of all system crashes','Tracking user events on a website','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Event sourcing allows you to rebuild the state of an application at any point in time.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is the ''Tail Latency'' (P99) problem?','The latency of the very first request','The phenomenon where a small percentage of requests (the ''tail'') take significantly longer than the average, impacting overall user experience','High latency on mobile devices only','Slow database queries','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'In a system with many dependencies, P99 latency can dominate the end-user experience.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is a ''Materialized View'' in the context of high performance?','A screenshot of the website','A pre-computed, stored result of a query used to improve read performance for expensive aggregations','A list of current users','A way to see the database code','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Materialized views trade storage and write time for ultra-fast query responses.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','When a system reaching millions of users faces ''Data Skew'', it means:','The data is corrupted','The distribution of data across shards is uneven, leading to some servers being overwhelmed while others are idle','The data is written in the wrong language','The database is too small','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Handling data skew often requires splitting hot partitions or adding salt to keys.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is ''HTTP/2'' multiplexing?','Sending multiple requests over the same TCP connection simultaneously','Using multiple browsers at once','Sending data to multiple servers','An encryption method','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Multiplexing reduces head-of-line blocking and improves performance compared to HTTP/1.1.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is ''Tiered Storage''?','Storing data in different formats','Moving data between different storage media (e.g., SSD for ''hot'' data, HDD for ''cold'' data) to balance cost and performance','Storing data in multiple data centers','A type of database indexing','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Tiered storage (or lifecycle management) optimizes storage costs at scale.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is a ''Region-wide failure''?','When a person in a specific country can''t login','The loss of all availability zones within a physical geographic area, usually due to a massive disaster','A temporary internet outage','A failure in the system''s code','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Protecting against region-wide failure requires multi-region active-passive or active-active architectures.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is ''Strangler Fig'' pattern in legacy migration?','A way to grow plants in a data center','Incrementally migrating a legacy system by replacing specific functional modules with new services until the old system is completely replaced','Deleting the entire old system at once','Renaming old variables','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'The Strangler Fig pattern reduces risk during the modernization of complex monoliths.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is ''Geo-hashing''?','A way to encrypt GPS coordinates','Representing a geographic area as a short, alphanumeric string, where longer strings represent more precise locations','A type of map drawing','A way to find the user''s country','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Geo-hashing allows for efficient range queries in spatial databases.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is ''Kappa Architecture'' in data processing?','A simplified version of Lambda Architecture that uses only a single stream-processing engine for all data processing','A database for images','A type of serverless function','Scaling Python code across many servers','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Kappa architecture simplifies maintenance by treating all data as a stream.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','In a search system like YouTube, what is ''Indexing Latency''?','The time it takes to search for a video','The time delay between a user uploading a video and it becoming searchable for other users','The speed of the video player','A connection error to the database','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Low indexing latency is essential for providing a ''fresh'' user experience in search engines.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is ''Database Denormalization'' trade-off?','Faster writes, slower reads','Faster reads, slower writes and potentially inconsistent data if not managed carefully','Lower storage costs, higher CPU usage','More users, less security','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Denormalization is a common optimization for read-heavy systems at scale.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is ''Global Server Load Balancing'' (GSLB)?','One load balancer for the entire planet','A DNS-based load balancing technique used to route traffic to the best data center based on physical distance and health','Scaling one server to handle all globally','A way to speed up user logins','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'GSLB helps distribute traffic globally across multiple data centers.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is the ''Compaction'' process in Kafka?','Deleting all old messages','Retention policy that ensures only the last known value for each message key is kept, reclaiming space','Compressing messages into a zip file','Reducing the number of partitions','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Topic compaction is useful for state storage where you only care about the most recent state.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is ''Autoscaling'' in cloud computing?','When a computer grows physically larger','The dynamic adjustment of computing resources based on real-time traffic and workload demands','Programming a computer to write its own code','A way to automatically pay cloud bills','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Autoscaling ensures you have enough capacity without overpaying for idle resources.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is ''Two-Phase Commit'' (2PC) major drawback?','It''s too easy to use','It is a blocking protocol that can lead to system-wide stalls if the coordinator fails','It doesn''t work with SQL','It makes the database too small','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Modern high-scale systems often use Three-Phase Commit (3PC) or Sagas instead of 2PC.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','In a ''Self-healing'' system, what is the role of an orchestrator (like Kubernetes)?','To write code automatically','To detect failed containers and automatically restart or replace them to maintain the desired state','To count the number of files','To optimize database queries','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Self-healing is a key component of highly available modern infrastructures.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is ''Distributed Lock'' manager used for?','Locking the server room door','Ensuring that only one process or node can perform a specific operation at a time across a distributed cluster','Encrypting the database logs','Making the database read-only','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Tools like Redis (Redlock) or Zookeeper provide distributed locking capabilities.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is ''Health Monitoring'' vs ''Application Monitoring''?','They are the same','Health checks look at infrastructure status (CPU, RAM); Application checks look at business logic and error rates','Application monitoring is only for UI','Health monitoring is more expensive','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Both are necessary for a complete view of system stability and performance.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','When building ''Twitter Search'' (relevance-based), what is the primary challenge?','Total storage','Handling a extreme ingestion rate (millions of tweets per minute) while providing sub-second search results','Drawing the user''s timeline','Counting the number of likes','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Real-time search at scale requires massive parallelization and specialized ingestion pipelines.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is the ''Backplane'' in a high-speed networking context?','A backup airplane for the CEO','The internal switching fabric of a router or server rack that connects many high-speed nodes together','The back of the server rack','A type of internet cable','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'Backplane throughput is a critical physical limit on the scalability of hardware clusters.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','What is ''Congestion Collapse'' in a network?','When a network is so busy that the overhead of retransmissions and dropped packets causes total throughput to drop to zero','When a server catches fire from too many users','When many users use the same cable','A way to speed up the internet','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'TCP congestion control is designed specifically to prevent this phenomenon.','pregenerated'),
('2b53670b-49ba-4921-a8cf-1617e02006c8','In AWS S3, a ''Bucket'' is a logical container for objects. Can buckets be nested?','Yes, infinitely','No, buckets are a flat namespace; you use ''prefixes'' (folders) to organize them','Yes, but only 3 levels deep','Only on weekends','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',60,'S3 buckets are flat; folders are purely visual organizational concepts using prefixes in the object key.','pregenerated')
