INSERT INTO questions(level_id,question_text,option_a,option_b,option_c,option_d,correct_options,question_type,timer_seconds,explanation,source) VALUES
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','What is the ''Halting Problem''?','The problem of determining if a computer is fast enough','The problem of determining whether a given Turing machine will eventually stop (halt) on a given input','The problem of finding the exit in a maze','A bug in the Windows operating system','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Alan Turing proved that no general algorithm exists that can solve the Halting Problem for all possible program-input pairs.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','A problem is in the ''NP'' (Non-deterministic Polynomial time) class if:','It can be solved in polynomial time by a standard computer','A proposed solution can be verified in polynomial time by a deterministic Turing Machine','It cannot be solved by any computer','It takes exponential time to verify','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Problems in NP might be hard to solve, but the answer is easy to check if it''s provided to you.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','What is meant by an ''NP-Complete'' problem?','A problem that is in NP and every other problem in NP can be reduced to it in polynomial time','A problem that has been completely solved','A problem that is neither in P nor in NP','A problem with only two possible answers','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'NP-Complete problems are the ''hardest'' problems in NP. If any NP-Complete problem is found to be in P, then P = NP.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','Which of the following problems are known to be Undecidable?','The Halting Problem','Post Correspondence Problem (PCP)','Determining if a CFG is ambiguous','Determining if a DFA accepts an empty string','["A","B","C"]'::jsonb,'multi_correct',45,'Determining if a DFA accepts empty is decidable (easy check). The others are mathematically proven to be undecidable.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','If P = NP were proven true, what would be the impact on modern cryptography (like RSA)?','It would become even more secure','It would likely be broken, as finding factors of large numbers would be efficiently solvable','It would have no impact','Computers would become slower','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'Many cryptographic systems rely on the assumption that certain problems (like factoring) are hard to solve but easy to verify (P != NP).','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','Which of the following describes the correctly established inclusion hierarchy?','P ⊆ NP ⊆ PSPACE ⊆ EXPTIME','NP ⊆ P ⊆ PSPACE','PSPACE ⊆ NP ⊆ P','EXPTIME ⊆ PSPACE ⊆ P','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'This is the standard hierarchy of time and space complexity classes.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','Which was the first problem proven to be NP-Complete (Cook-Levin Theorem)?','Traveling Salesperson Problem','Boolean Satisfiability Problem (SAT)','Vertex Cover','Knapsack Problem','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Stephen Cook and Leonid Levin independently proved that SAT is NP-complete by showing every NP problem reduces to it.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','To prove that a new problem B is NP-Complete, you must show:','B is in NP','A known NP-Complete problem A reduces to B in polynomial time','B is decidable','Both A and B','["D"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'NP-completeness requires both membership in NP and NP-hardness.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','What is the relationship between PSPACE and NPSPACE (Savitch''s Theorem)?','PSPACE is strictly smaller than NPSPACE','PSPACE = NPSPACE','NPSPACE is strictly smaller than PSPACE','They are unrelated','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Savitch''s Theorem states that any non-deterministic space complexity class can be simulated by a deterministic one with at most a quadratic increase in space.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','The class ''co-NP'' consists of problems whose:','Compliment is in NP','Compliment is in P','Solutions are verified in exponential time','Machines have 2 tapes','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'If a problem is in co-NP, then a ''No'' instance can be verified efficiently given a certificate.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','What does a ''Polynomial Time Reduction'' imply about the complexity of the two problems?','The target problem is at least as hard as the source problem','The source problem is harder','They are both in P','They are both undecidable','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'If A <=p B, and we can solve B fast, we can solve A fast. Thus, B is an upper bound on A''s difficulty.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','An ''NP-Hard'' problem is:','Always in NP','At least as hard as the hardest problems in NP, but not necessarily in NP itself','A problem with no known solution','A regular language','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'NP-hard problems include all NP-complete problems and even harder problems (like the Halting problem).','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','A Turing machine that always halts in O(N^k) steps for some constant k is a member of:','Class P','Class NP','Class EXPTIME','Class PSPACE','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'Polynomial time (P) is the class of ''efficiently'' solvable problems.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','Which of these is a classic NP-Complete problem?','Shortest Path (Dijkstra)','Traveling Salesperson Problem (TSP)','Sorting a list','Matrix Multiplication','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'TSP (the decision version) is one of Karp''s 21 NP-complete problems.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','Is the ''Validity Problem'' for first-order logic (checking if a formula is true in all models) decidable?','Yes','No, it is semi-decidable (RE)','No, it''s not even RE','Only for propositional logic','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Church and Turing independently proved that FO logic is undecidable via reduction from the Halting problem.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','According to Rice''s Theorem, which of these properties of RE languages is decidable?','L starts with ''a''','L is empty','L contains all strings','None of the above','["D"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'All listed properties are non-trivial properties of the recognized language, hence undecidable.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','The complexity class ''L'' (Logarithmic Space) corresponds to:','Problems solvable using a stack','Problems solvable in O(log n) read-write space on a Turing machine','Problems solvable in O(n log n) time','Regular languages only','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Log-space is a very restricted class, often used to define reductions.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','Which of these is a likely member of P?','Sudoku (N x N)','Finding the GCD of two numbers','Hamming Circuit','Graph Coloring','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'GCD (Euclidean algorithm) is extremely efficient.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','If P = NP, then every NP-Complete problem is:','Undecidable','Solvable in polynomial time','Exponential','Regular','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',35,'This would mean the entire NP class collapses into P.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','The ''Time Hierarchy Theorem'' proves that:','Computers get faster over time','More time allows a Turing machine to solve strictly more problems','P = NP','NP = PSPACE','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'Specifically, it shows that for any ''reasonable'' time function t(n), there are problems solvable in slightly more time that aren''t solvable in t(n) time.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','An ''Oracle Turing Machine'' is a TM that:','Predicts the future','Can solve a specific decision problem (the oracle) in a single step','Has infinite states','Uses quantum superposition','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Oracles are used to study relative computability and hierarchy structures.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','Which variant of SAT is in P?','3-SAT','2-SAT','MAX-SAT','All SAT problems are in P','["B"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'2-SAT is solvable in linear time using graph-based algorithms.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','3-SAT is proven to be NP-Complete.','True','False','Only for clauses > 100','Only if P = NP','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',35,'SAT reduces to 3-SAT in polynomial time.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','What is an ''Approximation Algorithm'' for an NP-Hard problem?','An algorithm that guesses the answer','An algorithm that finds a solution within a guaranteed factor of the optimum in polynomial time','A slow but exact algorithm','A regular expression','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Approximation is a practical way to deal with NP-hard optimization problems.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','What is the complexity of Integer Factoring?','Known to be in P','Known to be NP-Complete','In NP, but not known if P or NP-Complete (NP-Intermediate candidates)','Not in NP','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Factoring is ''suspected'' to be outside P on classical computers, which is the basis of RSA security.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','Is P closed under complement?','Yes','No','Unknown','Only for finite sets','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'If an algorithm solves a problem in polynomial time, just flip the ''Accept'' and ''Reject'' answers to solve the complement.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','Is NP closed under complement?','Yes','No','Unknown (Equivalent to NP vs co-NP question)','Only for regular languages','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'Whether NP = co-NP is a major open problem in computer science.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','Has it been proven that P != NP?','Yes','No, it is an open millennium prize problem','Yes, in 2021','It depends on the programming language','["B"]'::jsonb,'easy',20,'This remains the most famous unsolved problem in computer science.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','Richard Karp''s 1972 paper was famous for:','Inventing the Turing machine','Proving 21 major problems are NP-Complete','Designing the first compiler','Solving the Halting problem','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'This paper established the importance of NP-Completeness in real-world algorithms.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','Playing games like Chess or Go on an N x N board is generally:','In P','In NP','PSPACE-Complete or EXPTIME-Complete','Regular','["C"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'The massive state space of board games typically leads to very high complexity classes.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','Is the ''Tautology Problem'' in propositional logic (is a formula always true) decidable?','Yes, but likely hard (co-NP-Complete)','No','In linear time','Only for horn clauses','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'We can build a truth table, but it grows exponentially.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','The ''Busy Beaver'' function is:','A measure of CPU efficiency','A non-computable function describing the max steps a TM can take before halting','Used in game development','A regular grammar','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',45,'Busy Beaver grows faster than any computable function (recursive hierarchy).','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','Does P = NP imply that encryption is impossible?','No, but it makes it much harder to design and many current methods would fail','Yes, completely','No, it makes encryption stronger','It only affects hashing','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',25,'Encryption relies on certain one-way mathematical properties that might vanish if P = NP.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','What does ''PSPACE'' stand for?','Polynomial Space','Power Space','Partial Space','Parallel Space','["A"]'::jsonb,'medium',30,'PSPACE is the set of problems solvable using a polynomial amount of memory (space).','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','Is PSPACE closed under complement?','Yes','No','Unknown','Only if P = NP','["A"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'PSPACE = co-PSPACE (follows from Savitch''s theorem).','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','A ''Self-Reduction'' property of NP-Complete problems means:','They can reduce to themselves','If you can solve the decision version, you can efficiently construct the actual solution','They are recursive','They have small certificates','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',50,'For example, if you can check IF a path exists, you can find the path by checking if removing an edge still leaves a path.','pregenerated'),
('b772d02e-ffc2-4953-bec9-7d0d61656d05','Which class is the most likely to represent ''Intractable'' but solvable problems?','P','NP-Complete (assuming P != NP)','Regular','Undecidable','["B"]'::jsonb,'hard',40,'NP-complete problems likely require super-polynomial (e.g. exponential) time.','pregenerated'),
